26248	43	5	43	Y cam in the name of my fadir, and ye token not me. If another come in his owne name, ye schulen resseyue hym.
26249	43	5	44	Hou moun ye bileue, that resseyuen glorie ech of othere, and ye seken not the glorie `that is of God aloone?
26250	43	5	45	Nyle ye gesse, that Y am to accuse you anentis the fadir; it is Moises that accusith you, in whom ye hopen.
26251	43	5	46	For if ye bileueden to Moises, perauenture ye schulden bileue also to me; for he wroot of me.
26252	43	5	47	But if ye bileuen not to hise lettris, hou schulen ye bileue to my wordis?
26253	43	6	1	Aftir these thingis Jhesus wente ouere the see of Galilee, that is Tiberias.
26254	43	6	2	And a greet multitude suede hym; for thei sayn the tokenes, that he dide on hem that weren sijke.
26255	43	6	3	Therfor Jhesus wente in to an hil, and sat there with hise disciplis.
26256	43	6	4	And the paske was ful niy, a feeste dai of the Jewis.
26257	43	6	5	Therfor whanne Jhesus hadde lift vp hise iyen, and hadde seyn, that a greet multitude cam to hym, he seith to Filip, Wherof schulen we bie looues, that these men ete?
26258	43	6	6	But he seide this thing, temptynge hym; for he wiste what he was to do.
26259	43	6	7	Filip answerde to hym, The looues of tweyn hundrid pans sufficen not to hem, that ech man take a litil what.
26260	43	6	8	Oon of hise disciplis, Andrew, the brothir of Symount Petre,
26261	43	6	9	seith to him, A child is here, that hath fyue barli looues and twei fischis; but what ben these among so manye?
26262	43	6	10	Therfor Jhesus seith, Make ye hem sitte to the mete. And there was myche hey in the place. And so men saten to the mete, as `fyue thousynde in noumbre.
26263	43	6	11	And Jhesus took fyue looues, and whanne he hadde do thankyngis, he departide to men that saten to the mete, and also of the fischis, as myche as thei wolden.
26264	43	6	12	And whanne thei weren fillid, he seide to hise disciplis, Gadir ye the relifs that ben left, that thei perischen not.
26265	43	6	13	And so thei gadriden, and filliden twelue cofyns of relif of the fyue barli looues and twei fischis, that lefte to hem that hadden etun.
26266	43	6	14	Therfor tho men, whanne thei hadden seyn the signe that he hadde don, seiden, For this is verili the profete, that is to come in to the world.
26267	43	6	15	And whanne Jhesus hadde knowun, that thei weren to come to take hym, and make hym kyng, he fleiy `aloone eft in to an hille.
26268	43	6	16	And whanne euentid was comun, his disciplis wenten doun to the see.
26269	43	6	17	And thei wenten vp in to a boot, and thei camen ouer the see in to Cafarnaum. And derknessis weren maad thanne, and Jhesus was not come to hem.
26270	43	6	18	And for a greet wynde blew, the see roos vp.
26271	43	6	19	Therfor whanne thei hadden rowid as fyue and twenti furlongis or thretti, thei seen Jhesus walkynge on the see, and to be neiy the boot; and thei dredden.
26272	43	6	20	And he seide to hem, Y am; nyle ye drede.
26273	43	6	21	Therfor thei wolden take hym in to the boot, and anoon the boot was at the loond, to which thei wenten.
26274	43	6	22	On `the tother dai the puple, that stood ouer the see, say, that ther was noon other boot there but oon, and that Jhesu entride not with hise disciplis in to the boot, but hise disciplis aloone wenten.
26275	43	6	23	But othere bootis camen fro Tiberias bisidis the place, where thei hadden eetun breed, and diden thankyngis to God.
26276	43	6	24	Therfor whanne the puple hadde seyn, that Jhesu was not there, nether hise disciplis, thei wenten vp in to bootis, and camen to Cafarnaum, sekynge Jhesu.
26277	43	6	25	And whanne thei hadden foundun hym ouer the see, thei seiden to hym, Rabi, hou come thou hidur?
26278	43	6	26	Jhesus answerde to hem, and seide, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, ye seken me, not for ye sayn the myraclis, but for ye eten of looues, and weren fillid.
26279	43	6	27	Worche ye not mete that perischith, but that dwellith in to euerlastynge lijf, which mete mannys sone schal yyue to you; for God the fadir hath markid hym.
26280	43	6	28	Therfor thei seiden to hym, What schulen we do, that we worche the werkis of God?
26281	43	6	29	Jhesus answerde, and seide to hem, This is the werk of God, that ye bileue to hym, whom he sente.
26282	43	6	30	Therfor thei seiden to hym, What tokene thanne doist thou, that we seen, and bileue to thee? what worchist thou?
26283	43	6	31	Oure fadris eeten manna in desert, as it is writun, He yaf to hem breed fro heuene to ete.
26284	43	6	32	Therfor Jhesus seith to hem, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, Moyses yaf you not breed fro heuene, but my fadir yyueth you veri breed fro heuene;
26285	43	6	33	for it is very breed that cometh doun fro heuene, and yyueth lijf to the world.
26286	43	6	34	Therfor thei seiden to hym, Lord, euere yyue vs this breed.
26287	43	6	35	And Jhesus seide to hem, Y am breed of lijf; he that cometh to me, schal not hungur; he that bileueth in me, schal neuere thirste.
26288	43	6	36	But Y seid to you, that ye han seyn me, and ye bileueden not.
26289	43	6	37	Al thing, that the fadir yyueth to me, schal come to me; and Y schal not caste hym out, that cometh to me.
26290	43	6	38	For Y cam doun fro heuene, not that Y do my wille, but the wille of hym that sente me.
26291	43	6	39	And this is the wille of the fadir that sente me, that al thing that the fadir yaf me, Y leese not of it, but ayen reise it in the laste dai.
26292	43	6	40	And this is the wille of my fadir that sente me, that ech man that seeth the sone, and bileueth in hym, haue euerlastynge lijf; and Y schal ayen reyse hym in the laste dai.
26293	43	6	41	Therfor Jewis grutchiden of hym, for he hadde seid, Y am breed that cam doun fro heuene.
26294	43	6	42	And thei seiden, Whether this is not Jhesus, the sone of Joseph, whos fadir and modir we han knowun. Hou thanne seith this, That Y cam doun fro heuene?
26295	43	6	43	Therfor Jhesus answerde, and seide to hem, Nyle ye grutche togidere.
26296	43	6	44	No man may come to me, but if the fadir that sente me, drawe hym; and Y schal ayen reise hym in the laste dai. It is writun in prophetis,
26297	43	6	45	And alle men schulen be able for to be tauyt `of God. Ech man that herde of the fadir, and hath lerned, cometh to me.
26298	43	6	46	Not for ony man hath sey the fadir, but this that is of God, hath sey the fadir.
26299	43	6	47	Sotheli, sotheli, Y seie to you, he that bileueth in me, hath euerlastynge lijf.
26300	43	6	48	Y am breed of lijf.
26301	43	6	49	Youre fadris eeten manna in desert, and ben deed.
26302	43	6	50	This is breed comynge doun fro heuene, that if ony man ete therof, he die not.
26303	43	6	51	Y am lyuynge breed, that cam doun fro heuene.
26304	43	6	52	If ony man ete of this breed, he schal lyue withouten ende. And the breed that Y schal yyue, is my fleisch for the lijf of the world.
26305	43	6	53	Therfor the Jewis chidden togidere, and seiden, Hou may this yyue to vs his fleisch to ete?
26306	43	6	54	Therfor Jhesus seith to hem, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, but ye eten the fleisch of mannus sone, and drenken his blood, ye schulen not haue lijf in you.
26307	43	6	55	He that etith my fleisch, and drynkith my blood, hath euerlastynge lijf, and Y schal ayen reise hym in the laste dai.
26308	43	6	56	For my fleisch is veri mete, and my blood is very drynk.
26309	43	6	57	He that etith my fleisch, and drynkith my blood, dwellith in me, and Y in hym.
26310	43	6	58	As my fadir lyuynge sente me, and Y lyue for the fadir, and he that etith me, he schal lyue for me.
26311	43	6	59	This is breed, that cam doun fro heuene. Not as youre fadris eten manna, and ben deed; he that etith this breed, schal lyue withouten ende.
26312	43	6	60	He seide these thingis in the synagoge, techynge in Cafarnaum.
26313	43	6	61	Therfor many of hise disciplis herynge, seiden, This word is hard, who may here it?
26314	43	6	62	But Jhesus witynge at hym silf, that hise disciplis grutchiden of this thing, seide to hem, This thing sclaundrith you?
26315	43	6	63	Therfor if ye seen mannus sone stiynge, where he was bifor?
26316	43	6	64	It is the spirit that quykeneth, the fleisch profitith no thing; the wordis that Y haue spokun to you, ben spirit and lijf.
26317	43	6	65	But ther ben summe of you that bileuen not. For Jhesus wiste fro the bigynnynge, which weren bileuynge, and who was to bitraye hym.
26318	43	6	66	And he seide, Therfor Y seide to you, that no man may come to me, but it were youun to hym of my fadir.
26319	43	6	67	Fro this tyme many of hise disciplis wenten abak, and wenten not now with hym.
26320	43	6	68	Therfor Jhesus seide to the twelue, Whether ye wolen also go awei?
26321	43	6	69	And Symount Petre answeride to hym, Lord, to whom schulen we gon? Thou hast wordis of euerlastynge lijf;
26322	43	6	70	and we bileuen, and han knowun, that thou art Crist, the sone of God.
26323	43	6	71	Therfor Jhesus answerde to hem, Whether Y chees not you twelue, and oon of you is a feend?
26324	43	6	72	And he seide this of Judas of Symount Scarioth, for this was to bitraye hym, whanne he was oon of the twelue.
26325	43	7	1	Aftir these thingis Jhesus walkide in to Galilee, for he wolde not walke in to Judee, for the Jewis souyten to sle hym.
26326	43	7	2	And ther was neiy a feeste dai of the Jewis, Senofegia.
26327	43	7	3	And hise britheren seiden to hym, Passe fro hennus, and go in to Judee, that also thi disciplis seen thi werkis that thou doist;
26328	43	7	4	for no man doith ony thing in hiddlis, and hym silf sekith to be opyn. If thou doist these thingis, schewe thi silf to the world.
26329	43	7	5	For nether hise britheren bileueden in hym.
26330	43	7	6	Therfor Jhesus seith to hem, My tyme cam not yit, but youre tyme is euermore redi.
26331	43	7	7	The world may not hate you, sothely it hatith me; for Y bere witnessyng therof, that the werkis of it ben yuele.
26332	43	7	8	Go ye vp to this feeste dai, but Y schal not go vp to this feeste dai, for my tyme is not yit fulfillid.
26333	43	7	9	Whanne he hadde seid these thingis, he dwelte in Galilee.
26334	43	7	10	And aftir that hise britheren weren gon vp, thanne he yede vp to the feeste dai, not opynli, but as in priuyte.
26335	43	7	11	Therfor the Jewis souyten hym in the feeste dai, and seiden, Where is he?
26336	43	7	12	And myche grutchyng was of hym among the puple. For summe seiden, That he is good; and othere seiden, Nai, but he disceyueth the puple;
26337	43	7	13	netheles no man spak opynli of hym, for drede of the Jewis.
26338	43	7	14	But whanne the myddil feeste dai cam, Jhesus wente vp in to the temple, and tauyte.
26339	43	7	15	And the Jewis wondriden, and seiden, Hou can this man lettris, sithen he hath not lerned?
26340	43	7	16	Jhesus answerde to hem, and seide, My doctryne is not myn, but his that sente me.
26341	43	7	17	If ony man wole do his wille, he schal knowe of the techyng, whethir it be of God, or Y speke of my silf.
26342	43	7	18	He that spekith of hym silf, sekith his owne glorie; but he that sekith the glorie of hym that sente hym, is sothefast, and vnriytwisnesse is not in hym.
26343	43	7	19	Whether Moises yaf not to you a lawe, and noon of you doith the lawe?
26344	43	7	20	What seken ye to sle me? And the puple answerde, and seide, Thou hast a deuel; who sekith to sle thee?
26345	43	7	21	Jhesus answerde, and seide to hem, Y haue don o werk, and alle ye wondren.
26346	43	7	22	Therfor Moises yaf to you circumcisioun; not for it is of Moyses, but of the fadris; and in the sabat ye circumciden a man.
26347	43	7	23	If a man take circumcicioun in the sabat, that the lawe of Moises be not brokun, han ye indignacioun to me, for Y made al a man hool in the sabat?
26348	43	7	24	Nile ye deme aftir the face, but deme ye a riytful doom.
26349	43	7	25	Therfor summe of Jerusalem seiden, Whethir this is not he, whom the Jewis seken to sle?
26350	43	7	26	and lo! he spekith opynli, and thei seien no thing to hym. Whether the princes knewen verili, that this is Crist?
26351	43	7	27	But we knowun this man, of whennus he is; but whanne Crist schal come, no man woot of whennus he is.
26352	43	7	28	Therfor Jhesus criede in the temple `techynge, and seide, Ye knowen me, and `ye knowen of whennus Y am; and Y cam not of my silf, but he is trewe that sente me, whom ye knowen not.
26353	43	7	29	Y knowe hym, and if Y seie that Y knowe hym not, Y schal be lijk to you, a liere; but Y knowe hym, for of hym Y am, and he sente me.
26354	43	7	30	Therfor thei souyten to take hym, and no man sette on hym hoondis, for his our cam not yit.
26355	43	7	31	And many of the puple bileueden in hym, and seiden, Whanne Crist schal come, whether he schal do mo tokenes, than tho that this doith?
26356	43	7	32	Farisees herden the puple musinge of hym these thingis; and the princis and Farisees senten mynystris, to take hym.
26357	43	7	33	Therfor Jhesus seide to hem, Yit a litil tyme Y am with you, and Y go to the fadir, that sente me.
26358	43	7	34	Ye schulen seke me, and ye schulen not fynde; and where Y am, ye may not come.
26359	43	7	35	Therfor the Jewis seiden to hem silf, Whidur schal this gon, for we schulen not fynde hym? whether he wole go in to the scateryng of hethene men, and wole teche the hethene?
26360	43	7	36	What is this word, which he seide, Ye schulen seke me, and ye schulen not fynde; and where Y am, ye moun not come?
26361	43	7	37	But in the laste dai of the greet feeste, Jhesus stood, and criede, and seide, If ony man thirstith, come he to me, and drynke.
26362	43	7	38	He that bileueth in me, as the scripture seith, Floodis of quyk watir schulen flowe fro his wombe.
26363	43	7	39	But he seide this thing of the Spirit, whom men that bileueden in hym schulden take; for the Spirit was not yit youun, for Jhesus was not yit glorified.
26364	43	7	40	Therfor of that cumpanye, whanne thei hadden herd these wordis of hym, thei seiden, This is verili a prophete.
26365	43	7	41	Othere seiden, This is Crist. `But summe seiden, Whether Crist cometh fro Galilee?
26366	43	7	42	Whether the scripture seith not, that of the seed of Dauid, and of the castel of Bethleem, where Dauid was, Crist cometh?
26367	43	7	43	Therfor discencioun was maad among the puple for hym.
26368	43	7	44	For summe of hem wolden haue take hym, but no man sette hondis on hym.
26369	43	7	45	Therfor the mynystris camen to bischopis and Farisees, and thei seiden to hem, Whi brouyten ye not hym?
26370	43	7	46	The mynystris answeriden, Neuere man spak so, as this man spekith.
26371	43	7	47	Therfor the Farisees answeriden to hem, Whether ye ben disseyued also?
26372	43	7	48	whether ony of the pryncis or of the Farisees bileueden in hym?
26373	43	7	49	But this puple, that knowith not the lawe, ben cursid.
26374	43	7	50	Nychodeme seith to hem, he that cam to hym bi nyyt, that was oon of hem, Whethir oure lawe demith a man,
26375	43	7	51	but it haue first herde of hym, and knowe what he doith?
26376	43	7	52	Thei answeriden, and seiden to hym, Whether thou art a man of Galilee also? Seke thou scripturis, and se thou, that a prophete risith not of Galilee.
26377	43	7	53	And thei turneden ayen, ech in to his hous.
26378	43	8	1	But Jhesus wente in to the mount of Olyuete.
26379	43	8	2	And eerli eft he cam in to the temple; and al the puple cam to hym; and he sat, and tauyte hem.
26380	43	8	3	And scribis and Fariseis bryngen a womman takun in auoutrye, and thei settiden hir in the myddil,
26381	43	8	4	and seiden to hym, Maystir, this womman is now takun in auoutrie.
26382	43	8	5	And in the lawe Moises comaundide vs to stoone suche; therfor what seist thou?
26383	43	8	6	And thei seiden this thing temptynge hym, that thei myyten accuse hym. And Jhesus bowide hym silf doun, and wroot with his fyngur in the erthe.
26384	43	8	7	And whanne thei abiden axynge hym, he reiside hym silf, and seide to hem, He of you that is without synne, first caste a stoon in to hir.
26385	43	8	8	And eft he bowide hym silf, and wroot in the erthe.
26386	43	8	9	And thei herynge these thingis, wenten awei oon aftir anothir, and thei bigunnen fro the eldre men; and Jhesus dwelte aloone, and the womman stondynge in the myddil.
26387	43	8	10	And Jhesus reiside hym silf, and seide to hir, Womman, where ben thei that accusiden thee? no man hath dampned thee.
26388	43	8	11	Sche seide, No man, Lord. Jhesus seide `to hir, Nethir Y schal dampne thee; go thou, and now aftirward nyle thou synne more.
26389	43	8	12	Therfor eft Jhesus spak to hem, and seide, Y am the liyt of the world; he that sueth me, walkith not in derknessis, but schal haue the liyt of lijf.
26390	43	8	13	Therfor the Fariseis seiden, Thou berist witnessyng of thi silf; thi witnessyng is not trewe.
26391	43	8	14	Jhesus answerde, and seide to hem, And if Y bere witnessyng of my silf, my witnessyng is trewe; for Y woot fro whennus Y cam, and whidur Y go.
26392	43	8	15	But ye witen not fro whennus Y cam, ne whidur Y go. For ye demen aftir the fleisch, but Y deme no man;
26393	43	8	16	and if Y deme, my doom is trewe, for Y am not aloone, but Y and the fadir that sente me.
26394	43	8	17	And in youre lawe it is writun, that the witnessyng of twei men is trewe.
26395	43	8	18	Y am, that bere witnessyng of my silf, and the fadir that sente me, berith witnessyng of me.
26396	43	8	19	Therfor thei seiden to hym, Where is thi fadir? Jhesus answeride, Nether ye knowen me, nethir ye knowen my fadir; if ye knewen me, perauenture ye schulden knowe also my fadir.
26397	43	8	20	Jhesus spak these wordis in the tresorie, techynge in the temple; and no man took hym, for his our cam not yit.
26398	43	8	21	Therfor eft Jhesus seide to hem, Lo! Y go, and ye schulen seke me, and ye schulen die in youre synne; whidur Y go, ye moun not come.
26399	43	8	22	Therfor the Jewis seiden, Whether he schal sle hym silf, for he seith, Whidur Y go, ye moun not come?
26400	43	8	23	And he seide to hem, Ye ben of bynethe, Y am of aboue; ye ben of this world, Y am not of this world.
26401	43	8	24	Therfor Y seide to you, that ye schulen die in youre synnes; for if ye bileuen not that Y am, ye schulen die in youre synne.
26402	43	8	25	Therfor thei seiden to hym, Who art thou? Jhesus seide to hem, The bigynnyng, which also speke to you.
26403	43	8	26	Y haue many thingis to speke, and deme of you, but he that sente me is sothefast; and Y speke in the world these thingis, that Y herde of hym.
26404	43	8	27	And thei knewen not, that he clepide his fadir God.
26405	43	8	28	Therfor Jhesus seith to hem, Whanne ye han areisid mannus sone, thanne ye schulen knowe, that Y am, and of my silf Y do no thing; but as my fadir tauyte me, Y speke these thingis.
26406	43	8	29	And he that sente me is with me, and lefte me not aloone; for Y do euermore tho thingis, that ben plesynge to hym.
26407	43	8	30	Whanne he spak these thingis, manye bileueden in hym.
26408	43	8	31	Therfor Jhesus seide to the Jewis, that bileueden in hym, If ye dwellen in my word, verili ye schulen be my disciplis;
26409	43	8	32	and ye schulen knowe the treuthe, and the treuthe schal make you fre.
26410	43	8	33	Therfor the Jewis answeriden to hym, We ben the seed of Abraham, and we serueden neuere to man; hou seist thou, That ye schulen be fre?
26411	43	8	34	Jhesus answeride to hem, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, ech man that doith synne, is seruaunt of synne.
26412	43	8	35	And the seruaunt dwellith not in the hows with outen ende, but the sone dwellith with outen ende.
26413	43	8	36	Therfor if the sone make you fre, verili ye schulen be fre.
26414	43	8	37	Y woot that ye ben Abrahams sones, but ye seken to sle me, for my word takith not in you.
26415	43	8	38	Y speke tho thingis, that Y say at my fadir; and ye doen tho thingis, that ye sayn at youre fadir.
26416	43	8	39	Thei answerden, and seiden to hym, Abraham is oure fadir. Jhesus seith to hem, If ye ben the sones of Abraham, do ye the werkis of Abraham.
26417	43	8	40	But now ye seken to sle `me, a man that haue spoken to you treuthe, that Y herde of God; Abraham dide not this thing.
26418	43	8	41	Ye doen the werkis of youre fadir. Therfor thei seiden to hym, We ben not borun of fornycacioun; we han o fadir, God.
26419	43	8	42	But Jhesus seith to hem, If God were youre fadir, sotheli ye schulden loue me; for Y passide forth of God, and cam; for nether Y cam of my silf, but he sente me.
26420	43	8	43	Whi knowen ye not my speche? for ye moun not here my word.
26421	43	8	44	Ye ben of the fadir, the deuel, and ye wolen do the desyris of youre fadir. He was a mansleere fro the bigynnyng, and he stood not in treuthe; for treuthe is not in hym. Whanne he spekith lesyng, he spekith of his owne; for he is a liere, and fadir of it.
26422	43	8	45	But for Y seie treuthe, ye bileuen not to me.
26423	43	8	46	Who of you schal repreue me of synne? if Y sey treuthe, whi bileuen ye not to me?
26424	43	8	47	He that is of God, herith the wordis of God; therfor ye heren not, for ye ben not of God.
26425	43	8	48	Therfor the Jewis answeriden, and seiden, Whether we seien not wel, that thou art a Samaritan, and hast a deuel?
26426	43	8	49	Jhesus answerde, and seide, Y haue not a deuel, but Y onoure my fadir, and ye han vnhonourid me.
26427	43	8	50	For Y seke not my glorye; there is he, that sekith, and demeth.
26428	43	8	51	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, if ony man kepe my word, he schal not taste deth with outen ende.
26429	43	8	52	Therfor the Jewis seiden, Now we han knowun, that thou hast a deuel. Abraham is deed, and the prophetis, and thou seist, If ony man kepe my word, he schal not taste deth withouten ende.
26430	43	8	53	Whether thou art grettere than oure fader Abraham, that is deed, and the prophetis ben deed; whom makist thou thi silf?
26431	43	8	54	Jhesus answeride, If Y glorifie my silf, my glorie is nouyt; my fadir, is that glorifieth me, whom ye seien, that he is youre God.
26432	43	8	55	And ye han not knowun hym, but Y haue knowun hym; and if Y seie that Y knowe hym not, Y schal be a liere lich to you; but Y knowe hym, and Y kepe his word.
26433	43	8	56	Abraham, youre fadir, gladide to se my dai; and he saiy, and ioyede.
26434	43	8	57	Thanne the Jewis seiden to hym, Thou hast not yit fifti yeer, and hast thou seien Abraham?
26435	43	8	58	Therfor Jhesus seide to hem, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, bifor that Abraham schulde be, Y am.
26436	43	8	59	Therfor thei token stonys, to caste to hym; but Jhesus hidde hym, and wente out of the temple.
26437	43	9	1	And Jhesus passynge, seiy a man blynd fro the birthe.
26438	43	9	2	And hise disciplis axiden hym, Maistir, what synnede this man, or hise eldris, that he schulde be borun blynd?
26439	43	9	3	Jhesus answeride, Nether this man synnede, nether hise eldris; but that the werkis of God be schewid in hym.
26440	43	9	4	It bihoueth me to worche the werkis of hym that sente me, as longe as the dai is; the nyyt schal come, whanne no man may worche.
26441	43	9	5	As longe as Y am in the world, Y am the liyt of the world.
26442	43	9	6	Whanne he hadde seid these thingis, he spette in to the erthe, and made cley of the spotil, and anoyntide the cley on hise iyen,
26443	43	9	7	and seide to hym, Go, and be thou waisschun in the watir of Siloe, that is to seie, Sent. Thanne he wente, and waisschide, and cam seynge.
26444	43	9	8	And so neiyboris, and thei that hadden seyn him bifor, for he was a beggere, seiden, Whether this is not he, that sat, and beggide?
26445	43	9	9	Othere men seiden, That this it is; othere men seyden, Nai, but he is lijc hym.
26446	43	9	10	But he seide, That Y am. Therfor thei seiden to hym, Hou ben thin iyen openyd?
26447	43	9	11	He answerde, Thilke man, that is seid Jhesus, made clei, and anoyntide myn iyen, and seide to me, Go thou to the watre of Siloe, and wassche; and Y wente, and wasschide, and say.
26448	43	9	12	And thei seiden to hym, Where is he? He seide, Y woot not.
26449	43	9	13	Thei leden hym that was blynd to the Farisees.
26450	43	9	14	And it was sabat, whanne Jhesus made cley, and openyde hise iyen.
26451	43	9	15	Eft the Farisees axiden hym, hou he hadde seyn. And he seide to hem, He leide to me cley on the iyen; and Y wasschide, and Y se.
26452	43	9	16	Therfor summe of the Fariseis seiden, This man is not of God, that kepith not the sabat. Othere men seiden, Hou may a synful man do these signes. And strijf was among hem.
26453	43	9	17	Therfor thei seien eftsoone to the blynd man, What seist thou of hym, that openyde thin iyen? And he seide, That he is a prophete.
26454	43	9	18	Therfor Jewis bileueden not of hym, that he was blynd, and hadde seyn, til thei clepiden his fadir and modir, that hadde seyn.
26455	43	9	19	And thei axiden hem, and seiden, Is this youre sone, which ye seien was borun blynd? hou thanne seeth he now?
26456	43	9	20	His fadir and modir answeriden to hem, and seiden, We witen, that this is oure sone, and that he was borun blynd;
26457	43	9	21	but hou he seeth now, we witen neuer, or who openyde hise iyen, we witen nere; axe ye hym, he hath age, speke he of hym silf.
26458	43	9	22	His fader and modir seiden these thingis, for thei dredden the Jewis; for thanne the Jewis hadden conspirid, that if ony man knoulechide hym Crist, he schulde be don out of the synagoge.
26459	43	9	23	Therfor his fadir and modir seiden, That he hath age, axe ye hym.
26460	43	9	24	Therfor eftsoone thei clepiden the man, that was blynd, and seiden to hym, Yyue thou glorie to God; we witen, that this man is a synnere.
26461	43	9	25	Thanne he seide, If he is a synnere, Y woot neuer; o thing Y woot, that whanne Y was blynd, now Y se.
26462	43	9	26	Therfor thei seiden to hym, What dide he to thee? hou openyde he thin iyen?
26463	43	9	27	He answerde to hem, Y seide to you now, and ye herden; what wolen ye eftsoone here? whether ye wolen be maad hise discyplis?
26464	43	9	28	Therfor thei cursiden hym, and seiden, Be thou his disciple; we ben disciplis of Moises.
26465	43	9	29	We witen, that God spak to Moises; but we knowen not this, of whennus he is.
26466	43	9	30	Thilke man answeride, and seide to hem, For in this is a wondurful thing, that ye witen not, of whennus he is, and he hath openyd myn iyen.
26467	43	9	31	And we witen, that God herith not synful men, but if ony `man is worschypere of God, and doith his wille, he herith hym.
26468	43	9	32	Fro the world it is not herd, that ony man openyde the iyen of a blynd borun man; but this were of God,
26469	43	9	33	he myyt not do ony thing.
26470	43	9	34	Thei answeriden, and seiden to hym, Thou art al borun in synnes, and techist thou vs? And thei putten hym out.
26471	43	9	35	Jhesus herd, that thei hadden putte hym out; and whanne he hadde founde hym, he seide to hym, Bileuest thou in the sone of God?
26472	43	9	36	He answerde, and seide, Lord, who is he, that Y bileue in hym?
26473	43	9	37	And Jhesus seide to hym, And thou hast seyn him, and he it is, that spekith with thee.
26474	43	9	38	And he seide, Lord, Y byleue. And he felle doun, and worschipide hym.
26475	43	9	39	Therfore Jhesus seide to hym, Y cam in to this world, `in to doom, that thei that seen not, see, and thei that seen, be maad blynde.
26476	43	9	40	And summe of the Faryseis herden, that weren with hym, and thei seiden to hym, Whether we ben blynde?
26477	43	9	41	Jhesus seide to hem, If ye weren blynde, ye schulden not haue synne; but now ye seien, That we seen, youre synne dwellith stille.
26478	43	10	1	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, he that cometh not in by the dore in to the foold of scheep, but stieth bi another weie, is a nyyt theef and a dai theef.
26479	43	10	2	But he that entrith bi the dore, is the scheepherde of the scheep.
26480	43	10	3	To this the porter openeth, and the scheep heren his vois, and he clepith his owne scheep bi name, and ledith hem out.
26481	43	10	4	And whanne he hath don out his owne scheep, he goith bifor hem, and the scheep suen hym; for thei knowun his vois.
26482	43	10	5	But thei suen not an alien, but fleen from hym; for thei han not knowun the vois of aliens.
26483	43	10	6	Jhesus seide to hem this prouerbe; but thei knewen not what he spak to hem.
26484	43	10	7	Therfor Jhesus seide to hem eftsoone, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, that Y am the dore of the scheep.
26485	43	10	8	As many as han come, weren nyyt theues and day theues, but the scheep herden not hem.
26486	43	10	9	Y am the dore. If ony man schal entre bi me, he schal be sauyd; and he schal go ynne, and schal go out, and he schal fynde lesewis.
26487	43	10	10	A nyyt theef cometh not, but that he stele, sle, and leese; and Y cam, that thei han lijf, and haue more plenteousli.
26488	43	10	11	I am a good scheepherde; a good scheepherde yyueth his lijf for hise scheep.
26489	43	10	12	But an hirid hyne, and that is not the scheepherde, whos ben not the scheep his owne, seeth a wolf comynge, and he leeueth the scheep, and fleeth; and the wolf rauyschith, and disparplith the scheep.
26490	43	10	13	And the hirid hyne fleeth, for he is an hirid hyne, and it parteyneth not to hym of the scheep.
26491	43	10	14	Y am a good scheepherde, and Y knowe my scheep, and my scheep knowen me.
26492	43	10	15	As the fadir hath knowun me, Y knowe the fadir; and Y putte my lijf for my scheep.
26493	43	10	16	Y haue othere scheep, that ben not of this foolde, and it bihoueth me to brynge hem togidir, and thei schulen here my vois; and it schal be maad o foolde and o scheepherde.
26494	43	10	17	Therfor the fadir loueth me, for Y putte my lijf, that eftsoone Y take it.
26495	43	10	18	No man takith it fro me, but Y putte it of my silf. Y haue power to putte it, and Y haue power to take it ayen. This maundement Y haue takun of my fadir.
26496	43	10	19	Eft dissencioun was maad among the Jewis for these wordis.
26497	43	10	20	And many of hem seiden, He hath a deuel, and maddith; what heren ye hym?
26498	43	10	21	Othere men seiden, These wordis ben not of a man that hath a feend. Whether the deuel may opene the iyen of blynde men?
26499	43	10	22	But the feestis of halewyng of the temple weren maad in Jerusalem, and it was wyntir.
26500	43	10	23	And Jhesus walkide in the temple, in the porche of Salomon.
26501	43	10	24	Therfor the Jewis camen aboute hym, and seiden to hym, Hou long takist thou awei oure soule? if thou art Crist, seie thou to vs opynli.
26502	43	10	25	Jhesus answerde to hem, Y speke to you, and ye bileuen not; the werkis that Y do in the name of my fadir, beren witnessyng of me.
26503	43	10	26	But ye bileuen not, for ye ben not of my scheep.
26504	43	10	27	My scheep heren my vois, and Y knowe hem, and thei suen me.
26505	43	10	28	And Y yyue to hem euerelastynge lijf, and thei schulen not perische with outen ende, and noon schal rauysche hem fro myn hoond.
26506	43	10	29	That thing that my fadir yaf to me, is more than alle thingis; and no man may rauysche fro my fadris hoond.
26507	43	10	30	Y and the fadir ben oon.
26508	43	10	31	The Jewis token vp stoonys, to stoone hym.
26509	43	10	32	Jhesus answerde to hem, Y haue schewide to you many good werkis of my fadir, for which werk of hem stonen ye me?
26510	43	10	33	The Jewis answerden to hym, We stoonen thee not of good werk, but of blasfemye, and for thou, sithen thou art a man, makist thi silf God.
26511	43	10	34	Jhesus answerde to hem, Whether it is not writun in youre lawe, That Y seide, Ye ben goddis?
26512	43	10	35	Yf he seide that thei weren goddis, to whiche the word of God was maad, and scripture may not be vndon,
26513	43	10	36	thilke that the fadir hath halewid, and hath sent in to the world, ye seien, That `thou blasfemest, for Y seide, Y am Goddis sone?
26514	43	10	37	Yf Y do not the werkis of my fadir, nyle ye bileue to me;
26515	43	10	38	but if Y do, thouy ye wolen not bileue to me, bileue ye to the werkis; that ye knowe and bileue, that the fadir is in me, and Y in the fadir.
26516	43	10	39	Therfor thei souyten to take hym, and he wente out of her hondis.
26517	43	10	40	And he wente eftsoone ouer Jordan, in to that place where Joon was firste baptisynge, and he dwelte there.
26518	43	10	41	And manye camen to hym, and seiden, For Joon dide no myracle;
26519	43	10	42	and alle thingis what euer Joon seide of this, weren sothe. And many bileueden in hym.
26520	43	11	1	And ther was a sijk man, Lazarus of Bethanye, of the castel of Marie and Martha, hise sistris.
26521	43	11	2	And it was Marye, which anoyntide the Lord with oynement, and wipte hise feet with hir heeris, whos brother Lazarus was sijk.
26522	43	11	3	Therfor hise sistris senten to hym, and seide, Lord, lo! he whom thou louest, is sijk.
26523	43	11	4	And Jhesus herde, and seide to hem, This syknesse is not to the deth, but for the glorie of God, that mannus sone be glorified bi hym.
26524	43	11	5	And Jhesus louyde Martha, and hir sistir Marie, and Lazarus.
26525	43	11	6	Therfor whanne Jhesus herde, that he was sijk, thanne he dwellide in the same place twei daies.
26526	43	11	7	And after these thingis he seide to hise disciplis, Go we eft in to Judee.
26527	43	11	8	The disciplis seien to hym, Maister, now the Jewis souyten for to stoone thee, and eft goist thou thidir?
26528	43	11	9	Jhesus answerde, Whether ther ben not twelue ouris of the dai? If ony man wandre in the dai, he hirtith not, for he seeth the liyt of this world.
26529	43	11	10	But if he wandre in the niyt, he stomblith, for liyt is not in him.
26530	43	11	11	He seith these thingis, and aftir these thingis he seith to hem, Lazarus, oure freend, slepith, but Y go to reise hym fro sleep.
26531	43	11	12	Therfor hise disciplis seiden, Lord, if he slepith, he schal be saaf.
26532	43	11	13	But Jhesus hadde seid of his deth; but thei gessiden, that he seide of slepyng of sleep.
26533	43	11	14	Thanne therfor Jhesus seide to hem opynli, Lazarus is deed;
26534	43	11	15	and Y haue ioye for you, that ye bileue, for Y was not there; but go we to hym.
26535	43	11	16	Therfor Thomas, that is seid Didymus, seide to euen disciplis, Go we also, that we dien with hym.
26536	43	11	17	And so Jhesus cam, and foond hym hauynge thanne foure daies in the graue.
26537	43	11	18	And Bethany was bisidis Jerusalem, as it were fiftene furlongis.
26538	43	11	19	And many of the Jewis camen to Mary and Martha, to coumforte hem of her brothir.
26539	43	11	20	Therfor as Martha herde, that Jhesu cam, sche ran to hym; but Mary sat at home.
26540	43	11	21	Therfor Martha seide to Jhesu, Lord, if thou haddist be here, my brother hadde not be deed.
26541	43	11	22	But now Y woot, that what euere thingis thou schalt axe of God, God schal yyue to thee.
26542	43	11	23	Jhesus seith to hir, Thi brother schal rise ayen.
26543	43	11	24	Martha seith to hym, Y woot, that he schal rise ayen in the ayen risyng in the laste dai.
26544	43	11	25	Jhesus seith to hir, Y am ayen risyng and lijf; he that bileueth in me, yhe, thouy he be deed,
26545	43	11	26	he schal lyue; and ech that lyueth, and bileueth in me, schal not die with outen ende. Bileuest thou this thing?
26546	43	11	27	Sche seith to hym, Yhe, Lord, Y haue bileued, that thou art Crist, the sone of the lyuynge God, that hast come in to this world.
26547	43	11	28	And whanne sche hadde seid this thing, sche wente, and clepide Marie, hir sistir, in silence, and seide, The maister cometh, and clepith thee.
26548	43	11	29	Sche, as sche herd, aroos anoon, and cam to hym.
26549	43	11	30	And Jhesus cam not yit `in to the castel, but he was yit in that place, where Martha hadde comun ayens hym.
26550	43	11	31	Therfor the Jewis that weren with hir in the hous, and coumfortiden hir, whanne thei sayn Marie, that sche roos swithe, and wente out, thei sueden hir, and seiden, For sche goith to the graue, to wepe there.
26551	43	11	32	But whanne Marie was comun where Jhesus was, sche seynge hym felde doun to his feet, and seide to hym, Lord, if thou haddist be here, my brother hadde not be deed.
26552	43	11	33	And therfor whanne Jhesu saiy hir wepyng, and the Jewis wepynge that weren with hir, he `made noise in spirit, and troblide hym silf,
26553	43	11	34	and seide, Where han ye leid hym? Thei seien to hym, Lord, come, and se.
26554	43	11	35	And Jhesus wepte. Therfor the Jewis seiden,
26555	43	11	36	Lo! hou he louede hym.
26556	43	11	37	And summe of hem seiden, Whethir this man that openyde the iyen of the borun blynde man, myyte not make that this schulde not die?
26557	43	11	38	Therfor Jhesus eft makynge noise in hym silf, cam to the graue. And there was a denne, and a stoon was leid theronne.
26558	43	11	39	And Jhesus seith, Take ye awey the stoon. Martha, the sistir of hym that was deed, seith to hym, Lord, he stynkith now, for he hath leye foure daies.
26559	43	11	40	Jhesus seith to hir, Haue Y not seid to thee, that if thou bileuest, thou schalt se the glorie of God?
26560	43	11	41	Therfor thei token awei the stoon. And Jhesus lifte vp hise iyen, and seide, Fadir, Y do thankyngis to thee, for thou hast herd me; and Y wiste,
26561	43	11	42	that thou euermore herist me, but for the puple that stondith aboute, Y seide, that thei bileue, that thou hast sent me.
26562	43	11	43	Whanne he hadde seid these thingis, he criede with a greet vois, Lazarus, come thou forth.
26563	43	11	44	And anoon he that was deed, cam out, boundun the hondis and feet with boondis, and his face boundun with a sudarie. And Jhesus seith to hem, Vnbynde ye hym, and suffre ye hym to go forth.
26564	43	11	45	Therfor many of the Jewis that camen to Marie and Martha, and seyn what thingis Jhesus dide, bileueden in hym.
26565	43	11	46	But summe of hem wente to the Farisees, and seiden to hem, what thingis Jhesus `hadde don.
26566	43	11	47	Therfor the bischopis and the Farisees gadriden a counsel ayens Jhesu, and seiden, What do we? for this man doith many myraclis.
26567	43	11	48	If we leeue hym thus, alle men schulen bileue in hym; and Romayns schulen come, and schulen take our place and oure folk.
26568	43	11	49	But oon of hem, Cayfas bi name, whanne he was bischop of that yeer, seide to hem,
26569	43	11	50	Ye witen nothing, ne thenken, that it spedith to you, that o man die for the puple, and that al the folc perische not.
26570	43	11	51	But he seide not this thing of hym silf, but whanne he was bischop of that yeer, he prophesiede, that Jhesu was to die for the folc,
26571	43	11	52	and not oneli for the folc, but that he schulde gadere in to oon the sones of God that weren scaterid.
26572	43	11	53	Therfor fro that day thei souyten for to sle hym.
26573	43	11	54	Therfor Jhesus walkide not thanne opynli among the Jewis; but he wente in to a cuntre bisidis desert, in to a citee, that is seid Effren, and there he dwellide with hise disciplis.
26574	43	11	55	And the pask of the Jewis was niy, and many of the cuntrey wenten vp to Jerusalem bifor the pask, to halewe hem silf.
26575	43	11	56	Therfor thei souyten Jhesu, and spaken togidere, stondynge in the temple, What gessen ye, for he cometh not to the feeste day? For the bischopis and Farisees hadden youun a maundement, that if ony man knowe where he is, that he schewe, that thei take hym.
26576	43	12	1	Therfor Jhesus bifor sixe daies of pask cam to Bethanye, where Lazarus hadde be deed, whom Jhesus reiside.
26577	43	12	2	And thei maden to hym a soopere there, and Martha mynystride to hym; and Lazarus was oon of men that saten at the mete with hym.
26578	43	12	3	Therfor Marie took a pound of oynement of trewe narde precious, and anoyntide the feet of Jhesu, and wipte hise feet with hir heeris; and the hous was fulfillid of the sauour of the oynement.
26579	43	12	4	Therfor Judas Scarioth, oon of hise disciplis, that was to bitraye hym,
26580	43	12	5	seide, Whi is not this oynement seeld for thre hundrid pens, and is youun to nedi men?
26581	43	12	6	But he seide this thing, not for it perteynede to hym of nedi men, but for he was a theef, and he hadde the pursis, and bar tho thingis that weren sent.
26582	43	12	7	Therfor Jhesus seide, Suffre ye hir, that in to the day of my biriyng sche kepe that;
26583	43	12	8	for ye schulen euermore haue pore men with you, but ye schulen not euermore haue me.
26584	43	12	9	Therfore myche puple of Jewis knew, that Jhesus was there; and thei camen, not oonli for Jhesu, but to se Lazarus, whom he hadde reisid fro deth.
26585	43	12	10	But the princis of prestis thouyten to sle Lazarus,
26586	43	12	11	for manye of the Jewis wenten awei for him, and bileueden in Jhesu.
26587	43	12	12	But on the morew a myche puple, that cam togidere to the feeste dai, whanne thei hadden herd, that Jhesus cam to Jerusalem,
26588	43	12	13	token braunchis of palmes, and camen forth ayens hym, and crieden, Osanna, blessid is the kyng of Israel, that cometh in the name of the Lord.
26589	43	12	14	And Jhesus foond a yonge asse, and sat on hym,
26590	43	12	15	as it is writun, The douytir of Syon, nyle thou drede; lo! thi kyng cometh, sittynge on `an asse fole.
26591	43	12	16	Hise disciplis knewen not first these thingis, but whanne Jhesus was glorified, thanne thei hadden mynde, for these thingis weren writun of hym, and these thingis thei diden to hym.
26592	43	12	17	Therfor the puple bar witnessyng, that was with hym, whanne he clepide Lazarus fro the graue, and reiside hym fro deth.
26593	43	12	18	And therfor the puple cam, and mette with hym, for thei herden that he hadde don this signe.
26594	43	12	19	Therfor the Farisees seiden to hem silf, Ye seen, that we profiten no thing; lo! al the world wente aftir hym.
26595	43	12	20	And there weren summe hethene men, of hem that hadden come vp to worschipe in the feeste dai.
26596	43	12	21	And these camen to Filip, that was of Bethsaida of Galilee, and preieden hym, and seiden, Sire, we wolen se Jhesu.
26597	43	12	22	Filip cometh, and seith to Andrew; eft Andrew and Filip seiden to Jhesu.
26598	43	12	23	And Jhesus answerde `to hem, and seide, The our cometh, that mannus sone be clarified.
26599	43	12	24	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, but a corn of whete falle in to the erthe, and be deed, it dwellith aloone;
26600	43	12	25	but if it be deed, it bryngith myche fruyt. He that loueth his lijf, schal leese it; and he that hatith his lijf in this world, kepith it in to euerlastynge lijf.
26601	43	12	26	If ony man serue me, sue he me; and where Y am, there my mynystre schal be. If ony man serue me, my fadir schal worschipe hym.
26602	43	12	27	Now my soule is troublid, and what schal Y seie? Fadir, saue me fro this our; but therfor Y cam in to this our;
26603	43	12	28	fadir, clarifie thi name. And a vois cam fro heuene, and seide, And Y haue clarified, and eft Y schal clarifie.
26604	43	12	29	Therfor the puple that stood, and herde, seide, that `thundur was maad; othere men seide, an aungel spak to hym.
26605	43	12	30	Jhesus answerde, and seide, This vois cam not for me, but for you.
26606	43	12	31	Now is the doom of the world, now the prince of this world schal be cast out.
26607	43	12	32	And if Y schal be enhaunsid fro the erthe, Y schal drawe alle thingis to my silf.
26608	43	12	33	And he seide this thing, signifiynge bi what deth he `was to die.
26609	43	12	34	And the puple answeride to hym, We han herd of the lawe, that Crist dwellith with outen ende; and hou seist thou, It bihoueth mannys sone to be arerid?
26610	43	12	35	Who is this mannus sone? And thanne Jhesus seith to hem, Yit a litil liyt is in you; walke ye, the while ye han liyt, that derknessis catche you not; he that wandrith in derknessis, woot nere whidur he goith.
26611	43	12	36	While ye han liyt, bileue ye in liyt, that ye be the children of liyt. Jhesus spak these thingis, and wente, and hidde hym fro hem.
26612	43	12	37	And whanne he hadde don so many myraclis bifor hem, thei bileueden not `in to hym;
26613	43	12	38	that the word of Ysaie, the prophete, schulde be fulfillid, which he seide, Lord, who bileuede to oure heryng, and to whom is the arm of the Lord schewid?
26614	43	12	39	Therfor thei myyten not bileue, for eft Ysaye seide,
26615	43	12	40	He hath blyndid her iyen, and he hath maad hard the herte of hem, that thei se not with iyen, and vndurstonde with herte; and that thei be conuertid, and Y heele hem.
26616	43	12	41	Ysaye seide these thingis, whanne he say the glorie of hym, and spak of hym.
26617	43	12	42	Netheles `of the pryncis manye bileueden in hym, but for the Farisees thei knowlechiden not, that thei schulden not be put out of the synagoge;
26618	43	12	43	for thei loueden the glorie of men, more than the glorie of God.
26619	43	12	44	And Jhesus criede, and seide, He that bileueth in me, bileueth not in me, but in hym that sente me.
26620	43	12	45	He that seeth me, seeth hym that sente me.
26621	43	12	46	Y liyt cam in to the world, that ech that bileueth in me, dwelle not in derknessis.
26622	43	12	47	And if ony man herith my words, and kepith hem, Y deme hym not; for Y cam not, that Y deme the world, but that Y make the world saaf.
26623	43	12	48	He that dispisith me, and takith not my wordis, hath hym that schal iuge hym; thilke word that Y haue spokun, schal deme hym in the last dai.
26624	43	12	49	For Y haue not spokun of my silf, but thilke fadir that sente me, yaf to me a maundement, what Y schal seie, and what Y schal speke.
26625	43	12	50	And Y woot, that his maundement is euerlastynge lijf; therfor tho thingis that Y speke, as the fadir seide to me, so Y speke.
26626	43	13	1	Bifor the `feeste dai of pask Jhesus witynge, that his our is comun, that he passe fro this world to the fadir, whanne he hadde loued hise that weren in the world, in to the ende he louede hem.
26627	43	13	2	And whanne the souper was maad, whanne the deuel hadde put than in to the herte, that Judas of Symount Scarioth schulde bitraye hym,
26628	43	13	3	he witynge that the fadir yaf alle thingis to hym in to hise hoondis, and that he wente out fro God,
26629	43	13	4	and goith to God, he risith fro the souper, and doith of hise clothis; and whanne he hadde takun a lynun cloth, he girde hym.
26630	43	13	5	And aftirward he putte watir in to a basyn, and biganne to waische the disciplis feet, and to wipe with the lynnen cloth, with which he was gird.
26631	43	13	6	And so he cam to Symount Petre, and Petre seith to hym, Lord, waischist thou my feet?
26632	43	13	7	Jhesus answerde, and seide to hym, What Y do, thou wost not now; but thou schalt wite aftirward.
26633	43	13	8	Petre seith to hym, Thou schalt neuere waische my feet. Jhesus answeride to hym, If Y schal not waische thee, thou schalt not haue part with me.
26634	43	13	9	Symount Petre seith to hym, Lord, not oneli my feet, but bothe the hoondis and the heed.
26635	43	13	10	Jhesus seide to hym, He that is waischun, hath no nede but that he waische the feet, but he is al clene; and ye ben clene, but not alle.
26636	43	13	11	For he wiste, who `was he that schulde bitraye hym; therfor he seide, Ye ben not alle clene.
26637	43	13	12	And so aftir that he hadde waischun `the feet of hem, he took hise clothis; and whanne he was set to mete ayen, eft he seide to hem, Ye witen what Y haue don to you.
26638	43	13	13	Ye clepen me maistir and lord, and ye seien wel; for Y am.
26639	43	13	14	Therfor if Y, lord and maistir, haue waischun youre feet, and ye schulen waische oon anothers feet;
26640	43	13	15	for Y haue youun `ensaumple to you, `that as I haue do to you, so do ye.
26641	43	13	16	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, the seruaunt is not grettere than his lord, nether an apostle is grettere than he that sente hym.
26642	43	13	17	If ye witen these thingis, ye schulen be blessid, if ye doen hem.
26643	43	13	18	Y seie not of `alle you, Y woot whiche Y haue chosun; but that the scripture be fulfillid, He that etith my breed, schal reise his heele ayens me.
26644	43	13	19	Treuly, Y seie to you bifor it be don, that whanne it is don, ye bileue that Y am.
26645	43	13	20	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, he that takith whom euere Y schal sende, resseyueth me; and he that resseyueth me, resseyueth hym that sente me.
26646	43	13	21	Whanne Jhesus hadde seid these thingis, he was troblid in spirit, and witnesside, and seide, Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, that oon of you schal bitraye me.
26647	43	13	22	Therfor the disciplis lokiden togidere, doutynge of whom he seide.
26648	43	13	23	And so oon of hise disciplis was restynge in the bosum of Jhesu, whom Jhesu louede.
26649	43	13	24	Therfor Symount Petre bikeneth to hym, `and seith to hym, Who is it, of whom he seith?
26650	43	13	25	And so whanne he hadde restid ayen on the brest of Jhesu, he seith to hym, Lord, who is it?
26651	43	13	26	Jhesus answerde, He it is, to whom Y schal areche a sop of breed. And whanne he hadde wet breed, he yaf to Judas of Symount Scarioth.
26652	43	13	27	And aftir the mussel, thanne Sathanas entride in to hym. And Jhesus seith to hym, That thing that thou doist, do thou swithe.
26653	43	13	28	And noon of hem that saten at the mete wiste, wherto he seide to hym.
26654	43	13	29	For summe gessiden, for Judas hadde pursis, that Jhesus hadde seid to hym, Bie thou tho thingis, that ben nedeful to vs to the feeste dai, or that he schulde yyue sum thing to nedi men.
26655	43	13	30	Therfor whanne he hadde takun the mussel, he wente out anoon; and it was nyyt.
26656	43	13	31	And whanne he was gon out, Jhesus seide, Now mannus sone is clarified, and God is clarified in hym.
26657	43	13	32	If God is clarified in hym, God schal clarifie hym in hym silf, and anoon he schal clarifie hym.
26658	43	13	33	Litle sones, yit a litil Y am with you; ye schulen seke me, and, as Y seide to the Jewis, Whidur Y go, ye moun not come; and to you Y seie now.
26659	43	13	34	Y yyue to you a newe maundement, that ye loue togidir, as Y louede you, `and that ye loue togidir.
26660	43	13	35	In this thing alle men schulen knowe, that ye ben my disciplis, if ye han loue togidere.
26661	43	13	36	Symount Petre seith to hym, Lord, whidur goist thou? Jhesus answeride, Whidur Y go, thou mayst not sue me now, but thou schalt sue afterward.
26662	43	13	37	Petre seith to hym, Whi may Y not sue thee now? Y schal putte my lijf for thee.
26663	43	13	38	Jhesus answeride, Thou schalt putte thi lijf for me? Treuli, treuli, Y seie to thee, the cok schal not crowe, til thou schalt denye me thries. And he seith to hise disciplis.
26664	43	14	1	Be not youre herte afraied, ne drede it; ye bileuen in God, and bileue ye in me.
26665	43	14	2	In the hous of my fadir ben many dwellyngis; if ony thing lesse, Y hadde seid to you, for Y go to make redi to you a place.
26666	43	14	3	And if Y go, and make redi to you a place, eftsoones Y come, and Y schal take you to my silf, that where Y am, ye be.
26667	43	14	4	And whidur Y go, ye witen, and ye witen the weie.
26668	43	14	5	Thomas seith to hym, Lord, we witen not whidur thou goist, and hou moun we wite the weie?
26669	43	14	6	Jhesus seith to hym, Y am weie, treuthe, and lijf; no man cometh to the fadir, but bi me.
26670	43	14	7	If ye hadden knowe me, sotheli ye hadden knowe also my fadir; and aftirward ye schulen knowe hym, and ye han seyn hym.
26671	43	14	8	Filip seith to hym, Lord, schewe to vs the fadir, and it suffisith to vs.
26672	43	14	9	Jhesus seith to hym, So long tyme Y am with you, and `han ye not knowun me? Filip, he that seeth me, seeth also the fadir. Hou seist thou, schewe to vs the fadir?
26673	43	14	10	Bileuest thou not, that Y am in the fadir, and the fadir is in me? The wordis that Y speke to you, Y speke not of my silf; but the fadir hym silf dwellynge in me, doith the werkis.
26674	43	14	11	Bileue ye not, that Y am in the fadir, and the fadir is in me?
26675	43	14	12	Ellis bileue ye for thilke werkis. Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, if a man bileueth in me, also he schal do the werkis that Y do; and he schal do grettere werkis than these, for Y go to the fadir.
26676	43	14	13	And what euere thing ye axen the fadir in my name, Y schal do this thing, that the fadir be glorified in the sone.
26677	43	14	14	If ye axen ony thing in my name, Y schal do it.
26678	43	14	15	If ye louen me, kepe ye my comaundementis.
26679	43	14	16	And Y schal preye the fadir, and he schal yyue to you another coumfortour,
26680	43	14	17	the spirit of treuthe, to dwelle with you with outen ende; which spirit the world may not take, for it seeth hym not, nether knowith hym. But ye schulen knowe hym, for he schal dwelle with you, and he schal be in you.
26681	43	14	18	Y schal not leeue you fadirles, Y schal come to you.
26682	43	14	19	Yit a litil, and the world seeth not now me; but ye schulen se me, for Y lyue, and ye schulen lyue.
26683	43	14	20	In that dai ye schulen knowe, that Y am in my fadir, and ye in me, and Y in you.
26684	43	14	21	He that hath my comaundementis, and kepith hem, he it is that loueth me; and he that loueth me, schal be loued of my fadir, and Y schal loue hym, and Y schal schewe to hym my silf.
26685	43	14	22	Judas seith to hym, not he of Scarioth, Lord, what is don, that thou schalt schewe thi silf to vs, and not to the world?
26686	43	14	23	Jhesus answerde, and seide `to hym, If ony man loueth me, he schal kepe my word; and my fadir schal loue hym, and we schulen come to hym, and we schulen dwelle with hym.
26687	43	14	24	He that loueth me not, kepith not my wordis; and the word which ye han herd, is not myn, but the fadris, that sente me.
26688	43	14	25	These thingis Y haue spokun to you, dwellynge among you; but thilke Hooli Goost,
26689	43	14	26	the coumfortour, whom the fadir schal sende in my name, he schal teche you alle thingis, `and schal schewe to you alle thingis, what euere thingis Y schal seie to you.
26690	43	14	27	Pees Y leeue to you, my pees Y yyue to you; not as the world yyueth, Y yiue to you; be not youre herte affrayed, ne drede it.
26691	43	14	28	Ye han herd, that Y seide to you, Y go, and come to you. If ye loueden me, forsothe ye schulden haue ioye, for Y go to the fadir, for the fadir is grettere than Y.
26692	43	14	29	And now Y haue seid to you, bifor that it be don, that whanne it is don, ye bileuen.
26693	43	14	30	Now Y schal not speke many thingis with you; for the prince of this world cometh, and hath not in me ony thing.
26694	43	14	31	But that the world knowe, that Y loue the fadir; and as the fadir yaf a comaundement to me, so Y do. `Rise ye, go we hennus.
26695	43	15	1	Y am a very vyne, and my fadir is an erthe tilier.
26696	43	15	2	Ech braunch in me that berith not fruyt, he schal take awey it; and ech that berith fruyt, he schal purge it, that it bere the more fruyt.
26697	43	15	3	Now ye ben clene, for the word that Y haue spokun to you.
26698	43	15	4	Dwelle ye in me, and Y in you; as a braunche may not make fruyt of it silf, but it dwelle in the vyne, so nether ye, but ye dwelle in me.
26699	43	15	5	Y am a vyne, ye the braunchis. Who that dwellith in me, and Y in hym, this berith myche fruyt, for with outen me ye moun no thing do.
26700	43	15	6	If ony man dwellith not in me, he schal be caste out as a braunche, and schal wexe drie; and thei schulen gadere hym, and thei schulen caste hym in to the fier, and he brenneth.
26701	43	15	7	If ye dwellen in me, and my wordis dwelle in you, what euer thing ye wolen, ye schulen axe, and it schal be don to you.
26702	43	15	8	In this thing my fadir is clarified, that ye brynge forth ful myche fruyt, and that ye be maad my disciplis.
26703	43	15	9	As my fadir louede me, Y haue loued you; dwelle ye in my loue.
26704	43	15	10	If ye kepen my comaundementis, ye schulen dwelle in my loue; as Y haue kept the comaundementis of my fadir, and Y dwelle in his loue.
26705	43	15	11	These thingis Y spak to you, that my ioye be in you, and youre ioye be fulfillid.
26706	43	15	12	This is my comaundement, that ye loue togidere, as Y louede you.
26707	43	15	13	No man hath more loue than this, that a man putte his lijf for hise freendis.
26708	43	15	14	Ye ben my freendis if ye doen tho thingis, that Y comaunde to you.
26709	43	15	15	Now Y schal not clepe you seruauntis, for the seruaunt woot not, what his lord schal do; but Y haue clepid you freendis, for alle thingis what euere Y herde of my fadir, Y haue maad knowun to you.
26710	43	15	16	Ye han not chosun me, but Y chees you; and Y haue put you, that ye go, and brynge forth fruyt, and youre fruyt dwelle; that what euere thing ye axen the fadir in my name, he yyue to you.
26711	43	15	17	These thingis Y comaunde to you, that ye loue togidere.
26712	43	15	18	If the world hatith you, wite ye, that it hadde me in hate rather than you.
26713	43	15	19	If ye hadden be of the world, the world schulde loue that thing that was his; but for ye ben not of the world, but Y chees you fro the world, therfor the world hatith you.
26714	43	15	20	Haue ye mynde of my word, which Y seide to you, The seruaunt is not grettere than his lord. If thei han pursued me, thei schulen pursue you also; if thei han kept my word, thei schulen kepe youre also.
26715	43	15	21	But thei schulen do to you alle these thingis for my name, for thei knowen not hym that sente me.
26716	43	15	22	If Y hadde not comun, and hadde not spokun to hem, thei schulden not haue synne; but now thei haue noon excusacioun of her synne.
26717	43	15	23	He that hatith me, hatith also my fadir.
26718	43	15	24	If Y hadde not doon werkis in hem, whiche noon other man dide, thei schulden not haue synne; but now both thei han seyn, and hatid me and my fadir.
26719	43	15	25	But that the word be fulfillid, that is writun in her lawe, For thei hadden me in hate with outen cause.
26720	43	15	26	But whanne the coumfortour schal come, which Y schal sende to you fro the fadir, a spirit of treuthe, which cometh of the fadir, he schal bere witnessyng of me; and ye schulen bere witnessyng, for ye ben with me fro the bigynnyng.
26721	43	16	1	These thingis Y haue spokun to you, that ye be not sclaundrid.
26722	43	16	2	Thei schulen make you with outen the synagogis, but the our cometh, that ech man that sleeth you, deme that he doith seruyce to God.
26723	43	16	3	And thei schulen do to you these thingis, for thei han not knowun the fadir, nether me.
26724	43	16	4	But these thingis Y spak to you, that whanne the our `of hem schal come, ye haue mynde, that Y seide to you.
26725	43	16	5	Y seide not to you these thingis fro the bigynnyng, for Y was with you. And now Y go to hym that sente me, and no man of you axith me, Whidur `thou goist?
26726	43	16	6	but for Y haue spokun to you these thingis, heuynesse hath fulfillid youre herte.
26727	43	16	7	But Y seie to you treuthe, it spedith to you, that Y go; for if Y go not forth, the coumfortour schal not come to you; but if Y go forth, Y schal sende hym to you.
26728	43	16	8	And whanne he cometh, he schal repreue the world of synne, and of riytwisnesse, and of doom.
26729	43	16	9	Of synne, for thei han not bileued in me;
26730	43	16	10	and of riytwisnesse, for Y go to the fadir, and now ye schulen not se me;
26731	43	16	11	but of doom, for the prince of this world is now demed.
26732	43	16	12	Yit Y haue many thingis for to seie to you, but ye moun not bere hem now.
26733	43	16	13	But whanne thilke spirit of treuthe cometh, he schal teche you al trewthe; for he schal not speke of hym silf, but what euer thinges he schal here, he schal speke; and he schal telle to you tho thingis that ben to come.
26734	43	16	14	He schal clarifie me, for of myne he schal take, and schal telle to you.
26735	43	16	15	Alle thingis `whiche euer the fadir hath, ben myne; therfor Y seide to you, for of myne he schal take, and schal telle to you.
26736	43	16	16	A litil, and thanne ye schulen not se me; and eftsoone a litil, and ye schulen se me, for Y go to the fadir.
26737	43	16	17	Therfor summe of hise disciplis seiden togidere, What is this thing that he seith to vs, A litil, and ye schulen not se me; and eftsoone a litil, and ye schulen se me, for Y go to the fadir?
26738	43	16	18	Therfor thei seiden, What is this that he seith to vs, A litil? we witen not what he spekith.
26739	43	16	19	And Jhesus knew, that thei wolden axe hym, and he seide to hem, Of this thing ye seken among you, for Y seide, A litil, and ye schulen not se me; and eftsoone a litil, and ye schulen se me.
26740	43	16	20	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to you, that ye schulen mourne and wepe, but the world schal haue ioye; and ye schulen be soreuful, but youre sorewe schal turne in to ioye.
26741	43	16	21	A womman whanne sche berith child, hath heuynesse, for hir tyme is comun; but whanne sche hath borun a sone, now sche thenkith not on the peyne, for ioye, for a man is borun in to the world.
26742	43	16	22	And therfor ye han now sorew, but eftsoone Y schal se you, and youre herte schal haue ioie, and no man schal take fro you youre ioie.
26743	43	16	23	And in that day ye schulen not axe me ony thing; treuli, treuli, `Y seie to you, if ye axen the fadir ony thing in my name, he schal yyue to you.
26744	43	16	24	`Til now ye axiden no thing in my name; `axe ye, `and ye schulen take, that youre ioie be ful.
26745	43	16	25	Y haue spokun to you these thingis in prouerbis; the our cometh, whanne now Y schal not speke to you in prouerbis, but opynli of my fadir Y schal telle to you.
26746	43	16	26	In that dai ye schulen axe in my name; and Y seie not to you, that Y schal preye the fadir of you;
26747	43	16	27	for the fadir hym silf loueth you, for ye han loued me, and han bileued, that Y wente out fro God.
26748	43	16	28	Y wente out fro the fadir, and Y cam in to the world; eftsoone Y leeue the world, and Y go to the fadir.
26749	43	16	29	Hise disciplis seiden to hym, Lo! now thou spekist opynli, and thou seist no prouerbe.
26750	43	16	30	Now we witen, that thou wost alle thingis; and it is not nede to thee, that ony man axe thee. In this thing we bileuen, that thou wentist out fro God.
26751	43	16	31	Jhesus answeride to hem, Now ye bileuen.
26752	43	16	32	Lo! the our cometh, and now it cometh, that ye be disparplid, ech in to hise owne thingis, and that ye leeue me aloone; and Y am not aloone, for the fadir is with me.
26753	43	16	33	These thingis Y haue spokun to you, that ye haue pees in me; in the world ye schulen haue disese, but trust ye, Y haue ouercomun the world.
26754	43	17	1	These thingis Jhesus spak, and whanne he hadde cast vp hise iyen in to heuene, he seide, Fadir, the our cometh, clarifie thi sone, that thi sone clarifie thee.
26755	43	17	2	As thou hast youun to hym power on ech fleisch, that al thing that thou hast youun to hym, he yyue to hem euerlastynge lijf.
26756	43	17	3	And this is euerlastynge lijf, that thei knowe thee very God aloone, and whom thou hast sent, Jhesu Crist.
26757	43	17	4	Y haue clarified thee on the erthe, Y haue endid the werk, that thou hast youun to me to do.
26758	43	17	5	And now, fadir, clarifie thou me at thi silf, with the clerenesse that Y hadde at thee, bifor the world was maad.
26759	43	17	6	Y haue schewid thi name to tho men, whiche thou hast youun to me of the world; thei weren thine, and thou hast youun hem to me, and thei han kept thi word.
26760	43	17	7	And now thei han knowun, that alle thingis that thou hast youun to me, ben of thee.
26761	43	17	8	For the wordis that thou hast youun to me, Y yaf to hem; and thei han takun, and han knowun verili, that Y wente out fro thee; and thei bileueden, that thou sentist me.
26762	43	17	9	Y preie for hem, Y preye not for the world, but for hem that thou hast youun to me, for thei ben thine.
26763	43	17	10	And alle my thingis ben thine, and thi thingis ben myne; and Y am clarified in hem.
26764	43	17	11	And now Y am not in the world, and these ben in the world, and Y come to thee. Hooli fadir, kepe hem in thi name, whiche thou yauest to me, that thei ben oon, as we ben.
26765	43	17	12	While Y was with hem, Y kepte hem in thi name; thilke that thou yauest to me, Y kepte, and noon of hem perischide, but the sone of perdicioun, that the scripture be fulfillid.
26766	43	17	13	But now Y come to thee, and Y speke these thingis in the world, that thei haue my ioie fulfillid in hem silf.
26767	43	17	14	Y yaf to hem thi word, and the world hadde hem in hate; for thei ben not of the world, as Y am not of the world.
26768	43	17	15	Y preye not, that thou take hem awei fro the world, but that thou kepe hem fro yuel.
26769	43	17	16	They ben not of the world, as Y am not of the world.
26770	43	17	17	Halewe thou hem in treuth; thi word is treuthe.
26771	43	17	18	As thou sentist me in to the world, also Y sente hem `in to the world.
26772	43	17	19	And Y halewe my silf for hem, that also thei ben halewid in treuthe.
26773	43	17	20	And Y preye not oneli for hem, but also for hem that schulden bileue in to me bi the word of hem;
26774	43	17	21	that all ben oon, as thou, fadir, in me, and Y in thee, that also thei in vs be oon; that the world bileue, that thou hast sent me.
26775	43	17	22	And Y haue youun to hem the clerenesse, that thou hast youun to me, that thei ben oon,
26776	43	17	23	as we ben oon; Y in hem, and thou in me, that thei be endid in to oon; and that the world knowe, that thou sentist me, and hast loued hem, as thou hast loued also me.
26777	43	17	24	Fadir, thei whiche thou yauest to me, Y wole that where Y am, that thei be with me, that thei see my clerenesse, that thou hast youun to me; for thou louedist me bifor the makyng of the world.
26778	43	17	25	Fadir, riytfuli the world knew thee not, but Y knew thee, and these knewen, that thou sentist me.
26779	43	17	26	And Y haue maad thi name knowun to hem, and schal make knowun; that the loue bi which thou `hast loued me, be in hem, and Y in hem.
26780	43	18	1	Whanne Jhesus hadde seid these thingis, he wente out with hise disciplis ouer the strond of Cedron, where was a yerd, in to which he entride, and hise disciplis.
26781	43	18	2	And Judas, that bitrayede hym, knew the place, for ofte Jhesus cam thidur with hise disciplis.
26782	43	18	3	Therfor whanne Judas hadde takun a cumpany of knyytis, and mynystris of the bischopis and of the Fariseis, he cam thidur with lanternys, and brondis, and armeris.
26783	43	18	4	And so Jhesus witynge alle thingis that weren to come on hym, wente forth, and seide to hem, Whom seken ye?
26784	43	18	5	Thei answeriden to hym, Jhesu of Nazareth. Jhesus seith to hem, Y am. And Judas that bitraiede hym, stood with hem.
26785	43	18	6	And whanne he seide to hem, Y am, thei wenten abak, and fellen doun on the erthe.
26786	43	18	7	And eft he axide hem, Whom seken ye? And thei seiden, Jhesu of Nazareth.
26787	43	18	8	He answeride to hem, Y seide to you, that Y am; therfor if ye seken me, suffre ye these to go awei.
26788	43	18	9	That the word which he seide schulde be fulfillid, For Y loste not ony of hem, whiche thou `hast youun to me.
26789	43	18	10	Therfor Symount Petre hadde a swerd, and drow it out, and smoot the seruaunt of the bischop, and kittide of his riyt eer. And the name of the seruaunt was Malcus.
26790	43	18	11	Therfor Jhesus seide to Petre, Putte thou thi swerd in to thi schethe; wolt thou not, that Y drynke the cuppe, that my fadir yaf to me?
26791	43	18	12	Therfor the cumpenye of knyytis, and the tribune, and the mynystris of the Jewis, token Jhesu, and bounden hym,
26792	43	18	13	and ledden hym first to Annas; for he was fadir of Caifas wijf, that was bischop of that yeer.
26793	43	18	14	And it was Caifas, that yaf counsel to the Jewis, that it spedith, that o man die for the puple.
26794	43	18	15	But Symount Petre suede Jhesu, and another disciple; and thilke disciple was knowun to the bischop. And he entride with Jhesu, in to the halle of the bischop;
26795	43	18	16	but Petre stood at the dore with outforth. Therfor `the tother disciple, that was knowun to the bischop, wente out, and seide to the womman that kepte the dore, and brouyte in Petre.
26796	43	18	17	And the damysel, kepere of the dore, seide to Petre, Whether thou art also of this mannys disciplis? He seide, Y am not.
26797	43	18	18	And the seruantis and mynystris stooden at the coolis, for it was coold, and thei warmyden hem; and Petre was with hem, stondynge and warmynge hym.
26798	43	18	19	And the bischop axide Jhesu of hise disciplis, and of his techyng.
26799	43	18	20	Jhesus answerde to hym, Y haue spokun opynli to the world; Y tauyte euermore in the synagoge, and in the temple, whider alle the Jewis camen togidere, and in hiddlis Y spak no thing.
26800	43	18	21	What axist thou me? axe hem that herden, what Y haue spokun to hem; lo! thei witen, what thingis Y haue seid.
26801	43	18	22	Whanne he hadde seid these thingis, oon of the mynystris stondynge niy, yaf a buffat to Jhesu, and seide, Answerist thou so to the bischop?
26802	43	18	23	Jhesus answeride to hym, If Y haue spokun yuel, bere thou witnessyng of yuel; but if Y seide wel, whi smytist thou me?
26803	43	18	24	And Annas sente hym boundun to Caifas, the bischop.
26804	43	18	25	And Symount Petre stood, and warmyde him; and thei seiden to hym, Whether also thou art his disciple? He denyede, and seide, Y am not.
26805	43	18	26	Oon of the bischops seruantis, cosyn of hym, whos eere Petre kitte of, seide, Say Y thee not in the yerd with hym?
26806	43	18	27	And Petre eftsoone denyede, and anoon the cok crew.
26807	43	18	28	Thanne thei ledden Jhesu to Cayfas, in to the moot halle; and it was eerli, and thei entriden not in to the moot halle, that thei schulden not be defoulid, but that thei schulden ete pask.
26808	43	18	29	Therfor Pilat wente out with outforth to hem, and seide, What accusyng brynge ye ayens this man?
26809	43	18	30	Thei answeriden, and seiden to hym, If this were not a mysdoere, we hadden not bitakun hym to thee.
26810	43	18	31	Thanne Pilat seith to hem, Take ye hym, and deme ye him, after youre lawe. And the Jewis seiden to hym, It is not leueful to vs to sle ony man;
26811	43	18	32	that the word of Jhesu schulde be fulfillid, whiche he seide, signifiynge bi what deth he schulde die.
26812	43	18	33	Therfor eftsoone Pilat entride in to the moot halle, and clepide Jhesu, and seide to hym, Art thou kyng of Jewis?
26813	43	18	34	Jhesus answerde, and seide to hym, Seist thou this thing of thi silf, ether othere han seid to thee of me?
26814	43	18	35	Pilat answeride, Whether Y am a Jewe? Thi folc and bischops bitoken thee to me; what hast thou don?
26815	43	18	36	Jhesus answeride, My kingdom is not of this world; if my kingdom were of this world, my mynystris schulden stryue, that Y schulde not be takun to the Jewis; but now my kingdom is not here.
26816	43	18	37	And so Pilat seide to hym, Thanne `thou art a king. Jhesus answeride, Thou seist, that Y am a king. To this thing Y am borun, and to this Y `am comun in to the world, to bere witnessing to treuthe. Eche that is of treuthe, herith my vois.
26817	43	18	38	Pilat seith to hym, What is treuthe? And whanne he hadde seid this thing, eft he wente out to the Jewis, and seide to hem, Y fynde no cause in hym.
26818	43	18	39	But it is a custom to you, that Y delyuere oon to you in pask; therfor wole ye that Y delyuere to you the kyng of Jewis?
26819	43	18	40	Alle crieden eftsoone, and seiden, Not this, but Baraban. And Barabas was a theef.
26820	43	19	1	Therfor Pilat took thanne Jhesu, and scourgide.
26821	43	19	2	And kniytis writhen a coroun of thornes, and setten on his heed, and diden aboute hym a cloth of purpur,
26822	43	19	3	and camen to him, and seiden, Heil, kyng of Jewis. And thei yauen to him buffatis.
26823	43	19	4	Eftsoone Pilat wente out, and seide to hem, Lo! Y brynge hym out to you, that ye knowe, that Y fynde no cause in him.
26824	43	19	5	And so Jhesus wente out, berynge a coroun of thornes, and a cloth of purpur. And he seith to hem, Lo! the man.
26825	43	19	6	But whanne the bischopis and mynystris hadden seyn hym, thei crieden, and seiden, Crucifie, crucifie hym. Pilat seith to hem, Take ye hym, and crucifie ye, for Y fynde no cause in hym.
26826	43	19	7	The Jewis answeriden to hym. We han a lawe, and bi the lawe he owith to die, for he made hym Goddis sone.
26827	43	19	8	Therfor whanne Pilat hadde herd this word, he dredde the more.
26828	43	19	9	And he wente in to the moot halle eftsoone, and seide to Jhesu, Of whennus art thou? But Jhesus yaf noon answere to him.
26829	43	19	10	Pilat seith to him, Spekist thou not to me? Woost thou not, that Y haue power to crucifie thee, and Y haue power to delyuere thee?
26830	43	19	11	Jhesus answeride, Thou schuldist not `haue ony power ayens me, but it were youun to thee from aboue; therfor he that bitook me to thee, hath the more synne.
26831	43	19	12	Fro that tyme Pilat souyte to delyuere hym; but the Jewis crieden, and seiden, If thou delyuerist this man, thou art not the emperouris freend; for ech man that makith hym silf king, ayen seith the emperoure.
26832	43	19	13	And Pilat, whanne he hadde herd these wordis, ledde Jhesu forth, and sat for domesman in a place, that is seid Licostratos, but in Ebrew Golgatha.
26833	43	19	14	And it was pask eue, as it were the sixte our. And he seith to the Jewis, Lo! youre king.
26834	43	19	15	But thei crieden, and seiden, Take awei, take awei; crucifie him. Pilat seith to hem, Schal I crucifie youre king? The bischops answeriden, We han no king but the emperour.
26835	43	19	16	And thanne Pilat bitook him to hem, that he schulde be crucified. And thei token Jhesu, and ledden him out.
26836	43	19	17	And he bar to hym silf a cros, and wente out in to that place, that is seid of Caluarie, in Ebreu Golgatha;
26837	43	19	18	where thei crucifieden him, and othere tweyne with him, oon on this side and oon on that side, and Jhesus in the myddil.
26838	43	19	19	And Pilat wroot a title, and sette on the cros; and it was writun, Jhesu of Nazareth, king of Jewis.
26839	43	19	20	Therfor manye of the Jewis redden this title, for the place where Jhesus was crucified, was niy the citee, and it was writun in Ebreu, Greek, and Latyn.
26840	43	19	21	Therfor the bischops of the Jewis seiden to Pilat, Nyle thou write kyng of Jewis, but for he seide, Y am king of Jewis.
26841	43	19	22	Pilat answeride, That that Y haue writun, Y haue writun.
26842	43	19	23	Therfor the knyytis whanne thei hadden crucified hym, token hise clothis, and maden foure partis, to ech knyyt a part, and a coot. And the coot was without seem, and wouun al aboute.
26843	43	19	24	Therfor thei seiden togidere, Kitte we not it, but caste we lot, whos it is; that the scripture be fulfillid, seiynge, Thei partiden my clothis to hem, and on my cloth thei casten lot. And the kniytis diden these thingis.
26844	43	19	25	But bisidis the cros of Jhesu stoden his modir, and the sistir of his modir, Marie Cleofe, and Marie Maudeleyne.
26845	43	19	26	Therfor whanne Jhesu hadde seyn his modir, and the disciple stondynge, whom he louyde, he seith to hise modir, Womman, lo thi sone.
26846	43	19	27	Aftyrward he seith to the disciple, Lo! thi modir. And fro that our the disciple took hir in to his modir.
26847	43	19	28	Aftirward Jhesus witynge, that now alle thingis ben endid, that the scripture were fulfillid, he seith, Y thirste.
26848	43	19	29	And a vessel was set ful of vynegre. And thei `leiden in isope aboute the spounge ful of vynegre, and putten to his mouth.
26849	43	19	30	Therfor whanne Jhesus hadde `takun the vynegre, he seid, It is endid. And `whanne his heed was bowid doun, `he yaf vp the goost.
26850	43	19	31	Therfor for it was the pask eue, that the bodies schulden not abide on the cros in the sabat, for that was a greet sabat dai, the Jewis preiden Pilat, that the hipis of hem schulden be brokun, and thei takun awei.
26851	43	19	32	Therfor knyytis camen, and thei braken the thies of the firste, and of the tothere, that was crucified with hym.
26852	43	19	33	But whanne thei weren comun to Jhesu, as thei sayn him deed thanne, thei braken not hise thies;
26853	43	19	34	but oon of the knyytis openyde his side with a spere, and anoon blood and watir wenten out.
26854	43	19	35	And he that saiy, bare witnessyng, and his witnessing is trewe; and he woot that he seith trewe thingis, that ye bileue.
26855	43	19	36	And these thingis weren don, that the scripture schulde be fulfillid, Ye schulen not breke a boon of hym.
26856	43	19	37	And eftsoone another scripture seith, Thei schulen se in whom thei piyten thorow.
26857	43	19	38	But after these thingis Joseph of Armathi preyede Pilat, that he schulde take awei the bodi of Jhesu, for that he was a disciple of Jhesu, but priui for drede of the Jewis. And Pilat suffride. And so he cam, and took awei the bodi of Jhesu.
26858	43	19	39	And Nychodeme cam also, that hadde come to hym first bi nyyt, and brouyte a meddlynge of myrre and aloes, as it were an hundrid pound.
26859	43	19	40	And thei token the bodi of Jhesu, and boundun it in lynun clothis with swete smellynge oynementis, as it is custom to Jewis for to birie.
26860	43	19	41	And in the place where he was crucified, was a yerd, and in the yerd a newe graue, in which yit no man was leid.
26861	43	19	42	Therfor there thei putten Jhesu, for the vigilie of Jewis feeste, for the sepulcre was niy.
26862	43	20	1	And in o dai of the wouke Marie Maudeleyn cam eerli to the graue, whanne it was yit derk. And sche say the stoon moued awei fro the graue.
26863	43	20	2	Therfor sche ran, and cam to Symount Petre, and to another disciple, whom Jhesus louede, and seith to hem, Thei han takun the Lord fro the graue, and we witen not, where thei han leid hym.
26864	43	20	3	Therfor Petre wente out, and thilke other disciple, and thei camen to the graue.
26865	43	20	4	And thei tweyne runnen togidre, and thilke othere disciple ran bifor Petre, and cam first to the graue.
26866	43	20	5	And whanne he stoupide, he sai the schetis liynge, netheles he entride not.
26867	43	20	6	Therfor Symount Petre cam suynge hym, and he entride in to the graue, and he say the schetis leid,
26868	43	20	7	and the sudarie that was on his heed, not leid with the schetis, but bi it silf wlappid in to a place.
26869	43	20	8	Therfor thanne thilke disciple that cam first to the graue, entride, and sai, and bileuede.
26870	43	20	9	For thei knewen not yit the scripture, that it behofte him to rise ayen fro deth.
26871	43	20	10	Therfor the disciplis wenten eftsoone to hem silf.
26872	43	20	11	But Marie stood at the graue with outforth wepynge. And the while sche wepte, sche bowide hir, and bihelde forth in to the graue.
26873	43	20	12	And sche sai twei aungels sittinge in white, oon at the heed and oon at the feet, where the bodi of Jhesu was leid.
26874	43	20	13	And thei seien to hir, Womman, what wepist thou? Sche seide to hem, For thei han take awei my lord, and Y woot not, where thei han leid him.
26875	43	20	14	Whanne sche hadde seid these thingis, sche turnede bacward, and sai Jhesu stondinge, and wiste not that it was Jhesu.
26876	43	20	15	Jhesus seith to hir, Womman, what wepist thou? whom sekist thou? She gessynge that he was a gardynere, seith to him, Sire, if thou hast takun him vp, seie to me, where thou hast leid him, and Y schal take hym awei.
26877	43	20	16	Jhesus seith to hir, Marie. Sche `turnede, and seith to hym, Rabony, that is to seie, Maister.
26878	43	20	17	Jhesus seith to hir, Nyle thou touche me, for Y haue not yit stied to my fadir; but go to my britheren, and seie to hem, Y stie to my fadir and to youre fadir, to my God and to youre God.
26879	43	20	18	Marie Maudeleyne cam, tellinge to the disciplis, That Y sai the Lord, and these thingis he seide to me.
26880	43	20	19	Therfor whanne it was eue in that dai, oon of the sabatis, and the yatis weren schit, where the disciplis weren gaderid, for drede of the Jewis, Jhesus cam, and stood in the myddil of the disciplis, and he seith to hem, Pees to you.
26881	43	20	20	And whanne he hadde seid this, he schewide to hem hondis and side; therfor the disciplis ioieden, for the Lord was seyn.
26882	43	20	21	And he seith to hem eft, Pees to you; as the fadir sente me, Y sende you.
26883	43	20	22	Whanne he had seid this, he blewe on hem, and seide, Take ye the Hooli Goost;
26884	43	20	23	whos synnes ye foryyuen, tho ben foryouun to hem; and whos ye withholden, tho ben withholdun.
26885	43	20	24	But Thomas, oon of the twelue, that is seid Didimus, was not with hem, whanne Jhesus cam.
26886	43	20	25	Therfor the othere disciplis seiden, We han seyn the Lord. And he seide to hem, But Y se in hise hondis the fitchinge of the nailis, and putte my fyngur in to the places of the nailis, and putte myn hond in to his side, Y schal not bileue.
