26887	43	20	26	And after eiyte daies eftsoone hise disciplis weren with ynne, and Thomas with hem. Jhesus cam, while the yatis weren schit, and stood in the myddil, and seide, Pees to you.
26888	43	20	27	Afterward he seith to Thomas, Putte in here thi fyngur, and se myn hondis, and putte hidur thin hond, and putte in to my side, and nyle thou be vnbileueful, but feithful.
26889	43	20	28	Thomas answeride, and seide to him, My Lord and my God.
26890	43	20	29	Jhesus seith to him, Thomas, for thou hast seyn me, thou bileuedist; blessid ben thei, that seyn not, and han bileued.
26891	43	20	30	And Jhesus dide many othere signes in the siyt of hise disciplis, whiche ben not writun in this book.
26892	43	20	31	But these ben writun, that ye bileue, that Jhesus `is Crist, the sone of God, and that ye bileuynge haue lijf in his name.
26893	43	21	1	Afterward Jhesus eftsoone schewide hym to hise disciplis, at the see of Tiberias.
26894	43	21	2	And he schewide him thus. There weren togidere Symount Petre, and Thomas, that is seid Didimus, and Nathanael, that was of the Cane of Galilee, and the sones of Zebedee, and tweyne othere of hise disciplis.
26895	43	21	3	Symount Petre seith to hem, Y go to fische. Thei seyn to hym, And we comen with thee. And `thei wenten out, `and wenten in to a boot. And in that niyt thei token no thing.
26896	43	21	4	But whanne the morewe was comun, Jhesus stood in the brenke; netheles the disciplis knewen not, that it was Jhesus.
26897	43	21	5	Therfor Jhesus seith to hem, Children, whethir ye han ony souping thing? Thei answeriden to hym, Nay. He seide to hem,
26898	43	21	6	Putte ye the nett in to the riyt half of the rowing, and ye schulen fynde. And thei puttiden the nett; and thanne thei miyten not drawe it for multitude of fischis.
26899	43	21	7	Therfor thilke disciple, whom Jhesus louede, seide to Petre, It is the Lord. Symount Petre, whanne he hadde herd that it is the Lord, girte hym with a coote, for he was nakid, and wente in to the see.
26900	43	21	8	But the othere disciplis camen bi boot, for thei weren not fer fro the lond, but as a two hundrid cubitis, drawinge the nett of fischis.
26901	43	21	9	And as thei camen doun in to the lond, thei sayn coolis liynge, and a fisch leid on, and breed.
26902	43	21	10	Jhesus seith to hem, Bringe ye of the fyschis, whiche ye han takun now.
26903	43	21	11	Symount Petre wente vp, and drowy the nett in to the lond, ful of grete fischis, an hundrid fifti and thre; and whanne thei weren so manye, the nett was not brokun.
26904	43	21	12	Jhesus seith to hem, Come ye, ete ye. And no man of hem that saten at the mete, durste axe hym, Who art thou, witinge that it is the Lord.
26905	43	21	13	And Jhesus cam, and took breed, an yaf to hem, and fisch also.
26906	43	21	14	Now this thridde tyme Jhesus was schewid to hise disciplis, whanne he hadde risun ayen fro deth.
26907	43	21	15	And whanne thei hadde etun, Jhesus seith to Simount Petre, Symount of Joon, louest thou me more than these? He seith to him, Yhe, Lord, thou woost that Y loue thee. Jhesus seith to hym, Fede thou my lambren.
26908	43	21	16	Eft he seith to hym, Symount of Joon, louest thou me? He seith to him, Yhe, Lord, thou woost that Y loue thee. He seith to him, Fede thou my lambren.
26909	43	21	17	He seith to him the thridde tyme, Simount of Joon, louest thou me? Petre was heuy, for he seith to hym the thridde tyme, Louest thou me, and he seith to him, Lord, thou knowist alle thingis; thou woost that Y loue thee. Jhesus seith to hym, Fede my scheep.
26910	43	21	18	Treuli, treuli, Y seie to thee, whanne thou were yongere, thou girdidist thee, and wandridist where thou woldist; but whanne thou schalt waxe eldere, thou schalt holde forth thin hondis, and another schal girde thee, and schal lede thee whidur thou wolt not.
26911	43	21	19	He seide this thing, signifynge bi what deth he schulde glorifie God. And whanne he hadde seid these thingis, he seith to hym, Sue thou me.
26912	43	21	20	Petre turnede, and say thilke disciple suynge, whom Jhesus louede, which also restid in the soper on his brest, and he seide to hym, Lord, who is it, that schal bitraie thee?
26913	43	21	21	Therfor whanne Petre hadde seyn this, he seith to Jhesu, Lord, but what this?
26914	43	21	22	Jhesus seith to him, So I wole that he dwelle til that Y come, what to thee? sue thou me.
26915	43	21	23	Therfor this word wente out among the britheren, that thilke disciple dieth not. And Jhesus seide not to hym, that he dieth not, but, So Y wole that he dwelle til Y come, what to thee?
26916	43	21	24	This is thilke disciple, that berith witnessyng of these thingis, and wroot hem; and we witen, that his witnessyng is trewe.
26917	43	21	25	And ther ben also manye othere thingis that Jhesus dide, whiche if thei ben writun bi ech bi hym silf, Y deme that the world hym silf schal not take tho bookis, that ben to be writun.
26918	44	1	1	Theofle, first `Y made a sermoun of alle thingis, that Jhesu bigan to do and to teche,
26919	44	1	2	in to the daie of his ascencioun, in which he comaundide bi the Hooli Goost to hise apostlis, whiche he hadde chosun;
26920	44	1	3	to whiche he schewide hym silf `alyue aftir his passioun, by many argumentis, apperinge to hem fourti daies, and spekinge of the rewme of God.
26921	44	1	4	And he ete with hem, and comaundide, that thei schulden not departe fro Jerusalem, but abide the biheest of the fadir, which ye herden, he seide, bi my mouth;
26922	44	1	5	for Joon baptiside in watir, but ye schulen be baptisid in the Hooli Goost, aftir these fewe daies.
26923	44	1	6	Therfor thei that weren come to gidere, axiden hym, and seiden, Lord, whether in this time thou schalt restore the kingdom of Israel?
26924	44	1	7	And he seide to hem, It is not youre to knowe the tymes ether momentis, whiche the fadir hath put in his power;
26925	44	1	8	but ye schulen take the vertu of the Hooli Goost comynge fro aboue in to you, and ye schulen be my witnessis in Jerusalem, and in al Judee, and Samarie, and to the vtmeste of the erthe.
26926	44	1	9	And whanne he had seid these thingis, in her siyt he was lift vp, and a cloude resseyuede him fro her iyen.
26927	44	1	10	And whanne thei biheelden hym goynge in to heuene, lo! `twei men stoden bisidis hem in white clothing, and seiden,
26928	44	1	11	Men of Galile, what stonden ye biholdinge in to heuene? This Jhesu, which is takun vp `fro you in to heuene, schal come, as ye seyn hym goynge in to heuene.
26929	44	1	12	Thanne thei turneden ayen to Jerusalem, fro the hille that is clepid `the hille of Olyuete, which is bisidis Jerusalem an halidaies iourney.
26930	44	1	13	And whanne thei weren entrid in to the hous, where thei dwelliden, thei wenten vp in to the soler, Petir and Joon, James and Andreu, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matheu, James of Alphei, and Symount Zelotes, and Judas of James.
26931	44	1	14	Alle these weren lastingli contynuynge with o wille in preier, with wymmen, and Marie, the moder of Jhesu, and with hise britheren.
26932	44	1	15	In tho daies Petre roos vp in the myddil of the britheren, and seide; and ther was a company of men togidere, almest an hundrid and twenti;
26933	44	1	16	Britheren, it bihoueth that the scripture be fillid, whiche the Hooly Goost bifore seide bi the mouth of Dauith, of Judas that was ledere of hem that token Jhesu;
26934	44	1	17	and was noumbrid among vs, and gat a part of this seruyce.
26935	44	1	18	And this Judas hadde a feeld of the hire of wickidnesse, and he was hangid, and `to-brast the myddil, and alle hise entrailes weren sched abrood.
26936	44	1	19	And it was maad knowun to alle men that dwelten in Jerusalem, so that the ilke feeld was clepid Acheldemak in the langage of hem, that is, the feeld of blood.
26937	44	1	20	And it is writun in the book of Salmes, The abitacioun of hem be maad desert, and be ther noon that dwelle in it, and an other take his bishopriche.
26938	44	1	21	Therfor it bihoueth of these men, that ben gaderid togidere with vs in al the tyme, in which the Lord Jhesu entride, and wente out among vs,
26939	44	1	22	and bigan fro the baptym of Joon til in to the dai in which he was takun vp fro vs, that oon of these be maad a witnesse of his resurreccioun with vs.
26940	44	1	23	And thei ordeyneden tweyn, Joseph, that was clepid Barsabas, that was named Just, and Mathie.
26941	44	1	24	And thei preieden, and seiden, Thou, Lord, that knowist the hertis of alle men, schewe whom thou hast chosun of these tweyne,
26942	44	1	25	that oon take the place of this seruyce and apostlehed, of which Judas trespasside, that he schulde go in to his place.
26943	44	1	26	And thei yauen lottis to hem, and the lot felde on Mathie; and he was noumbrid with enleuen apostlis.
26944	44	2	1	And whanne the daies of Pentecost weren fillid, alle the disciplis weren togidre in the same place.
26945	44	2	2	And sodeynli ther was maad a sown fro heuene, as of a greet wynde comynge, and it fillide al the hous where thei saten.
26946	44	2	3	And diuerse tungis as fier apperiden to hem, and it sat on ech of hem.
26947	44	2	4	And alle weren fillid with the Hooli Goost, and thei bigunnen to speke diuerse langagis, as the Hooli Goost yaf to hem for to speke.
26948	44	2	5	And ther weren in Jerusalem dwellinge Jewis, religiouse men, of ech nacioun that is vndur heuene.
26949	44	2	6	And whanne this vois was maad, the multitude cam togidere, and thei weren astonyed in thouyt, for ech man herde hem spekinge in his langage.
26950	44	2	7	And alle weren astonyed, and wondriden, and seiden togidere, Whether not alle these that speken ben men of Galyle,
26951	44	2	8	and hou herden we ech man his langage in which we ben borun?
26952	44	2	9	Parthi, and Medi, and Elamyte, and thei that dwellen at Mesopotami, Judee, and Capodosie, and Ponte,
26953	44	2	10	and Asie, Frigie, and Pamfilie, Egipt, and the parties of Libie, that is aboue Sirenen, and `comelingis Romayns, and Jewis,
26954	44	2	11	and proselitis, men of Crete, and of Arabie, we han herd hem spekynge in oure langagis the grete thingis of God.
26955	44	2	12	And alle weren astonyed, and wondriden, `and seiden togidere, What wole this thing be?
26956	44	2	13	And othere scorneden, and seiden, For these men ben ful of must.
26957	44	2	14	But Petre stood with the enleuene, and reiside vp his vois, and spak to hem, Ye Jewis, and alle that dwellen at Jerusalem, be this knowun to you, and with eris perseyue ye my wordis.
26958	44	2	15	For not as ye wenen, these ben dronkun, whanne it is the thridde our of the dai;
26959	44	2	16	but this it is, that was seid bi the prophete Johel,
26960	44	2	17	And it schal be in the laste daies, the Lord seith, Y schal helde out my spirit on ech fleisch; and youre sones and youre douytris schulen prophesie, and youre yonge men schulen se visiouns, and youre eldris schulen dreme sweuenes.
26961	44	2	18	And on my seruauntis and myn handmaidens in tho daies Y schal schede out of my spirit, and thei schulen prophecie.
26962	44	2	19	And Y schal yyue grete wondris in heuene aboue, and signes in erthe bynethe, blood, and fier, and heete of smoke.
26963	44	2	20	The sunne schal be turned in to derknessis, and the moone in to blood, bifor that the greet and the opyn dai of the Lord come.
26964	44	2	21	And it schal be, ech man which euere schal clepe to help the name of the Lord, schal be saaf.
26965	44	2	22	Ye men of Israel, here ye these wordis. Jhesu of Nazareth, a man preued of God bifor you bi vertues, and wondris, and tokenes, which God dide bi hym in the myddil of you,
26966	44	2	23	as ye witen, ye turmentiden, and killiden hym bi the hoondis of wyckid men, bi counseil determyned and bitakun bi the forknouwyng of God.
26967	44	2	24	Whom God reiside, whanne sorewis of helle weren vnboundun, bi that that it was impossible that he were holdun of it.
26968	44	2	25	For Dauid seith of hym, Y saiy afer the Lord bifore me euermore, for he is on my riythalf, that Y be not mouyd.
26969	44	2	26	For this thing myn herte ioiede, and my tunge made ful out ioye, and more ouere my fleisch schal reste in hope.
26970	44	2	27	For thou schalt not leeue my soule in helle, nethir thou schalt yiue thin hooli to se corrupcioun.
26971	44	2	28	Thou hast maad knowun to me the weies of lijf, thou schalt fille me in myrthe with thi face.
26972	44	2	29	Britheren, be it leueful boldli to seie to you of the patriark Dauid, for he is deed and biried, and his sepulcre is among vs in to this dai.
26973	44	2	30	Therfore whanne he was a prophete, and wiste, that with a greet ooth God hadde sworn to hym, that of the fruyt of his leende schulde oon sitte on his seete,
26974	44	2	31	he seynge afer spak of the resurreccioun of Crist, for nether he was left in helle, nether his fleisch saiy corrupcioun.
26975	44	2	32	God reiside this Jhesu, to whom we alle ben witnessis.
26976	44	2	33	Therfor he was enhaunsid bi the riythoond of God, and thorouy the biheest of the Hooli Goost that he took of the fadir, he schedde out this spirit, that ye seen and heren.
26977	44	2	34	For Dauid stiede not in to heuene; but he seith, The Lord seide to my Lord,
26978	44	2	35	Sitte thou on my riyt half, til Y putte thin enemyes a stool of thi feet.
26979	44	2	36	Therfor moost certeynli wite al the hous of Israel, that God made hym bothe Lord and Crist, this Jhesu, whom ye crucefieden.
26980	44	2	37	Whanne thei herden these thingis, thei weren compunct in herte; and thei seiden to Petre and othere apostlis, Britheren, what schulen we do?
26981	44	2	38	And Petre seide to hem, Do ye penaunce, and eche of you be baptisid in the name of Jhesu Crist, in to remissioun of youre synnes; and ye schulen take the yifte of the Hooli Goost.
26982	44	2	39	For the biheest is to you, and to youre sones, and to alle that ben fer, which euer oure Lord God hath clepid.
26983	44	2	40	Also with othere wordis ful many he witnesside to hem, and monestide hem, and seide, Be ye sauyd fro this schrewid generacioun.
26984	44	2	41	Thanne thei that resseyueden his word weren baptisid, and in that dai soulis weren encreesid, aboute thre thousinde;
26985	44	2	42	and weren lastynge stabli in the teching of the apostlis, and in comynyng of the breking of breed, in preieris.
26986	44	2	43	And drede was maad to ech man. And many wondris and signes weren don bi the apostlis in Jerusalem, and greet drede was in alle.
26987	44	2	44	And alle that bileueden weren togidre, and hadden alle thingis comyn.
26988	44	2	45	Thei selden possessiouns and catel, and departiden tho thingis to alle men, as it was nede to ech.
26989	44	2	46	And ech dai thei dwelliden stabli with o wille in the temple, and braken breed aboute housis, and token mete with ful out ioye and symplenesse of herte,
26990	44	2	47	and herieden togidere God, and hadden grace to al the folk. And the Lord encreside hem that weren maad saaf, ech dai in to the same thing.
26991	44	3	1	And Petre and Joon wenten vp in to the temple, at the nynthe our of preiyng.
26992	44	3	2	And a man that was lame fro the wombe of his modir, was borun, and was leid ech dai at the yate of the temple, that is seid feir, to axe almes of men that entriden in to the temple.
26993	44	3	3	This, whanne he say Petre and Joon bigynnynge to entre in to the temple, preyede that he schulde take almes.
26994	44	3	4	And Petre with Joon bihelde on hym, and seide, Biholde thou in to vs.
26995	44	3	5	And he biheelde in to hem, and hopide, that he schulde take sumwhat of hem.
26996	44	3	6	But Petre seide, Y haue nether siluer ne gold; but that that Y haue, Y yiue to thee. In the name of Jhesu Crist of Nazareth, rise thou vp, and go.
26997	44	3	7	And he took hym bi the riythoond, and heuede hym vp; and anoon hise leggis and hise feet weren sowdid togidere;
26998	44	3	8	and he lippide, and stood, and wandride. And he entride with hem in to the temple, and wandride, and lippide, and heriede God.
26999	44	3	9	And al the puple sai hym walkinge, and heriynge God.
27000	44	3	10	And thei knewen hym, that he it was that sat at almes at the feire yate of the temple. And thei weren fillid with wondryng, and stoniynge, in that thing that byfelde to hym.
27001	44	3	11	But whanne thei sien Petre and Joon, al the puple ran to hem at the porche that was clepid of Salomon, and wondriden greetli.
27002	44	3	12	And Petre siy, and answeride to the puple, Men of Israel, what wondren ye in this thing? ether what biholden ye vs, as by oure vertue ethir power we maden this man for to walke?
27003	44	3	13	God of Abraham, and God of Ysaac, and God of Jacob, God of oure fadris, hath glorified his sone Jhesu, whom ye bitraieden, and denyeden bifor the face of Pilat, whanne he demede hym to be delyuered.
27004	44	3	14	But ye denyeden the hooli and the riytful, and axiden a mansleer to be youun to you.
27005	44	3	15	And ye slowen the maker of lijf, whom God reiside fro deth, of whom we ben witnessis.
27006	44	3	16	And in the feith of his name he hath confermyd this man, whom ye seen and knowen; the name of hym, and the feith that is bi him, yaf to this man ful heelthe in the siyt of alle you.
27007	44	3	17	And now, britheren, Y woot that bi vnwityng ye diden, as also youre princis.
27008	44	3	18	But God that bifor telde bi the mouth of alle profetis, that his Crist schulde suffre, hath fillid so.
27009	44	3	19	Therfor be ye repentaunt, and be ye conuertid, that youre synnes be don awei,
27010	44	3	20	that whanne the tymes of refresching schulen come from the siyt of the Lord, and he schal sende thilke Jhesu Crist,
27011	44	3	21	that is now prechid to you. Whom it bihoueth heuene to resseyue, in to the tymes of restitucioun of alle thingis, which the Lord spak bi the mouth of hise hooli prophetis fro the world.
27012	44	3	22	For Moises seide, For the Lord youre God schal reise to you a profete, of youre britheren; as me, ye schulen here hym bi alle thingis, what euer he schal speke to you.
27013	44	3	23	And it schal be, that euery man that schal not here the ilke profete, schal be distried fro the puple.
27014	44	3	24	And alle prophetis fro Samuel and aftirward, that spaken, telden these daies.
27015	44	3	25	But ye ben the sones of prophetis, and of the testament, that God ordeynede to oure fadris, and seide to Abraham, In thi seed alle the meynes of erthe schulen be blessid.
27016	44	3	26	God reiside his sone first to you, and sente hym blessynge you, that ech man conuerte hym from his wickidnesse.
27017	44	4	1	And while thei spaken to the puple, the preestis and magistratis of the temple, and the Saduceis camen vpon hem, and soreweden,
27018	44	4	2	that thei tauyten the puple, and telden in Jhesu the ayenrisyng fro deth.
27019	44	4	3	And thei leiden hondis on hem, and puttiden hem in to warde in to the morewe; for it was thanne euentid.
27020	44	4	4	But manye of hem that hadden herd the word, bileueden; and the noumbre of men was maad fyue thousyndis.
27021	44	4	5	And amorewe it was don, that the princis of hem, and eldre men and scribis weren gadirid in Jerusalem;
27022	44	4	6	and Annas, prince of preestis, and Caifas, and Joon, and Alisaundre, and hou manye euere weren of the kynde of preestis.
27023	44	4	7	And thei settiden hem in the myddil, and axiden, In what vertue, ether in what name, han ye don this thing?
27024	44	4	8	Thanne Petre was fillid with the Hooli Goost, and seide to hem, Ye pryncis of the puple, and ye eldre men, here ye.
27025	44	4	9	If we to dai be demyd in the good dede of a sijk man, in whom this man is maad saaf,
27026	44	4	10	be it knowun to you alle, and to al the puple of Israel, that in the name of Jhesu Crist of Nazareth, whom ye crucifieden, whom God reiside fro deth, in this this man stondith hool bifor you.
27027	44	4	11	This is the stoon, which was repreued of you bildinge, which is maad in to the heed of the corner;
27028	44	4	12	and heelthe is not in ony othir. For nether other name vndur heuene is youun to men, in which it bihoueth vs to be maad saaf.
27029	44	4	13	And thei siyen the stidfastnesse of Petre and of Joon, for it was foundun that thei weren men vnlettrid, and lewid men, and thei wondriden, and knewen hem that thei weren with Jhesu.
27030	44	4	14	And thei siyen the man that was helid, stondinge with hem, and thei myyten no thing ayenseie.
27031	44	4	15	But thei comaundiden hem to go forth with out the counsel. And thei spaken togidere,
27032	44	4	16	and seiden, What schulen we do to these men? for the signe is maad knowun bi hem to alle men, that dwellen at Jerusalem; it is opyn, and we moun not denye.
27033	44	4	17	But that it be no more pupplischid in to the puple, manasse we to hem, that thei speke no more in this name to ony men.
27034	44	4	18	And thei clepiden hem, and denounsiden to hem, that on no maner thei schulden speke, nether teche, in the name of Jhesu.
27035	44	4	19	But Petre and Joon answeriden, and seiden to hem, If it be riytful in the siyt of God to here you rather than God, deme ye.
27036	44	4	20	For we moten nedis speke tho thingis, that we han sayn and herd.
27037	44	4	21	And thei manassiden, and leften hem, and foundun not hou thei schulden punische hem, for the puple; for alle men clarifieden that thing that was don in that that was bifalle.
27038	44	4	22	For the man was more than of fourty yeer, in which this signe of heelthe was maad.
27039	44	4	23	And whanne thei weren delyuerid, thei camen to her felowis, and telden to hem, hou grete thingis the princis of preestis and the eldre men hadden seid to hem.
27040	44	4	24	And whanne thei herden, with oon herte thei reiseden vois to the Lord, and seiden, Lord, thou that madist heuene and erthe, see, and alle thingis that ben in hem, which seidist bi the Hooli Goost,
27041	44	4	25	bi the mouth of oure fadir Dauid, thi child, Whi hethen men gnastiden with teeth togidre, and the puplis thouyten veyn thingis?
27042	44	4	26	Kyngis of the erthe stoden nyy, and princis camen togidre `in to oon, ayens the Lord, and ayens his Crist.
27043	44	4	27	For verili Eroude and Pounce Pilat, with hethene men, and puplis of Israel, camen togidre in this citee ayens thin hooli child Jhesu,
27044	44	4	28	whom thou anoyntidist, to do the thingis, that thin hoond and thi counsel demyden to be don.
27045	44	4	29	And now, Lord, biholde in to the thretnyngis of hem, and graunte to thi seruauntis to speke thi word with al trist,
27046	44	4	30	in that thing that thou holde forth thin hond, that heelthis and signes and wondris be maad bi the name of thin hooli sone Jhesu.
27047	44	4	31	And whanne thei hadden preyed, the place was moued, in which thei weren gaderid; and alle weren fillid with the Hooli Goost, and spaken the word of God with trist.
27048	44	4	32	And of al the multitude of men bileuynge was oon herte and oon wille; nether ony man seide ony thingis of tho thingis that he weldide to be his owne, but alle thingis weren comyn to hem.
27049	44	4	33	And with greet vertu the apostlis yeldiden witnessyng of the ayenrysyng of Jhesu Crist oure Lord, and greet grace was in alle hem.
27050	44	4	34	For nether ony nedi man was among hem, for how manye euere weren possessouris of feeldis, ether of housis, thei seelden, and brouyten the pricis of tho thingis that thei seelden,
27051	44	4	35	and leiden bifor the feet of the apostlis. And it was departid to ech, as it was nede to ech.
27052	44	4	36	Forsothe Joseph, that was named Barsabas of apostlis, that is to seie, the sone of coumfort, of the lynage of Leuy,
27053	44	4	37	a man of Cipre, whanne he hadde a feeld, seelde it, and brouyte the prijs, and leide it bifor the feet of apostlis.
27054	44	5	1	But a man, Anany bi name, with Safira, his wijf,
27055	44	5	2	seelde a feeld, and defraudide of the prijs of the feeld; and his wijf was witinge. And he brouyte a part, and leide bifor the feet of the apostlis.
27056	44	5	3	And Petre seide to hym, Anany, whi hath Sathanas temptid thin herte, that thou lye to the Hooli Goost, and to defraude of the prijs of the feeld?
27057	44	5	4	Whethir it vnseld was not thin; and whanne it was seld, it was in thi power? Whi hast thou put this thing in thin herte? Thou hast not lied to men, but to God.
27058	44	5	5	Anany herde these wordis, and felde doun, and was deed. And greet drede was maad on alle that herden.
27059	44	5	6	And yonge men risen, and mouyden hym awei, and baren hym out, and birieden.
27060	44	5	7	And ther was maad as a space of thre ouris, and his wijf knewe not that thing that was don, and entride.
27061	44	5	8	And Petre answerde to hir, Womman, seie to me, whether ye seelden the feeld for so mych? And sche seide, Yhe, for so mych.
27062	44	5	9	And Petre seide to hyr, What bifelde to you, to tempte the spirit of the Lord? Lo! the feet of hem that han birieden thin hosebonde ben at the dore, and thei schulen bere thee out.
27063	44	5	10	Anoon sche felde doun at hise feet, and diede. And the yonge men entriden, and founden hir deed, and thei baren hir out, and birieden to hir hosebonde.
27064	44	5	11	And greet drede was maad in al the chirche, and in to alle that herden these thingis.
27065	44	5	12	And bi the hoondis of the apostlis signes and many wondris weren maad in the puple. And alle weren of oon acord in the porche of Salomon.
27066	44	5	13	But no man of othere durste ioyne hymsilf with hem, but the puple magnyfiede hem.
27067	44	5	14	And the multitude of men and of wymmen bileuynge in the Lord was more encreessid,
27068	44	5	15	so that thei brouyten out sike men in to stretis, and leiden in litle beddis and couchis, that whanne Petre cam, nameli the schadew of hym schulde schadewe ech of hem, and thei schulden be delyuerid fro her syknessis.
27069	44	5	16	And the multitude of citees niy to Jerusalem ran, bryngynge sijk men, and that weren trauelid of vnclene spiritis, whiche alle weren heelid.
27070	44	5	17	But the prince of preestis roos vp, and alle that weren with hym, that is the eresye of Saduceis, and weren fillid with enuye;
27071	44	5	18	and leiden hondis on the apostlis, and puttiden hem in the comyn warde.
27072	44	5	19	But the aungel of the Lord openyde bi nyyt the yatis of the prisoun, and ledde hem out, and seide, Go ye,
27073	44	5	20	and stonde ye, and speke in the temple to the puple alle the wordis of this lijf.
27074	44	5	21	Whom whanne thei hadden herd, thei entriden eerli in to the temple, and tauyten. And the prince of preestis cam, and thei that weren with him, and clepiden togidre the counsel, and alle the eldre men of the children of Israel; and senten to the prisoun, that thei schulden be brouyt forth.
27075	44	5	22	And whanne the mynystris camen, founden hem not, and for the prisoun was openyd, thei turneden ayen,
27076	44	5	23	and teelden, and seiden, We founden the prisoun schit with al diligence, and the keperis stondynge at the yatis; but we opneden, and founden no man ther ynne.
27077	44	5	24	And as the maiestratis of the temple, and the princis of preestis herden these wordis, thei doutiden of hem, what was don.
27078	44	5	25	But a man cam, and teelde to hem, For lo! tho men whiche ye han put in to prisoun, ben in the temple, and stonden, and techen the puple.
27079	44	5	26	Thanne the magistrat wente with the mynystris, and brouyte hem with out violence; for thei dredden the puple, lest thei schulden be stonyd.
27080	44	5	27	And whanne thei hadden brouyt hem, thei settiden hem in the counsel; and the princes of prestis axiden hem,
27081	44	5	28	and seiden, In comaundement we comaundiden you, that ye schulden not teche in this name, and lo! ye han fillid Jerusalem with youre teching, and ye wolen bringe on vs the blood of this man.
27082	44	5	29	And Petre answeride, and the apostlis, and seiden, It bihoueth to obeie to God, more than to men.
27083	44	5	30	God of oure fadris reiside Jhesu, whom ye slowen, hangynge in a tre.
27084	44	5	31	God enhaunside with his riythond this prince and sauyour, that penaunce were yyue to Israel, and remyssioun of synnes.
27085	44	5	32	And we ben witnessis of these wordis, and the Hooli Goost, whom God yaf to alle obeischinge to him.
27086	44	5	33	Whanne thei herden these thingis, thei weren turmentid, and thouyten to sle hem.
27087	44	5	34	But a man roos in the counsel, a Farise, Gamaliel bi name, a doctour of the lawe, a worschipful man to al the puple, and comaundide the men to be put without forth for a while.
27088	44	5	35	And he seide to hem, Ye men of Israel, take tent to you silf on these men, what ye schulen do.
27089	44	5	36	For bifore these daies Teodas, that seide hym silf to be sum man, to whom a noumbre of men consentiden, aboute foure hundrid; which was slayn, and alle that bileueden to hym, weren disparplit, and brouyt to nouyt.
27090	44	5	37	Aftir this, Judas of Galilee was in the daies of professioun, and turnyde awei the puple aftir hym; and alle hou manye euere consentiden to hym, weren scatered, and he perischide.
27091	44	5	38	And now therfor Y seie to you, departe ye fro these men, and suffre ye hem; for if this counsel ether werk is of men, it schal be vndon;
27092	44	5	39	but if it is of God, ye moun not vndo hem, lest perauenture ye be foundun to repugne God.
27093	44	5	40	And thei consentiden to him; and thei clepiden togidere the apostlis, and denounsiden to hem, that weren betun, that thei schulden no more speke in the name of Jhesu, and thei leten hem go.
27094	44	5	41	And thei wenten ioiynge fro the siyt of the counsel, that thei weren had worthi to suffre dispisyng for the name of Jhesu. But ech dai thei ceessiden not in the temple, and aboute housis, to teche and to preche Jhesu Crist.
27095	44	6	1	But in tho daies, whanne the noumbre of disciplis encreesside, the Grekis grutchiden ayens the Ebrews, for that her widewis weren dispisid in euery daies mynystryng.
27096	44	6	2	And the twelue clepiden togidere the multitude of disciplis, and seiden, It is not ryytful, that we leeuen the word of God, and mynystren to boordis.
27097	44	6	3	Therfor, britheren, biholde ye men of you of good fame, ful of the Hooli Goost and of wisdom, whiche we schulen ordeyne on this werk;
27098	44	6	4	for we schulen be bisi to preier, and preche the word of God.
27099	44	6	5	And the word pleside bifor al the multitude; and thei chesiden Styuen, a man ful of feith and of the Hooli Goost, and Filip, and Procore, and Nycanor, and Tymon, and Parmanam, and Nycol, a comelyng, a man of Antioche.
27100	44	6	6	Thei ordeyneden these bifor the siyt of apostlis, and thei preyeden, and leiden hoondis on hem.
27101	44	6	7	And the word of the Lord wexide, and the noumbre of the disciplis in Jerusalem was myche multiplied; also myche cumpany of preestis obeiede to the feith.
27102	44	6	8	And Steuen, ful of grace and of strengthe, made wondris and grete signes in the puple.
27103	44	6	9	But summe rysen of the synagoge, that was clepid of Libertyns, and Cirenensis, and of men of Alisaundre, and of hem that weren of Cilice and of Asie, and disputiden with Steuene.
27104	44	6	10	And thei miyten not withstonde the wisdom and the spirit, that spak.
27105	44	6	11	Thanne thei priueli senten men, that schulden seie, that thei herden hym seiynge wordis of blasfemye ayens Moises and God.
27106	44	6	12	And so thei moueden togidere the puple, and the eldre men, and the scribis; and thei rannen togidre, and token hym, and brouyten in to the counsel.
27107	44	6	13	And thei ordeyneden false witnessis, that seiden, This man ceessith not to speke wordis ayens the hooli place, and the lawe.
27108	44	6	14	For we herden hym seiynge, That this Jhesus of Nazareth schal destrye this place, and schal chaunge the tradiciouns, whiche Moyses bitook to us.
27109	44	6	15	And alle men that seten in the counsel bihelden hym, and sayn his face as the face of an aungel.
27110	44	7	1	And the prynce of prestis seide to Steuene, Whethir these thingis han hem so?
27111	44	7	2	Which seide, Britheren and fadris, here ye. God of glorie apperide to oure fadir Abraham, whanne he was in Mesopotamie, bifor that he dwelte in Carram, and seide to hym,
27112	44	7	3	Go out of thi loond, and of thi kynrede, and come in to the loond, which Y schal schewe to thee.
27113	44	7	4	Thanne he wente out of the loond of Caldeis, and dwelte in Carram. And fro thens aftir that his fader was deed, he translatide him in to this loond, in which ye dwellen now.
27114	44	7	5	And he yaf not to hym eritage in it, nethir a paas of a foot, but he bihiyte to yyue hym it in to possessioun, and to his seed aftir hym, whanne he hadde not a sone.
27115	44	7	6	And God spak to hym, That his seed schal be comling in an alien lond, and thei schulen make hem suget to seruage, and schulen yuel trete hem, foure hundrid yeris and thritti;
27116	44	7	7	and Y schal iuge the folk, to which thei schulen serue, seith the Lord. And after these thingis thei schulen go out, and thei schulen serue to me in this place.
27117	44	7	8	And he yaf to hym the testament of circumcisioun; and so he gendride Ysaac, and circumcidide hym in the eiyt dai. And Isaac gendride Jacob, and Jacob gendride the twelue patriarkis.
27118	44	7	9	And the patriarkis hadden enuye to Joseph, and selden hym in to Egipt.
27119	44	7	10	And God was with hym, and delyuerede hym of alle hise tribulaciouns, and yaf to hym grace and wisdom in the siyt of Farao, king of Egipt. And he ordeynede hym souereyn on Egipt, and on al his hous.
27120	44	7	11	And hungur cam in to al Egipt, and Canaan, and greet tribulacioun; and oure fadris founden not mete.
27121	44	7	12	But whanne Jacob hadde herd, that whete was in Egipt, he sente oure fadris first.
27122	44	7	13	And in the secounde tyme Joseph was knowun of hise britheren, and his kyn was maad knowun to Farao.
27123	44	7	14	And Joseph sente, and clepide Jacob, his fadir, and al his kynrede, seuenti and fyue men.
27124	44	7	15	And Jacob cam doun in to Egipt, and was deed, he and oure fadris;
27125	44	7	16	and thei weren translatid in to Sichen, and weren leid in the sepulcre, that Abraham bouyte bi prijs of siluer of the sones of Emor, the sone of Sichen.
27126	44	7	17	And whanne the tyme of biheeste cam niy, which God hadde knoulechid to Abraham, the puple waxede, and multipliede in Egipt,
27127	44	7	18	til another kyng roos in Egipt, which knewe not Joseph.
27128	44	7	19	This bigilide oure kyn, and turmentide oure fadris, that thei schulden putte awey her yonge children, for thei schulden not lyue.
27129	44	7	20	In the same tyme Moyses was borun, and he was louyd of God; and he was norischid thre monethis in the hous of his fadir.
27130	44	7	21	And whanne he was put out in the flood, the douyter of Farao took hym vp, and nurischide hym in to hir sone.
27131	44	7	22	And Moises was lerned in al the wisdom of Egipcians, and he was myyti in his wordis and werkis.
27132	44	7	23	But whanne the tyme of fourti yeer was fillid to hym, it roos vp `in to his herte, that he schulde visite hise britheren, the sones of Israel.
27133	44	7	24	And whanne he say a man suffringe wronge, he vengide hym, and dide veniaunce for hym that suffride the wronge, and he killide the Egipcian.
27134	44	7	25	For he gesside that his britheren schulden vndurstonde, that God schulde yyue to hem helthe bi the hoond of hym; but thei vndurstoden not.
27135	44	7	26	For in the dai suynge he apperide to hem chidinge, and he acordide hem in pees, and seide, Men, ye ben britheren; whi noyen ye ech othere?
27136	44	7	27	But he that dide the wronge to his neiybore, puttide hym awey, and seide, Who ordeynede thee prince and domesman on vs?
27137	44	7	28	Whethir thou wolt sle me, as yistirdai thou killidist the Egipcian?
27138	44	7	29	And in this word Moises flei, and was maad a comeling in the loond of Madian, where he bigat twei sones.
27139	44	7	30	And whanne he hadde fillid fourti yeer, an aungel apperide to hym in fier of flawme of a buysch, in desert of the mount of Syna.
27140	44	7	31	And Moises siy, and wondride on the siyt. And whanne he neiyede to biholde, the vois of the Lord was maad to hym,
27141	44	7	32	and seide, Y am God of youre fadris, God of Abraham, God of Ysaac, God of Jacob. Moises was maad tremblynge, and durste not biholde.
27142	44	7	33	But God seide to hym, Do of the schoon of thi feet, for the place in which thou stondist is hooli erthe.
27143	44	7	34	Y seynge say the turmentyng of my puple that is in Egipt, and Y herde the mornyng of hem, and Y cam doun to delyuere hem. And now come thou, and Y schal sende thee in to Egipt.
27144	44	7	35	This Moises whom thei denyeden, seiynge, Who ordeynede thee prince and domesman on vs? God sente this prince and ayenbiere, with the hoond of the aungel, that apperide to hym in the busch.
27145	44	7	36	This Moises ledde hem out, and dide wondris and signes in the loond of Egipt, and in the reed see, and in desert fourti yeeris.
27146	44	7	37	This is Moises, that seide to the sones of Israel, God schal reise to you a profete of youre bretheren, as me ye schulen here him.
27147	44	7	38	This it is, that was in the chirche in wildirnesse, with the aungel that spak to hym in the mount of Syna, and with oure fadris; which took words of lijf to yyue to vs.
27148	44	7	39	To whom oure fadris wolden not obeie, but puttiden hym awei, and weren turned awei in hertis in to Egipt,
27149	44	7	40	seiynge to Aaron, Make thou to vs goddis, that schulen go bifore vs; for to this Moyses that ledde vs out of the lond of Egipt, we witen not what is don to hym.
27150	44	7	41	And thei maden a calf in tho daies, and offriden a sacrifice to the mawmet; and thei weren glad in the werkis of her hondis.
27151	44	7	42	And God turnede, and bitook hem to serue to the knyythod of heuene, as it is writun in the book of profetis, Whether ye, hous of Israel, offriden to me slayn sacrificis, ether sacrificis, fourti yeris in desert?
27152	44	7	43	And ye han take the tabernacle of Moloc, and the sterre of youre god Renfam, figuris that ye han maad to worschipe hem; and Y schal translate you in to Babiloyn.
27153	44	7	44	The tabernacle of witnessing was with oure fadris in desert, as God disposide to hem, and spak to Moyses, that he schulde make it aftir the fourme that he say.
27154	44	7	45	Which also oure fadris token with Jhesu, and brouyten in to the possessioun of hethene men, whiche God puttide awey fro the face of oure fadris, til in to the daies of Dauid,
27155	44	7	46	that fonde grace anentis God, and axide that he schulde fynde a tabernacle to God of Jacob.
27156	44	7	47	But Salomon bildide the hous `to hym.
27157	44	7	48	But the hiy God dwellith not in thingis maad bi hoond,
27158	44	7	49	as he seith bi the profete, Heuene is a seete to me, and the erthe is the stool of my feet; what hous schulen ye bilde to me, seith the Lord, ether what place is of my restyng?
27159	44	7	50	Whether myn hoond made not alle these thingis?
27160	44	7	51	With hard nol, and vncircumcidid hertis and eris ye withstoden eueremore the Hooli Goost; and as youre fadris, so ye.
27161	44	7	52	Whom of the profetis han not youre fadris pursued, and han slayn hem that bifor telden of the comyng of the riytful man, whos traitouris and mansleeris ye weren now?
27162	44	7	53	Whiche token the lawe in ordynaunce of aungels, and han not kept it.
27163	44	7	54	And thei herden these thingis, and weren dyuersli turmentid in her hertis, and grenneden with teeth on hym.
27164	44	7	55	But whanne Steuene was ful of the Hooli Goost, he bihelde in to heuene, and say the glorie of God, and Jhesu stondinge on the riythalf of the vertu of God. And he seide, Lo! Y se heuenes openyd, and mannus sone stondynge on the riythalf of the vertu of God.
27165	44	7	56	And thei crieden with a greet vois, and stoppiden her eris, and maden with o wille an assauyt in to hym.
27166	44	7	57	And thei brouyten hym out of the citee, and stonyden. And the witnessis diden of her clothis, bisidis the feet of a yong man, that was clepid Saule.
27167	44	7	58	And thei stonyden Steuene, that clepide God to help, seiynge, Lord Jhesu, resseyue my spirit.
27168	44	7	59	And he knelide, and criede with a greet vois, and seide, Lord, sette not to hem this synne. And whanne he hadde seid this thing, he diede.
27169	44	8	1	But Saul was consentynge to his deth.
27170	44	8	1	And greet persecucioun was maad that dai in the chirche, that was in Jerusalem. And alle men weren scatered bi the cuntrees of Judee and Samarie, outakun the apostlis.
27171	44	8	2	But good men birieden Steuene, and maden greet mornyng on hym.
27172	44	8	3	But Saul greetli distruyede the chirche, and entryde bi housis, and drowe men and wymmen, and bitook hem in to prisoun.
27173	44	8	4	And thei that weren scaterid, passiden forth, prechynge the word of God.
27174	44	8	5	And Filip cam doun in to a citee of Samarie, and prechide to hem Crist.
27175	44	8	6	And the puple yaf tent to thes thingis that weren seid of Filip, with o wille herynge and seynge the signes that he dide.
27176	44	8	7	For manye of hem that hadden vnclene spirits, crieden with a greet vois, and wenten out.
27177	44	8	8	And manye sijk in the palsi, and crokid, weren heelid.
27178	44	8	9	Therfor greet ioye was maad in that citee. But there was a man in that citee, whos name was Symount, a witche, that hadde disseyued the folc of Samarie, seiynge, that him silf was sum greet man.
27179	44	8	10	Whom alle herkeneden, fro the leest to the moost, and seiden, This is the vertu of God, which is clepid greet.
27180	44	8	11	And thei leueden hym, for long tyme he hadde maddid hem with his witche craftis.
27181	44	8	12	But whanne thei hadden bileued to Filip, `that prechide of the kingdom of God, men and wymmen weren baptisid in the name of Jhesu Crist.
27182	44	8	13	And thanne also Symount him silf bileued; and whanne he was baptisid, he drouy to Filip; and he sai also that signes and grete vertues weren don, he was astonyed, and wondride.
27183	44	8	14	But whanne the apostlis that weren at Jerusalem, hadden herd that Samarie hadde resseyued the word of God, thei senten to hem Petre and Joon.
27184	44	8	15	And whanne thei camen, thei preieden for hem, that thei schulden resseyue the Hooli Goost;
27185	44	8	16	for he cam not yit in to ony of hem, but thei weren baptisid oonli in the name of the Lord Jhesu.
27186	44	8	17	Thanne thei leiden hoondis on hem, and thei resseyueden the Hooli Goost.
27187	44	8	18	And whanne Symount hadde seyn, that the Hooly Goost was youun bi leiyng on of the hoondis of the apostlis, and he proferide to hem money, and seide,
27188	44	8	19	Yyue ye also to me this power, that whom euere Y schal leye on myn hoondis, that he resseyue the Hooli Goost.
27189	44	8	20	But Petir seide to hym, Thi money be with thee into perdicioun, for thou gessidist the yifte of God schulde be had for monei.
27190	44	8	21	Ther is no part, ne sort to thee, in this word, for thin herte is not riytful bifor God.
27191	44	8	22	Therfor do thou penaunce for this wickidnesse of thee, and preie God, if perauenture this thouyt of thin herte be foryouun to thee.
27192	44	8	23	For Y se that thou art in the gall of bitternesse and in the boond of wickidnesse.
27193	44	8	24	And Symount answeride, and seide, Preie ye for me to the Lord, that no thing of these thingis that ye han seid, com on me.
27194	44	8	25	And thei witnessiden, and spaken the word of the Lord, and yeden ayen to Jerusalem, and prechiden to many cuntrees of Samaritans.
27195	44	8	26	And an aungel of the Lord spak to Filip, and seide, Ryse thou, and go ayens the south, to the weie that goith doun fro Jerusalem in to Gasa; this is desert.
27196	44	8	27	And he roos, and wente forth. And lo! a man of Ethiopie, a myyti man seruaunt, a yelding of Candace, the queen of Ethiopiens, which was on alle her richessis, cam to worschipe in Jerusalem.
27197	44	8	28	And he turnede ayen, sittinge on his chare, and redinge Isaie, the profete.
27198	44	8	29	And the spirit seide to Filip, Neiye thou, and ioyne thee to this chare.
27199	44	8	30	And Filip `ran to, and herde hym redynge Ysaie, the prophete. And he seide, Gessist thou, whether thou vndirstondist, what thingis thou redist?
27200	44	8	31	And he seide, How may Y, if no man schewe to me? And he preiede Filip, that he schulde come vp, and sitte with hym.
27201	44	8	32	And the place of the scripture that he redde, was this, As a scheep he was led to sleyng, and as a lomb bifor a man that scherith him is doumb with out vois, so he openyde not his mouth.
27202	44	8	33	In mekenesse his dom was takun vp; who schal telle out the generacioun of hym? For his lijf schal be takun awei fro the erthe.
27203	44	8	34	And the gelding answeride to Filip, and seide, Y biseche thee, of `what profete seith he this thing? of him silf, ethir of ony othere?
27204	44	8	35	And Filip openyde his mouth, and bigan at this scripture, and prechide to him Jhesu.
27205	44	8	36	And the while thei wenten bi the weie, thei camen to a water. And the gelding seide, Lo! watir; who forbedith me to be baptisid?
27206	44	8	37	And Filip seide, If thou bileuest of al the herte, it is leueful. And he answeride, and seide, Y bileue that Jhesu Crist is the sone of God.
27207	44	8	38	And he comaundide the chare to stonde stille. And thei wenten doun bothe into the watir, Filip and the gelding, and Filip baptiside hym.
27208	44	8	39	And whanne thei weren come vp of the watir, the spirit of the Lord rauyschide Filip, and the gelding say hym no more.
27209	44	8	40	And Filip was foundun in Azotus; and he passide forth, and prechide to alle citees, til he cam to Cesarie.
27210	44	9	1	But Saul, yit a blower of manassis and of betingis ayens the disciplis of the Lord,
27211	44	9	2	cam to the prince of preestis, and axide of hym lettris in to Damask, to the synagogis; that if he fond ony men and wymmen of this lijf, he schulde lede hem boundun to Jerusalem.
27212	44	9	3	And whanne he made his iourney, it bifelde, that he cam nyy to Damask. And sudenli a liyt from heuene schoon aboute hym;
27213	44	9	4	and he fallide to the erthe, and herde a vois seiynge to hym, Saul, Saul, what pursuest thou me?
27214	44	9	5	And he seide, Who art thou, Lord? And he seide, Y am Jhesu of Nazareth, whom thou pursuest. It is hard to thee, to kike ayens the pricke.
27215	44	9	6	And he tremblide, and wondride, and seide, Lord, what wolt thou that Y do?
27216	44	9	7	And the Lord seide to hym, Rise vp, and entre in to the citee, and it schal be seide to thee, what it bihoueth thee to do. And tho men that wenten with hym, stoden astonyed; for thei herden a vois, but thei sien no man.
27217	44	9	8	And Saul roos fro the earth; and whanne hise iyen weren opened, he say no thing. And thei drowen hym bi the hondis, and ledden hym in to Damask.
27218	44	9	9	And he was thre daies not seynge; `and he eete not, nether drank.
27219	44	9	10	And a disciple, Ananye bi name, was at Damask. And the Lord seide to hym in `a visioun, Ananye. And he seide, Lo!
27220	44	9	11	Y, Lord. And the Lord seide to hym, Rise thou, and go in to a streete that is clepid Rectus; and seke, in the hous of Judas, Saul bi name of Tharse. For lo! he preieth; and he say a man,
27221	44	9	12	Ananye bi name, entringe and leiynge on hym hoondis, that he resseyue siyt.
27222	44	9	13	And Ananye answerde, Lord, Y haue herd of many of this man, how greete yuelis he dide to thi seyntis in Jerusalem;
27223	44	9	14	and this hath power of the princis of preestis, to bynde alle men that clepen thi name to helpe.
27224	44	9	15	And the Lord seide to hym, Go thou, for this is to me a vessel of chesing, that he bere my name bifore hethene men, and kingis, and tofore the sones of Israel.
27225	44	9	16	For Y schal schewe to hym, how grete thingis it bihoueth hym to suffre for my name.
27226	44	9	17	And Ananye wente, and entride in to the hous; and leide on hym his hondis, and seide, Saul brothir, the Lord Jhesu sente me, that apperide to thee in the weie, in which thou camest, that thou se, and be fulfillid with the Hooli Goost.
27227	44	9	18	And anoon as the scalis felden fro hise iyen, he resseyuede siyt. And he roos, and was baptisid.
27228	44	9	19	And whanne he hadde takun mete, he was coumfortid. And he was bi sum daies with the disciplis, that weren at Damask.
27229	44	9	20	And anoon he entride in to the synagogis, and prechide the Lord Jhesu, for this is the sone of God.
27230	44	9	21	And alle men that herden hym, wondriden, and seiden, Whether this is not he that impugnede in Jerusalem hem that clepiden to help this name? and hidir he cam for this thing, that he schulde leede hem boundun to the princis of preestis?
27231	44	9	22	But Saul myche more wexede strong, and confoundide the Jewis that dwelliden at Damask, and affermyde that this is Crist.
27232	44	9	23	And whanne manye daies weren fillid, Jewis maden a counsel, that thei schulden sle hym.
27233	44	9	24	And the aspies of hem weren maad knowun to Saul. And thei kepten the yatis dai and niyt, that thei schulden sle him.
27234	44	9	25	But hise disciplis token hym bi nyyt, and delyuereden hym, and leeten him doun in a leep bi the wal.
27235	44	9	26	And whanne he cam in to Jerusalem, he assaiede to ioyne hym to the disciplis; and alle dredden hym, and leueden not that he was a disciple.
27236	44	9	27	But Barnabas took, and ledde hym to the apostlis, and telde to hem, how in the weie he hadde seyn the Lord, and that he spak to hym, and hou in Damask he dide tristili in the name of Jhesu.
27237	44	9	28	And he was with hem, and entride, and yede out in Jerusalem, and dide tristili in the name of Jhesu.
27238	44	9	29	And he spak with hethene men, and disputide with Grekis. And thei souyten to sle hym.
27239	44	9	30	Which thing whanne the britheren hadden knowe, thei ledden hym bi nyyt to Cesarie, and leten hym go to Tarsis.
27240	44	9	31	And the chirche bi al Judee, and Galilee, and Samarie, hadde pees, and was edefied, and walkide in the drede of the Lord, and was fillid with coumfort of the Hooli Goost.
27241	44	9	32	And it bifelde, that Petre, the while he passide aboute alle, cam to the hooli men that dwelliden at Lidde.
27242	44	9	33	And he foond a man, Eneas bi name, that fro eiyte yeer he hadde leie `in bed; and he was sijk in palsy.
27243	44	9	34	And Petre seide to hym, Eneas, the Lord Jhesu Crist heele thee; rise thou, and araye thee. And anoon he roos.
27244	44	9	35	And alle men that dwelten at Lidde, and at Sarone, saien hym, whiche weren conuertid to the Lord.
27245	44	9	36	And in Joppe was a disciplesse, whos name was Tabita, that is to seie, Dorcas. This was ful of good werkis and almesdedis, that sche dide.
27246	44	9	37	And it bifelde in tho daies, that sche was sijk, and diede. And whanne thei hadden waischun hir, thei leiden hir in a soler.
27247	44	9	38	And for Lidda was nyy Joppe, the disciplis herden that Petre was thereynne, and senten twei men to hym, and preieden, That thou tarie not to come to vs.
27248	44	9	39	And Petre roos vp, and cam with hem. And whanne he was comun, thei ledden hym in to the soler. And alle widewis stoden aboute hym, wepynge, and schewynge cootis and clothis, which Dorcas made to hem.
27249	44	9	40	And whanne alle men weren put with out forth, Petre knelide, and preiede. And he turnede to the bodi, and seide, Tabita, rise thou. And sche openyde hir iyen, and whanne sche siy Petre, sche sat vp ayen.
27250	44	9	41	And he took hir bi the hond, and reiside hir. And whanne he hadde clepid the hooli men and widewis, he assignede hir alyue.
27251	44	9	42	And it was maad knowun bi al Joppe; and many bileueden in the Lord.
27252	44	9	43	And it was maad, that many daies he dwellide in Joppe, at oon Symount, a curiour.
27253	44	10	1	A man was in Cesarie, Cornelie bi name, a centurien of the cumpanye of knyytis, that is seid of Italie;
27254	44	10	2	a religious man, and dredinge the Lord, with al his meyne; doynge many almessis to the puple, and preynge the Lord euere more.
27255	44	10	3	This say in a visioun opinli, as in the nynthe oure of the dai, an aungel of God entringe in to hym, and seiynge to hym, Cornelie.
27256	44	10	4	And he bihelde hym, and was a dred, and seide, Who art thou, Lord? And he seide to hym, Thi preieris and thin almesdedis han stied vp in to mynde, in the siyt of the Lord.
27257	44	10	5	And now sende thou men in to Joppe, and clepe oon Symount, that is named Petre.
27258	44	10	6	This is herborid at a man Symount, curiour, whos hous is bisidis the see. This schal seie to thee, what it bihoueth thee to do.
27259	44	10	7	And whanne the aungel that spak to hym, was gon awei, he clepide twei men of his hous, and a knyyt that dredde the Lord, whiche weren at his bidding.
27260	44	10	8	And whanne he hadde told hem alle these thingis, he sente hem in to Joppe.
27261	44	10	9	And on the dai suynge, while thei maden iournei, and neiyeden to the citee, Petre wente vp in to the hiest place of the hous to preie, aboute the sixte our.
27262	44	10	10	And whanne he was hungrid, he wolde haue ete. But while thei maden redi, a rauysching of spirit felde on hym;
27263	44	10	11	and he say heuene openyd, and a vessel comynge doun, as a greet scheet with foure corneris, to be lette doun fro heuene in to erthe,
27264	44	10	12	in which weren alle foure footid beestis, and crepinge of the erthe, and volatilis of heuene.
27265	44	10	13	And a vois was maad to hym, Rise thou, Petre, and sle, and ete.
27266	44	10	14	And Petre seide, Lord, forbede, for Y neuer ete ony comun thing and vnclene.
27267	44	10	15	And eft the secounde tyme the vois was maad to him, That thing that God hath clensid, seye thou not vnclene.
27268	44	10	16	And this thing was don bi thries; and anoon the vessel was resseyued ayen.
27269	44	10	17	And while that Petre doutide with ynne hym silf, what the visioun was that he say, lo! the men, that weren sent fro Corneli, souyten the hous of Symount, and stoden at the yate.
27270	44	10	18	And whanne thei hadden clepid, thei axiden if Symount, that is named Petre, hadde there herbore.
27271	44	10	19	And while Petre thouyte on the visioun, the spirit seide to hym, Lo! thre men seken thee.
27272	44	10	20	Therfor ryse thou, and go doun, and go with hem, and doute thou no thing, for Y sente hem.
27273	44	10	21	And Petre cam doun to the men, and seide, Lo! Y am, whom ye seken; what is the cause, for which ye ben come?
27274	44	10	22	And thei seiden, Cornelie, the centurien, a iust man, and dredinge God, and hath good witnessyng of alle the folc of Jewis, took aunswere of an hooli aungel, to clepe thee in to his hous, and to here wordis of thee.
27275	44	10	23	Therfor he ledde hem inne, and resseyuede in herbore; and that nyyt thei dwelliden with hym. And in the dai suynge he roos, and wente forth with hem; and sum of the britheren folewiden hym fro Joppe, that thei be witnessis to Petre.
27276	44	10	24	And the other dai he entride in to Cesarie. And Cornelie abood hem, with hise cousyns, and necessarie freendis, that weren clepid togidere.
27277	44	10	25	And it was don, whanne Petre was come ynne, Corneli cam metynge hym, and felle doun at hise feet, and worschipide him.
27278	44	10	26	But Petre reiside hym, and seide, Aryse thou, also Y my silf am a man, as thou.
27279	44	10	27	And he spak with hym, and wente in, and foonde many that weren come togidere.
27280	44	10	28	And he seide to hem, Ye witen, how abhomynable it is to a Jewe, to be ioyned ether to come to an alien; but God schewide to me, that no man seye a man comyn, ethir vnclene.
27281	44	10	29	For which thing Y cam, whanne Y was clepid, with out douting. Therfor Y axe you, for what cause han ye clepid me?
27282	44	10	30	And Cornelie seide, To dai foure daies in to this our, Y was preiynge and fastynge in the nynthe our in myn hous. And lo! a man stood bifore me in a whijt cloth, and seide,
27283	44	10	31	Cornelie, thi preier is herd, and thin almesdedis ben in mynde in the siyt of God.
27284	44	10	32	Therfor sende thou in to Joppe, and clepe Symount, that is named Petre; this is herborid in the hous of Symount coriour, bisidis the see. This, whanne he schal come, schal speke to thee.
27285	44	10	33	Therfor anoon Y sente to thee, and thou didist wel in comynge to vs. `Now therfor we alle ben present in thi siyt, to here the wordis, what euer ben comaundid to thee of the Lord.
27286	44	10	34	And Petre openyde his mouth, and seide, In trewthe Y haue foundun, that God is no acceptor of persoones;
27287	44	10	35	but in eche folk he that dredith God, and worchith riytwisnesse, is accept to hym.
27288	44	10	36	God sente a word to the children of Israel, schewinge pees bi Jhesu Crist; this is Lord of alle thingis.
27289	44	10	37	Ye witen the word that is maad thorou al Judee, and bigan at Galile, aftir the baptym that Joon prechide, Jhesu of Nazareth;
27290	44	10	38	hou God anoyntide hym with the Hooli Goost, and vertu; which passide forth in doynge wel, and heelynge alle men oppressid of the deuel, for God was with hym.
27291	44	10	39	And we ben witnessis of alle thingis, whiche he dide in the cuntrei of Jewis, and of Jerusalem; whom thei slowen, hangynge in a tre.
27292	44	10	40	And God reiside this in the thridde dai, and yaf hym to be maad knowun,
27293	44	10	41	not to al puple, but to witnessis bifor ordeyned of God; to vs that eeten and drunken with hym, after that he roos ayen fro deth.
27294	44	10	42	And he comaundide to vs to preche to the puple, and to witnesse, that he it is, that is ordeyned of God domesman of the quyk and of deede.
27295	44	10	43	To this alle prophetis beren witnessing, that alle men that bileuen in hym, schulen resseyue remyssioun of synnes bi his name.
27296	44	10	44	And yit while that Petre spak these wordis, the Hooli Goost felde on alle that herden the word.
27297	44	10	45	And the feithful men of circumcisioun, that camen with Petre, wondriden, that also in to naciouns the grace of the Hooli Goost is sched out.
27298	44	10	46	For thei herden hem spekynge in langagis, and magnyfiynge God.
27299	44	10	47	Thanne Petre answeride, Whether ony man may forbede watir, that these ben not baptisid, that han also resseyued the Hooli Goost as we?
27300	44	10	48	And he comaundide hem to be baptisid in the name of the Lord Jhesu Crist. Thanne thei preieden hym, that he schulde dwelle with hem sum daies.
27301	44	11	1	And the apostlis, and the britheren that weren in Judee, herden that also hethene men resseyueden the word of God, and thei glorifieden God.
27302	44	11	2	But whanne Petre cam to Jerusalem, thei that weren of circumcisioun, disputiden ayens hym,
27303	44	11	3	and seiden, Whi entridist thou to men that han prepucie, and hast eete with hem?
27304	44	11	4	And Petre bigan, and expownede to hem bi ordre,
27305	44	11	5	and seide, Y was in the citee of Joppe, and preiede, and Y sai in rauysching of my mynde a visioun, that a vessel cam doun, as a greet scheete with foure coordis, and was sent doun fro heuene; and it cam to me.
27306	44	11	6	In to which Y lokinge biheld, and sai foure footid beestis of the erthe, and beestis, and crepynge beestis, and volatils of heuene.
27307	44	11	7	And Y herde also a vois that seide to me, Petre, rise thou, and sle, and eete.
27308	44	11	8	But Y seide, Nay, Lord; for comyn thing ether vnclene entride neuer in to my mouth.
27309	44	11	9	And the vois answeride the secounde tyme fro heuene, That thing that God hath clensid, seie thou not vnclene.
27310	44	11	10	And this was don bi thries, and alle thingis weren resseyued ayen in to heuene.
27311	44	11	11	And lo! thre men anoon stooden in the hous, in which Y was; and thei weren sent fro Cesarie to me.
27312	44	11	12	And the spirit seide to me, that Y schulde go with hem, and doute no thing. Yhe, and these sixe britheren camen with me, and we entriden in to the hous of the man.
27313	44	11	13	And he telde to vs, how he say an aungel in his hous, stondinge and seiynge to hym, Sende thou in to Joppe, and clepe Symount, that is named Petre, which schal speke to thee wordis,
27314	44	11	14	in whiche thou schalt be saaf, and al thin hous.
27315	44	11	15	And whanne Y hadde bigunnun to speke, the Hooli Goost felle on hem, as in to vs in the bigynnyng.
27316	44	11	16	And Y bithouyte on the word of the Lord, as he seide, For Joon baptiside in watir, but ye schulen be baptisid in the Hooli Goost.
27317	44	11	17	Therfor if God yaf to hem the same grace, as to vs that bileueden in the Lord Jhesu Crist, who was Y, that myyte forbeede the Lord, that he yyue not the Hooli Goost to hem that bileueden in the name of Jhesu Crist?
27318	44	11	18	Whanne these thingis weren herd, thei helden pees, and glorifieden God, and seiden, Therfor also to hethene men God hath youun penaunce to lijf.
27319	44	11	19	And thei that weren scaterid of the tribulacioun that was maad vndir Steuene, walkiden forth to Fenyce, and to Cipre, and to Antioche, and spaken the word to no man, but to Jewis aloone.
27320	44	11	20	But sum of hem weren men of Cipre, and of Cirenen; whiche whanne thei hadden entride in to Antioche, thei spaken to the Grekis, and prechiden the Lord Jhesu.
27321	44	11	21	And the hond of the Lord was with hem, and myche noumbre of men bileuynge was conuertid to the Lord.
27322	44	11	22	And the word cam to the eris of the chirche, that was at Jerusalem, on these thingis; and thei senten Barnabas to Antioche.
27323	44	11	23	And whanne he was come, and siy the grace of the Lord, he ioyede, and monestide alle men to dwelle in the Lord in purpos of herte;
27324	44	11	24	for he was a good man, and ful of the Hooli Goost, and of feith. And myche puple was encresid to the Lord.
27325	44	11	25	And he wente forth to Tharsis, to seke Saul; and whanne he hadde foundun hym, he ledde to Antioche.
27326	44	11	26	And al a yeer thei lyueden ther in the chirche, and tauyten myche puple, so that the disciplis weren namyd first at Antioche cristen men.
27327	44	11	27	And in these daies profetis camen ouer fro Jerusalem to Antioche.
27328	44	11	28	And oon of hem roos vp, Agabus bi name, and signefiede bi the spirit a greet hungur to comynge in al the world, which hungur was maad vndur Claudius.
27329	44	11	29	And alle the disciplis purposiden, after that ech hadde, for to sende in to mynysterie to britheren that dwelliden in Judee.
27330	44	11	30	Which thing also thei diden, and sente it to the eldre men, bi the hoondis of Barnabas and Saul.
27331	44	12	1	And in the same tyme Eroude the king sente power, to turmente sum men of the chirche.
27332	44	12	2	And he slowe bi swerd James, the brothir of Joon.
27333	44	12	3	And he siy that it pleside to Jewis, and keste to take also Petre; and the daies of therf looues weren.
27334	44	12	4	And whanne he hadde cauyte Petre, he sente hym in to prisoun; and bitook to foure quaternyouns of knyytis, to kepe hym, and wolde aftir pask bringe hym forth to the puple.
27335	44	12	5	And Petre was kept in prisoun; but preier was maad of the chirche with out ceessing to God for hym.
27336	44	12	6	But whanne Eroude schulde bringe hym forth, in that nyyt Petre was slepinge bitwixe twei knyytis, and was boundun with twei cheynes; and the keperis bifor the dore kepten the prisoun.
27337	44	12	7	And lo! an aungel of the Lord stoode nyy, and liyt schoon in the prisoun hous. And whanne he hadde smyte the side of Petre, he reiside hym, and seide, Rise thou swiftli. And anoon the cheynes felden doun fro hise hoondis.
27338	44	12	8	And the aungel seide to hym, Girde thee, and do on thin hoosis. And he dide so. And he seide to hym, Do aboute thee thi clothis, and sue me.
27339	44	12	9	And he yede out, and suede hym; and he wiste not that it was soth, that was don bi the aungel; for he gesside hym silf to haue sey a visioun.
27340	44	12	10	And thei passiden the first and the secounde warde, and camen to the iren yate that ledith to the citee, which anoon was opened to hem. And thei yeden out, and camen in to o street, and anoon the aungel passide awei fro hym.
27341	44	12	11	And Petre turnede ayen to hym silf, and seide, Now Y woot verili, that the Lord sente his aungel, `and delyueride me fro the hoond of Eroude, and fro al the abiding of the puple of Jewis.
27342	44	12	12	And he bihelde, and cam to the hous of Marie, modir of Joon, that is named Marcus, where many weren gaderid togidre, and preiynge.
27343	44	12	13	And whanne he knockid at the dore of the yate, a damysel, Rode bi name, cam forth to se.
27344	44	12	14	And whanne sche knewe the vois of Petre, for ioye sche openyde not the yate, but ran in, and telde, that Petre stood at the yate.
27345	44	12	15	And thei seiden `to hir, Thou maddist. But sche affermyde, that it was so. And thei seiden, It is his aungel.
27346	44	12	16	But Petre abood stille, and knockide. And whanne thei hadden opened the dore, thei sayen hym, and wondriden.
27347	44	12	17	And he bekenyde to hem with his hoond to be stille, and telde hou the Lord hadde led hym out of the prisoun. And he seide, Telle ye to James and to the britheren these thingis. And he yede out, and wente in to an othere place.
27348	44	12	18	And whanne the dai was come, ther was not lytil troubling among the knyytis, what was don of Petre.
27349	44	12	19	And whanne Eroude hadde souyt hym, and foonde not, aftir that he hadde made enqueryng of the keperis, he comaundide hem to be brouyt to hym. And he cam doun fro Judee in to Cesarie, and dwellide there.
27350	44	12	20	And he was wroth to men of Tyre and of Sidon. And thei of oon acord camen to hym, whanne thei hadden counseilid with Bastus, that was the kingis chaumbirleyn, thei axiden pees, for as myche that her cuntrees weren vitailid of hym.
27351	44	12	21	And in a dai that was ordeyned, Eroude was clothid with kyngis clothing, and sat for domesman, and spak to hem.
27352	44	12	22	And the puple criede, The voicis of God, and not of man.
27353	44	12	23	And anoon an aungel of the Lord smoot hym, for he hadde not youun onour to God; and he was wastid of wormes, and diede.
27354	44	12	24	And the word of the Lord waxide, and was multiplied.
27355	44	12	25	And Barnabas and Saul turneden ayen fro Jerusalem, whanne the mynystrie was fillid, and token Joon, that was named Marcus.
27356	44	13	1	And profetis and doctouris weren in the chirche that was at Antioche, in which Barnabas, and Symount, that was clepid Blac, and Lucius Cironense, and Manaen, that was the soukynge fere of Eroude tetrarke, and Saul weren.
27357	44	13	2	And whanne thei mynystriden to the Lord, and fastiden, the Hooli Goost seide to hem, Departe ye to me Saul and Barnabas, in to the werk to which Y haue takun hem.
27358	44	13	3	Thanne thei fastiden, and preieden, and leiden hondis on hem, and leten hem go.
27359	44	13	4	But thei weren sent of the Hooli Goost, and wenten forth to Seleucia, and fro thennus thei wenten bi boot to Cipre.
27360	44	13	5	And whanne thei camen to Salamyne, thei prechiden the word of God in the synagogis of Jewis; and thei hadden also Joon in mynystrie.
27361	44	13	6	And whanne thei hadden walkid bi al the ile to Pafum, thei founden a man, a witche, a false profete, a Jewe, to whom the name was Bariesu,
27362	44	13	7	that was with the proconsul Sergius Paule, a prudent man. This clepide Barnabas and Poul, and desiride to here the word of God.
27363	44	13	8	But Elymas witche withstoode hem; for his name is expowned so; and he souyte to turne awei the proconsul fro bileue.
27364	44	13	9	But Saul, which is seid also Paul, was fillid with the Hooli Goost, and bihelde in to hym, and seide, A!
27365	44	13	10	thou ful of al gile, and al falsnesse, thou sone of the deuel, thou enemye of al riytwisnesse, thou leeuest not to turne vpsodoun the riytful weies of the Lord.
27366	44	13	11	And now lo! the hoond of the Lord is on thee, and thou schalt be blynde, and not seynge the sunne in to a tyme. And anoon myste and derknesse felden doun on hym; and he yede aboute, and souyte hym that schulde yyue hoond to hym.
27367	44	13	12	Thanne the proconsul, whanne he hadde seyn the dede, bileuede, wondringe on the techyng of the Lord.
27368	44	13	13	And whanne fro Pafum Poul hadde go bi a boot, and thei that weren with hym, thei camen to Pergen of Pamfilie; but Joon departide fro hem, and turnede ayen to Jerusalem.
27369	44	13	14	And thei yeden to Pergen, and camen to Antioche of Persidie; and thei entriden in to the synagoge in the dai of sabatis, and saten.
27370	44	13	15	And after the redyng of the lawe and of the prophetis, the princis of the synagoge senten to hem, and seiden, Britheren, if ony word of exortacioun to the puple is in you, seie ye.
27371	44	13	16	And Poul roos, and with hoond baad silence, and seide, Men of Israel, and ye that dreden God, here ye.
27372	44	13	17	God of the puple of Israel chees oure fadris, and enhaunside the puple, whanne thei weren comelingis in the loond of Egipt, and in an hiy arme he ledde hem out of it;
27373	44	13	18	and bi the tyme of fourti yeeris he suffride her maneres in desert.
27374	44	13	19	And he destriede seuene folkis in the loond of Canaan, and bi sort departide to hem her lond,
27375	44	13	20	as aftir foure hundrid and fifti yeeris. And aftir these thingis he yaf domesmen, to Samuel, the profete.
27376	44	13	21	And fro that tyme thei axiden a kyng, and God yaf to hem Saul, the sone of Cis, a man of the lynage of Beniamyn, bi fourti yeeris.
27377	44	13	22	And whanne he was don awei, he reiside to hem Dauid king, to whom he bar witnessing, and seide, Y haue foundun Dauid, the sone of Jesse, a man aftir myn herte, which schal do alle my willis.
27378	44	13	23	Of whos seed bi the biheest God hath led out to Israel a sauyoure Jhesu,
27379	44	13	24	whanne Joon prechide bifor the face of his comyng the baptym of penaunce to al the puple of Israel.
27380	44	13	25	But whanne Joon fillide his cours, he seide, Y am not he, whom ye demen me to be; but lo! he cometh aftir me, and Y am not worthi to doon of the schoon of hise feet.
27381	44	13	26	Britheren, and sones of the kynde of Abraham, and whiche that in you dreden God, to you the word of helthe is sent.
27382	44	13	27	For thei that dwelliden at Jerusalem, and princis of it, that knewen not this Jhesu, and the voicis of prophetis, that by euery sabat ben red, demyden, and filliden;
27383	44	13	28	and thei founden in hym no cause of deth, and axiden of Pilat, that thei schulden sle hym.
27384	44	13	29	And whanne thei hadden endid alle thingis that weren writun of hym, thei token hym doun of the tre, and leiden hym in a graue.
27385	44	13	30	And God reiside hym fro deth in the thridde dai; which was seyn bi mony daies to
27386	44	13	31	hem that wenten vp togidere with hym fro Galilee in to Jerusalem, which ben til now his witnessis to the puple.
27387	44	13	32	And we schewen to you the biheest that was maad to oure fadris;
27388	44	13	33	for God hath fulfillid this to her sones, and ayenreisid Jhesu; as in the secounde salm it is writun, Thou art my sone, to dai Y bigat thee.
27389	44	13	34	And he ayenreiside hym fro deth, that he schulde not turne ayen in to corrupcioun, seide thus, For Y schal yyue to you the hooli trewe thingis of Dauid.
27390	44	13	35	And therfor and on an othere stide he seith, Thou schalt not yyue thin hooli to se corrupcioun.
27391	44	13	36	But Dauid in his generacioun, whanne he hadde mynstrid to the wille of God, diede, and was leid with hise fadris, and say corrupcioun;
27392	44	13	37	but he whom God reiside fro deth, say not corrupcioun.
27393	44	13	38	Therfor, britheren, be it knowun to you, that bi hym remyssioun of synnes is teld to you, fro alle synnes, of whiche ye myyten not be iustified in the lawe of Moises.
27394	44	13	39	In this ech man that bileueth, is iustified.
27395	44	13	40	Therfor se ye, that it come not to you, that is biforeseid in the profetis,
27396	44	13	41	Ye dispiseris, se ye, and wondre ye, and be ye scaterid abrood; for Y worche a werk in youre daies, a werk that ye schulen not bileue, if ony man schal telle it to you.
27397	44	13	42	And whanne thei yeden out, thei preieden, that in the sabat suynge thei schulden speke to hem these wordis.
27398	44	13	43	And whanne the synagoge was left, manye of Jewis and of comelingis worschypynge God supeden Poul and Barnabas; that spaken, and counseliden hem, that thei schulden dwelle in the grace of God.
27399	44	13	44	And in the sabat suynge almest al the citee cam togidir, to here the word of God.
27400	44	13	45	And Jewis sien the puple, and weren fillid with enuye, and ayenseiden these thingis that weren seyd of Poul, and blasfemyden.
27401	44	13	46	Thanne Poul and Barnabas stidfastli seiden, To you it bihofte first to speke the word of God; but for ye putten it awei, and han demyd you vnworthi to euerlastinge lijf, lo! we turnen to hethen men.
27402	44	13	47	For so the Lord comaundide vs, Y haue set thee in to liyt to hethen men, that thou be in to helthe to the vtmest of erthe.
27403	44	13	48	And hethen men herden, `and ioieden, and glorifieden the word of the Lord; and bileueden, as manye as weren bifore ordeyned to euerlastinge lijf.
27404	44	13	49	And the word of the Lord was sowun bi al the cuntre.
27405	44	13	50	But the Jewis stiriden religiouse wymmen, and onest, and the worthiest men of the citee, and stireden persecucioun ayens Poul and Barnabas, and dryuen hem out of her cuntreis.
27406	44	13	51	And thei schoken awei in to hem the duste of her feet, and camen to Yconye.
27407	44	13	52	And the disciplis weren fillid with ioye and the Hooli Goost.
27408	44	14	1	But it bifelde at Yconye, that thei entriden togidir in to the synagoge of Jewis, and spaken, so that ful greet multitude of Jewis and Grekis bileueden.
27409	44	14	2	But the Jewis that weren vnbileueful, reiseden persecucioun, and stiriden to wraththe the soulis of hethene men ayens the britheren; but the Lord yaf soone pees.
27410	44	14	3	Therfor thei dwelliden myche tyme, and diden tristili in the Lord, berynge witnessyng to the word of his grace, yyuynge signes and wondris to be maad bi the hondis of hem.
27411	44	14	4	But the multitude of the citee was departid, and sum weren with the Jewis, and sum with the apostlis.
27412	44	14	5	But whanne ther was maad `an asaute of the hethene men and the Jewis, with her princis, to turmenten and to stonen hem,
27413	44	14	6	thei vndurstoden, and fledden togidere to the citees of Licaonye, and Listris, and Derben, and into al the cuntre aboute. And thei prechiden there the gospel, and al the multitude was moued togider in the teching of hem. Poul and Barnabas dwelten at Listris.
27414	44	14	7	And a man at Listris was sijk in the feet, and hadde sete crokid fro his modris wombe, which neuer hadde goen.
27415	44	14	8	This herde Poul spekinge; and Poul biheld hym, and siy that he hadde feith, that he schulde be maad saaf,
27416	44	14	9	and seide with a greet vois, Rise thou `vp riyt on thi feet. And he lippide, and walkide.
27417	44	14	10	And the puple, whanne thei hadde seyn that that Poul dide, reriden her vois in Licaon tunge, and seiden, Goddis maad lijk to men ben comun doun to vs.
27418	44	14	11	And thei clepiden Barnabas Jubiter, and Poul Mercurie, for he was ledere of the word.
27419	44	14	12	And the preest of Jubiter that was bifor the citee, brouyte boolis and crownes bifor the yatis, with puplis, and wolde haue maad sacrifice.
27420	44	14	13	And whanne the apostlis Barnabas and Poul herden this, thei to-renten her cootis; and thei skipten out among the puple,
27421	44	14	14	and crieden, and seiden, Men, what don ye this thing? and we ben deedli men lijk you, and schewen to you, that ye be conuertid fro these veyn thingis to the lyuynge God, that maad heuene, and erthe, and the see, and alle thingis that ben in hem;
27422	44	14	15	which in generaciouns passid suffride alle folkis to gon in to her owne weies.
27423	44	14	16	And yit he lefte not hym silf with out witnessing in wel doyng, for he yaf reyns fro heuene, and times beringe fruyt, and fulfillide youre hertis with meete and gladnesse.
27424	44	14	17	And thei seiynge these thingis, vnnethis swagiden the puple, that thei offriden not to hem.
27425	44	14	18	But sum Jewis camen ouer fro Antioche and Iconye, and counseilden the puple, and stonyden Poul, and drowen out of the citee, and gessiden that he was deed.
27426	44	14	19	But whanne disciplis weren comun aboute him, he roos, and wente in to the citee; and in the dai suynge he wente forth with Barnabas in to Derben.
27427	44	14	20	And whanne thei hadden prechid to the ilk citee, and tauyte manye, thei turneden ayen to Listris, and Iconye, and to Antioche; confermynge the soulis of disciplis,
27428	44	14	21	and monestinge, that thei schulden dwelle in feith, and seiden, That bi many tribulaciouns it bihoueth vs to entre in to the kingdom of heuenes.
27429	44	14	22	And whanne thei hadden ordeined prestis to hem bi alle citees, and hadden preied with fastyngis, thei bitoken hem to the Lord, in whom thei bileueden.
27430	44	14	23	And thei passiden Persidie, and camen to Pamfilie;
27431	44	14	24	and thei spaken the word `of the Lord in Pergen, and camen doun in to Italie.
27432	44	14	25	And fro thennys thei wenten bi boot to Antiochie, fro whennus thei weren takun to the grace of God, in to the werk that thei filliden.
27433	44	14	26	And whanne thei weren comun, and hadden gaderid the chirche, thei telden hou grete thingis God dide with hem, and that he hadde openyde to hethene men the dore of feith.
27434	44	14	27	And thei dwelliden not a litil tyme with the disciplis.
27435	44	15	1	And summe camen doun fro Judee, and tauyten britheren, That but ye ben circumcidid after the lawe of Moises, ye moun not be maad saaf.
27436	44	15	2	Therfor whanne ther was maad not a litil discencioun to Poul and Barnabas ayens hem, thei ordeyneden, that Poul and Barnabas, and summe othere of hem, schulden go vp to the apostlis and preestis in Jerusalem, on this questioun.
27437	44	15	3	And so thei weren led forth of the chirche, and passiden bi Fenyce and Samarie; and thei telden the conuersacioun of hethene men, and thei maden greet ioie to alle the britheren.
27438	44	15	4	And whanne thei camen to Jerusalem, thei weren resseyued of the chirche and of the apostlis, and of the eldre men, and telden, hou greet thingis God dide with hem.
27439	44	15	5	But summe of the erise of Fariseis, that bileueden, risen vp, and seiden, That it bihoueth hem to be circumsidid, and to comaunde to kepe also the lawe of Moises.
27440	44	15	6	And the apostlis and eldre men camen togidre, to se of `this word.
27441	44	15	7	And whanne there was maad a greet sekyng herof, Petre roos, and seide to hem, Britheren, ye witen, that of elde daies in you God chees bi my mouth hethene, to here the word of the gospel, and to bileue;
27442	44	15	8	and God, that knewe hertis, bar witnessing, and yaf to hem the Hooli Goost, as also to vs;
27443	44	15	9	and no thing diuerside bitwixe vs and hem, `and clenside the hertis of hem bi feith.
27444	44	15	10	Now thanne what tempten ye God, to putte a yok on the necke of the disciplis, which nether we, nether oure fadris miyten bere?
27445	44	15	11	But bi the grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist we bileuen to be saued, as also thei.
27446	44	15	12	And al the multitude helde pees, and herden Barnaban and Poul, tellinge hou grete signes and wondris God dide bi hem in hethene men.
27447	44	15	13	And aftir that thei helden pees, James answeride, and seide, Britheren, here ye me.
27448	44	15	14	Symount telde, hou God visitide, first to take of hethene men a puple to his name.
27449	44	15	15	And the wordis of prophetis acorden to him,
27450	44	15	16	as it is writun, Aftir this Y schal turne ayen, and bilde the tabernacle of Dauid, that felle doun; and Y schal bilde ayen the cast doun thingis of it, and Y schal reise it;
27451	44	15	17	that other men seke the Lord, and alle folkis on which my name is clepid to helpe; the Lord doynge this thing, seith.
27452	44	15	18	Fro the world, the werk of the Lord is knowun to the Lord.
27453	44	15	19	For which thing Y deme hem that of hethene men ben conuertid to God,
27454	44	15	20	to be not disesid, but to write to hem, that thei absteyne hem fro defoulingis of maumetis, and fro fornicacioun, and stranglid thingis, and blood.
27455	44	15	21	For Moyses of elde tymes hath in alle citees hem that prechen him in synagogis, where bi ech sabat he is red.
