28018	45	4	5	Sotheli to hym that worchith not, but bileueth in to hym that iustefieth a wickid man, his feith is arettid to riytwisnesse, aftir the purpos of Goddis grace.
28019	45	4	6	As Dauid seith the blessidnesse of a man, whom God acceptith, he yyueth to hym riytwisnesse with outen werkis of the lawe,
28020	45	4	7	Blessid ben thei, whos wickidnessis ben foryouun, and whos synnes ben hid.
28021	45	4	8	Blessid is that man, to whom God arettide not synne.
28022	45	4	9	Thanne whether dwellith this blisfulnesse oneli in circumcisioun, or also in prepucie? For we seien, that the feith was arettid to Abraham to riytwisnesse.
28023	45	4	10	Hou thanne was it arettid? in circumcisioun, or in prepucie? Not in circumcisioun, but in prepucie.
28024	45	4	11	And he took a signe of circumcisioun, a tokenyng of riytwisnesse of the feith which is in prepucie, that he be fadir of alle men bileuynge bi prepucie, that it be arettid also to hem to riytwisnesse;
28025	45	4	12	and that he be fadir of circumcisioun, not onely to hem that ben of circumcisioun, but also to hem that suen the steppis of the feith, which feith is in prepucie of oure fader Abraham.
28026	45	4	13	For not bi the lawe is biheest to Abraham, or to his seed, that he schulde be eir of the world, but bi the riytwisnesse of feith.
28027	45	4	14	For if thei that ben of the lawe, ben eiris, feith is distried, biheest is don awey.
28028	45	4	15	For the lawe worchith wraththe; for where is no lawe, there is no trespas, nethir is trespassyng.
28029	45	4	16	Therfor riytfulnesse is of the feith, that bi grace biheeste be stable to ech seed, not to that seed oneli that is of the lawe, but to that that is of the feith of Abraham, which is fadir of vs alle.
28030	45	4	17	As it is writun, For Y haue set thee fadir of many folkis, bifor God to whom thou hast bileued. Which God quykeneth deed men, and clepith tho thingis that ben not, as tho that ben.
28031	45	4	18	Which Abraham ayens hope bileuede in to hope, that he schulde be maad fader of many folkis, as it was seid to hym, Thus schal thi seed be, as the sterris of heuene, and as the grauel that is in the brenke of the see.
28032	45	4	19	And he was not maad vnstidfast in the bileue, nether he biheelde his bodi thanne nyy deed, whanne he was almost of an hundrid yeer, ne the wombe of Sare nyy deed.
28033	45	4	20	Also in the biheeste of God he doutide not with vntrist; but he was coumfortid in bileue,
28034	45	4	21	yyuynge glorie to God, witynge moost fulli that what euere thingis God hath bihiyt, he is myyti also to do.
28035	45	4	22	Therfor it was arettid to hym to riytwisnesse.
28036	45	4	23	And it is not writun oneli for him, that it was arettid to hym to riytwisnesse,
28037	45	4	24	but also for vs, to whiche it schal be arettid, that bileuen in him that reiside oure Lord Jhesu Crist fro deeth.
28038	45	4	25	Which was bitakun for oure synnes, and roos ayen for oure iustefiyng.
28039	45	5	1	Therfor we, iustified of feith, haue we pees at God bi oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28040	45	5	2	Bi whom we han niy goyng to, bi feith in to this grace, in which we stonden, and han glorie in the hope of the glorie of Goddis children.
28041	45	5	3	And not this oneli, but also we glorien in tribulaciouns, witynge that tribulacioun worchith pacience,
28042	45	5	4	and pacience preuyng, and preuyng hope.
28043	45	5	5	And hope confoundith not, for the charite of God is spred abrood in oure hertis bi the Hooli Goost, that is youun to vs.
28044	45	5	6	And while that we weren sijk aftir the tyme, what diede Crist for wickid men?
28045	45	5	7	For vnnethis dieth ony man for the iust man; and yit for a good man perauenture summan dar die.
28046	45	5	8	But God comendith his charite in vs; for if whanne we weren yit synneris,
28047	45	5	9	aftir the tyme Crist was deed for vs, thanne myche more now we iustified in his blood, schulen be saaf fro wraththe bi him.
28048	45	5	10	For if whanne we weren enemyes, we ben recounselid to God bi the deth of his sone, myche more we recounselid schulen be saaf in the lijf of hym.
28049	45	5	11	And not oneli this, but also we glorien in God, bi oure Lord Jhesu Crist, bi whom we han resseyued now recounseling.
28050	45	5	12	Therfor as bi o man synne entride in to this world, and bi synne deth, and so deth passide forth in to alle men, in which man alle men synneden.
28051	45	5	13	For `til to the lawe synne was in the world; but synne was not rettid, whanne lawe was not.
28052	45	5	14	But deth regnyde from Adam `til to Moises, also in to hem that synneden not in licnesse of the trespassyng of Adam, the which is licnesse of Crist to comynge.
28053	45	5	15	But not as gilt, so the yifte; for if thorouy the gilt of oon manye ben deed, myche more the grace of God and the yifte in the grace of o man Jhesu Crist hath aboundid in to many men.
28054	45	5	16	And not as bi o synne, so bi the yifte; for the doom of oon in to condempnacioun, but grace of many giltis in to iustificacioun.
28055	45	5	17	For if in the gilt of oon deth regnede thorouy oon, myche more men that takyn plente of grace, and of yyuyng, and of riytwisnesse, schulen regne in lijf bi oon Jhesu Crist.
28056	45	5	18	Therfor as bi the gilt of oon in to alle men in to condempnacioun, so bi the riytwisnesse of oon in to alle men in to iustifiyng of lijf.
28057	45	5	19	For as bi inobedience of o man manye ben maad synneris, so bi the obedience of oon manye schulen be iust.
28058	45	5	20	And the lawe entride, that gilt schulde be plenteuouse; but where gilt was plenteuouse,
28059	45	5	21	grace was more plenteuouse. That as synne regnede in to deth, so grace regne bi riytwisnesse in to euerlastynge lijf, bi `Crist Jhesu oure Lord.
28060	45	6	1	Therfor what schulen we seie? Schulen we dwelle in synne, that grace be plenteuouse?
28061	45	6	2	God forbede. For hou schulen we that ben deed to synne, lyue yit ther ynne?
28062	45	6	3	Whether, britheren, ye knowen not, that whiche euere we ben baptisid in Crist Jhesu, we ben baptisid in his deth?
28063	45	6	4	For we ben togidere biried with hym bi baptym `in to deth; that as Crist aroos fro deth bi the glorie of the fadir, so walke we in a newnesse of lijf.
28064	45	6	5	For if we plauntid togidere ben maad to the licnesse of his deth, also we schulen be of the licnesse of his risyng ayen;
28065	45	6	6	witynge this thing, that oure olde man is crucified togidere, that the bodi of synne be distruyed, that we serue no more to synne.
28066	45	6	7	For he that is deed, is iustefied fro synne.
28067	45	6	8	And if we ben deed with Crist, we bileuen that also we schulen lyue togidere with hym;
28068	45	6	9	witinge for Crist, rysynge ayen fro deth, now dieth not, deeth schal no more haue lordschip on hym.
28069	45	6	10	For that he was deed to synne, he was deed onys; but that he lyueth, he liueth to God.
28070	45	6	11	So ye deme you silf to be deed to synne, but lyuynge to God in `Jhesu Crist oure Lord.
28071	45	6	12	Therfor regne not synne in youre deedli bodi, that ye obeische to hise coueityngis.
28072	45	6	13	Nether yyue ye youre membris armuris of wickidnesse to synne, but yyue ye you silf to God, as thei that lyuen of deed men, and youre membris armuris of riytwisnesse to God.
28073	45	6	14	For synne schal not haue lordschipe on you; for ye ben not vndur the lawe, but vndur grace.
28074	45	6	15	What therfor? Schulen we do synne, for we ben not vndur the lawe, but vndur grace?
28075	45	6	16	God forbede. Witen ye not, that to whom ye yyuen you seruauntis to obeie to, ye ben seruauntis of that thing, to which ye han obeschid, ether of synne to deth, ether of obedience to riytwisnesse?
28076	45	6	17	But Y thanke God, that ye weren seruauntis of synne; but ye han obeischid of herte in to that fourme of techyng, in which ye ben bitakun.
28077	45	6	18	And ye delyuered fro synne, ben maad seruauntis of riytwisnesse.
28078	45	6	19	Y seie that thing that is of man, for the vnstidefastnesse of youre fleisch. But as ye han youun youre membris to serue to vnclennesse, and to wickidnesse `in to wickidnesse, so now yyue ye youre membris to serue to riytwisnesse in to hoolynesse.
28079	45	6	20	For whanne ye weren seruauntis of synne, ye weren fre of riytfulnesse.
28080	45	6	21	Therfor what fruyt hadden ye thanne in tho thingis, in whiche ye schamen now? For the ende of hem is deth.
28081	45	6	22	But now ye delyuered fro synne, and maad seruauntis to God, han your fruyt in to holinesse, and the ende euerlastinge lijf. For the wagis of synne is deth; the grace of God is euerlastynge lijf in Crist Jhesu our Lord.
28082	45	7	1	Britheren, whethir ye knowun not; for Y speke to men `that knowen the lawe; for the lawe hath lordschip in a man, as long tyme as it lyueth?
28083	45	7	2	For that womman that is vndur an hosebonde, is boundun to the lawe, while the hosebonde lyueth; but if hir hosebonde is deed, sche is delyuered fro the lawe of the hosebonde.
28084	45	7	3	Therfor sche schal be clepid auoutresse, if sche be with another man, while the hosebonde lyueth; but if hir hosebonde is deed, sche is delyuered fro the lawe of the hosebonde, that sche be not auoutresse, if sche be with another man.
28085	45	7	4	And so, my britheren, ye ben maad deed to the lawe bi the bodi of Crist, that ye ben of another, that roos ayen fro deth, that ye bere fruyt to God.
28086	45	7	5	For whanne we weren in fleisch, passiouns of synnes, that weren bi the lawe, wrouyten in oure membris, to bere fruyt to deth.
28087	45	7	6	But now we ben vnboundun fro the lawe of deth, in which we weren holdun, so that we seruen in newnesse of spirit, and not in eldnesse of lettre.
28088	45	7	7	What therfor schulen we seie? The lawe is synne? God forbede. But Y knew not synne, but bi lawe; for Y wiste not that coueitynge was synne, but for the lawe seide, Thou schalt not coueyte.
28089	45	7	8	And thoruy occasioun takun, synne bi the maundement hath wrouyt in me al coueytise; for withouten the lawe, synne was deed.
28090	45	7	9	And Y lyuede withouten the lawe sumtyme; but whanne the comaundement was comun, synne lyuede ayen.
28091	45	7	10	But Y was deed, and this comaundement that was to lijf, was foundun to me, to be to deth.
28092	45	7	11	For synne, thorouy occasioun takun bi the comaundement, disceyuede me, and bi that it slow me.
28093	45	7	12	Therfor the lawe is hooli, and the comaundement is hooli, and iust, and good.
28094	45	7	13	Is thanne that thing that is good, maad deth to me? God forbede. But synne, that it seme synne, thorouy good thing wrouyte deth to me, that me synne ouer maner thorouy the comaundement.
28095	45	7	14	And we witen, that the lawe is spiritual; but Y am fleischli, seld vndur synne.
28096	45	7	15	For Y vndurstonde not that that Y worche; for Y do not the good thing that Y wole, but Y do thilke yuel thing that Y hate.
28097	45	7	16	And if Y do that thing that Y wole not, Y consente to the lawe, that it is good.
28098	45	7	17	But now Y worche not it now, but the synne that dwellith in me.
28099	45	7	18	But and Y woot, that in me, that is, in my fleisch, dwellith no good; for wille lieth to me, but Y fynde not to performe good thing.
28100	45	7	19	For Y do not thilke good thing that Y wole, but Y do thilke yuel thing that Y wole not.
28101	45	7	20	And if Y do that yuel thing that Y wole not, Y worche not it, but the synne that dwellith in me.
28102	45	7	21	Therfor Y fynde the lawe to me willynge to do good thing, for yuel thing lieth to me.
28103	45	7	22	For Y delite togidere to the lawe of God, aftir the ynnere man. But Y se another lawe in my membris,
28104	45	7	23	ayenfiytynge the lawe of my soule, and makynge me caitif in the lawe of synne, that is in my membris.
28105	45	7	24	Y am an vnceli man; who schal delyuer me fro the bodi of this synne?
28106	45	7	25	The grace of God, bi Jhesu Crist oure Lord. Therfor Y my silf bi the soule serue to the lawe of God; but bi fleisch to the lawe of synne.
28107	45	8	1	Therfor now no thing of dampnacioun is to hem that ben in Crist Jhesu, whiche wandren not after the flesch.
28108	45	8	2	For the lawe of the spirit of lijf in Crist Jhesu hath delyuerid me fro the lawe of synne, and of deth.
28109	45	8	3	For that that was vnpossible to the lawe, in what thing it was sijk bi flesch, God sente his sone in to the licknesse of fleisch of synne, and of synne dampnede synne in fleisch;
28110	45	8	4	that the iustefiyng of the lawe were fulfillid in vs, that goen not aftir the fleisch, but aftir the spirit.
28111	45	8	5	For thei that ben aftir the fleisch, saueren tho thingis that ben of the fleisch; but thei that ben after the spirit, feelen tho thingis that ben of the spirit. For the prudence of fleisch is deth;
28112	45	8	6	but the prudence of spirit is lijf and pees.
28113	45	8	7	For the wisdom of the fleisch is enemye to God; for it is not suget to the lawe of God, for nether it may.
28114	45	8	8	And thei that ben in fleisch, moun not plese to God.
28115	45	8	9	But ye ben not in fleisch, but in spirit; if netheles the spirit of God dwellith in you. But if ony hath not the spirit of Crist, this is not his.
28116	45	8	10	For if Crist is in you, the bodi is deed for synne, but the spirit lyueth for iustefiyng.
28117	45	8	11	And if the spirit of hym that reiside Jhesu Crist fro deth dwellith in you, he that reiside Jhesu Crist fro deth, shal quykene also youre deedli bodies, for the spirit of hym that dwellith in you.
28118	45	8	12	Therfor, britheren, we ben dettouris, not to the flesch, that we lyuen aftir the flesch.
28119	45	8	13	For if ye lyuen aftir the fleisch, ye schulen die; but if ye bi the spirit sleen the dedis of the fleisch, ye schulen lyue.
28120	45	8	14	For who euere ben led bi the spirit of God, these ben the sones of God.
28121	45	8	15	For ye han not take eftsoone the spirit of seruage in drede, but ye han taken the spirit of adopcioun of sones, in which we crien, Abba, fadir.
28122	45	8	16	And the ilke spirit yeldith witnessyng to oure spirit, that we ben the sones of God;
28123	45	8	17	if sones, and eiris, `and eiris of God, and eiris togidere with Crist; if netheles we suffren togidere, that also we ben glorified togidere.
28124	45	8	18	And Y deme, that the passiouns of this tyme ben not worthi to the glorie to comynge, that schal be schewid in vs.
28125	45	8	19	For the abidyng of creature abidith the schewyng of the sones of God.
28126	45	8	20	But the creature is suget to vanyte, not willynge, but for hym that made it suget in hope;
28127	45	8	21	for the ilke creature schal be delyuered fro seruage of corrupcioun in to liberte of the glorie of the sones of God.
28128	45	8	22	And we witen, that ech creature sorewith, and trauelith with peyne til yit.
28129	45	8	23	And not oneli it, but also we vs silf, that han the first fruytis of the spirit, and we vs silf sorewen with ynne vs for the adopcioun of Goddis sonys, abidynge the ayenbiyng of oure bodi.
28130	45	8	24	But bi hope we ben maad saaf. For hope that is seyn, is not hope; for who hopith that thing, that he seeth?
28131	45	8	25	And if we hopen that thing that we seen not, we abiden bi pacience.
28132	45	8	26	And also the spirit helpith oure infirmyte; for what we schulen preie, as it bihoueth, we witen not, but the ilke spirit axith for vs with sorewyngis, that moun not be teld out.
28133	45	8	27	For he that sekith the hertis, woot what the spirit desirith, for bi God he axith for hooli men.
28134	45	8	28	And we witen, that to men `that louen God, alle thingis worchen togidere in to good, to hem that aftir purpos ben clepid seyntis.
28135	45	8	29	For thilke that he knewe bifor, he bifor ordenede bi grace to be maad lijk to the ymage of his sone, that he be the first bigetun among many britheren.
28136	45	8	30	And thilke that he bifore ordeynede to blis, hem he clepide; and whiche he clepide, hem he iustifiede; and whiche he iustifiede, and hem he glorifiede.
28137	45	8	31	What thanne schulen we seie to these thingis? If God for vs, who is ayens vs?
28138	45	8	32	The which also sparide not his owne sone, but `for vs alle bitook hym, hou also yaf he not to vs alle thingis with hym?
28139	45	8	33	Who schal accuse ayens the chosun men of God? It is God that iustifieth,
28140	45	8	34	who is it that condempneth? It is Jhesus Crist that was deed, yhe, the which roos ayen, the which is on the riyt half of God, and the which preieth for vs.
28141	45	8	35	Who thanne schal departe vs fro the charite of Crist? tribulacioun, or anguysch, or hungur, or nakidnesse, or persecucioun, or perel, or swerd?
28142	45	8	36	As it is writun, For we ben slayn al dai for thee; we ben gessid as scheep of slauytir.
28143	45	8	37	But in alle these thingis we ouercomen, for hym that louyde vs.
28144	45	8	38	But Y am certeyn, that nethir deeth, nether lijf, nether aungels, nethir principatus, nether vertues, nether present thingis, nether thingis to comynge, nether strengthe,
28145	45	8	39	nether heiyth, nether depnesse, nether noon othir creature may departe vs fro the charite of God, that is in `Crist Jhesu oure Lord.
28146	45	9	1	I seie treuthe in Crist Jhesu, Y lye not, for my conscience berith witnessyng to me in the Hooli Goost,
28147	45	9	2	for greet heuynesse is to me, and contynuel sorewe to my herte.
28148	45	9	3	For Y my silf desiride to be departid fro Crist for my britheren, that ben my cosyns aftir the fleisch, that ben men of Israel;
28149	45	9	4	whos is adopcioun of sones, and glorie, and testament, and yyuyng of the lawe, and seruyce, and biheestis;
28150	45	9	5	whos ben the fadris, and of which is Crist after the fleisch, that is God aboue alle thingis, blessid in to worldis.
28151	45	9	6	Amen. But not that the word of God hath falle doun. For not alle that ben of Israel, these ben Israelitis.
28152	45	9	7	Nethir thei that ben seed of Abraham, `alle ben sonys; but in Ysaac the seed schal be clepid to thee;
28153	45	9	8	that is to seie, not thei that ben sones of the fleisch, ben sones of God, but thei that ben sones of biheeste ben demed in the seed.
28154	45	9	9	For whi this is the word of biheest, Aftir this tyme Y schal come, and a sone schal be to Sare.
28155	45	9	10	And not oneli sche, but also Rebecca hadde twey sones of o liggyng bi of Ysaac, oure fadir.
28156	45	9	11	And whanne thei weren not yit borun, nether hadden don ony thing of good ether of yuel, that the purpos of God schulde dwelle bi eleccioun,
28157	45	9	12	not of werkis, but of God clepynge, it was seid to hym,
28158	45	9	13	that the more schulde serue the lesse, as it is writun, Y louede Jacob, but Y hatide Esau.
28159	45	9	14	What therfor schulen we seie? Whether wickidnesse be anentis God?
28160	45	9	15	God forbede. For he seith to Moyses, Y schal haue merci on whom Y haue merci; and Y schal yyue merci on whom Y schal haue merci.
28161	45	9	16	Therfor it is not nether of man willynge, nethir rennynge, but of God hauynge mercy.
28162	45	9	17	And the scripture seith to Farao, For to this thing Y haue stirid thee, that Y schewe in thee my vertu, and that my name be teld in al erthe.
28163	45	9	18	Therfor of whom God wole, he hath merci; and whom he wole, he endurith.
28164	45	9	19	Thanne seist thou to me, What is souyt yit? for who withstondith his wille?
28165	45	9	20	O! man, who art thou, that answerist to God? Whether a maad thing seith to hym that made it, What hast thou maad me so?
28166	45	9	21	Whether a potter of cley hath not power to make of the same gobet o vessel in to honour, an othere in to dispit?
28167	45	9	22	That if God willynge to schewe his wraththe, and to make his power knowun, hath suffrid in greet pacience vessels of wraththe able in to deth,
28168	45	9	23	to schewe the riytchessis of his glorie in to vessels of merci, whiche he made redi in to glorie.
28169	45	9	24	Whiche also he clepide not oneli of Jewis, but also of hethene men, as he seith in Osee,
28170	45	9	25	Y schal clepe not my puple my puple, and not my loued my louyd, and not getynge mercy getynge merci;
28171	45	9	26	and it schal be in the place, where it is seid to hem, Not ye my puple, there thei schulen be clepid the sones of `God lyuynge.
28172	45	9	27	But Isaye crieth for Israel, If the noumbre of Israel schal be as grauel of the see, the relifs schulen be maad saaf.
28173	45	9	28	Forsothe a word makynge an ende, and abreggynge in equyte, for the Lord schal make a word breggid on al the erthe.
28174	45	9	29	And as Ysaye bifor seide, But God of oostis hadde left to vs seed, we hadden be maad as Sodom, and we hadden be lijk as Gommor.
28175	45	9	30	Therfor what schulen we seie? That hethene men that sueden not riytwisnesse, han gete riytwisnesse, yhe, the riytwisnesse that is of feith.
28176	45	9	31	But Israel suynge the lawe of riytwisnesse, cam not parfitli in to the lawe of riytwisnesse.
28177	45	9	32	Whi? For not of feith, but as of werkys. And thei spurneden ayens the stoon of offencioun,
28178	45	9	33	as it is writun, Lo! Y putte a stoon of offensioun in Syon, and a stoon of sclaundre; and ech that schal bileue `in it, schal not be confoundid.
28179	45	10	1	Britheren, the wille of myn herte and mi biseching is maad to God for hem in to helthe.
28180	45	10	2	But Y bere witnessyng to hem, that thei han loue of God, but not aftir kunnyng.
28181	45	10	3	For thei vnknowynge Goddis riytwisnesse, and sekynge to make stidefast her owne riytfulnesse, ben not suget to the riytwisnesse of God.
28182	45	10	4	For the ende of the lawe is Crist, to riytwisnesse to ech man that bileueth.
28183	45	10	5	For Moises wroot, For the man that schal do riytwisnesse that is of the lawe, schal lyue in it.
28184	45	10	6	But the riytwisnesse that is of bileue, seith thus, Seie thou not in thin herte, Who schal stie in to heuene? that is to seie, to lede doun Crist;
28185	45	10	7	or who schal go doun in to helle? that is, to ayenclepe Crist fro deth.
28186	45	10	8	But what seith the scripture? The word is nyy in thi mouth, and in thin herte; this is the word of bileue, which we prechen.
28187	45	10	9	That if thou knoulechist in thi mouth the Lord Jhesu Crist, and bileuest in thin herte, that God reiside hym fro deth, thou schalt be saaf.
28188	45	10	10	For bi herte me bileueth to riytwisnesse, but bi mouth knowleching is maad to helthe.
28189	45	10	11	For whi the scripture seith, Ech that bileueth in hym, schal not be confoundid.
28190	45	10	12	And ther is no distinccioun of Jew and of Greke; for the same Lord of alle is riche in alle, that inwardli clepen hym.
28191	45	10	13	For ech man `who euere schal inwardli clepe the name of the Lord, schal be saaf.
28192	45	10	14	Hou thanne schulen thei inwardli clepe hym, in to whom thei han not bileued? or hou schulen thei bileue to hym, whom thei han not herd? Hou schulen thei here, with outen a prechour?
28193	45	10	15	and hou schulen thei preche, but thei be sent? As it is writun, Hou faire ben the feet of hem that prechen pees, of hem that prechen good thingis.
28194	45	10	16	But not alle men obeien to the gospel. For Ysaie seith, Lord, who bileuede to oure heryng?
28195	45	10	17	Therfor feith is of heryng, but heryng bi the word of Crist.
28196	45	10	18	But Y seie, Whether thei herden not? Yhis, sothely the word of hem wente out in to al the erthe, and her wordis in to the endis of the world.
28197	45	10	19	But Y seie, Whether Israel knewe not? First Moyses seith, Y schal lede you to enuye, that ye ben no folc; that ye ben an vnwise folc, Y schal sende you in to wraththe.
28198	45	10	20	And Ysaie is bold, and seith, Y am foundun of men that seken me not; opynli Y apperide to hem, that axiden not me.
28199	45	10	21	But to Israel he seith, Al dai Y streiyte out myn hondis to a puple that bileuede not, but ayen seide me.
28200	45	11	1	Therfor Y seie, Whether God hath put awei his puple? God forbede. For Y am an Israelite, of the seed of Abraham, of the lynage of Beniamyn.
28201	45	11	2	God hath not put awei his puple, which he bifor knew. Whether ye witen not, what the scripture seith in Elie? Hou he preieth God ayens Israel,
28202	45	11	3	Lord, thei han slayn thi prophetis, thei han vndurdoluun thin auteris, and Y am lefte aloone, and thei seken my lijf.
28203	45	11	4	But what seith Goddis answere to hym? Y haue left to me seuene thousyndes of men, that han not bowid her knees bifore Baal.
28204	45	11	5	So therfor also in this tyme, the relifs ben maad saaf, bi the chesyng of the grace of God.
28205	45	11	6	And if it be bi the grace of God, it is not now of werkis; ellis grace is not now grace.
28206	45	11	7	What thanne? Israel hath not getun this that he souyte, but eleccioun hath getun; and the othere ben blyndid.
28207	45	11	8	As it is writun, God yaf to hem a spirit of compunccioun, iyen that thei se not, and eeris, that thei here not, in to this dai.
28208	45	11	9	And Dauith seith, Be the boord of hem maad in to a gryn bifor hem, and in to catchyng, and in to sclaundre, and in to yeldyng to hem.
28209	45	11	10	Be the iyen of hem maad derk, that thei se not; and bowe thou doun algatis the bak of hem.
28210	45	11	11	Therfor Y seie, Whether thei offendiden so, that thei schulden falle doun? God forbede. But bi the gilt of hem helthe is maad to hethene men, that thei sue hem.
28211	45	11	12	That if the gilt of hem ben richessis of the world, and the makyng lesse of hem ben richessis of hethene men, hou myche more the plente of hem?
28212	45	11	13	But Y seie to you, hethene men, for as longe as Y am apostle of hethene men, Y schal onoure my mynysterie,
28213	45	11	14	if in ony maner Y stire my fleisch for to folowe, and that Y make summe of hem saaf.
28214	45	11	15	For if the loss of hem is the recouncelyng of the world, what is the takyng vp, but lijf of deede men?
28215	45	11	16	For if a litil part of that that is tastid be hooli, the hool gobet is hooli; and if the roote is hooli, also the braunchis.
28216	45	11	17	What if ony of the braunchis ben brokun, whanne thou were a wielde olyue tre, art graffid among hem, and art maad felowe of the roote, and of the fatnesse of the olyue tre,
28217	45	11	18	nyle thou haue glorie ayens the braunchis. For if thou gloriest, thou berist not the roote, but the roote thee.
28218	45	11	19	Therfor thou seist, The braunchis ben brokun, that Y be graffid in.
28219	45	11	20	Wel, for vnbileue the braunchis ben brokun; but thou stondist bi feith. Nyle thou sauere hiye thing,
28220	45	11	21	but drede thou, for if God sparide not the kyndli braunchis, lest perauenture he spare not thee.
28221	45	11	22	Therfor se the goodnesse, and the fersnesse of God; yhe, the feersnesse in to hem that felden doun, but the goodnesse of God in to thee, if thou dwellist in goodnesse, ellis also thou schalt be kit doun.
28222	45	11	23	Yhe, and thei schulen be set yn, if thei dwellen not in vnbileue. For God is myyti, to sette hem in eftsoone.
28223	45	11	24	For if thou art kit doun of the kyndeli wielde olyue tre, and ayens kynd art set in to a good olyue tre, hou myche more thei that ben bi kynde, schulen be set in her olyue tree?
28224	45	11	25	But, britheren, Y wole not that ye vnknowen this mysterie, that ye be not wise to you silf; for blyndenesse hath feld a parti in Israel, til that the plente of hethene men entride,
28225	45	11	26	and so al Israel schulde be maad saaf. As it is writun, He schal come of Syon, that schal delyuere, and turne awei the wickidnesse of Jacob.
28226	45	11	27	And this testament to hem of me, whanne Y schal do awei her synnes.
28227	45	11	28	Aftir the gospel thei ben enemyes for you, but thei ben moost dereworthe bi the eleccioun for the fadris.
28228	45	11	29	And the yiftis and the cleping of God ben with outen forthenkyng.
28229	45	11	30	And as sum tyme also ye bileueden not to God, but now ye han gete mercy for the vnbileue of hem;
28230	45	11	31	so and these now bileueden not in to youre merci, that also thei geten merci.
28231	45	11	32	For God closide alle thingis togidere in vnbileue, that he haue mercy on alle.
28232	45	11	33	O! the heiynesse of the ritchessis of the wisdom and of the kunnyng of God; hou incomprehensible ben hise domes, and hise weies ben vnserchable.
28233	45	11	34	For whi who knew the wit of the Lord, or who was his counselour? or who formere yaf to hym,
28234	45	11	35	and it schal be quyt to hym?
28235	45	11	36	For of hym, and bi hym, and in hym ben alle thingis. To hym be glorie in to worldis. Amen.
28236	45	12	1	Therfore, britheren, Y biseche you bi the mercy of God, that ye yyue youre bodies a lyuynge sacrifice, hooli, plesynge to God, and youre seruyse resonable.
28237	45	12	2	And nyle ye be confourmyd to this world, but be ye reformed in newnesse of youre wit, that ye preue which is the wille of God, good, and wel plesynge, and parfit.
28238	45	12	3	For Y seie, bi the grace that is youun to me, to alle that ben among you, that ye sauere no more than it bihoueth to sauere, but for to sauere to sobrenesse; and to ech man, as God hath departid the mesure of feith.
28239	45	12	4	For as in o bodi we han many membris, but alle the membris han not the same dede;
28240	45	12	5	so we many ben o bodi in Crist, and eche ben membris oon of anothir.
28241	45	12	6	Therfor we that han yiftis dyuersynge, aftir the grace that is youun to vs,
28242	45	12	7	ethir prophecie, aftir the resoun of feith; ethir seruise, in mynystryng; ether he that techith, in techyng;
28243	45	12	8	he that stirith softli, in monestyng; he that yyueth, in symplenesse; he that is souereyn, in bisynesse; he that hath merci, in gladnesse.
28244	45	12	9	Loue with outen feynyng, hatynge yuel, drawynge to good;
28245	45	12	10	louynge togidere the charite of britherhod. Eche come bifore to worschipen othere;
28246	45	12	11	not slow in bisynesse, feruent in spirit, seruynge to the Lord,
28247	45	12	12	ioiynge in hope, pacient in tribulacioun, bisy in preier,
28248	45	12	13	yyuynge good to the nedis of seyntis, kepynge hospitalite.
28249	45	12	14	Blesse ye men that pursuen you; blesse ye, and nyle ye curse;
28250	45	12	15	for to ioye with men that ioyen, for to wepe with men that wepen.
28251	45	12	16	Fele ye the same thing togidere; not sauerynge heiy thingis, but consentynge to meke thingis. Nile ye be prudent anentis you silf;
28252	45	12	17	to no man yeldynge yuel for yuel, but purueye ye good thingis, not oneli bifor God, but also bifor alle men.
28253	45	12	18	If it may be don, that that is of you, haue ye pees with alle men.
28254	45	12	19	Ye moost dere britheren, not defendynge you silf, but yyue ye place to wraththe; for it is writun, The Lord seith, To me veniaunce, and Y schal yelde.
28255	45	12	20	But if thin enemy hungrith, fede thou hym; if he thirstith, yyue thou drynke to hym; for thou doynge this thing schalt gidere togidere colis on his heed.
28256	45	12	21	Nyle thou be ouercomun of yuel, but ouercome thou yuel bi good.
28257	45	13	1	Euery soule be suget to heiyere powers. For ther is no power but of God, and tho thingis that ben of God, ben ordeyned.
28258	45	13	2	Therfor he that ayenstondith power, ayenstondith the ordynaunce of God; and thei that ayenstonden, geten to hem silf dampnacioun.
28259	45	13	3	For princes ben not to the drede of good work, but of yuel. But wilt thou, that thou drede not power? Do thou good thing, and thou schalt haue preisyng of it;
28260	45	13	4	for he is the mynystre of God to thee in to good. But if thou doist yuel, drede thou; for not with outen cause he berith the swerd, for he is the mynystre of God, vengere in to wraththe to hym that doith yuel.
28261	45	13	5	And therfor bi nede be ye suget, not oneli for wraththe, but also for conscience.
28262	45	13	6	For therfor ye yyuen tributis, thei ben the mynystris of God, and seruen for this same thing.
28263	45	13	7	Therfor yelde ye to alle men dettis, to whom tribut, tribut, to whom tol, tol, to whom drede, drede, to whom onour, onour.
28264	45	13	8	To no man owe ye ony thing, but that ye loue togidere. For he that loueth his neiybore, hath fulfillid the lawe.
28265	45	13	9	For, Thou schalt do no letcherie, Thou schalt not sle, Thou schalt not stele, Thou schalt not seie fals witnessyng, Thou schalt not coueyte the thing of thi neiybore, and if ther be ony othere maundement, it is instorid in this word, Thou schalt loue thi neiybore as thi silf.
28266	45	13	10	The loue of neiybore worchith not yuel; therfor loue is the fulfillyng of the lawe.
28267	45	13	11	And we knowen this tyme, that the our is now, that we rise fro sleep; for now oure heelthe is neer, than whanne we bileueden.
28268	45	13	12	The nyyt wente bifore, but the dai hath neiyed. Therfor caste we awei the werkis of derknessis, and be we clothid in the armeris of liyt.
28269	45	13	13	As in dai wandre we onestli, not in superflu feestis and drunkenessis, not in beddis and vnchastitees, not in strijf and in enuye;
28270	45	13	14	but be ye clothid in the Lord Jhesu Crist, and do ye not the bisynesse of fleisch in desiris.
28271	45	14	1	But take ye a sijk man in bileue, not in demyngis of thouytis.
28272	45	14	2	For another man leueth, that he mai ete alle thingis; but he that is sijk, ete wortis.
28273	45	14	3	He that etith, dispise not hym that etith not; and he that etith not, deme not hym that etith. For God hath take him to hym.
28274	45	14	4	Who art thou, that demest anothris seruaunt? To his lord he stondith, or fallith fro hym. But he schal stonde; for the Lord is myyti to make hym parfit.
28275	45	14	5	For whi oon demeth a day bitwixe a dai, another demeth ech dai.
28276	45	14	6	Ech man encrees in his wit. He that vnderstondith the dai, vnderstondith to the Lord. And he that etith, etith to the Lord, for he doith thankyngis to God. And he that etith not, etith not to the Lord, and doith thankyngis to God.
28277	45	14	7	For no man of vs lyueth to hymsilf, and no man dieth to hymself.
28278	45	14	8	For whether we lyuen, we lyuen to the Lord; and whethir we dien, we dien to the Lord. Therfor whethir we lyuen or dien, we ben of the Lord.
28279	45	14	9	For whi for this thing Crist was deed, and roos ayen, that he be Lord bothe of quyke and of deed men.
28280	45	14	10	But what demest thou thi brothir? or whi dispisist thou thi brothir? for alle we schulen stonde bifore the trone of Crist.
28281	45	14	11	For it is writun, Y lyue, seith the Lord, for to me ech kne schal be bowid, and ech tunge schal knouleche to God.
28282	45	14	12	Therfor ech of vs schal yelde resoun to God for hym silf.
28283	45	14	13	Therfor `no more deme we ech other; but more deme ye this thing, that ye putte not hirtyng, or sclaundre, to a brothir.
28284	45	14	14	I woot and triste in the Lord Jhesu, that no thing is vnclene bi hym, no but to him that demeth ony thing to be vnclene, to him it is vnclene.
28285	45	14	15	And if thi brother be maad sori in conscience for mete, now thou walkist not aftir charite. Nyle thou thorouy thi mete lese hym, for whom Crist diede.
28286	45	14	16	Therfor be not oure good thing blasfemed.
28287	45	14	17	For whi the rewme of God is not mete and drynk, but riytwisnesse and pees and ioye in the Hooli Goost.
28288	45	14	18	And he that in this thing serueth Crist, plesith God, and is proued to men.
28289	45	14	19	Therfor sue we tho thingis that ben of pees, and kepe we togidere `tho thingis that ben of edificacioun.
28290	45	14	20	Nyle thou for mete distrie the werk of God. For alle thingis ben clene, but it is yuel to the man that etith bi offendyng.
28291	45	14	21	It is good to not ete fleisch, and to not drynke wyn, nethir in what thing thi brother offendith, or is sclaundrid, or is maad sijk.
28292	45	14	22	Thou hast feith anentis thi silf, haue thou bifore God. Blessid is he that demeth not hym silf in that thing that he preueth.
28293	45	14	23	For he that demeth, is dampned, if he etith; for it is not of feith. And al thing that is not of feith, is synne.
28294	45	15	1	But we saddere men owen to susteyne the feblenesses of sijke men, and not plese to vs silf.
28295	45	15	2	Eche of vs plese to his neiybore in good, to edificacioun.
28296	45	15	3	For Crist pleside not to hym silf, as it is writun, The repreues of men dispisynge thee, felden on me.
28297	45	15	4	For what euere thingis ben writun, tho ben writun to oure techynge, that bi pacience and coumfort of scripturis we haue hope.
28298	45	15	5	But God of pacience and of solace yyue to you to vndurstonde the same thing, ech in to othere aftir Jhesu Crist,
28299	45	15	6	that ye of o wille with o mouth worschipe God and the fadir of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28300	45	15	7	For which thing take ye togidere, as also Crist took you in to the onour of God.
28301	45	15	8	For Y seie, that Jhesu Crist was a mynystre of circumcisioun for the treuthe of God, to conferme the biheestis of fadris.
28302	45	15	9	And hethene men owen to onoure God for merci; as it is writun, Therfor, Lord, Y schal knowleche to thee among hethene men, and Y schal synge to thi name.
28303	45	15	10	And eft he seith, Ye hethene men, be ye glad with his puple.
28304	45	15	11	And eft, Alle hethene men, herie ye the Lord; and alle puplis, magnefie ye hym.
28305	45	15	12	And eft Isaie seith, Ther schal be a roote of Jesse, that schal rise vp to gouerne hethene men, and hethene men schulen hope in hym.
28306	45	15	13	And God of hope fulfille you in al ioye and pees in bileuynge, that ye encrees in hope and vertu of the Hooli Goost.
28307	45	15	14	And, britheren, Y my silf am certeyn of you, that also ye ben ful of loue, and ye ben fillid with al kunnyng, so that ye moun moneste ech other.
28308	45	15	15	And, britheren, more boldli Y wroot to you a parti, as bryngynge you in to mynde, for the grace that is youun to me of God,
28309	45	15	16	that Y be the mynystre of Crist Jhesu among hethene men. And Y halewe the gospel of God, that the offryng of hethene men be acceptid, and halewid in the Hooli Goost.
28310	45	15	17	Therfor Y haue glorie in Crist Jhesu to God.
28311	45	15	18	For Y dar not speke ony thing of tho thingis, whiche Crist doith not bi me, in to obedience of hethene men, in word and dedis,
28312	45	15	19	in vertu of tokenes and grete wondris, in vertu of the Hooli Goost, so that fro Jerusalem bi cumpas to the Illirik see Y haue fillid the gospel of Crist.
28313	45	15	20	And so Y haue prechid this gospel, not where Crist was named, lest Y bilde vpon anotheres ground, but as it is writun,
28314	45	15	21	For to whom it is not teld of him, thei schulen se, and thei that herden not, schulen vndurstonde.
28315	45	15	22	For which thing Y was lettid ful myche to come to you, and Y am lettid to this tyme.
28316	45	15	23	And now Y haue not ferthere place in these cuntrees, but Y haue desire to come to you, of many yeris that ben passid.
28317	45	15	24	Whanne Y bygynne to passe in to Spayne, Y hope that in my goyng Y schal se you, and of you Y schal be led thidur, if Y vse you first in parti.
28318	45	15	25	Therfor now Y schal passe forth to Jerusalem, to mynystre to seyntis.
28319	45	15	26	For Macedonye and Acaie han assaied to make sum yifte to pore men of seyntis, that ben in Jerusalem.
28320	45	15	27	For it pleside to hem, and thei ben dettouris of hem; for hethene men ben maad parteneris of her goostli thingis, thei owen also in fleischli thingis to mynystre to hem.
28321	45	15	28	Therfor whanne Y haue endid this thing, and haue asigned to hem this fruyt, Y schal passe bi you in to Spayne.
28322	45	15	29	And Y woot, that Y comynge to you, schal come `in to the abundaunce of the blessing of Crist.
28323	45	15	30	Therfor, britheren, Y biseche you bi oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and bi charite of the Hooli Goost, that ye helpe me in youre preyeris to the Lord,
28324	45	15	31	that Y be delyuerid fro the vnfeithful men, that ben in Judee, and that the offryng of my seruyce be acceptid in Jerusalem to seyntis;
28325	45	15	32	that Y come to you in ioye, bi the wille of God, and that Y be refreischid with you. And God of pees be with you alle. Amen.
28326	45	16	1	And Y comende to you Feben, oure sister, which is in the seruyce of the chirche that is at Teucris,
28327	45	16	2	that ye resseyue hir in the Lord worthili to seyntis, and `that ye helpe hir in what euere cause sche schal nede of you. For sche helpide many men, and my silf.
28328	45	16	3	Grete ye Prisca and Aquyla, myn helperis in Crist Jhesu,
28329	45	16	4	which vndurputtiden her neckis for my lijf; to whiche not Y aloone do thankyngis, but also alle the chirchis of hethene men.
28330	45	16	5	And grete ye wel her meyneal chirche. Grete wel Efenete, louyd to me, that is the firste of Asie in Crist Jhesu.
28331	45	16	6	Grete wel Marie, the whiche hath trauelid myche in vs.
28332	45	16	7	Grete wel Andronyk and Julian, my cosyns, and myn euen prisouneris, which ben noble among the apostlis, and whiche weren bifor me in Crist.
28333	45	16	8	Grete wel Ampliate, most dereworth to me in the Lord.
28334	45	16	9	Grete wel Vrban, oure helpere in Crist Jhesus, and Stacchen, my derlyng.
28335	45	16	10	Grete wel Appellem, the noble in Crist.
28336	45	16	11	Grete wel hem that ben of Aristoblis hous. Grete wel Erodion, my cosyn. Grete wel hem that ben of Narciscies hous, that ben in the Lord.
28337	45	16	12	Grete wel Trifenam and Trifosam, whiche wymmen trauelen in the Lord. Grete wel Persida, most dereworthe womman, that hath trauelid myche in the Lord.
28338	45	16	13	Grete wel Rufus, chosun in the Lord, and his modir, and myn.
28339	45	16	14	Grete wel Ansicrete, Flegoncia, Hermen, Patroban, Herman, and britheren that ben with hem.
28340	45	16	15	Grete wel Filologus, and Julian, and Nereum, and his sistir, and Olympiades, and alle the seyntis that ben with hem.
28341	45	16	16	Grete ye wel togidere in hooli coss. Alle the chirches of Crist greten you wel.
28342	45	16	17	But, britheren, Y preye you, that ye aspie hem that maken discenciouns and hirtyngis, bisidis the doctryne that ye han lerned, and bowe ye awei fro hem.
28343	45	16	18	For suche men seruen not to the Lord Crist, but to her wombe, and bi swete wordis and blessyngis disseyuen the hertis of innocent men.
28344	45	16	19	But youre obedience is pupplischid in to euery place, therfor Y haue ioye in you. But Y wole that ye be wise in good thing, and symple in yuel.
28345	45	16	20	And God of pees tredde Sathanas vndur youre feet swiftli. The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with you.
28346	45	16	21	Tymothe, myn helpere, gretith you wel, and also Lucius, and Jason, and Sosipater, my cosyns.
28347	45	16	22	Y Tercius grete you wel, that wroot this epistle, in the Lord.
28348	45	16	23	Gayus, myn oost, gretith you wel, and al the chirche. Erastus, tresorere of the city, gretith you wel, and Quartus brother.
28349	45	16	24	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with you alle.
28350	45	16	25	Amen. And onour and glorie be to hym, that is myyti to conferme you bi my gospel, and prechyng of Jhesu Crist, bi the reuelacioun of mysterie holdun stylle in tymes euerlastinge;
28351	45	16	26	which mysterie is now maad opyn bi scripturis of prophetis, bi the comaundement of God with outen bigynnyng and endyng, to the obedience of feith in alle hethene men, the mysterie
28352	45	16	27	knowun bi Jhesu Crist to God aloone wiss, to whom be onour and glorie in to worldis of worldis. Amen.
28353	46	1	1	Poul, clepid apostle of Jhesu Crist, bi the wille of God, and Sostenes, brothir, to the chirche of God that is at Corynthe,
28354	46	1	2	to hem that ben halewid in Crist Jhesu, and clepid seyntis, with alle that inwardli clepen the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, in ech place of hem and of oure,
28355	46	1	3	grace to you and pees of God, oure fadir, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
28356	46	1	4	Y do thankyngis to my God eueremore for you, in the grace of God that is youun to you in Crist Jhesu.
28357	46	1	5	For in alle thingis ye ben maad riche in hym, in ech word, and in ech kunnyng,
28358	46	1	6	as the witnessyng of Crist is confermyd in you;
28359	46	1	7	so that no thing faile to you in ony grace, that abiden the schewyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist;
28360	46	1	8	which also schal conferme you in to the ende with outen cryme, in the dai of the comyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28361	46	1	9	`A trewe God, bi whom ye ben clepid in to the felouschipe of his sone Jhesu Crist oure Lord.
28362	46	1	10	But, britheren, Y biseche you, bi the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, that ye alle seie the same thing, and that dissenciouns be not among you; but be ye perfit in the same wit, and in the same kunnyng.
28363	46	1	11	For, my britheren, it is teld to me of hem that ben at Cloes, that stryues ben among you.
28364	46	1	12	And Y seie that, that ech of you seith, For Y am of Poul, and Y am of Apollo, and Y am of Cefas, but Y am of Crist.
28365	46	1	13	Whether Crist is departid? whether Poul was crucified for you, ether ye ben baptisid in the name of Poul?
28366	46	1	14	Y do thankyngis to my God, that Y baptiside noon of you, but Crispus and Gayus;
28367	46	1	15	lest ony man seie, that ye ben baptisid in my name.
28368	46	1	16	And Y baptiside also the hous of Stephan, but Y woot not, that Y baptiside ony other.
28369	46	1	17	For Crist sente me not to baptise, but to preche the gospel; not in wisdom of word, that the cros of Crist be not voidid awei.
28370	46	1	18	For the word of the cros is foli to hem that perischen; but to hem that ben maad saaf, that is to seie, to vs, it is the vertu of God.
28371	46	1	19	For it is writun, Y schal distruye the wisdom of wise men, and Y schal reproue the prudence of prudent men.
28372	46	1	20	Where is the wise man? where is the wise lawiere? where is the purchasour of this world? Whether God hath not maad the wisdom of this world fonned?
28373	46	1	21	For the world in wisdom of God knewe not God bi wisdom, it pleside to God, bi foli of prechyng, `to maken hem saaf that bileueden.
28374	46	1	22	For Jewis seken signes, and Grekis seken wisdom;
28375	46	1	23	but we prechen Crist crucified, to Jewis sclaundre, and to hethene men foli;
28376	46	1	24	but to tho Jewis and Grekis that ben clepid, we prechen Crist the vertu of God and the wisdom of God.
28377	46	1	25	For that that is foli thing of God, is wiser than men; and that that is the feble thing of God, is strengere than men.
28378	46	1	26	But, britheren, se ye youre clepyng; for not many wise men aftir the fleisch, not many myyti, not many noble.
28379	46	1	27	But God chees tho thingis that ben fonned of the world, to confounde wise men;
28380	46	1	28	and God chees the feble thingis of the world, to confounde the stronge thingis; and God chees the vnnoble thingis `and dispisable thingis of the world, and tho thingis that ben not, to distruye tho thingis that ben;
28381	46	1	29	that ech man haue not glorie in his siyt.
28382	46	1	30	But of hym ye ben in Crist Jhesu, which is maad of God to vs wisdom, and riytwisnesse, and holynesse, and ayenbiyng; that,
28383	46	1	31	as it is wrytun, He that glorieth, haue glorie in the Lord.
28384	46	2	1	And Y, britheren, whanne Y cam to you, cam not in the heiynesse of word, ethir of wisdom, tellynge to you the witnessyng of Crist.
28385	46	2	2	For Y demede not me to kunne ony thing among you, but Crist Jhesu, and hym crucified.
28386	46	2	3	And Y in sikenesse, and drede, and myche trembling, was among you;
28387	46	2	4	and my word and my preching was not in suteli sturyng wordis of mannus wisdom, but in schewyng of spirit and of vertu;
28388	46	2	5	that youre feith be not in the wisdom of men, but in the vertu of God.
28389	46	2	6	For we speken wisdom among perfit men, but not wisdom of this world, nether of princes of this world, that ben distried;
28390	46	2	7	but we speken the wisdom of God in mysterie, `which wisdom is hid; which wisdom God bifor ordeynede bifor worldis in to oure glorie,
28391	46	2	8	which noon of the princes of this world knew; for if thei hadden knowe, thei schulden neuere haue crucified the Lord of glorie.
28392	46	2	9	But as it is writun, That iye say not, ne eere herde, nether it stiede in to herte of man, what thingis God arayede to hem that louen hym;
28393	46	2	10	but God schewide to vs bi his spirit. For whi the spirit serchith alle thingis, yhe, the depe thingis of God.
28394	46	2	11	And who of men woot, what thingis ben of man, but the spirit of man that is in hym? So what thingis ben of God, no man knowith, but the spirit of God.
28395	46	2	12	And we han not resseiued the spirit of this world, but the spirit that is of God, that we wite what thingis ben youun to vs of God.
28396	46	2	13	Whiche thingis we speken also, not in wise wordis of mannus wisdom, but in the doctryn of the spirit, and maken a liknesse of spiritual thingis to goostli men.
28397	46	2	14	For a beestli man perseyueth not tho thingis that ben of the spirit of God; for it is foli to hym, and he may not vndurstonde, for it is examyned goostli.
28398	46	2	15	But a spiritual man demeth alle thingis, and he is demed of no man.
28399	46	2	16	As it is writun, And who knew the wit of the Lord, or who tauyte hym? And we han the wit of Crist.
28400	46	3	1	And Y, britheren, myyte not speke to you as to spiritual men, but as to fleischli men;
28401	46	3	2	as to litle children in Crist, Y yaf to you mylk drynke, not mete; for ye myyten not yit, nether ye moun now, for yit ye ben fleischli.
28402	46	3	3	For while strijf is among you, whether ye ben not fleischli, and ye gon aftir man?
28403	46	3	4	For whanne summe seith, Y am of Poul, another, But Y am of Apollo, whethir ye ben not men? What therfor is Apollo, and what Poul?
28404	46	3	5	Thei ben mynystris of hym, to whom ye han bileuyd; and to ech man as God hath youun.
28405	46	3	6	Y plauntide, Apollo moystide, but God yaf encreessyng.
28406	46	3	7	Therfor nether he that plauntith is ony thing, nethir he that moistith, but God that yiueth encreessyng.
28407	46	3	8	And he that plauntith, and he that moistith, ben oon; and ech schal take his owne mede, aftir his trauel.
28408	46	3	9	For we ben the helperis of God; ye ben the erthetiliyng of God, ye ben the bildyng of God.
28409	46	3	10	Aftir the grace `of God that is youun to me, as a wise maistir carpenter Y settide the foundement; and another bildith aboue. But ech man se, hou he bildith aboue.
28410	46	3	11	For no man may sette another foundement, outtakun that that is sett, which is Crist Jhesus.
28411	46	3	12	For if ony bildith ouer this foundement, gold, siluer, preciouse stoonys, stickis, hey, or stobil, euery mannus werk schal be open;
28412	46	3	13	for the dai of the Lord schal declare, for it schal be schewid in fier; the fier schal preue the werk of ech man, what maner werk it is.
28413	46	3	14	If the werk of ony man dwelle stille, which he bildide aboue, he schal resseyue mede.
28414	46	3	15	If ony mannus werk brenne, he schal suffre harm; but he schal be saaf, so netheles as bi fier.
28415	46	3	16	Witen ye not, that ye ben the temple of God, and the spirit of God dwellith in you?
28416	46	3	17	And if ony defoulith the temple of God, God schal leese hym; for the temple of God is hooli, which ye ben.
28417	46	3	18	No man disseyue hym silf. If ony man among you is seyn to be wiys in this world, be he maad a fool, that he be wijs.
28418	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foli anentis God; for it is writun, Y schal catche wise men in her fel wisdom;
28419	46	3	20	and eft, The Lord knowith the thouytis of wise men, for tho ben veyn.
28420	46	3	21	Therfor no man haue glorie in men.
28421	46	3	22	For alle thingis ben youre, ethir Poul, ether Apollo, ether Cefas, ether the world, ether lijf, ether deth, ether thingis present, ethir thingis to comynge; for alle thingis ben youre,
28422	46	3	23	and ye ben of Crist, and Crist is of God.
28423	46	4	1	So a man gesse vs, as mynystris of Crist, and dispenderis of the mynysteries of God.
28424	46	4	2	Now it is souyt here among the dispenderis, that a man be foundun trewe.
28425	46	4	3	And to me it is for the leest thing, that Y be demyd of you, or of mannus dai; but nether Y deme my silf.
28426	46	4	4	For Y am no thing ouer trowynge to my silf, but not in this thing Y am iustified; for he that demeth me, is the Lord.
28427	46	4	5	Therfor nyle ye deme bifore the tyme, til that the Lord come, which schal liytne the hyd thingis of derknessis, and schal schewe the counseils of hertis; and thanne preisyng schal be to ech man of God.
28428	46	4	6	And, britheren, Y haue transfigurid these thingis in to me and in to Apollo, for you; that in vs ye lerne, lest ouer that it is writun, oon ayens another be blowun with pride for another.
28429	46	4	7	Who demeth thee? And what hast thou, that thou hast not resseyued? And if thou hast resseyued, what gloriest thou, as thou haddist not resseyued?
28430	46	4	8	Nowe ye ben fyllid, now ye ben maad riche; ye regnen with outen vs; and Y wolde that ye regnen, that also we regnen with you.
28431	46	4	9	And Y gesse, that God schewide vs the laste apostlis, as thilke that ben sent to the deth; for we ben maad a spectacle to the world, and to aungels, and to men.
28432	46	4	10	We foolis for Crist, but ye prudent in Crist; we sike, but ye stronge; ye noble, but we vnnoble.
28433	46	4	11	Til in to this our we hungren, and thirsten, and ben nakid, and ben smytun with buffatis,
28434	46	4	12	and we ben vnstable, and we trauelen worchynge with oure hondis; we ben cursid, and we blessen; we suffren persecucioun, and we abiden longe; we ben blasfemyd, and we bisechen;
28435	46	4	13	as clensyngis of this world we ben maad the `out castyng of alle thingis `til yit.
28436	46	4	14	Y write not these thingis, that Y confounde you, but Y warne as my moste dereworthe sones.
28437	46	4	15	For whi if ye han ten thousynde of vndur maistris in Crist, but not many fadris; for in Crist Jhesu Y haue gendrid you bi the gospel.
28438	46	4	16	Therfor, britheren, Y preye you, be ye foleweris of me, as Y of Crist.
28439	46	4	17	Therfor Y sente to you Tymothe, which is my most dereworthe sone, and feithful in the Lord, which schal teche you my weies, that ben in Crist Jhesu; as Y teche euery where in ech chirche.
28440	46	4	18	As thouy Y schulde not come to you, so summe ben blowun with pride;
28441	46	4	19	but Y schal come to you soone, if God wole; and Y schal knowe not the word of hem that ben blowun with pride, but the vertu.
28442	46	4	20	For the rewme of God is not in word, but in vertu.
28443	46	4	21	What wole ye? Schal Y come to you in a yerde, or in charite, and in spirit of myldenesse?
28444	46	5	1	In al maner fornycacioun is herd among you, and siche fornycacioun, which is not among hethene men, so that summan haue the wijf of his fadir.
28445	46	5	2	And ye ben bolnyd with pride, and not more hadden weilyng, that he that dide this werk, be takun awei fro the myddil of you.
28446	46	5	3	And Y absent in bodi, but present in spirit, now haue demyd as present hym that hath thus wrouyt, whanne
28447	46	5	4	ye ben gaderid togidere in the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and my spirit, with the vertu of the Lord Jhesu,
28448	46	5	5	to take siche a man to Sathanas, in to the perischyng of fleisch, that the spirit be saaf in the dai of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28449	46	5	6	Youre gloriyng is not good. Witen ye not, that a litil sourdow apeyrith al the gobet?
28450	46	5	7	Clense ye out the old sourdow, that ye be new sprengyng togidere, as ye ben therf. For Crist offrid is oure pask.
28451	46	5	8	Therfor ete we, not in eld sourdowy, nether in sourdowy of malice and weywardnesse, but in therf thingis of clernesse and of treuthe.
28452	46	5	9	I wroot to you in a pistle, that ye be not medlid with letchours,
28453	46	5	10	not with letchours of this world, ne coueitous men, ne raueynours, ne with men seruynge to mawmetis, ellis ye schulden haue go out of this world.
28454	46	5	11	But now Y wroot to you, that ye be not meynd. But if he that is named a brother among you, and is a letchour, or coueitouse, or seruynge to ydols, or cursere, or ful of drunkenesse, or raueynour, to take no mete with siche.
28455	46	5	12	For what is it to me to deme of hem that ben with oute forth? Whether ye demen not of thingis that ben with ynne forth?
28456	46	5	13	For God schal deme hem that ben withouten forth. Do ye awei yuel fro you silf.
28457	46	6	1	Dar any of you that hath a cause ayens another, be demed at wickid men, and not at hooli men?
28458	46	6	2	Whether ye witen not, that seyntis schulen deme of this world? And if the world schal be demed bi you, be ye vnworthi to deme of the leste thingis?
28459	46	6	3	Witen ye not, that we schulen deme aungels? hou myche more worldli thingis?
28460	46	6	4	Therfor if ye han worldli domes, ordeyne ye tho contemptible men, that ben in the chirche, to deme.
28461	46	6	5	Y seie to make you aschamed. So ther is not ony wise man, that may deme bitwixe a brothir and his brothir;
28462	46	6	6	but a brothir with brothir stryueth in dom, and that among vnfeithful men.
28463	46	6	7	And now trespas is algatis in you, for ye han domes among you. Whi rather take ye no wrong? whi rather suffre ye not disseit?
28464	46	6	8	But and ye doen wrong, and doen fraude, and that to britheren.
28465	46	6	9	Whether ye witen not, that wickid men schulen not welde the kyngdom of God? Nyle ye erre; nethir letchours, nether men that seruen mawmetis, nether auouteris,
28466	46	6	10	nether letchouris ayen kynde, nether thei that doon letcheri with men, nether theues, nether auerouse men, nethir `ful of drunkenesse, nether curseris, nether rauenours, schulen welde the kyngdom of God.
28467	46	6	11	And ye weren sum tyme these thingis; but ye ben waischun, but ye ben halewid, but ye ben iustefied in the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and in the spirit of oure God.
28468	46	6	12	Alle thingis ben leeueful to me, but not alle thingis ben spedeful. Alle thingis ben leeueful to me, but Y schal not be brouyt doun vndur ony mannus power.
28469	46	6	13	Mete to the wombe, and the wombe to metis; and God schal distruye bothe this and that. And the bodi not to fornycacioun, but to the Lord, and the Lord to the bodi.
28470	46	6	14	For God reiside the Lord, and schal reise vs bi his vertu.
28471	46	6	15	Witen ye not, that youre bodies ben membris of Crist? Schal Y thanne take the membris of Crist, and schal Y make the membris of an hoore? God forbede.
28472	46	6	16	Whether ye witen not, that he that cleueth to an hoore, is maad o bodi? For he seith, Ther schulen be tweyne in o fleisch.
28473	46	6	17	And he that cleueth to the Lord, is o spirit.
28474	46	6	18	Fle ye fornycacioun; al synne what euere synne a man doith, is with out the bodi; but he that doith fornycacioun, synneth ayens his bodi.
28475	46	6	19	Whether ye witen not, that youre membris ben the temple of the Hooli Goost, that is in you, whom ye han of God, and ye ben not youre owne?
28476	46	6	20	For ye ben bouyt with greet prijs. Glorifie ye, and bere ye God in youre bodi.
28477	46	7	1	But of thilke thingis that ye han write to me, it is good to a man to touche not a womman.
28478	46	7	2	But for fornycacioun eche man haue his owne wijf, and ech womman haue hir owne hosebonde.
28479	46	7	3	The hosebonde yelde dette to the wijf, and also the wijf to the hosebonde.
28480	46	7	4	The womman hath not power of hir bodi, but the hosebonde; and the hosebonde hath not power of his bodi, but the womman.
28481	46	7	5	Nyle ye defraude eche to othere, but perauenture of consent to a tyme, that ye yyue tent to preier; and eft turne ye ayen to the same thing, lest Sathanas tempte you for youre vncontynence.
28482	46	7	6	But Y seie this thing as yyuyng leeue, not bi comaundement.
28483	46	7	7	For Y wole, that alle men be as my silf. But eche man hath his propre yifte of God; oon thus, and another thus.
28484	46	7	8	But Y seie to hem, that ben not weddid, and to widewis, it is good to hem, if thei dwellen so as Y.
28485	46	7	9	That if thei conteynen not hem silf, be thei weddid; for it is betere to be weddid, than to be brent.
28486	46	7	10	But to hem that ben ioyned in matrymonye, Y comaunde, not Y, but the Lord, that the wijf departe not fro the hosebonde;
28487	46	7	11	and that if sche departith, that sche dwelle vnweddid, or be recounselid to hir hosebonde; and the hosebonde forsake not the wijf.
28488	46	7	12	But to othere Y seie, not the Lord. If ony brother hath an vnfeithful wijf, and sche consenteth to dwelle with hym, leeue he hir not.
28489	46	7	13	And if ony womman hath an vnfeithful hosebonde, and this consentith to dwelle with hir, leeue sche not the hosebonde.
28490	46	7	14	For the vnfeithful hosebonde is halewid bi the feithful womman, and the vnfeithful womman is halewid bi the feithful hosebonde. Ellis youre children weren vncleene, but now thei ben hooli.
28491	46	7	15	That if the vnfeithful departith, departe he. For whi the brother or sistir is not suget to seruage in siche; for God hath clepid vs in pees.
28492	46	7	16	And wherof wost thou, womman, if thou schalt make the man saaf; or wherof wost thou, man, if thou schalt make the womman saaf?
28493	46	7	17	But as the Lord hath departid to ech, and as God hath clepid ech man, so go he, as Y teche in alle chirchis.
28494	46	7	18	A man circumcidid is clepid, brynge he not to the prepucie. A man is clepid in prepucie, be he not circumcidid.
28495	46	7	19	Circumcisioun is nouyt, and prepucie is nouyt, but the kepyng of the maundementis of God.
28496	46	7	20	Ech man in what clepyng he is clepid, in that dwelle he.
28497	46	7	21	Thou seruaunt art clepid, be it no charge to thee; but if thou maist be fre, `the rather vse thou.
28498	46	7	22	He that is a seruaunt, and is clepid in the Lord, is a freman of the Lord. Also he that is a freman, and is clepid, is the seruaunt of Crist.
28499	46	7	23	With prijs ye ben bouyt; nyle ye be maad seruauntis of men.
28500	46	7	24	Therfor ech man in what thing he is clepid a brothir, dwelle he in this anentis God.
28501	46	7	25	But of virgyns Y haue no comaundement of God; but Y yyue counseil, as he that hath mercy of the Lord, that Y be trewe.
28502	46	7	26	Therfor Y gesse, that this thing is good for the present nede; for it is good to a man to be so.
28503	46	7	27	Thou art boundun to a wijf, nyle thou seke vnbyndyng; thou art vnboundun fro a wijf, nyle thou seke a wijf.
28504	46	7	28	But if thou hast takun a wijf, thou hast not synned; and if a maidun is weddid, sche synnede not; nethelesse siche schulen haue tribulacioun of fleisch.
28505	46	7	29	But Y spare you. Therfor, britheren, Y seie this thing, The tyme is schort. Another is this, that thei that han wyues, be as thouy thei hadden noon;
28506	46	7	30	and thei that wepen, as thei wepten not; and thei that ioien, as thei ioieden not; and thei that bien, as thei hadden not;
28507	46	7	31	and thei that vsen this world, as thei that vsen not. For whi the figure of this world passith.
28508	46	7	32	But Y wole, that ye be without bisynesse, for he that is without wijf, is bisi what thingis ben of the Lord, hou he schal plese God.
28509	46	7	33	But he that is with a wijf, is bysy what thingis ben of the world, hou he schal plese the wijf, and he is departid.
28510	46	7	34	And a womman vnweddid and maidun thenkith what thingis ben of the Lord, that sche be hooli in bodi and spirit. But sche that is weddid, thenkith what thingis ben of the world, hou sche schal plese the hosebonde.
28511	46	7	35	And Y seie these thingis to youre profit, not that Y caste to you a snare, but to that that is onest, and that yyueth esynesse, with outen lettyng to make preieris to the Lord.
28512	46	7	36	And if ony man gessith hym silf to be seyn foule on his virgyn, that sche is ful woxun, and so it bihoueth to be doon, do sche that that sche wole; sche synneth not, if sche be weddid.
28513	46	7	37	For he that ordeynede stabli in his herte, not hauynge nede, but hauynge power of his wille, and hath demed in his herte this thing, to kepe his virgyn, doith wel.
28514	46	7	38	Therfore he that ioyneth his virgyn in matrymonye, doith wel; and he that ioyneth not, doith betere.
28515	46	7	39	The womman is boundun to the lawe, as longe tyme as hir hosebonde lyueth; and if hir hosebonde is deed, sche is delyuered fro the lawe of the hosebonde, be sche weddid to whom sche wole, oneli in the Lord.
28516	46	7	40	But sche schal be more blessid, if sche dwellith thus, aftir my counsel; and Y wene, that Y haue the Spirit of God.
28517	46	8	1	But of these thingis that ben sacrified to ydols, we witen, for alle we han kunnyng. But kunnyng blowith, charite edefieth.
28518	46	8	2	But if ony man gessith, that he kan ony thing, he hath not yit knowe hou it bihoueth hym to kunne.
28519	46	8	3	And if ony man loueth God, this is knowun of hym.
28520	46	8	4	But of metis that ben offrid to idols, we witen, that an idol is no thing in the world, and that ther is no God but oon.
28521	46	8	5	For thouy ther ben summe that ben seid goddis, ethir in heuene, ether in erthe, as ther ben many goddis, and many lordis;
28522	46	8	6	netheles to vs is o God, the fadir, of whom ben alle thingis, and we in hym; and o Lord Jhesu Crist, bi whom ben alle thingis, and we bi hym.
28523	46	8	7	But not in alle men is kunnyng. For summen with conscience of ydol til now eten as thing offrid to idolis; and her conscience is defoulid, for it is sijk.
28524	46	8	8	Mete comendith vs not to God; for nether we schulen faile, if we eten not, nether if we eten, we schulen haue plente.
28525	46	8	9	But se ye, lest perauenture this your leeue be maad hurtyng to sijke men.
28526	46	8	10	For if ony man schal se hym, that hath kunnyng, etynge in a place where idols ben worschipid, whethir his conscience, sithen it is sijke, schal not be edified to ete thingis offrid to idols?
28527	46	8	11	And the sijk brothir, for whom Crist diede, schal perische in thi kunnyng.
28528	46	8	12	For thus ye synnyng ayens britheren, and smytynge her sijk conscience synnen ayens Crist.
28529	46	8	13	Wherfor if mete sclaundrith my brother, Y schal neuere ete fleisch, lest Y sclaundre my brothir.
28530	46	9	1	Whether Y am not fre? Am Y not apostle? Whether Y saiy not `Crist Jhesu, `oure Lord? Whether ye ben not my werk in the Lord?
28531	46	9	2	And thouy to othere Y am not apostle, but netheles to you Y am; for ye ben the litle signe of myn apostlehed in the Lord.
28532	46	9	3	My defense to hem that axen me, that is.
28533	46	9	4	Whether we han not power to ete and drynke?
28534	46	9	5	Whether we han not power to lede aboute a womman a sistir, as also othere apostlis, and britheren of the Lord, and Cefas?
28535	46	9	6	Or Y aloone and Barnabas han not power to worche these thingis?
28536	46	9	7	Who traueilith ony tyme with hise owne wagis? Who plauntith a vynyerd, and etith not of his fruyt? Who kepith a flok, and etith not of the mylk of the flok?
28537	46	9	8	Whether aftir man Y sey these thingis? whether also the lawe seith not these thingis?
28538	46	9	9	For it is writun in the lawe of Moises, Thou schalt not bynde the mouth of the ox threischynge. Whethir of oxun is charge to God?
28539	46	9	10	Whether for vs he seith these thingis? For whi tho ben writun for vs; for he that erith, owith to ere in hope, and he that threischith, in hope to take fruytis.
28540	46	9	11	If we sowen spiritual thingis to you, is it grete, if we repen youre fleischli thingis?
28541	46	9	12	If othere ben parteneris of youre power, whi not rathere we? But we vsen not this power, but we suffren alle thingis, that we yyuen no lettyng to the euangelie of Crist.
28542	46	9	13	Witen ye not, that thei that worchen in the temple, eten tho thingis that ben of the temple, and thei that seruen to the auter, ben partyneris of the auter?
28543	46	9	14	So the Lord ordeynede to hem that tellen the gospel, to lyue of the gospel.
28544	46	9	15	But Y vside noon of these thingis; sotheli Y wroot not these thingis, that tho be don so in me; for it is good `to me rather to die, than that ony man `auoyde my glorie.
28545	46	9	16	For if Y preche the gospel, glorie is not to me, for nedelich Y mot don it; for wo to me, if Y preche not the gospel.
28546	46	9	17	But if Y do this thing wilfuli, Y haue mede; but if ayens my wille, dispending is bitakun to me.
28547	46	9	18	What thanne is my mede? That Y prechynge the gospel, putte the gospel with outen otheris cost, that Y vse not my power in the gospel.
28548	46	9	19	Forwhi whanne Y was fre of alle men, Y made me seruaunt of alle men, to wynne the mo men.
28549	46	9	20	And to Jewis Y am maad as a Jew, to wynne the Jewis; to hem that ben vndur the lawe,
28550	46	9	21	as Y were vndur the lawe, whanne Y was not vndur the lawe, to wynne hem that weren vndur the lawe; to hem that weren with out lawe, as Y were with out lawe, whanne Y was not with out the lawe of God, but Y was in the lawe of Crist, to wynne hem that weren with out lawe.
28551	46	9	22	Y am maad sijk to sike men, to wynne sike men; to alle men Y am maad alle thingis, to make alle men saaf.
28552	46	9	23	But Y do alle thingis for the gospel, that Y be maad partener of it.
28553	46	9	24	Witen ye not, that thei that rennen in a furlong, alle rennen, but oon takith the prijs? So renne ye, that ye catche.
28554	46	9	25	Ech man that stryueth in fiyt, absteyneth hym fro alle thingis; and thei, that thei take a corruptible coroun, but we an vncorrupt.
28555	46	9	26	Therfor Y renne so, not as `in to vncerteyn thing; thus Y fiyte, not as betynge the eir;
28556	46	9	27	but Y chastise my bodi, and bryng it in to seruage; lest perauenture whanne Y preche to othere, Y my silf be maad repreuable.
28557	46	10	1	Britheren, Y nyle, that ye vnknowe, that alle oure fadris weren vndur cloude, and alle passiden the see;
28558	46	10	2	and alle weren baptisid in Moises, in the cloude and in the see;
28559	46	10	3	and alle eeten the same spiritual mete,
28560	46	10	4	and alle drunken the same spiritual drynke; thei drunken of the spiritual stoon folewynge hem; and the stoon was Crist.
28561	46	10	5	But not in ful manye of hem it was wel pleasaunt to God; for whi thei weren cast doun in desert.
28562	46	10	6	But these thingis ben don in figure of vs, that we be not coueyteris of yuele thingis, as thei coueitiden.
28563	46	10	7	Nether be ye maad idolatreris, as summe of hem; as it is writun, The puple sat to ete and drynke, and thei risen vp to pleie.
28564	46	10	8	Nether do we fornycacioun, as summe of hem diden fornicacioun, and thre and twenti thousyndis weren deed in o dai.
28565	46	10	9	Nethir tempte we Crist, as summe of hem temptiden, and perischiden of serpentis.
28566	46	10	10	Nether grutche ye, as summe of hem grutchiden, and thei perischiden of a distrier.
28567	46	10	11	And alle these thingis felliden to hem in figure; but thei ben writun to oure amendyng, in to whiche the endis of the worldis ben comun.
28568	46	10	12	Therfor he that gessith hym, `that he stondith, se he, that he falle not.
28569	46	10	13	Temptacioun take `not you, but mannus temptacioun; for God is trewe, which schal not suffre you to be temptid aboue that that ye moun; but he schal make with temptacioun also purueyaunce, that ye moun suffre.
28570	46	10	14	Wherfor, ye most dereworthe to me, fle ye fro worschiping of maumetis.
28571	46	10	15	As to prudent men Y speke, deme ye you silf that thing that Y seie.
28572	46	10	16	Whether the cuppe of blessyng which we blessen, is not the comynyng of Cristis blood? and whether the breed which we breken, is not the takyng of the bodi of the Lord?
28573	46	10	17	For we manye ben o breed and o bodi, alle we that taken part of o breed and of o cuppe.
28574	46	10	18	Se ye Israel aftir the fleisch, whethir thei that eeten sacrifices, ben not partyneris of the auter?
28575	46	10	19	What therfor seie Y, that a thing that is offrid to idols is ony thing, or that the idol is ony thing?
28576	46	10	20	But tho thingis that hethene men offren, thei offren to deuelis, and not to God. But Y nyle, that ye ben maad felowis of feendis; for ye moun not drynke the cuppe of the Lord, and the cuppe of fendis;
28577	46	10	21	ye moun not be parteneris of the boord of the Lord, and of the bord of feendis.
28578	46	10	22	Whether we han enuye to the Lord? whether we ben strengere then he? Alle thingis ben leeueful to me, but not alle thingis ben spedeful.
28579	46	10	23	Alle thingis ben leeueful to me, but not alle thingis edifien.
28580	46	10	24	No man seke that thing that is his owne, but that thing that is of an othere.
28581	46	10	25	Al thing that is seld in the bocherie, ete ye, axynge no thing for conscience.
28582	46	10	26	The erthe and the plente of it is, the Lordis.
28583	46	10	27	If ony of hethene men clepith you to soper, and ye wole go, al thing that is set to you, ete ye, axynge no thing for conscience.
28584	46	10	28	But if ony man seith, This thing is offrid to idols, nyle ye ete, for hym that schewide, and for conscience; and Y seie not,
28585	46	10	29	thi conscience, but of an othere. But wherto is my fredom demed of an othere mannus conscience?
28586	46	10	30	Therfor if Y take part with grace, what am Y blasfemed, for that that Y do thankyngis?
28587	46	10	31	Therfor whether ye eten, or drynken, or don ony other thing, do ye alle thingis `in to the glorie of God.
28588	46	10	32	Be ye with outen sclaundre to Jewis, and to hethene men, and to the chirche of God;
28589	46	10	33	as Y bi alle thingis plese to alle men, not sekynge that that is profitable to me, but that that is profitable to manye men, that thei be maad saaf.
28590	46	11	1	Be ye my foleweris, as Y am of Crist.
28591	46	11	2	And, britheren, Y preise you, that bi alle thingis ye ben myndeful of me; and as Y bitook to you my comaundementis, ye holden.
28592	46	11	3	But Y wole that ye wite, that Crist is heed of ech man; but the heed of the womman is the man; and the heed of Crist is God.
28593	46	11	4	Ech man preiynge, or profeciynge, whanne his heed is hilid, defoulith his heed.
28594	46	11	5	But ech womman preiynge, or profeciynge, whanne hir heed is not hilid, defoulith hir heed; for it is oon, as if sche were pollid.
28595	46	11	6	And if a womman be not keuered, be sche pollid; and if it is foul thing to a womman to be pollid, or to be maad ballid, hile sche hir heed.
28596	46	11	7	But a man schal not hile his heed, for he is the ymage and the glorie of God; but a womman is the glorie of man.
28597	46	11	8	For a man is not of the womman, but the womman of the man.
28598	46	11	9	And the man is not maad for the womman, but the womman for the man.
28599	46	11	10	Therfor the womman schal haue an hilyng on hir heed, also for aungelis.
28600	46	11	11	Netheles nether the man is with outen womman, nether the womman is with oute man, in the Lord.
28601	46	11	12	Forwhi as the womman is of man, so the man is bi the womman; but alle thingis ben of God.
28602	46	11	13	Deme ye you silf; bisemeth it a womman not hilid on the heed to preye God?
28603	46	11	14	Nether the kynde it silf techith vs, for if a man nursche longe heer, it is schenschipe to hym;
28604	46	11	15	but if a womman nurische longe heer, it is glorie to hir, for heeris ben youun to hir for keueryng.
28605	46	11	16	But if ony man is seyn to be ful of strijf, we han noon siche custom, nethir the chirche of God.
28606	46	11	17	But this thing Y comaunde, not preisynge, that ye comen togidere not in to the betere, but in to the worse.
28607	46	11	18	First for whanne ye comen togidere in to the chirche, Y here that discenciouns ben, and in parti Y bileue.
28608	46	11	19	For it bihoueth eresies to be, that thei that ben prouyd, ben opynli knowun in you.
28609	46	11	20	Therfor whanne ye comen togidere in to oon, now it is not to ete the Lordis soper;
28610	46	11	21	for whi ech man bifor takith his soper to ete, and oon is hungry, and another is drunkun.
28611	46	11	22	Whether ye han not housis to ete and drynke, or ye dispisen the chirche of God, and confounden hem that han noon? What schal Y seie to you? Y preise you, but here yn Y preise you not.
28612	46	11	23	For Y haue takun of the Lord that thing, which Y haue bitakun to you. For the Lord Jhesu, in what niyt he was bitraied,
28613	46	11	24	took breed, and dide thankyngis, and brak, and seide, Take ye, and ete ye; this is my bodi, which schal be bitraied for you; do ye this thing in to my mynde.
28614	46	11	25	Also the cuppe, aftir that he hadde soupid, and seide, This cuppe is the newe testament in my blood; do ye this thing, as ofte as ye schulen drynke, in to my mynde.
28615	46	11	26	For as ofte as ye schulen ete this breed, and schulen drynke the cuppe, ye schulen telle the deth of the Lord, til that he come.
28616	46	11	27	Therfor who euere etith the breed, or drynkith the cuppe of the Lord vnworthili, he schal be gilti of the bodi and of the blood of the Lord.
28617	46	11	28	But preue a man hym silf, and so ete he of `the ilke breed, and drynke of the cuppe.
28618	46	11	29	For he that etith and drinkith vnworthili, etith and drinkith doom to hym, not wiseli demyng the bodi of the Lord.
28619	46	11	30	Therfor among you many ben sijke and feble, and manye slepen.
28620	46	11	31	And if we demyden wiseli vs silf, we schulden not be demyd;
28621	46	11	32	but while we ben demyd of the Lord, we ben chastisid, that we be not dampnyd with this world.
28622	46	11	33	Therfor, my britheren, whanne ye comen togidere to ete, abide ye togidere.
28623	46	11	34	If ony man hungrith, ete he at home, that ye come not togidere in to doom. And Y schal dispose othere thingis, whanne Y come.
28624	46	12	1	But of spiritual thingis, britheren, Y nyle that ye vnknowun.
28625	46	12	2	For ye witen, that whanne ye weren hethene men, hou ye weren led goynge to doumbe maumetis.
28626	46	12	3	Therfor Y make knowun to you, that no man spekynge in the spirit of God, seith departyng fro Jhesu; and no man may seie the Lord Jhesu, but in the Hooli Goost.
28627	46	12	4	And dyuerse graces ther ben, but it is al oon Spirit;
28628	46	12	5	and dyuerse seruyces ther ben, but it is al oon Lord; and dyuerse worchingis ther ben,
28629	46	12	6	but `al is oon God, that worchith alle thingis in alle thingis.
28630	46	12	7	And to ech man the schewyng of spirit is youun to profit. The word of wisdom is youun to oon bi spirit;
28631	46	12	8	to another the word of kunnyng, bi the same spirit;
28632	46	12	9	feith to another, in the same spirit; to anothere, grace of helthis, in o spirit;
28633	46	12	10	to another, the worchyng of vertues; to another, profecie; to another, very knowyng of spiritis; to another, kyndis of langagis; to another, expownyng of wordis.
28634	46	12	11	And oon and the same spirit worchith alle these thingis, departynge to ech bi hem silf as he wole.
28635	46	12	12	For as ther is o body, and hath many membris, and alle the membris of the bodi whanne tho ben manye, ben o bodi, so also Crist.
28636	46	12	13	For in o spirit alle we ben baptisid `in to o bodi, ether Jewis, ether hethene, ether seruauntis, ether free; and alle we ben fillid with drink in o spirit.
28637	46	12	14	For the bodi is not o membre, but manye.
28638	46	12	15	If the foot seith, For Y am not the hoond, Y am not of the bodi; not therfor it is not of the bodi.
28639	46	12	16	And if the ere seith, For Y am not the iye, Y am not of the bodi; not therfor it is not of the bodi.
28640	46	12	17	If al the bodi is the iye, where is heryng? and if al the bodi is heryng, where is smellyng?
28641	46	12	18	But now God hath set membris, and ech of hem in the bodi, as he wolde.
28642	46	12	19	That if alle weren o membre, where were the bodi?
28643	46	12	20	But now ther ben many membris, but o bodi.
28644	46	12	21	And the iye may not seie to the hond, Y haue no nede to thi werkis; or eft the heed to the feet, Ye ben not necessarie to me.
28645	46	12	22	But myche more tho that ben seyn to be the lowere membris of the bodi, ben more nedeful;
28646	46	12	23	and thilke that we gessen to be the vnworthier membris of the bodi, we yyuen more honour `to hem; and tho membris that ben vnonest, han more oneste.
28647	46	12	24	For oure oneste membris han nede of noon; but God tempride the bodi, yyuynge more worschip to it, to whom it failide,
28648	46	12	25	that debate be not in the bodi, but that the membris be bisi in to the same thing ech for othere.
28649	46	12	26	And if o membre suffrith ony thing, alle membris suffren therwith; ethir if o membre ioieth, alle membris ioien togidere.
