28650	46	12	27	And ye ben the bodi of Crist, and membris of membre.
28651	46	12	28	But God sette sum men in the chirche, fyrst apostlis, the secunde tyme prophetis, the thridde techeris, aftirward vertues, aftirward graces of heelyngis, helpyngis, gouernails, kyndis of langagis, interpretaciouns of wordis.
28652	46	12	29	Whether alle apostlis? whethir alle prophetis? whether alle techeris? whether alle vertues?
28653	46	12	30	whether alle men han grace of heelyngis? whether alle speken with langagis? whether alle expownen?
28654	46	12	31	But sue ye the betere goostli yiftis. And yit Y schewe to you a more exellent weye.
28655	46	13	1	If Y speke with tungis of men and of aungels, and Y haue not charite, Y am maad as bras sownynge, or a cymbal tynkynge.
28656	46	13	2	And if Y haue prophecie, and knowe alle mysteries, and al kunnynge, and if Y haue al feith, so that Y meue hillis fro her place, and Y haue not charite, Y am nouyt.
28657	46	13	3	And if Y departe alle my goodis in to the metis of pore men, and yf Y bitake my bodi, so that Y brenne, and if Y haue not charite, it profitith to me no thing.
28658	46	13	4	Charite is pacient, it is benygne; charite enuyeth not, it doith not wickidli, it is not blowun,
28659	46	13	5	it is not coueytouse, it sekith not tho thingis that ben hise owne, it is not stirid to wraththe, it thenkith not yuel,
28660	46	13	6	it ioyeth not on wickidnesse, but it ioieth togidere to treuthe;
28661	46	13	7	it suffrith alle thingis, it bileueth alle thingis, it hopith alle thingis, it susteyneth alle thingis.
28662	46	13	8	Charite fallith neuere doun, whether prophecies schulen be voidid, ethir langagis schulen ceesse, ethir science schal be distried.
28663	46	13	9	For a parti we knowun, and a parti we prophecien;
28664	46	13	10	but whanne that schal come that is parfit, that thing that is of parti schal be auoidid.
28665	46	13	11	Whanne Y was a litil child, Y spak as a litil child, Y vndurstood as a litil child, Y thouyte as a litil child; but whanne Y was maad a man, Y auoidide tho thingis that weren of a litil child.
28666	46	13	12	And we seen now bi a myrour in derknesse, but thanne face to face; now Y knowe of parti, but thanne Y schal knowe, as Y am knowun.
28667	46	13	13	And now dwellen feith, hope, and charite, these thre; but the most of these is charite.
28668	46	14	1	Sue ye charite, loue ye spiritual thingis, but more that ye prophecien.
28669	46	14	2	And he that spekith in tunge, spekith not to men, but to God; for no man herith. But the spirit spekith mysteries.
28670	46	14	3	For he that prophecieth, spekith to men to edificacioun, and monestyng, and coumfortyng.
28671	46	14	4	He that spekith in tunge, edifieth hym silf; but he that prophecieth, edifieth the chirche of God.
28672	46	14	5	And Y wole, that alle ye speke in tungis, but more that ye prophecie. For he that prophecieth, is more than he that spekith in langagis; but perauenture he expoune, that the chirche take edificacioun.
28673	46	14	6	But now, britheren, if Y come to you, and speke in langagis, what schal Y profite to you, but if Y speke to you ethir in reuelacioun, ethir in science, ethir in prophecie, ether in techyng?
28674	46	14	7	For tho thingis that ben withouten soule, and yyueth voices, ethir pipe, ether harpe, but tho yyuen distinccioun of sownyngis, hou schal it be knowun that is sungun, ether that that is trumpid?
28675	46	14	8	For if a trumpe yyue an vncerteyn soune, who schal make hym silf redi to batel?
28676	46	14	9	So but ye yyuen an opyn word bi tunge, hou schal that that is seid be knowun? For ye schulen be spekynge in veyn.
28677	46	14	10	There ben many kyndis of langagis in this world, and no thing is with outen vois.
28678	46	14	11	But if Y knowe not the vertu of a vois, Y schal be to hym, to whom Y schal speke, a barbarik; and he that spekith to me, schal be a barbarik.
28679	46	14	12	So ye, for ye ben loueris of spiritis, seke ye that ye be plenteuouse to edificacioun of the chirche.
28680	46	14	13	And therfor he that spekith in langage, preie, that he expowne.
28681	46	14	14	For if Y preye in tunge, my spirit preieth; myn vndurstondyng is with outen fruyt.
28682	46	14	15	What thanne? Y schal preye in spirit, Y schal preye in mynde; Y schal seie salm, in spirit, Y schal seie salm also in mynde.
28683	46	14	16	For if thou blessist in spirit, who fillith the place of an ydiot, hou schal he seie Amen on thi blessyng, for he woot not, what thou seist?
28684	46	14	17	For thou doist wel thankyngis, but an othir man is not edefied.
28685	46	14	18	Y thanke my God, for Y speke in the langage of alle you;
28686	46	14	19	but in the chirche Y wole speke fyue wordis in my wit, that also Y teche othere men, than ten thousynde of wordis in tunge.
28687	46	14	20	Britheren, nyle ye be maad children in wittis, but in malice be ye children; but in wittis be ye parfit.
28688	46	14	21	For in the lawe it is writun, That in othere tungis and othere lippis Y schal speke to this puple, and nether so thei schulen here me, seith the Lord.
28689	46	14	22	Therfor langagis ben in to tokene, not to feithful men, but to men out of the feith; but prophecies ben not to men out of the feith, but to feithful men.
28690	46	14	23	Therfor if alle the chirche come togidere in to oon, and alle men speken in tungis, if idiotis, ether men out of the feith, entren, whether thei schulen not seie, What ben ye woode?
28691	46	14	24	But if alle men prophecien, if ony vnfeithful man or idiot entre, he is conuyct of alle, he is wiseli demyd of alle.
28692	46	14	25	For the hid thingis of his herte ben knowun, and so he schal falle doun on the face, and schal worschipe God, and schewe verili that God is in you.
28693	46	14	26	What thanne, britheren? Whanne ye comen togidere, ech of you hath a salm, he hath techyng, he hath apocalips, he hath tunge, he hath expownyng; alle thingis be thei don to edificacioun.
28694	46	14	27	Whether a man spekith in tunge, bi twei men, ethir thre at the moste, and bi partis, that oon interprete.
28695	46	14	28	But if there be not an interpretour, be he stille in the chirche, and speke he to hym silf and to God.
28696	46	14	29	Prophetis tweine or thre seie, and othere wiseli deme.
28697	46	14	30	But if ony thing be schewid to a sittere, the formere be stille.
28698	46	14	31	For ye moun `prophecie alle, ech bi hym silf, that alle men lerne, and alle moneste.
28699	46	14	32	And the spiritis of prophetis ben suget to prophetis;
28700	46	14	33	for whi God is not of discencioun, but of pees; as in alle chirchis of hooli men `Y teche.
28701	46	14	34	Wymmen in chirchis be stille; for it is not suffrid to hem to speke, but to be suget, as the lawe seith.
28702	46	14	35	But if thei wolen ony thing lerne, `at home axe thei her hosebondis; for it is foule thing to a womman to speke in chirche.
28703	46	14	36	Whether `of you the word of God cam forth, or to you aloone it cam?
28704	46	14	37	If ony man is seyn to be a prophete, or spiritual, knowe he tho thingis that Y write to you, for tho ben the comaundementis of the Lord.
28705	46	14	38	And if ony man vnknowith, he schal be vnknowun.
28706	46	14	39	`Therfor, britheren, loue ye to prophecie, and nyle ye forbede to speke in tungis.
28707	46	14	40	But be alle thingis don onestli, and bi due ordre in you.
28708	46	15	1	`Sotheli, britheren, Y make the gospel knowun to you, which Y haue prechid to you, the which also ye han takun, in which ye stonden,
28709	46	15	2	also bi which ye schulen be sauyd; `bi which resoun Y haue prechid to you, if ye holden, `if ye han not bileuyd ideli.
28710	46	15	3	For Y bitook to you at the bigynnyng that thing which also Y haue resseyued; that Crist was deed for oure synnes, bi the scripturis;
28711	46	15	4	and that he was biried, and that he roos ayen in the thridde dai, after scripturis;
28712	46	15	5	and that he was seyn to Cephas, and aftir these thingis to enleuene;
28713	46	15	6	aftirward he was seyn to mo than fyue hundrid britheren togidere, of whiche manye lyuen yit, but summe ben deed; aftirward he was seyn to James,
28714	46	15	7	and aftirward to alle the apostlis.
28715	46	15	8	And last of alle he was seyn also to me, as to a deed borun child.
28716	46	15	9	For Y am the leste of apostlis, that am not worthi to be clepid apostle, for Y pursuede the chirche of God.
28717	46	15	10	But bi the grace of God Y am that thing that Y am; and his grace was not voide in me. For Y trauelide more plenteuously than alle thei; but not Y, but the grace of God with me.
28718	46	15	11	But whether Y, or thei, so we han prechid, and so ye han bileuyd.
28719	46	15	12	And if Crist is prechid, that he roos ayen fro deeth, hou seien summen among you, that the ayenrisyng of deed men is not?
28720	46	15	13	And if the ayenrisyng of deed men is not, nethir Crist roos ayen fro deeth.
28721	46	15	14	And if Crist roos not, oure preching is veyn, oure feith is veyn.
28722	46	15	15	And we ben foundun false witnessis of God, for we han seid witnessyng ayens God, that he reiside Crist, whom he reiside not, if deed men risen not ayen.
28723	46	15	16	Forwhi if deed men risen not ayen, nether Crist roos ayen;
28724	46	15	17	and if Crist roos not ayen, oure feith is veyn; and yit ye ben in youre synnes.
28725	46	15	18	And thanne thei that han diede in Crist, han perischid.
28726	46	15	19	If in this life oneli we ben hoping in Crist, we ben more wretchis than alle men.
28727	46	15	20	But now Crist roos ayen fro deth, the firste fruit of deed men;
28728	46	15	21	for deeth was bi a man, and bi a man is ayenrisyng fro deth.
28729	46	15	22	And as in Adam alle men dien, so in Crist alle men schulen be quykenyd.
28730	46	15	23	But ech man in his ordre; the firste fruit, Crist, afterward thei that ben of Crist, that bileueden in the comyng of Crist;
28731	46	15	24	aftirward an ende, whanne he schal bitake the kyngdom to God and to the fadir, whanne he schal auoide al princehod, and power, and vertu.
28732	46	15	25	But it bihoueth hym to regne, til he putte alle hise enemyes vndur hise feet.
28733	46	15	26	And at the laste, deth the enemye schal be distried; for he hath maad suget alle thingis vndur hise feet.
28734	46	15	27	And whanne he seith, alle thingis ben suget to hym, with outen doubt outakun hym that sugetide alle thingis to hym.
28735	46	15	28	And whanne alle thingis ben suget to hym, thanne the sone hym silf schal be suget to hym, that made `alle thingis suget to hym, that God be alle thingis in alle thingis.
28736	46	15	29	Ellis what schulen thei do, that ben baptisid for deed men, if in no wise deed men risen ayen? wherto ben thei baptisid for hem?
28737	46	15	30	And wherto ben we in perel euery our?
28738	46	15	31	Ech dai Y die for youre glorie, britheren, which glorie Y haue in Crist Jhesu oure Lord.
28739	46	15	32	If aftir man Y haue fouyten to beestis at Efesi, what profitith it to me, if deed men risen not ayen? Ete we, and drynke we, for we schulen die to morewe.
28740	46	15	33	Nyle ye be disseyued; for yuel spechis distrien good thewis.
28741	46	15	34	Awake ye, iuste men, and nyle ye do synne; for summen han ignoraunce of God, but to reuerence Y speke to you.
28742	46	15	35	But summan seith, Hou schulen deed men rise ayen, or in what maner bodi schulen thei come?
28743	46	15	36	Vnwise man, that thing that thou sowist, is not quykened, but it die first;
28744	46	15	37	and that thing that thou sowist, `thou sowist not the bodi that is to come, but a nakid corn, as of whete, or of summe othere seedis;
28745	46	15	38	and God yyueth to it a bodi, as he wole, and to ech of seedis a propir bodi.
28746	46	15	39	Not ech fleisch is the same fleisch, but oon is of men, another is of beestis, another is of briddis, an othere of fischis.
28747	46	15	40	And `heuenli bodies ben, and `ertheli bodies ben; but oon glorie is of heuenely bodies, and anothir is of ertheli.
28748	46	15	41	An othere clerenesse is of the sunne, anothere clerenesse is of the moone, and anothere clerenesse is of sterris; and a sterre dyuersith fro a sterre in clerenesse.
28749	46	15	42	And so the ayenrisyng of deed men. It is sowun in corrupcioun, it schal rise in vncorrupcioun;
28750	46	15	43	it is sowun in vnnoblei, it schal rise in glorie; it is sowun in infirmyte, it schal rise in vertu;
28751	46	15	44	it is sowun a beestly bodi, it schal rise a spiritual bodi. If ther is a beestli bodi, ther is also a spiritual bodi;
28752	46	15	45	as it is writun, The firste man Adam was maad in to a soule lyuynge, the laste Adam in to a spirit quykenynge.
28753	46	15	46	But the firste is not that that is spiritual, but that that is beestlich, aftirward that that is spiritual.
28754	46	15	47	The firste man of erthe is ertheli; the secounde man of heuene is heuenelich.
28755	46	15	48	Such as the ertheli man is, such ben the ertheli men; and such as the heueneli man is, suche ben also the heueneli men.
28756	46	15	49	Therfor as we han bore the ymage of the ertheli man, bere we also the ymage of the heuenli.
28757	46	15	50	Britheren, Y seie this thing, that fleisch and bloud moun not welde the kyngdom of God, nethir corrupcioun schal welde vncorrupcioun.
28758	46	15	51	Lo! Y seie to you priuyte of hooli thingis. And alle we schulen rise ayen, but not alle we schulen be chaungid;
28759	46	15	52	in a moment, in the twynklyng of an iye, in the laste trumpe; for the trumpe schal sowne, and deed men schulen rise ayen, with oute corrupcioun, and we schulen be chaungid.
28760	46	15	53	For it byhoueth this corruptible thing to clothe vncorrupcioun, and this deedli thing to putte awei vndeedlinesse.
28761	46	15	54	But whanne this deedli thing schal clothe vndeedlynesse, thanne schal the word be doon, that is writun, Deth is sopun vp in victorie.
28762	46	15	55	Deth, where is thi victorie? Deth, where is thi pricke?
28763	46	15	56	But the pricke of deth is synne; and the vertu of synne is the lawe.
28764	46	15	57	But do we thankyngis to God, that yaf to vs victorie bi oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28765	46	15	58	Therfore, my dereworthe britheren, be ye stidefast, and vnmouable, beynge plenteuouse in werk of the Lord, euere more witynge that youre trauel is not idel in the Lord.
28766	46	16	1	But of the gaderyngis of money that ben maad in to seyntis, as Y ordeynede in the chirchis of Galathie, so also do ye o dai of the wouke.
28767	46	16	2	Ech of you kepe at hym silf, kepynge that that plesith to him, that whanne Y come, the gaderyngis ben not maad.
28768	46	16	3	And whanne Y schal be present, whiche men ye preuen, Y schal sende hem bi epistlis to bere youre grace in to Jerusalem.
28769	46	16	4	That if it be worthi that also Y go, thei schulen go with me.
28770	46	16	5	But Y schal come to you, whanne Y schal passe bi Macedonye; for whi Y schal passe bi Macedonye.
28771	46	16	6	But perauenture Y schal dwelle at you, or also dwelle the wynter, that and ye lede me whidir euere Y schal go.
28772	46	16	7	And Y wole not now se you in my passyng, for Y hope to dwelle with you awhile, if the Lord schal suffre.
28773	46	16	8	But Y schal dwelle at Efesi, `til to Witsuntide.
28774	46	16	9	For a grete dore and an opyn is openyd to me, and many aduersaries.
28775	46	16	10	And if Thimothe come, se ye that he be with out drede with you, for he worcheth the werk of the Lord, as Y.
28776	46	16	11	Therfor no man dispise hym; but lede ye hym forth in pees, that he come to me; for Y abide hym with britheren.
28777	46	16	12	But, britheren, Y make knowun to you of Apollo, that Y preiede him myche, that he schulde come to you, with britheren. But it was not his wille to come now; but he schal come, whanne he schal haue leiser.
28778	46	16	13	Walke ye, and stonde ye in the feith; do ye manli, and be ye coumfortid in the Lord,
28779	46	16	14	and be alle youre thingis don in charite.
28780	46	16	15	And, britheren, Y biseche you, ye knowen the hous of Stephan, and of Fortunati, and Acaicy, for thei ben the firste fruytis of Acaie, and in to mynystrie of seyntis thei han ordeyned hem silf;
28781	46	16	16	that also ye be sugetis to suche, and to ech worchynge togidere and trauelynge.
28782	46	16	17	For Y haue ioie in the presence of Stephan, and of Fortunate, and Acaici;
28783	46	16	18	for thei filliden that thing that failide to you; for thei han refreischid bothe my spirit and youre. Therfor knowe ye hem, that ben suche maner men.
28784	46	16	19	Alle the chirchis of Asie greten you wel. Aquila and Prisca, with her homeli chirche, greten you myche in the Lord, at the whiche also Y am herborid.
28785	46	16	20	Alle bretheren greten you wel. Grete ye wel togidere in hooli cos.
28786	46	16	21	My gretyng bi Poulis hoond.
28787	46	16	22	If ony man loueth not oure Lord Jhesu Crist, be he cursid, Maranatha.
28788	46	16	23	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with you.
28789	46	16	24	My charite be with you alle in Crist Jhesu oure Lord. Amen.
28790	47	1	1	Poul, apostle of Jhesu Crist, bi the wille of God, and Tymothe, brothir, to the chirche of God that is at Corinthi, with alle seyntis that ben in al Acaie, grace to you,
28791	47	1	2	and pees of God oure fadir and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
28792	47	1	3	Blessid be God and the fadir of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, fadir of mercies, and God of al coumfort,
28793	47	1	4	which coumfortith vs in al oure tribulacioun, that also we moun coumforte hem, that ben in al diseese, bi the monestyng bi which also we ben monestid of God.
28794	47	1	5	For as the passiouns of Crist ben plenteuouse in vs, so also bi Crist oure coumfort is plenteuouse.
28795	47	1	6	And whether we ben in tribulacioun, for youre tribulacioun and heelthe, ethir we ben coumfortid, for youre coumfort, ethir we ben monestid, for youre monestyng and heelthe. Which worchith in you the suffring of the same passiouns, whiche `we also suffren,
28796	47	1	7	that oure hope be sad for you; witynge for as ye ben felowis of passiouns, so ye schulen ben also of coumfort.
28797	47	1	8	For, britheren, we wolen that ye wite of oure tribulacioun, that was don in Asie; for ouer maner we weren greued ouer myyt, so that it anoiede vs, yhe, to lyue.
28798	47	1	9	But we in vs silf hadden answere of deth, that we truste not in vs, but in God that reisith deed men.
28799	47	1	10	Which delyuerede vs, and delyuerith fro so grete perelis, in to whom we hopen, also yit he schal delyuere,
28800	47	1	11	while also ye helpen in preier for vs; that of the persones of many faces of that yyuyng that is in vs, thankyngis ben don for vs bi many men to God.
28801	47	1	12	For oure glorie is this, the witnessyng of oure conscience, that in symplenesse and clennesse of God, and not in fleischli wisdom, but in the grace of God, we lyueden in this world, but more plenteuousli to you.
28802	47	1	13	And we writen not othere thingis to you, than tho that ye han red and knowe, and Y hope that in to the ende ye schulen knowe,
28803	47	1	14	as also ye han knowe vs a parti; for we ben youre glorie, as also ye ben oure in the dai of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
28804	47	1	15	And in this tristyng Y wolde first come to you, that ye schulden haue the secounde grace,
28805	47	1	16	and passe bi you in to Macedonye, and eft fro Macedonye come to you, and of you be led in to Judee.
28806	47	1	17	But whanne Y wolde this thing, whether Y vside vnstidfastnesse, ether tho thingis that Y thenke, Y thenke aftir the fleisch, that at me be, it is and it is not?
28807	47	1	18	But God is trewe, for oure word that was at you is and is not, is not ther ynne, but is is in it.
28808	47	1	19	For whi Jhesus Crist, the sone of God, which is prechid among you bi vs, bi me, and Syluan, and Tymothe, ther was not in hym is and is not, but is was in hym.
28809	47	1	20	For whi hou many euer ben biheestis of God, in thilke is, `that is, ben fillid. And therfor and bi hym we seien amen to God, to oure glorie.
28810	47	1	21	Sotheli it is God that confermeth vs with you in Crist, and the which God anoyntide vs,
28811	47	1	22	and which markide vs, and yaf ernes of the spirit in oure hertis.
28812	47	1	23	For Y clepide God to witnesse ayens my soule, that Y sparynge you cam not ouer to Corynthe; not that we ben lordis of youre feith, but we ben helperis of youre ioye; for thorouy bileue ye stonden.
28813	47	2	1	And Y ordeynede this ilke thing at me, that Y schulde not come eftsoone in heuynes to you.
28814	47	2	2	For if Y make you sori, who is he that gladith me, but he that is soreuful of me?
28815	47	2	3	And this same thing Y wroot to you, that whanne Y come, Y haue not sorewe on sorewe, of the whiche it behofte me to haue ioie. And Y triste in you alle, that my ioye is of alle you.
28816	47	2	4	For of myche tribulacioun and angwisch of herte Y wroot to you by many teeris, not that ye be sori, but that ye wite what charite Y haue more plenteuously in you.
28817	47	2	5	For if ony man hath maad me soreuful, he hath not maad me sorewful but a parti, that Y charge not you alle.
28818	47	2	6	This blamyng that ys maad of manye, suffisith to hym, that is sich oon;
28819	47	2	7	so that ayenward ye rathir foryyuen and coumfort, lest perauenture he that is suche a maner man, be sopun vp bi more grete heuynesse.
28820	47	2	8	For which thing Y biseche you, that ye conferme charite in to hym.
28821	47	2	9	For whi therfor Y wroot this, that Y knowe youre preuyng, whether in alle thingis ye ben obedient.
28822	47	2	10	For to whom ye han foryyuen ony thing, also Y haue foryyue. For Y that that Y foryaf, yif Y foryaf ony thing, haue youun for you in the persone of Crist,
28823	47	2	11	that we be not disseyued of Sathanas; for we knowen hise thouytis.
28824	47	2	12	But whanne Y was comun to Troade for the gospel of Crist, and a dore was opened to me in the Lord,
28825	47	2	13	Y hadde not rest to my spirit, for Y foond not my brother Tite, but Y seide to hem farewel, and Y passide in to Macedonye.
28826	47	2	14	And Y do thankyngis to God, that euere more makith vs to haue victorie in Crist Jhesu, and schewith bi vs the odour of his knowing in ech place;
28827	47	2	15	for we ben the good odour of Crist to God, among these that ben maad saaf, and among these that perischen.
28828	47	2	16	To othere sotheli odour of deth in to deth, but to othere we ben odour of lijf in to lijf. And to these thingis who is so able?
28829	47	2	17	For we ben not as many, that don auoutrie bi the word of God, but we speken of clennesse, as of God, bifor God in Crist.
28830	47	3	1	Bigynnen we therfor eftsoone to preise vs silf? or whether we neden, as summen, pistlis of preisinge to you, or of you?
28831	47	3	2	Ye ben oure pistle, writun in oure hertis, which is knowun and red of alle men,
28832	47	3	3	and maad opyn, for ye ben the pistle of Crist mynystrid of vs, and writun, not with enke, but bi the spirit of the lyuynge God; not in stony tablis, but in fleischli tablis of herte.
28833	47	3	4	For we han such trist bi Crist to God;
28834	47	3	5	not that we ben sufficient to thenke ony thing of vs, as of vs, but oure sufficience is of God.
28835	47	3	6	Which also made vs able mynystris of the newe testament, not bi lettre, but bi spirit; for the lettre sleeth, but the spirit quykeneth.
28836	47	3	7	And if the mynystracioun of deth write bi lettris in stoonys was in glorie, so that the children of Israel myyten not biholde in to the face of Moises, for the glorie of his cheer, which is auoidid,
28837	47	3	8	hou schal not the mynystracioun of the spirit be more in glorie?
28838	47	3	9	For if the mynystracioun of dampnacioun was in glorie, myche more the mynysterie of riytwisnesse is plenteuouse in glorie.
28839	47	3	10	For nether that that was cleer was glorified in this part for the excellent glorie; and if that that is auoidid,
28840	47	3	11	was bi glorie, myche more that that dwellith stille is in glorie.
28841	47	3	12	Therfor we that han suche hope, vsen myche trist;
28842	47	3	13	and not as Moises leide a veil on his face, that the children of Israel schulden not biholde in to his face, which veil is auoidid.
28843	47	3	14	But the wittis of hem ben astonyed; for in to this dai the same veil in reding of the olde testament dwellith not schewid, for it is auoidid in Crist, but in to this dai,
28844	47	3	15	whanne Moises is red, the veil is put on her hertis.
28845	47	3	16	But whanne Israel schal be conuertid to God, the veil schal be don awei.
28846	47	3	17	And the spirit is the Lord; and where the spirit of the Lord is, there is fredom.
28847	47	3	18	And alle we that with open face seen the glorie of the Lord, ben transformed in to the same ymage, fro clerenesse in to clerenesse, as of the spirit of the Lord.
28848	47	4	1	Therfor we that han this admynystracioun, aftir this that we han getun merci,
28849	47	4	2	faile we not, but do we awei the preue thingis of schame, not walkinge in sutil gile, nether doynge auoutrye bi the word of God, but in schewynge of the treuthe comendynge vs silf to ech conscience of men bifor God.
28850	47	4	3	For if also oure gospel is kyuerid, in these that perischen it is kyuerid;
28851	47	4	4	in which God hath blent the soulis of vnfeithful men of this world, that the liytnyng of the gospel of the glorie of Crist, which is the ymage of God, schyne not.
28852	47	4	5	But we prechen not vs silf, but oure Lord Jhesu Crist; and vs youre seruauntis bi Jhesu.
28853	47	4	6	For God, that seide liyt to schyne of derknessis, he hath youe liyt in oure hertis, to the liytnyng of the science of the clerenesse of God, in the face of Jhesu Crist.
28854	47	4	7	And we han this tresour in britil vessels, that the worthinesse be of Goddis vertu, and not of vs.
28855	47	4	8	In alle thingis we suffren tribulacioun, but we ben not angwischid, or annoyed; we ben maad pore, but `we lacken nothing; we suffren persecucioun,
28856	47	4	9	but we ben not forsakun; we ben maad lowe, but we ben not confoundid; we ben cast doun, but we perischen not.
28857	47	4	10	And euere more we beren aboute the sleyng of Jhesu in oure bodi, that also the lijf of Jhesu be schewid in oure bodies.
28858	47	4	11	For euere more we that lyuen, ben takun in to deth for Jhesu, that the lijf of Jhesu be schewid in oure deedli fleisch.
28859	47	4	12	Therfor deth worchith in vs, but lijf worchith in you.
28860	47	4	13	And we han the same spirit of feith, as it is writun, Y haue bileuyd, Y haue spoke; and we bileuen, wherfor also we speken;
28861	47	4	14	witynge that he that reiside Jhesu, schal reise also vs with Jhesu, and schal ordeyne with you.
28862	47	4	15	And alle thingis for you, that a plenteuouse grace bi many thankyngis be plenteuouse in to the glorie of God.
28863	47	4	16	For which thing we failen not, for thouy oure vtter man be corruptid; netheles the ynner man is renewid fro dai to dai.
28864	47	4	17	But that liyt thing of oure tribulacioun that lastith now, but as it were by a moment, worchith in vs ouer mesure an euerlastynge birthin in to the heiynesse of glorie;
28865	47	4	18	while that we biholden not tho thingis that ben seyn, but tho that ben not seyn. For tho thingis that ben seyn, ben but durynge for a schort tyme; but tho thingis that ben not seyn, ben euerlastynge.
28866	47	5	1	And we witen, that if oure ertheli hous of this dwellynge be dissoluyd, that we han a bildyng of God, an hous not maad bi hondis, euerlastynge in heuenes.
28867	47	5	2	For whi in this thing we mornen, coueitynge to be clothid aboue with oure dwellyng, which is of heuene; if netheles we ben foundun clothid,
28868	47	5	3	and not nakid.
28869	47	5	4	For whi and we that ben in this tabernacle, sorewen with ynne, and ben heuyed, for that we wolen not be spuylid, but be clothid aboue; that the ilke thing that is deedli, be sopun vp of lijf.
28870	47	5	5	But who is it that makith vs in to this same thing? God, that yaf to vs the ernes of the spirit.
28871	47	5	6	Therfor we ben hardi algatis, and witen that the while we ben in this bodi, we goen in pilgrymage fro the Lord;
28872	47	5	7	for we walken bi feith, and not bi cleer siyt.
28873	47	5	8	But we ben hardi, and han good wille, more to be in pilgrymage fro the bodi, and to be present to God.
28874	47	5	9	And therfor we stryuen, whether absent, whether present, to plese hym.
28875	47	5	10	For it bihoueth vs alle to be schewid bifor the trone of Crist, that euery man telle the propre thingis of the bodi, as he hath don, ethir good, ether yuel.
28876	47	5	11	Therfor we witynge the drede of the Lord, councelen men, for to God we ben opyn; and Y hope, that we ben opyn also in youre consciencis.
28877	47	5	12	We comenden not vs silf eftsoone to you, but we yyuen to you occasioun to haue glorie for vs, that ye haue to hem that glorien in the face, and not in the herte.
28878	47	5	13	For ethir we bi mynde passen to God, ether we ben sobre to you.
28879	47	5	14	For the charite of Crist dryueth vs; gessynge this thing, that if oon died for alle, thanne alle weren deed.
28880	47	5	15	And Crist diede for alle, that thei that lyuen, lyue not now to hem silf, but to hym that diede for hem, and roos ayen.
28881	47	5	16	Therfor we fro this tyme knowen no man aftir the fleische; thouy we knowun Crist aftir the fleisch, but nowe we knowun not.
28882	47	5	17	Therfor if ony newe creature is in Crist, the elde thingis ben passid.
28883	47	5	18	And lo! alle thingis ben of God, which recounselide vs to hym bi Crist, and yaf to vs the seruyce of recounselyng.
28884	47	5	19	And God was in Crist, recounselynge to hym the world, not rettynge to hem her giltes, and puttide in vs the word of recounselyng.
28885	47	5	20	Therfor we vsen message for Crist, as if God monestith bi vs; we bisechen for Crist, be ye recounselid to God.
28886	47	5	21	God the fadir made hym synne for vs, which knewe not synne, that we schulden be maad riytwisnesse of God in hym.
28887	47	6	1	But we helpynge monesten, that ye resseyuen not the grace of God in veyn.
28888	47	6	2	For he seith, In tyme wel plesinge Y haue herd thee, and in the dai of heelthe Y haue helpid thee. Lo! now a tyme acceptable, lo! now a dai of heelthe.
28889	47	6	3	Yyue we to no man ony offencioun, that oure seruyce be not repreued;
28890	47	6	4	but in alle thingis yyue we vs silf as the mynystris of God, in myche pacience, in tribulaciouns,
28891	47	6	5	in nedis, in angwischis, in betyngis, in prisouns, in dissensiouns with ynne, in trauels, in wakyngis, in fastyngis,
28892	47	6	6	in chastite, in kunnyng, in long abiding, in swetnesse, in the Hooli Goost,
28893	47	6	7	in charite not feined, in the word of treuthe, in the vertu of God; bi armeris of riytwisnesse on the riythalf and on the lefthalf;
28894	47	6	8	bi glorie and vnnoblei; bi yuel fame and good fame; as disseyueris, and trewe men; as thei that ben vnknowun, and knowun;
28895	47	6	9	as men diynge, and lo! we lyuen; as chastisid, and not maad deed;
28896	47	6	10	as sorewful, euere more ioiynge; as hauynge nede, but makynge many men riche; as no thing hauynge, and weldynge alle thingis.
28897	47	6	11	A! ye Corynthies, oure mouth is open to you, oure herte is alargid;
28898	47	6	12	ye ben not angwischid in vs, but ye ben anguischid in youre inwardnessis.
28899	47	6	13	And Y seie as to sones, ye that han the same reward, be ye alargid.
28900	47	6	14	Nyle ye bere the yok with vnfeithful men. For what parting of riytwisnes with wickidnesse? or what felouschipe of liyt to derknessis?
28901	47	6	15	and what acording of Crist to Belial? or what part of a feithful with the vnfeithful?
28902	47	6	16	and what consent to the temple of God with mawmetis? And ye ben the temple of the lyuynge God, as the Lord seith, For Y schal dwelle in hem, and Y schal walke among hem; and Y schal be God of hem, and thei schulen be a puple to me.
28903	47	6	17	For which thing go ye out of the myddil of hem, and be ye departid, seith the Lord, and touche ye not vnclene thing;
28904	47	6	18	and Y schal resseyue you, and schal be to you in to a fadir, and ye schulen be to me in to sones and douytris, seith the Lord almyyti.
28905	47	7	1	Therfor, most dereworthe britheren, we that han these biheestis, clense we vs fro al filthe of the fleische and of the spirit, doynge holynesse in the drede of God.
28906	47	7	2	Take ye vs; we han hirt no man, we han apeirid no man, we han bigilid no man.
28907	47	7	3	Y seie not to youre condempnyng; for Y seide bifor, that ye ben in youre hertis, to die togidere and to lyue togidere.
28908	47	7	4	Myche trist is to me anentis you, myche gloriyng is to me for you. Y am fillid with coumfort, Y am plenteuouse in ioie in al oure tribulacioun.
28909	47	7	5	For whanne we weren comun to Macedonye, oure fleisch hadde no reste, but we suffriden al tribulacioun; with outforth fiytingis, and dredis with ynne.
28910	47	7	6	But God that coumfortith meke men, coumfortide vs in the comyng of Tite.
28911	47	7	7	And not oneli in the comyng of him, but also in the coumfort bi which he was coumfortid in you, tellinge to vs youre desire, youre weping, youre loue for me, so that Y ioiede more.
28912	47	7	8	For thouy Y made you sorie in a pistle, it rewith me not; thouy it rewide, seynge that thouy thilke pistle made you sori at an our, now Y haue ioie;
28913	47	7	9	not for ye weren maad soreuful, but for ye weren maad soreuful to penaunce. For whi ye ben maad sori aftir God, that in no thing ye suffre peirement of vs.
28914	47	7	10	For the sorewe that is aftir God, worchith penaunce in to stidfast heelthe; but sorewe of the world worchith deth.
28915	47	7	11	For lo! this same thing, that ye ben soreuful aftir God, hou myche bisynesse it worchith in you; but defendyng, but indignacioun, but drede, but desire, but loue, but veniaunce. In alle thingis ye han youun you silf to be vndefoulid in the cause.
28916	47	7	12	Therfor thouy Y wroot to you, Y wroot not for hym that dide the iniurie, nether for hym that suffride, but to schewe oure bisinesse, which we han for you bifor God.
28917	47	7	13	Therfor we ben coumfortid, but in youre coumfort more plenteuousli we ioyeden more on the ioie of Tite, for his spirit is fulfillid of alle you.
28918	47	7	14	And if Y gloriede ony thing anentis hym of you, Y am not confoundid; but as we han spoke to you alle thingis, so also oure glorie that was at Tite, is maad treuthe.
28919	47	7	15	And the inwardnesse of hym be more plenteuousli in you, which hath in mynde the obedience of you alle, hou with drede and trembling ye resseyueden hym.
28920	47	7	16	Y haue ioye, that in alle thingis Y triste in you.
28921	47	8	1	But, britheren, we maken knowun to you the grace of God, that is youun in the chirchis of Macedonye,
28922	47	8	2	that in myche asaiyng of tribulacioun, the plente of the ioye of hem was, and the hiyeste pouert of hem was plenteuouse `in to the richessis of the symplenesse of hem.
28923	47	8	3	For Y bere witnessyng to hem, aftir miyt and aboue miyt thei weren wilful,
28924	47	8	4	with myche monestyng bisechynge vs the grace and the comynyng of mynystring, that is maad to hooli men.
28925	47	8	5	And not as we hopiden, but thei yauen hem silf first to the Lord, aftirward to vs bi the wille of God.
28926	47	8	6	So that we preyeden Tite, that as he bigan, so also he performe in you this grace.
28927	47	8	7	But as ye abounden in alle thingis, in feith, and word, and kunnyng, and al bisynesse, more ouer and in youre charite in to vs, that and in this grace ye abounden.
28928	47	8	8	Y seie not as comaundinge, but bi the bisynesse of othere men appreuynge also the good wit of youre charite.
28929	47	8	9	And ye witen the grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, for he was maad nedi for you, whanne he was riche, that ye schulden be maad riche bi his nedynesse.
28930	47	8	10	And Y yyue counsel in this thing; for this is profitable to you, that not oneli han bigunne to do, but also ye bigunnen to haue wille fro the formere yere.
28931	47	8	11	But now parfourme ye in deed, that as the discrecioun of wille is redi, so be it also of parformyng of that that ye han.
28932	47	8	12	For if the wille be redi, it is acceptid aftir that that it hath, not aftir that that it hath not.
28933	47	8	13	And not that it be remyssioun to othere men, and to you tribulacioun;
28934	47	8	14	but of euenesse in the present tyme youre aboundance fulfille the myseese of hem, that also the aboundaunce of hem be a fulfillynge of youre myseise, that euenesse be maad; as it is writun,
28935	47	8	15	He that gaderide myche, was not encresid, and he that gaderide litil, hadde not lesse.
28936	47	8	16	And Y do thankyngis to God, that yaf the same bisynesse for you in the herte of Tite,
28937	47	8	17	for he resseyuede exortacioun; but whanne he was bisier, bi his wille he wente forth to you.
28938	47	8	18	And we senten with hym a brother, whose preisyng is in the gospel bi alle chirchis.
28939	47	8	19	And not oneli, but also he is ordeyned of chirchis the felowe of oure pilgrimage in to this grace, that is mynystrid of vs to the glorie of the Lord, and to oure ordeyned wille;
28940	47	8	20	eschewynge this thing, that no man blame vs in this plente, that is mynystrid of vs to the glorye of the Lord.
28941	47	8	21	For we purueyen good thingis, not onely bifor God, but also bifor alle men.
28942	47	8	22	For we senten with hem also oure brothir, whom we han preued in many thingis ofte, that he was bisi, but nowe myche bisier, for myche trist in you,
28943	47	8	23	ethir for Tite, that is my felowe and helpere in you, ethir for oure britheren, apostlis of the chirches of the glorie of Crist.
28944	47	8	24	Therfor schewe ye in to hem in the face of chirchis, that schewynge that is of youre charite and of oure glorie for you.
28945	47	9	1	For of the mynystrie that is maad to hooli men, it is to me of plente to write to you.
28946	47	9	2	For Y knowe youre wille, for the which Y haue glorie of you anentis Macedonyes, for also Acaie is redi fro a yeer passid, and youre loue hath stirid ful manye.
28947	47	9	3	And we han sent britheren, that this thing that we glorien of you, be not auoidid in this parti, that as Y seide, ye be redi.
28948	47	9	4	Lest whanne Macedonyes comen with me, and fynden you vnredi, we be schamed, that we seien you not, in this substaunce.
28949	47	9	5	Therfor Y gesside necessarie to preie britheren, that thei come bifore to you, and make redi this bihiyt blessyng to be redi, so as blessing, and not as aueryce.
28950	47	9	6	For Y seie this thing, he that sowith scarseli, schal also repe scarseli; and he that sowith in blessyngis, schal `repe also of blessyngis.
28951	47	9	7	Ech man as he castide in his herte, not of heuynesse, or of nede; for God loueth a glad yyuere.
28952	47	9	8	And God is miyti to make al grace abounde in you, that ye in alle thingis euere more han al sufficience, and abounde in to al good werk;
28953	47	9	9	as it is writun, He delide abrood, he yaf to pore men, his riytwisnesse dwellith withouten ende.
28954	47	9	10	And he that mynystrith seed to the sowere, schal yyue also breed to ete, and he schal multiplie youre seed, and make myche the encreessingis of fruytis of youre riytwisnesse;
28955	47	9	11	that in alle thingis ye maad riche waxen plenteuouse in to al symplenesse, which worchith bi vs doing of thankingis to God.
28956	47	9	12	For the mynystrie of this office not oneli fillith tho thingis that failen to holi men, but also multiplieth many thankyngis to God,
28957	47	9	13	bi the preuyng of this mynystrie, which glorifien God in the obedience of youre knouleching in the gospel of Crist, and in symplenesse of comynycacioun in to hem and in to alle,
28958	47	9	14	and in the biseching of hem for you, that desiren you for the excellent grace of God in you.
28959	47	9	15	Y do thankyngis to God of the yifte of hym, that may not be teld.
28960	47	10	1	And Y my silf Poul biseche you, bi the myldenesse and softnesse of Crist, which in the face am meke among you, and Y absent triste in you.
28961	47	10	2	For Y preie you, that lest Y present be not bold bi the trist, in which Y am gessid to be bold in to summe, that demen vs, as if we wandren aftir the fleisch.
28962	47	10	3	For we walkynge in fleisch, fiyten not aftir the fleisch.
28963	47	10	4	For the armuris of oure knyythod ben not fleischli, but myyti bi God to the distruccioun of strengthis. And we distrien counsels,
28964	47	10	5	and alle hiynesse that hiyeth it silf ayens the science of God, and dryuen `in to caitifte al vndirstonding in to the seruyce of Crist.
28965	47	10	6	And we han redi to venge al vnobedience, whanne youre obedience schal be fillid.
28966	47	10	7	Se ye the thingis that ben after the face. If ony man trustith to him silf, that he is of Crist, thenke he this thing eft anentis hym silf,
28967	47	10	8	for as he is Cristis, so also we. For if Y schal glorie ony thing more of oure power, which the Lord yaf to vs in to edifiyng, and not in to youre distruccioun, Y schal not be schamed.
28968	47	10	9	But that Y be not gessid as to fere you bi epistlis,
28969	47	10	10	for thei seien, That epistlis ben greuouse and stronge, but the presence of the bodi is feble, and the word worthi to be dispisid.
28970	47	10	11	He that is suche oon, thenke this, for suche as we absent ben in word bi pistlis, suche we ben present in dede.
28971	47	10	12	For we doren not putte vs among, or comparisoune vs to summen, that comenden hem silf; but we mesuren vs in vs silf, and comparisounen vs silf to vs.
28972	47	10	13	For we schulen not haue glorie ouer mesure, but bi the mesure of the reule which God mesuride to vs, the mesure that stretchith to you.
28973	47	10	14	For we ouerstretchen not forth vs, as not stretchinge to you. For to you we camen in the gospel of Crist,
28974	47	10	15	not gloriynge ouer mesure in othere mennus trauelis. For we `han hope of youre feith that wexith in you to be magnefied bi oure reule in abundaunce,
28975	47	10	16	also to preche in to tho thingis that ben biyendis you, not to haue glorie in othere mennus reule, in these thingis that ben maad redi.
28976	47	10	17	He that glorieth, haue glorie in the Lord.
28977	47	10	18	For not he that comendith hym silf is preuyd, but whom God comendith.
28978	47	11	1	I wolde that ye wolden suffre a litil thing of myn vnwisdom, but also supporte ye me.
28979	47	11	2	For Y loue you bi the loue of God; for Y haue spousid you to oon hosebonde, to yelde a chast virgyn to Crist.
28980	47	11	3	But Y drede, lest as the serpent disseyuede Eue with his sutil fraude, so youre wittis ben corrupt, and fallen doun fro the symplenesse that is in Crist.
28981	47	11	4	For if he that cometh, prechith anothir Crist, whom we precheden not, or if ye taken another spirit, whom ye token not, or another gospel, which ye resseyueden not, riytli ye schulden suffre.
28982	47	11	5	For Y wene that Y haue don no thing lesse than the grete apostlis.
28983	47	11	6	For thouy Y be vnlerud in word, but not in kunnyng. For in alle thingis Y am open to you.
28984	47	11	7	Or whether Y haue don synne, mekynge my silf, that ye be enhaunsid, for freli Y prechide to you the gospel of God?
28985	47	11	8	Y made nakid othere chirchis, and Y took sowde to youre seruyce.
28986	47	11	9	And whanne Y was among you, and hadde nede, Y was chargeouse to no man; for britheren that camen fro Macedonye, fulfilliden that that failide to me. And in alle thingis Y haue kept, and schal kepe me with outen charge to you.
28987	47	11	10	The treuthe of Crist is in me; for this glorie schal not be brokun in me in the cuntreis of Acaie.
28988	47	11	11	Whi? for Y loue not you?
28989	47	11	12	God woot. For that that Y do, and that Y schal do, is that Y kitte awei the occasioun of hem that wolen occasioun, that in the thing, in which thei glorien, thei be foundun as we.
28990	47	11	13	For siche false apostlis ben trecherouse werk men, and transfiguren hem in to apostlis of Crist.
28991	47	11	14	And no wondur, for Sathanas hym silf transfigurith hym in to an aungel of light.
28992	47	11	15	Therfor it is not greet, if hise mynystris ben transfigurid as the mynystris of riytwisnesse, whos ende schal be aftir her werkis.
28993	47	11	16	Eft Y seie, lest ony man gesse me to be vnwise; ellis take ye me as vnwise, that also Y haue glorie a litil what.
28994	47	11	17	That that Y speke, Y speke not aftir God, but as in vnwisdom, in this substaunce of glorie.
28995	47	11	18	For many men glorien aftir the fleisch, and Y schal glorie.
28996	47	11	19	For ye suffren gladli vnwise men, whanne ye silf ben wise.
28997	47	11	20	For ye susteynen, if ony man dryueth you in to seruage, if ony man deuourith, if ony man takith, if ony man is enhaunsid, if ony man smytith you on the face.
28998	47	11	21	Bi vnnoblei Y seie, as if we weren sike in this parti. In what thing ony man dar, in vnwisdom Y seie, and Y dar.
28999	47	11	22	Thei ben Ebrewis, and Y; thei ben Israelitis, and Y; thei ben the seed of Abraham, and Y;
29000	47	11	23	thei ben the mynystris of Crist, and Y. As lesse wise Y seie, Y more; in ful many trauelis, in prisouns more plenteuousli, in woundis aboue maner, in deethis ofte tymes.
29001	47	11	24	Y resseyuede of the Jewis fyue sithis fourti strokis oon lesse;
29002	47	11	25	thries Y was betun with yerdis, onys Y was stonyd, thries Y was at shipbreche, a nyyt and a dai Y was in the depnesse of the see;
29003	47	11	26	in weies ofte, in perelis of floodis, in perelis of theues, in perelis of kyn, in perelis of hethene men, in perelis in citee, in perelis in desert, in perelis in the see, in perelis among false britheren, in trauel and nedynesse,
29004	47	11	27	in many wakyngis, in hungur, in thirst, in many fastyngis, in coold and nakidnesse.
29005	47	11	28	Withouten tho thingis that ben withoutforth, myn ech daies trauelyng is the bisynesse of alle chirchis.
29006	47	11	29	Who is sijk, and Y am not sijk? who is sclaundrid, and Y am not brent?
29007	47	11	30	If it bihoueth to glorie, Y schal glorie in tho thingis that ben of myn infirmyte.
29008	47	11	31	God and the fadir of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, that is blessid in to worldis, woot that Y lie not.
29009	47	11	32	The preuost of Damask, of the kyng of the folk Arethe, kepte the citee of Damascenes to take me;
29010	47	11	33	and bi a wyndow in a leep Y was latun doun bi the wal, and so Y ascapide hise hondis.
29011	47	12	1	If it bihoueth to haue glorie, it spedith not; but Y schal come to the visiouns and to the reuelaciouns of the Lord.
29012	47	12	2	I woot a man in Crist that bifore fouretene yeer; whether in bodi, whether out of the bodi, Y woot not, God woot; that siche a man was rauyschid `til to the thridde heuene.
29013	47	12	3	And Y woot sich a man; whether in bodi, or out of bodi, Y noot, God woot;
29014	47	12	4	that he was rauyschid in to paradis, and herde preuy wordis, whiche it is not leueful to a man to speke.
29015	47	12	5	For such maner thingis Y schal glorie; but for me no thing, no but in myn infirmytees.
29016	47	12	6	For if Y schal wilne to glorie, Y schal not be vnwijs, for Y schal seie treuthe; but Y spare, lest ony man gesse me ouer that thing that he seeth in me, or herith ony thing of me.
29017	47	12	7	And lest the greetnesse of reuelaciouns enhaunse me in pride, the pricke of my fleisch, an aungel of Sathanas, is youun to me, that he buffate me.
29018	47	12	8	For whiche thing thries Y preiede the Lord, that it schulde go awei fro me.
29019	47	12	9	And he seide to me, My grace suffisith to thee; for vertu is parfitli maad in infirmyte. Therfor gladli Y schal glorie in myn infirmytees, that the vertu of Crist dwelle in me.
29020	47	12	10	For which thing Y am plesid in myn infirmytees, in dispisyngis, in nedis, in persecuciouns, in anguyschis, for Crist; for whanne Y am sijk, thanne Y am miyti.
29021	47	12	11	Y am maad vnwitti, ye constreyneden me. For Y ouyte to be comendid of you; for Y dide no thing lesse than thei that ben apostlis `aboue maner.
29022	47	12	12	Thouy Y am nouyt, netheles the signes of myn apostilhed ben maad on you, in al pacience, and signes, and grete wondris, and vertues.
29023	47	12	13	And what is it, that ye hadden lesse than othere chirchis, but that Y my silf greuyde you not? Foryyue ye to me this wrong.
29024	47	12	14	Lo! this thridde tyme Y am redi to come to you, and Y schal not be greuous to you; for Y seke not tho thingis that ben youre, but you. For nether sones owen to tresoure to fadir and modir, but the fadir and modir to the sones.
29025	47	12	15	For Y schal yyue moost wilfuli, and Y my silf schal be youun aboue for youre soulis; thouy Y more loue you, and be lesse louyd.
29026	47	12	16	But be it; Y greuyde not you, but whanne Y was sutil, Y took you with gile.
29027	47	12	17	Whether Y disseyuede you bi ony of hem, which Y sente to you?
29028	47	12	18	Y preiede Tite, and Y sente with hym a brother. Whether Tite begilide you? whether we yeden not in the same spirit? whether not in the same steppis?
29029	47	12	19	Sum tyme ye wenen, that we schulen excuse vs anentis you. Bifor God in Crist we speken; and, moost dere britheren, alle thingis for youre edifiyng.
29030	47	12	20	But Y drede, lest whanne Y come, Y schal fynde you not suche as Y wole, and Y schal be foundun of you suche as ye wolen not; lest perauenture stryuyngis, enuyes, sturdynessis, dissenciouns and detraccions, preuy spechis of discord, bolnyngis bi pride, debatis ben among you;
29031	47	12	21	and lest eftsoone whanne Y come, God make me low anentis you, and Y biweile many of hem, that bifor synneden, and diden not penaunce on the vnclennesse, and fornicacioun, and vnchastite, that thei han don.
29032	47	13	1	Lo! this thridde tyme Y come to you, and in the mouth of tweyne or of thre witnessis euery word schal stonde.
29033	47	13	2	Y seide bifor, and seie bifor, as present twies, and now absent, to hem that bifor han synned, and to alle othere; for if Y come eftsoone, Y schal not spare.
29034	47	13	3	Whether ye seken the preef of that Crist, that spekith in me, which is not feble in you?
29035	47	13	4	For thouy he was crucified of infirmyte, but he lyueth of the vertu of God. For also we ben sijk in hym, but we schulen lyue with him of the vertu of God in vs.
29036	47	13	5	Asaie you silf, if ye ben in the feith; ye you silf preue. Whether ye knowen not you silf, for Crist Jhesu is in you? but in happe ye ben repreuable.
29037	47	13	6	But Y hope, that ye knowen, that we ben not repreuable.
29038	47	13	7	And we preien the Lord, that ye do no thing of yuel; not that we seme preued, but that ye do that that is good, and that we ben as repreuable.
29039	47	13	8	For we moun no thing ayens treuthe, but for the treuthe.
29040	47	13	9	For we ioyen, whanne we ben sijk, but ye ben myyti; and we preien this thing, youre perfeccioun.
29041	47	13	10	Therfor Y absent write these thingis, that Y present do not hardere, bi the powere, which the Lord yaf to me in to edificacioun, and not in to youre distruccioun.
29042	47	13	11	Britheren, `hennus forward ioye ye, be ye perfit, excite ye; vndurstonde ye the same thing; haue ye pees, and God of pees and of loue schal be with you.
29043	47	13	12	Grete ye wel togidere in hooli cos. Alle hooli men greten you wel.
29044	47	13	13	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and the charite of God, and the comynyng of the Hooli Gost, be with `you alle. Amen.
29045	48	1	1	Poul the apostle, not of men, ne bi man, but bi Jhesu Crist, and God the fadir,
29046	48	1	2	that reiside hym fro deth, and alle the britheren that ben with me, to the chirchis of Galathie,
29047	48	1	3	grace to you and pees of God the fadir, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist,
29048	48	1	4	that yaf hym silf for oure synnes, to delyuere vs fro the present wickid world, bi the wille of God and of oure fadir,
29049	48	1	5	to whom is worschip and glorie in to worldis of worldis. Amen.
29050	48	1	6	I wondur, that so soone ye be thus moued fro hym that clepid you in to the grace of Crist, in to another euangelie; which is not anothir,
29051	48	1	7	but that ther ben summe that troublen you, and wolen mysturne the euangelie of Crist.
29052	48	1	8	But thouy we, or an aungel of heuene, prechide to you, bisidis that that we han prechid to you, be he acursid.
29053	48	1	9	As Y haue seid bifore, and now eftsoones Y seie, if ony preche to you bisidis that that ye han vndurfongun, be he cursid.
29054	48	1	10	For now whether counsele Y men, or God? or whether Y seche to plese men? If Y pleside yit men, Y were not Cristis seruaunt.
29055	48	1	11	For, britheren, Y make knowun to you the euangelie, that was prechid of me, for it is not bi man;
29056	48	1	12	ne Y took it of man, ne lernyde, but bi reuelacioun of Jhesu Crist.
29057	48	1	13	For ye han herd my conuersacioun sumtyme in the Jurie, and that Y pursuede passyngli the chirche of God, and fauyt ayen it.
29058	48	1	14	And Y profitide in the Jurie aboue many of myn eueneldis in my kynrede, and was more aboundauntli a folewere of my fadris tradiciouns.
29059	48	1	15	But whanne it pleside hym, that departide me fro my modir wombe,
29060	48	1	16	and clepide bi his grace, to schewe his sone in me, that Y schulde preche hym among the hethene, anoon Y drowy me not to fleisch and blood; ne Y cam to Jerusalem to the apostlis,
29061	48	1	17	that weren tofor me, but Y wente in to Arabie, and eftsoones Y turnede ayen in to Damask.
29062	48	1	18	And sith thre yeer aftir Y cam to Jerusalem, to se Petre, and Y dwellide with hym fiftene daies;
29063	48	1	19	but Y sawy noon othere of the apostlis, but James, oure Lordis brother.
29064	48	1	20	And these thingis which Y write to you, lo! tofor God Y lie not.
29065	48	1	21	Afterward Y cam in to the coostis of Syrie and Cilicie.
29066	48	1	22	But Y was vnknowun bi face to the chirchis of Judee, that weren in Crist; and thei hadden oonli an heryng,
29067	48	1	23	that he that pursuede vs sum tyme, prechide now the feith, ayens which he fauyte sum tyme;
29068	48	1	24	and in me thei glorifieden God.
29069	48	2	1	And sith fourtene yeer aftir, eftsones Y wente vp to Jerusalem with Barnabas, and took with me Tite.
29070	48	2	2	Y wente vp bi reuelacioun, and spak with hem the euangelie, which Y preche among the hethene; and bi hem silf to these that semeden to be sumwhat, lest Y runne, or hadde runne in veyne.
29071	48	2	3	And nother Tite, that hadde be with me, while he was hethene, was compellid to be circumsidid;
29072	48	2	4	but for false britheren that weren brouyt ynne, whiche hadden entrid to aspie oure fredom, which we han in Jhesu Crist, to bring vs in to seruage.
29073	48	2	5	But we yyue no place to subieccioun, that the treuthe of the gospel schulde dwelle with you.
29074	48	2	6	But of these that semeden to be sumwhat; whiche thei weren sum tyme, it perteyneth not to me, for God takith not the persoone of man; for thei that semeden to be sumwhat, yauen me no thing.
29075	48	2	7	But ayenward, whanne thei hadden seyn, that the euangelie of prepucie was youun to me, as the euangelie of circumcisioun was youun to Petre;
29076	48	2	8	for he that wrouyte to Petre in apostlehed of circumcisioun, wrouyte also to me among the hethene;
29077	48	2	9	and whanne thei hadden knowe the grace of God, that was youun to me, James, and Petre, and Joon, whiche weren seyn to be the pileris, thei yauen riythond of felowschip to me and to Barnabas, that we among the hethene, and thei in to circumcisioun;
29078	48	2	10	oneli that we hadde mynde of pore men `of Crist, the which thing Y was ful bisi to doon.
29079	48	2	11	But whanne Petre was comun to Antioche, Y ayenstood hym in the face, for he was worthi to be vndirnommen.
29080	48	2	12	For bifor that ther camen summen fro James, he eete with the hethene men; but whanne thei weren comun, he withdrowy, and departide hym, dredinge hem that weren of circumcisioun.
29081	48	2	13	And the othere Jewis assentiden to his feynyng, so that Barnabas was drawun of hem in to that feynyng.
29082	48	2	14	But whanne Y sawy, that thei walkiden not riytli to the treuthe of the gospel, Y seide to Petre bifor alle men, If thou, that art a Jew, lyuest hethenlich, and not Jewelich, hou constreynest thou hethene men to bicome Jewis?
29083	48	2	15	We Jewis of kynde, and not synful men of the hethene,
29084	48	2	16	knowen that a man is not iustified of the werkis of lawe, but bi the feith of Jhesu Crist; and we bileuen in Jhesu Crist, that we ben iustified of the feith of Crist, and not of the werkis of lawe. Wherfor of the werkis of lawe ech fleisch schal not be iustified.
29085	48	2	17	And if we sechen to be iustified in Crist, we oure silf ben foundun synful men, whether Crist be mynystre of synne?
29086	48	2	18	God forbede. And if Y bylde ayen thingis that Y haue distruyed, Y make my silf a trespassour.
29087	48	2	19	For bi the lawe Y am deed to the lawe, and Y am fitchid to the crosse, that Y lyue to God with Crist.
29088	48	2	20	And now lyue not Y, but Crist lyueth in me. But that Y lyue now in fleisch, Y lyue in the feith of Goddis sone, that louede me, and yaf hym silf for me.
29089	48	2	21	Y caste not awey the grace of God; for if riytwisnesse be thoruy lawe, thanne Crist diede with out cause.
29090	48	3	1	Vnwitti Galathies, tofor whos iyen Jhesu Crist is exilid, and is crucified in you, who hath disseyued you, that ye obeyen not to treuthe?
29091	48	3	2	This oneli Y wilne to lerne of you, whether ye han vndurfonge the spirit of werkis of the lawe, or of heryng of bileue?
29092	48	3	3	So ye ben foolis, that whanne ye han bigunne in spirit, ye ben endid in fleisch.
29093	48	3	4	So grete thingis ye han suffrid without cause, if it be withoute cause.
29094	48	3	5	He that yyueth to you spirit, and worchith vertues in you, whether of werkis of the lawe, or of hering of bileue?
29095	48	3	6	As it is writun, Abraham bileuede to God, and it was rettid to hym to riytfulnesse.
29096	48	3	7	And therfor knowe ye, that these that ben of bileue, ben the sones of Abraham.
29097	48	3	8	And the scripture seynge afer, that God iustifieth the hethene, of bileue told tofor to Abraham, That in thee alle the hethene schulen be blessid.
29098	48	3	9	And therfor these that ben of bileue, schulen be blessid with feithful Abraham.
29099	48	3	10	For alle that ben of the werkis of the lawe, ben vndur curse; for it is writun, Ech man is cursid, that abidith not in alle thingis that ben writun in the book of the lawe, to do tho thingis.
29100	48	3	11	And that no man is iustified in the lawe bifor God, it is opyn, for a riytful man lyueth of bileue.
29101	48	3	12	But the lawe is not of bileue, but he that doith tho thingis of the lawe, schal lyue in hem.
29102	48	3	13	But Crist ayenbouyte us fro the curse of the lawe, and was maad acursid for vs; for it is writun, Ech man is cursid that hangith in the tre;
29103	48	3	14	that among the hethene the blessyng of Abraham were maad in `Crist Jhesu, that we vndurfonge the biheeste of spirit thoruy bileue.
29104	48	3	15	Britheren, Y seie aftir man, no man dispisith the testament of a man that is confermed, or ordeyneth aboue.
29105	48	3	16	The biheestis weren seid to Abraham and to his seed; he seith not, In seedis, as in many, but as in oon, And to thi seed, that is, Crist.
29106	48	3	17	But Y seie, this testament is confermed of God; the lawe that was maad after foure hundrid and thritti yeer, makith not the testament veyn to auoide awei the biheest.
29107	48	3	18	For if eritage were of the lawe, it were not now of biheeste. But God grauntide to Abraham thoruy biheest.
29108	48	3	19	What thanne the lawe? It was sett for trespassing, to the seed come, to whom he hadde maad his biheest. Whiche lawe was ordeyned bi aungels, in the hoond of a mediatour. But a mediatour is not of oon. But God is oon.
29109	48	3	21	Is thanne the lawe ayens the biheestis of God? God forbede. For if the lawe were youun, that myyte quikene, verili were riytfulnesse of lawe.
29110	48	3	22	But scripture hath concludid alle thingis vndir synne, that the biheeste of the feith of Jhesu Crist were yyuen to hem that bileuen.
29111	48	3	23	And tofor that bileue cam, thei weren kept vndur the lawe, enclosid in to that bileue that was to be schewid.
29112	48	3	24	And so the lawe was oure vndirsmaister in Crist, that we ben iustified of bileue.
29113	48	3	25	But aftir that bileue cam, we ben not now vndur the vndurmaistir.
29114	48	3	26	For alle ye ben the children of God thoruy the bileue of Jhesu Crist.
29115	48	3	27	For alle ye that ben baptisid, ben clothid with Crist.
29116	48	3	28	Ther is no Jewe, ne Greke, ne bond man, ne fre man, ne male, ne female; for alle ye ben oon in `Jhesu Crist.
29117	48	3	29	And if ye ben oon in `Jhesu Crist, thanne ye ben the seed of Abraham, and eiris bi biheest.
29118	48	4	1	But Y seie, as long tyme as the eir is a litil child, he dyuersith no thing fro a seruaunt, whanne he is lord of alle thingis;
29119	48	4	2	but he is vndur keperis and tutoris, in to the tyme determyned of the fadir.
29120	48	4	3	So we, whanne we weren litle children, we serueden vndur the elementis of the world.
29121	48	4	4	But aftir that the fulfilling of tyme cam, God sente his sone,
29122	48	4	5	maad of a womman, maad vndur the lawe, that he schulde ayenbie hem that weren vndur the lawe, that we schulden vnderfonge the adopcioun of sones.
29123	48	4	6	And for ye ben Goddis sones, God sente his spirit in to youre hertis, criynge, Abba, fadir.
29124	48	4	7	And so ther is not now a seruaunt, but a sone; and if he is a sone, he is an eir bi God.
29125	48	4	8	But thanne ye vnknowynge God, serueden to hem that in kynde weren not goddis.
29126	48	4	9	But now whanne ye han knowe God, and ben knowun of God, hou ben ye turned eftsoone to the febil and nedi elementis, to the whiche ye wolen eft serue?
29127	48	4	10	Ye taken kepe to daies, and monethis, and tymes, and yeris.
29128	48	4	11	But Y drede you, lest without cause Y haue trauelid among you.
29129	48	4	12	Be ye as Y, for Y am as ye. Britheren, Y biseche you, ye han hurt me no thing.
29130	48	4	13	But ye knowen, that bi infirmyte of fleisch Y haue prechid to you now bifore;
29131	48	4	14	and ye dispiseden not, nether forsoken youre temptacioun in my fleisch, but ye resseyueden me as an aungel of God, as `Crist Jhesu.
29132	48	4	15	Where thanne is youre blessyng? For Y bere you witnesse, that if it myyte haue be don. ye wolden haue put out youre iyen, and haue yyuen hem to me.
29133	48	4	16	Am Y thanne maad an enemye to you, seiynge to you the sothe?
29134	48	4	17	Thei louen not you wel, but thei wolen exclude you, that ye suen hem.
29135	48	4	18	But sue ye the good euermore in good, and not oneli whanne Y am present with you.
29136	48	4	19	My smale children, whiche Y bere eftsoones, til that Crist be fourmed in you,
29137	48	4	20	and Y wolde now be at you, and chaunge my vois, for Y am confoundid among you.
29138	48	4	21	Seie to me, ye that wolen be vndir the lawe, `han ye not red the lawe?
29139	48	4	22	For it is writun, that Abraham hadde two sones, oon of a seruaunt, and oon of a fre womman.
29140	48	4	23	But he that was of the seruaunt, was borun after the flesh; but he that was of the fre womman, by a biheeste.
29141	48	4	24	The whiche thingis ben seid bi an othir vndirstonding. For these ben two testamentis; oon in the hille of Synai, gendringe in to seruage, which is Agar.
29142	48	4	25	For Syna is an hille that is in Arabie, which hille is ioyned to it that is now Jerusalem, and seruith with hir children.
29143	48	4	26	But that Jerusalem that is aboue, is fre, whiche is oure modir.
29144	48	4	27	For it is writun, Be glad, thou bareyn, that berist not; breke out and crye, that bringist forth no children; for many sones ben of hir that is left of hir hosebonde, more than of hir that hath an hosebonde.
29145	48	4	28	For, britheren, we ben sones of biheeste aftir Isaac;
29146	48	4	29	but now as this that was borun after the fleisch pursuede him that was aftir the spirit, so now.
29147	48	4	30	But what seith the scripture? Caste out the seruaunt and hir sone, for the sone of the seruaunt schal not be eir with the sone of the fre wijf.
29148	48	4	31	And so, britheren, we ben not sones of the seruaunt, but of the fre wijf, bi which fredom Crist hath maad vs fre.
29149	48	5	1	Stonde ye therfor, and nyl ye eftsoones be holdun in the yok of seruage.
29150	48	5	2	Lo! Y Poul seie to you, that if ye ben circumcidid, Crist schal no thing profite to you.
29151	48	5	3	And Y witnesse eftsoones to ech man that circumcidith hym silf, that he is dettour of al the lawe to be don.
29152	48	5	4	And ye ben voidid awei fro Crist, and ye that be iustified in the lawe, ye han fallen awei fro grace.
29153	48	5	5	For we thoruy the spirit of bileue abiden the hope of riytfulnesse.
29154	48	5	6	For in Jhesu Crist nether circumcisioun is ony thing worth, nether prepucie, but the bileue that worchith bi charite.
29155	48	5	7	Ye runnen wel; who lettide you that ye obeyede not to treuthe?
29156	48	5	8	Consente ye to no man; for this counsel ys not of hym that hath clepid you.
29157	48	5	9	A litil souredowy apeirith al the gobet.
29158	48	5	10	I trust on you in oure Lord, that ye schulden vndurstonde noon other thing. And who that disturblith you, schal bere dom, who euere he be.
29159	48	5	11	And, britheren, if Y preche yit circumcisioun, what suffre Y yit persecucioun? thanne the sclaundre of the crosse is auoidid.
29160	48	5	12	Y wolde that thei weren cut awei, that disturblen you.
29161	48	5	13	For, britheren, ye ben clepid in to fredom; oneli yyue ye not fredom in to occasioun of fleisch, but bi charite of spirit serue ye togidere.
29162	48	5	14	For euery lawe is fulfillid in o word, Thou schalt loue thi neiybore as thi silf.
29163	48	5	15	And if ye bite, and ete ech othere, se ye, lest ye be wastid ech fro othere.
29164	48	5	16	And Y seie you in Crist, walke ye in spirit, and ye schulen not performe the desiris of the fleisch.
29165	48	5	17	For the fleisch coueitith ayens the spirit, and the spirit ayen the fleisch; for these ben aduersaries togidere, that ye don not alle thingis that ye wolen.
29166	48	5	18	That if ye be led bi spirit, ye ben not vnder the lawe.
29167	48	5	19	And werkis of the fleisch ben opyn, whiche ben fornicacioun, vnclennes, vnchastite, letcherie, seruice of false goddis,
29168	48	5	20	witchecraftis, enmytees, striuyngis, indignaciouns, wraththis, chidingis, discenciouns, sectis, enuyes,
29169	48	5	21	manslauytris, dronkennessis, vnmesurable etyngis, and thingis lijk to these, whiche Y seie to you, as Y haue told to you `to fore, for thei that doon suche thingis, schulen not haue the kyngdom of God.
29170	48	5	22	But the fruyt of the spirit is charite, ioye, pees, pacience, long abidyng,
29171	48	5	23	benygnyte, goodnesse, myldenesse, feith, temperaunce, contynence, chastite; ayen suche thingis is no lawe.
29172	48	5	24	And they that ben of Crist, han crucified her fleisch with vices and coueytyngis.
29173	48	5	25	If we lyuen bi spirit, walke we bi spirit; be we not made coueytouse of veyn glorie, stirynge ech othere to wraththe, or hauynge enuye ech to othere.
29174	48	6	1	Britheren, if a man be occupied in ony gilt, ye that ben spiritual, enforme ye such oon in spirit of softnesse, biholdinge thi silf, lest that thou be temptid.
29175	48	6	2	Ech bere othere chargis, and so ye schulen fulfille the lawe of Crist.
29176	48	6	3	For who that trowith that he be ouyt, whanne he is nouyt, he bigilith him silf.
29177	48	6	4	But ech man preue his owne werk, and so he schal haue glorie in him silf, and not in an othere.
29178	48	6	5	For ech man schal bere his owne charge.
29179	48	6	6	He that is tauyt bi word, comune he with him that techith hym, in `alle goodis.
29180	48	6	7	Nyle ye erre, God is not scorned;
29181	48	6	8	for tho thingis that a man sowith, tho thingis he schal repe. For he that sowith in his fleisch, of the fleisch he schal repe corrupcioun; but he that sowith in the spirit, of the spirit he schal repe euerelastynge lijf.
29182	48	6	9	And doynge good faile we not; for in his tyme we schal repe, not failinge.
29183	48	6	10	Therfor while we han tyme, worche we good to alle men; but most to hem that ben homliche of the feith.
29184	48	6	11	Se ye, what maner lettris Y haue write to you with myn owne hoond.
29185	48	6	12	For who euere wole plese in the fleisch, `this constreyneth you to be circumcidid, oonli that thei suffren not the persecucioun of Cristis crosse.
29186	48	6	13	For nether thei that ben circumcidid kepen the lawe; but thei wolen that ye be circumcidid, that thei haue glorie in youre fleisch.
29187	48	6	14	But fer be it fro me to haue glorie, no but in the crosse of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, bi whom the world is crucified to me, and Y to the world.
29188	48	6	15	For in Jhesu Crist nether circumcisioun is ony thing worth, ne prepucie, but a newe creature.
29189	48	6	16	And who euere suwen this reule, pees on hem, and merci, and on Israel of God.
29190	48	6	17	And heraftir no man be heuy to me; for Y bere in my bodi the tokenes of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29191	48	6	18	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with youre spirit, britheren. Amen.
29192	49	1	1	Poul, the apostle of Jhesu Crist, bi the wille of God, to alle seyntis that ben at Effesie, and to the feithful men in Jhesu Crist,
29193	49	1	2	grace be to you and pees of God, oure fader, and oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29194	49	1	3	Blessid be God and the fadir of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, that hath blessid vs in al spiritual blessing in heuenli thingis in Crist,
29195	49	1	4	as he hath chosun vs in hym silf bifor the makyng of the world, that we weren hooli, and with out wem in his siyt, in charite.
29196	49	1	5	Which hath bifor ordeyned vs in to adopcioun of sones bi Jhesu Crist in to hym, bi the purpos of his wille,
29197	49	1	6	in to the heriyng of the glorie of his grace;
29198	49	1	7	in which he hath glorified vs in his dereworthe sone. In whom we han redempcioun bi his blood, foryyuenesse of synnes, aftir the ritchessis of his grace,
29199	49	1	8	that aboundide greetli in vs in al wisdom and prudence,
29200	49	1	9	to make knowun to vs the sacrament of his wille, bi the good plesaunce of hym; the which sacrament he purposide in
29201	49	1	10	hym in the dispensacioun of plente of tymes to enstore alle thingis in Crist, whiche ben in heuenes, and whiche ben in erthe, in hym.
29202	49	1	11	In whom we ben clepid bi sort, bifor ordeyned bi the purpos of hym that worchith alle thingis bi the counsel of his wille;
29203	49	1	12	that we be in to the heriyng of his glorie, we that han hopid bifor in Crist.
29204	49	1	13	In whom also ye weren clepid, whanne ye herden the word of treuthe, the gospel of youre heelthe, in whom ye bileuynge ben merkid with the Hooli Goost of biheest, which is the ernes of oure eritage,
29205	49	1	14	in to the redempcioun of purchasyng, in to heriyng of his glorie.
29206	49	1	15	Therfor and Y herynge youre feith, that is in Crist Jhesu, and the loue in to alle seyntis,
29207	49	1	16	ceesse not to do thankyngis for you, makynge mynde of you in my preieris;
29208	49	1	17	that God of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, the fadir of glorie, yyue to you the spirit of wisdom and of reuelacioun, in to the knowyng of hym;
29209	49	1	18	and the iyen of youre herte liytned, that ye wite, which is the hope of his clepyng, and whiche ben the richessis of the glorie of his eritage in seyntis;
29210	49	1	19	and whych is the excellent greetnesse of his vertu in to vs that han bileuyd, bi the worchyng of the myyt of his vertu,
29211	49	1	20	which he wrouyte in Crist, reisynge hym fro deth, and settynge him on his riyt half in heuenli thingis,
29212	49	1	21	aboue ech principat, and potestat, and vertu, and domynacioun, and aboue ech name that is named, not oneli in this world, but also in the world to comynge;
29213	49	1	22	and made alle thingis suget vndur hise feet, and yaf hym to be heed ouer al the chirche,
29214	49	1	23	that is the bodi of hym, and the plente of hym, which is alle thingis in alle thingis fulfillid.
29215	49	2	1	And whanne ye weren deed in youre giltis and synnes,
29216	49	2	2	in which ye wandriden sum tyme aftir the cours of this world, aftir the prince of the power of this eir, of the spirit that worchith now in to the sones of vnbileue;
29217	49	2	3	in which also we `alle lyueden sum tyme in the desiris of oure fleisch, doynge the willis of the fleisch and of thouytis, and we weren bi kynde the sones of wraththe, as othere men;
29218	49	2	4	but God, that is riche in merci, for his ful myche charite in which he louyde vs,
29219	49	2	5	yhe, whanne we weren deed in synnes, quikenede vs togidere in Crist, bi whos grace ye ben sauyd, and ayen reiside togidere,
29220	49	2	6	and made togidere to sitte in heuenli thingis in Crist Jhesu;
29221	49	2	7	that he schulde schewe in the worldis aboue comynge the plenteuouse ritchessis of his grace in goodnesse on vs in Crist Jhesu.
29222	49	2	8	For bi grace ye ben sauyd bi feith, and this not of you; for it is the yifte of God,
29223	49	2	9	not of werkis, that no man haue glorie.
29224	49	2	10	For we ben the makyng of hym, maad of nouyt in Crist Jhesu, in good werkis, whiche God hath ordeyned, that we go in tho werkis.
29225	49	2	11	For which thing be ye myndeful, that sumtyme ye weren hethene in fleisch, which weren seid prepucie, fro that that is seid circumcisioun maad bi hond in fleisch;
29226	49	2	12	and ye weren in that time with out Crist, alienyd fro the lyuyng of Israel, and gestis of testamentis, not hauynge hope of biheest, and with outen God in this world.
29227	49	2	13	But now in Crist Jhesu ye that weren sum tyme fer, ben maad nyy in the blood of Crist.
29228	49	2	14	For he is oure pees, that made bothe oon, and vnbyndynge the myddil wal of a wal with out morter, enmytees in his fleisch;
29229	49	2	15	and auoidide the lawe of maundementis bi domes, that he make twei in hym silf in to a newe man,
29230	49	2	16	makynge pees, to recounsele bothe in o bodi to God bi the cros, sleynge the enemytees in hym silf.
29231	49	2	17	And he comynge prechide pees to you that weren fer, and pees to hem that weren niy;
29232	49	2	18	for bi hym we bothe han niy comyng in o spirit to the fadir.
29233	49	2	19	Therfor now ye ben not gestis and straungeris, but ye ben citeseyns of seyntis, and houshold meine of God;
29234	49	2	20	aboue bildid on the foundement of apostlis and of profetis, vpon that hiyeste corner stoon, Crist Jhesu;
29235	49	2	21	in whom ech bildyng maad waxith in to an hooli temple in the Lord.
29236	49	2	22	In whom also `be ye bildid togidere in to the habitacle of God, in the Hooli Goost.
29237	49	3	1	For the grace of this thing I Poul, the boundun of Crist Jhesu, for you hethene men,
29238	49	3	2	if netheles ye han herd the dispensacioun of Goddis grace, that is youun to me in you.
29239	49	3	3	For bi reuelacioun the sacrament is maad knowun to me, as Y aboue wroot in schort thing,
29240	49	3	4	as ye moun rede, and vndurstonde my prudence in the mysterie of Crist.
29241	49	3	5	Which was not knowun to othere generaciouns to the sones of men, as it is now schewid to his hooli apostlis and prophetis in the spirit,
29242	49	3	6	that hethene men ben euen eiris, and of oo bodi, and parteneris togidere of his biheest in Crist Jhesu bi the euangelie;
29243	49	3	7	whos mynystre Y am maad, bi the yifte of Goddis grace, which is youun to me bi the worchyng of his vertu.
29244	49	3	8	To me, leeste of alle seyntis, this grace is youun to preche among hethene men the vnserchable richessis of Crist, and to liytne alle men,
29245	49	3	9	which is the dispensacioun of sacrament hid fro worldis in God, that made alle thingis of nouyt;
29246	49	3	10	that the myche fold wisdom of God be knowun to princis and potestatis in heuenli thingis bi the chirche,
29247	49	3	11	bi the bifore ordinaunce of worldis, which he made in Crist Jhesu oure Lord.
29248	49	3	12	In whom we han trist and nyy comyng, in tristenyng bi the feith of hym.
29249	49	3	13	For which thing Y axe, that ye faile not in my tribulaciouns for you, which is youre glorie.
29250	49	3	14	For grace of this thing Y bowe my knees to the fadir of oure Lord Jhesu Crist,
29251	49	3	15	of whom ech fadirhod in heuenes and in erthe is named,
29252	49	3	16	that he yyue to you, aftir the richessis of his glorie, vertu to be strengthid bi his spirit in the ynnere man,
29253	49	3	17	that Crist dwelle bi feith in youre hertis; that ye rootid and groundid in charite,
29254	49	3	18	moun comprehende with alle seyntis, which is the breede, and the lengthe, and the hiynesse, and the depnesse;
29255	49	3	19	also to wite the charite of Crist more excellent than science, that ye be fillid in al the plentee of God.
29256	49	3	20	And to hym that is myyti to do alle thingis more plenteuousli than we axen or vndurstondun, bi the vertu that worchith in vs,
29257	49	3	21	to hym be glorie in the chirche, and in Crist Jhesu, in to alle the generaciouns of the world of worldis. Amen.
29258	49	4	1	Therfor Y boundun for the Lord biseche you, that ye walke worthili in the clepyng,
29259	49	4	2	in which ye ben clepid, with al mekenesse and myldenesse, with pacience supportinge ech other in charite,
29260	49	4	3	bisi to kepe vnyte of spirit in the boond of pees.
29261	49	4	4	O bodi and o spirit, as ye ben clepid in oon hope of youre cleping;
29262	49	4	5	o Lord,
29263	49	4	6	o feith, o baptym, o God and fadir of alle, which is aboue alle men, and bi alle thingis, and in vs alle.
29264	49	4	7	But to ech of vs grace is youun bi the mesure of the yyuyng of Crist;
29265	49	4	8	for which thing he seith, He stiynge an hiy, ledde caitifte caitif, he yaf yiftis to men.
29266	49	4	9	But what is it, that he stiede vp, no but that also he cam doun first in to the lowere partis of the erthe?
29267	49	4	10	He it is that cam doun, and that stiede on alle heuenes, that he schulde fille alle thingis.
29268	49	4	11	And he yaf summe apostlis, summe prophetis, othere euangelistis, othere scheepherdis and techeris,
29269	49	4	12	to the ful endyng of seyntis, in to the werk of mynystrie, in to edificacioun of Cristis bodi,
29270	49	4	13	til we rennen alle, in to vnyte of feith and of knowyng of Goddis sone, in to a parfit man, aftir the mesure of age of the plente of Crist;
29271	49	4	14	that we be not now litle children, mouynge as wawis, and be not borun aboute with ech wynd of teching, in the weiwardnesse of men, in sutil wit, to the disseyuyng of errour.
29272	49	4	15	But do we treuthe in charite, and wexe in him by alle thingis, that is Crist oure heed;
29273	49	4	16	of whom alle the bodi set togidere, and boundun togidere bi ech ioynture of vnder seruyng, bi worching in to the mesure of ech membre, makith encreesyng of the bodi, in to edificacioun of it silf in charite.
29274	49	4	17	Therfor Y seie and witnesse this thing in the Lord, that ye walke not now, as hethene men walken, in the vanyte of her wit;
29275	49	4	18	that han vndurstondyng derkned with derknessis, and ben alienyd fro the lijf of God, bi ignoraunce that is in hem, for the blyndenesse of her herte.
29276	49	4	19	Which dispeirynge bitoken hem silf to vnchastite, in to the worchyng of al vnclennesse in coueitise.
29277	49	4	20	But ye han not so lerud Crist, if netheles ye herden hym,
29278	49	4	21	and ben tauyt in hym, as is treuthe in Jhesu.
29279	49	4	22	Do ye awey bi the elde lyuyng the elde man, that is corrupt bi the desiris of errour;
29280	49	4	23	and be ye renewlid in the spirit of youre soule;
29281	49	4	24	and clothe ye the newe man, which is maad aftir God in riytwisnesse and hoolynesse of treuthe.
29282	49	4	25	For which thing `ye putte awei leesyng, and speke ye treuthe ech man with his neiybore, for we ben membris ech to othere.
29283	49	4	26	Be ye wrooth, and nyle ye do synne; the sunne falle not doun on youre wraththe.
29284	49	4	27	Nyle ye yyue stide to the deuel.
29285	49	4	28	He that stal, now stele he not; but more trauele he in worchinge with hise hondis that that is good, that he haue whereof he schal yyue to nedi.
29286	49	4	29	Ech yuel word go not of youre mouth; but if ony is good to the edificacioun of feith, that it yyue grace to men that heren.
29287	49	4	30	And nyle ye make the Hooli Goost of God sori, in which ye ben markid in the dai of redempcioun.
29288	49	4	31	Al bitternesse, and wraththe, and indignacioun, and cry, and blasfemye be takun awey fro you, with al malice;
