29289	49	4	32	and be ye togidere benygne, merciful, foryyuynge togidere, as also God foryaf to you in Crist.
29290	49	5	1	Therfor be ye foloweris of God, as moost dereworthe sones;
29291	49	5	2	and walke ye in loue, as Crist louyde vs, and yaf hym silf for vs an offryng and a sacrifice to God, in to the odour of swetnesse.
29292	49	5	3	And fornycacioun, and al vnclennesse, or aueryce, be not named among you, as it bicometh holi men;
29293	49	5	4	ethir filthe, or foli speche, or harlatrye, that perteyneth not to profit, but more doyng of thankyngis.
29294	49	5	5	For wite ye this, and vndurstonde, that ech letchour, or vnclene man, or coueytouse, that serueth to mawmetis, hath not eritage in the kingdom of Crist and of God.
29295	49	5	6	No man disseyue you bi veyn wordis; for whi for these thingis the wraththe of God cam on the sones of vnbileue.
29296	49	5	7	Therfor nyle ye be maad parteneris of hem.
29297	49	5	8	For ye weren sum tyme derknessis, but now `ye ben liyt in the Lord. Walke ye as the sones of liyt.
29298	49	5	9	For the fruyt of liyt is in al goodnesse, and riytwisnesse, and treuthe.
29299	49	5	10	And preue ye what `thing is wel plesynge to God.
29300	49	5	11	And nyle ye comyne to vnfruytouse werkis of derknessis; but more repreue ye.
29301	49	5	12	For what thingis ben don of hem in priuy, it is foule, yhe, to speke.
29302	49	5	13	And alle thingis that ben repreuyd of the liyt, ben opynli schewid; for al thing that is schewid, is liyt.
29303	49	5	14	For which thing he seith, Rise thou that slepist, and rise vp fro deth, and Crist schal liytne thee.
29304	49	5	15	Therfor, britheren, se ye, hou warli ye schulen go;
29305	49	5	16	not as vnwise men, but as wise men, ayenbiynge tyme, for the daies ben yuele.
29306	49	5	17	Therfor nyle ye be maad vnwise, but vndurstondynge which is the wille of God.
29307	49	5	18	And nyle ye be drunkun of wyn, in which is letcherie, but be ye fillid with the Hooli Goost; and speke ye to you silf in salmes,
29308	49	5	19	and ymnes, and spiritual songis, syngynge and seiynge salm in youre hertis to the Lord;
29309	49	5	20	euermore doynge thankingis for alle thingis in the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist to God and to the fadir.
29310	49	5	21	Be ye suget togidere in the drede of Crist.
29311	49	5	22	Wymmen, be thei suget to her hosebondis,
29312	49	5	23	as to the Lord, for the man is heed of the wymman, as Crist is heed of the chirche; he is sauyour of his bodi.
29313	49	5	24	But as the chirche is suget to Crist, so wymmen to her hosebondis in alle thingis.
29314	49	5	25	Men, loue ye youre wyues, as Crist louyde the chirche, and yaf hym silf for it, to make it holi;
29315	49	5	26	and clenside it with the waisching of watir, in the word of lijf,
29316	49	5	27	to yyue the chirche gloriouse to hym silf, that it hadde no wem, ne ryueling, or ony siche thing, but that it be hooli and vndefoulid.
29317	49	5	28	So and men `schulen loue her wyues, as her owne bodies. He that loueth his wijf, loueth hym silf;
29318	49	5	29	for no man hatide euere his owne fleisch, but nurischith and fostrith it, as Crist doith the chirche.
29319	49	5	30	And we ben membris of his bodi, of his fleisch, and of his boonys.
29320	49	5	31	For this thing a man schal forsake his fadir and modir, and he schal drawe to his wijf; and thei schulen be tweyne in o fleisch.
29321	49	5	32	This sacrament is greet; yhe, Y seie in Crist, and in the chirche.
29322	49	5	33	Netheles ye alle, ech man loue his wijf as hym silf; and the wijf drede hir hosebonde.
29323	49	6	1	Sones, obeische ye to youre fadir and modir, in the Lord; for this thing is riytful.
29324	49	6	2	Onoure thou thi fadir and thi modir, that is the firste maundement in biheest;
29325	49	6	3	that it be wel to thee, and that thou be long lyuynge on the erthe.
29326	49	6	4	And, fadris, nyle ye terre youre sones to wraththe; but nurische ye hem in the teching and chastising of the Lord.
29327	49	6	5	Seruauntis, obeische ye to fleischli lordis with drede and trembling, in simplenesse of youre herte, as to Crist;
29328	49	6	6	not seruynge at the iye, as plesinge to men, but as seruauntis of Crist; doynge the wille of God bi discrecioun,
29329	49	6	7	with good wille seruynge as to the Lord, and not as to men;
29330	49	6	8	witinge that ech man, what euere good thing he schal do, he schal resseyue this of the Lord, whether seruaunt, whether fre man.
29331	49	6	9	And, ye lordis, do the same thingis to hem, foryyuynge manaasis; witinge that bothe her Lord and youre is in heuenes, and the taking of persones is not anentis God.
29332	49	6	10	Her aftirward, britheren, be ye coumfortid in the Lord, and in the miyt of his vertu.
29333	49	6	11	Clothe you with the armere of God, that ye moun stonde ayens aspiynges of the deuel.
29334	49	6	12	For whi stryuyng is not to vs ayens fleisch and blood, but ayens princis and potestatis, ayens gouernours of the world of these derknessis, ayens spiritual thingis of wickidnesse, in heuenli thingis.
29335	49	6	13	Therfor take ye the armere of God, that ye moun ayenstonde in the yuel dai; and in alle thingis stonde perfit.
29336	49	6	14	Therfor stonde ye, and be gird aboute youre leendis in sothefastnesse, and clothid with the haburioun of riytwisnesse,
29337	49	6	15	and youre feet schood in making redi of the gospel of pees.
29338	49	6	16	In alle thingis take ye the scheld of feith, in which ye moun quenche alle the firy dartis of `the worste.
29339	49	6	17	And take ye the helm of helthe, and the swerd of the Goost, that is, the word of God.
29340	49	6	18	Bi al preier and bisechyng preie ye al tyme in spirit, and in hym wakinge in al bisynesse, and bisechyng for alle hooli men, and for me;
29341	49	6	19	that word be youun to me in openyng of my mouth, with trist to make knowun the mysterie of the gospel,
29342	49	6	20	for which Y am set in message in a chayne; so that in it Y be hardi to speke, as it bihoueth me.
29343	49	6	21	And ye wite, what thingis ben aboute me, what Y do, Titicus, my moost dere brother, and trewe mynystre in the Lord, schal make alle thingis knowun to you;
29344	49	6	22	whom Y sente to you for this same thing, that ye knowe what thingis ben aboute vs, and that he coumforte youre hertis.
29345	49	6	23	Pees to britheren, and charite, with feith of God oure fadir, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
29346	49	6	24	Grace with alle men that louen oure Lord Jhesu Crist in vncorrupcioun. Amen, `that is, So be it.
29347	50	1	1	Poul and Tymothe, seruauntis of Jhesu Crist, to alle the hooli men in Crist Jhesu, that ben at Filippis, with bischopis and dekenes,
29348	50	1	2	grace and pees to you of God oure fadir, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
29349	50	1	3	I do thankyngis to my God
29350	50	1	4	in al mynde of you euere more in alle my preyeris for alle you with ioye, and
29351	50	1	5	make a bisechyng on youre comynyng in the gospel of Crist, fro the firste day til nowe;
29352	50	1	6	tristenynge this ilke thing, that he that bigan in you a good werk, schal perfourme it til in to the dai of Jhesu Crist.
29353	50	1	7	As it is iust to me to feele this thing for alle you, for that Y haue you in herte, and in my boondis, and in defending and confermyng of the gospel, that alle ye be felowis of my ioye.
29354	50	1	8	For God is a witnesse to me, hou Y coueyte alle you in the bowelis of Jhesu Crist.
29355	50	1	9	And this thing Y preie, that youre charite be plenteuouse more and more in kunnyng, and in al wit;
29356	50	1	10	that ye preue the betere thingis, that ye be clene and without offence in the dai of Crist;
29357	50	1	11	fillid with the fruyt of riytwysnesse bi Jhesu Crist, in to the glory and the heriyng of God.
29358	50	1	12	For, britheren, Y wole that ye wite, that the thingis that ben aboute me han comun more to the profit of the gospel,
29359	50	1	13	so that my boondis weren maad knowun in Crist, in ech moot halle, and in alle other placis;
29360	50	1	14	that mo of britheren tristinge in the Lord more plenteuously for my boondis, dursten without drede speke the word of God.
29361	50	1	15	But summe for enuye and strijf, summe for good wille, prechen Crist;
29362	50	1	16	and summe of charite, witinge that Y am put in the defense of the gospel.
29363	50	1	17	But summe of strijf schewen Crist not cleneli, gessynge hem to reise tribulacioun to my boondis.
29364	50	1	18	But what? the while on al maner, ethir bi occasioun, ethir bi treuthe, Crist is schewid; and in this thing Y haue ioye, but also Y schal haue ioye.
29365	50	1	19	And Y woot, that this thing schal come to me in to heelthe bi youre preyer, and the vndurmynystring of the spirit of `Jhesu Crist, bi myn abidyng and hope.
29366	50	1	20	For in no thing Y schal be schamed, but in al trist as euere more and now, Crist schal be magnefied in my bodi, ether bi lijf, ether bi deth.
29367	50	1	21	For me to lyue is Crist, and to die is wynnyng.
29368	50	1	22	That if to lyue in fleisch, is fruyt of werk to me, lo! what Y schal chese, Y knowe not.
29369	50	1	23	But Y am constreyned of twei thingis, Y haue desire to be dissolued, and to be with Crist, it is myche more betere; but to dwelle in fleisch,
29370	50	1	24	is nedeful for you.
29371	50	1	25	And Y tristinge this thing, woot that Y schal dwelle, and perfitli dwelle to alle you, to youre profit and ioye of feith,
29372	50	1	26	that youre thanking abounde in Crist Jhesu in me, bi my comyng eftsoone to you.
29373	50	1	27	Oneli lyue ye worthili to the gospel of Crist, that whether whanne Y come and se you, ethir absent Y here of you, that ye stonden in o spirit of o wille, trauelinge togidere to the feith of the gospel.
29374	50	1	28	And in no thing be ye aferd of aduersaries, which is to hem cause of perdicioun,
29375	50	1	29	but to you cause of heelthe. And this thing is of God. For it is youun to you for Crist, that not oneli ye bileuen in hym, but also that ye suffren for hym;
29376	50	1	30	hauynge the same strijf, which ye saien in me, and now ye han herd of me.
29377	50	2	1	Therfor if ony coumfort is in Crist, if ony solace of charite, if ony felouschipe of spirit, if ony inwardnesse of merci doyng,
29378	50	2	2	fille ye my ioye, that ye vndurstonde the same thing, and haue the same charite, of o wille, and feelen the same thing;
29379	50	2	3	no thing bi strijf, nether by veyn glorie, but in mekenesse, demynge eche othere to be heiyer than hym silf;
29380	50	2	4	not biholdinge ech bi hym silf what thingis ben his owne, but tho thingis that ben of othere men.
29381	50	2	5	And fele ye this thing in you, which also in Crist Jhesu;
29382	50	2	6	that whanne he was in the forme of God, demyde not raueyn, that hym silf were euene to God;
29383	50	2	7	but he lowide hym silf, takinge the forme of a seruaunt, and was maad in to the licknesse of men, and in abite was foundun as a man.
29384	50	2	8	He mekide hym silf, and was maad obedient to the deth, yhe, to the deth of the cross.
29385	50	2	9	For which thing God enhaunside hym, and yaf to hym a name that is aboue al name;
29386	50	2	10	that in the name of Jhesu ech kne be bowid, of heuenli thingis, of ertheli thingis, and of hellis;
29387	50	2	11	and ech tunge knouleche, that the Lord Jhesu Crist is in the glorie of God the fadir.
29388	50	2	12	Therfor, my most dereworthe britheren, as euere more ye han obeischid, not in my presence onely, but myche more now in myn absence, worche ye with drede and trembling youre heelthe.
29389	50	2	13	For it is God that worchith in you, bothe to wilne, and to performe, for good wille.
29390	50	2	14	And do ye alle thingis with out grutchingis and doutyngis;
29391	50	2	15	that ye be with out playnt, and symple as the sones of God, with out repreef, in the myddil of a schrewid nacioun and a weiward; among whiche ye schynen as yyueris of liyt in the world.
29392	50	2	16	And holde ye togidere the word of lijf to my glorie in the day of Crist; for Y haue not runnen in veyn, nether Y haue trauelid in veyn.
29393	50	2	17	But thouy Y be offrid or slayn on the sacrifice and seruyce of youre feith, Y haue ioye, and Y thanke you alle.
29394	50	2	18	And the same thing haue ye ioye, and thanke ye me.
29395	50	2	19	And Y hope in the Lord Jhesu, that Y schal sende Tymothe soone to you, that Y be of good coumfort, whanne tho thingis ben knowun that ben aboute you.
29396	50	2	20	For Y haue no man so of o wille, that is bisi for you with clene affeccioun.
29397	50	2	21	For alle men seken tho thingis that ben her owne, not tho that ben of Crist Jhesu.
29398	50	2	22	But knowe ye the asaie of hym, for as a sone to the fadir he hath seruyd with me in the gospel.
29399	50	2	23	Therfor Y hope that Y schal sende hym to you, anoon as Y se what thingis ben aboute me.
29400	50	2	24	And Y triste in the Lord, that also my silf schal come to you soone.
29401	50	2	25	And Y gesside it nedeful to sende to you Epafrodite, my brother and euene worchere, and myn euene knyyt, but youre apostle, and the mynystre of my nede.
29402	50	2	26	For he desiride you alle, and he was sorewful, therfor that ye herden that he was sijk.
29403	50	2	27	For he was sijk to the deth, but God hadde merci on him; and not oneli on hym, but also on me, lest Y hadde heuynesse on heuynesse.
29404	50	2	28	Therfor more hastili Y sente hym, that whanne ye han seyn hym, ye haue ioye eft, and Y be withouten heuynesse.
29405	50	2	29	Therfor resseyue ye hym with al ioye in the Lord, and haue ye suche with al onour.
29406	50	2	30	For the werk of Crist he wente to deth, yyuynge his lijf, that he schulde fulfille that that failide of you anentis my seruyce.
29407	50	3	1	Hennus forward, my britheren, haue ye ioye in the Lord. To write to you the same thingis, to me it is not slow, and to you it is necessarie.
29408	50	3	2	Se ye houndis, se ye yuele werk men, se ye dyuysioun.
29409	50	3	3	For we ben circumcisioun, which bi spirit seruen to God, and glorien in Crist Jhesu, and han not trist in the fleisch,
29410	50	3	4	thouy Y haue trust, yhe, in the fleisch. If ony othere man is seyn to triste in the fleisch,
29411	50	3	5	Y more, that was circumcidid in the eiytthe dai, of the kyn of Israel, of the lynage of Beniamyn, an Ebrew of Ebrewis, bi the lawe a Farisee,
29412	50	3	6	bi loue pursuynge the chirche of God, bi riytwisnesse that is in the lawe lyuynge with out playnt.
29413	50	3	7	But whiche thingis weren to me wynnyngis, Y haue demed these apeyryngis for Crist.
29414	50	3	8	Netheles Y gesse alle thingis to be peirement for the cleer science of Jhesu Crist my Lord. For whom Y made alle thingis peyrement, and Y deme as drit,
29415	50	3	9	that Y wynne Crist, and that Y be foundun in hym, not hauynge my riytwisnesse that is of the lawe, but that that is of the feith of Crist Jhesu, that is of God the riytwisnesse in feith,
29416	50	3	10	to knowe hym, and the vertu of his risyng ayen, and the felouschipe of his passioun, and be maad lijk to his deeth,
29417	50	3	11	if on ony maner Y come to the resurreccioun that is fro deth.
29418	50	3	12	Not that now Y haue takun, or now am parfit; but Y sue, if in ony maner Y comprehende, in which thing also Y am comprehendid of Crist Jhesu.
29419	50	3	13	Bretheren, Y deme me not that Y haue comprehendid; but o thing, Y foryete tho thingis that ben bihyndis, and stretche forth my silf to tho thingis that ben bifore,
29420	50	3	14	and pursue to the ordeyned mede of the hiy clepyng of God in Crist Jhesu.
29421	50	3	15	Therfor who euere we ben perfit, feele we this thing. And if ye vndurstonden in othere manere ony thing, this thing God schal schewe to you.
29422	50	3	16	Netheles to what thing we han comun, that we vndurstonden the same thing, and that we perfitli dwelle in the same reule.
29423	50	3	17	Britheren, be ye my foleweris, and weyte ye hem that walken so, as ye han oure fourme.
29424	50	3	18	For many walken, whiche Y haue seid ofte to you, but now Y wepinge seie, the enemyes of Cristis cros,
29425	50	3	19	who ende is deth, whos god is the wombe, and the glorie in confusioun of hem, that saueren ertheli thingis.
29426	50	3	20	But oure lyuyng is in heuenes; fro whennus also we abiden the sauyour oure Lord Jhesu Crist,
29427	50	3	21	which schal reforme the bodi of oure mekenesse, that is maad lijk to the bodi of his clerenesse, bi the worching bi which he mai `also make alle thingis suget to hym.
29428	50	4	1	Therfor, my britheren most dereworthe and most desirid, my ioye and my coroun, so stonde ye in the Lord, most dere britheren.
29429	50	4	2	Y preye Eucodiam, and biseche Synticem, to vndurstonde the same thing in the Lord.
29430	50	4	3	Also Y preye and thee, german felow, helpe thou the ilke wymmen that traueliden with me in the gospel, with Clement and othere myn helperis, whos names ben in the book of lijf.
29431	50	4	4	Ioye ye in the Lord euere more; eft Y seie, ioye ye.
29432	50	4	5	Be youre pacyence knowun to alle men; the Lord is niy.
29433	50	4	6	Be ye nothing bisi, but in al preyer and biseching, with doyng of thankyngis, be youre axyngis knowun at God.
29434	50	4	7	And the pees of God, that passith al wit, kepe youre hertis and vndurstondingis in Crist Jhesu.
29435	50	4	8	Fro hennus forth, britheren, what euere thingis ben sothe, what euere thingis chast, what euere thingis iust, what euere thingis hooli, what euere thingis able to be louyd, what euere thingis of good fame, if ony vertu, if ony preising of discipline, thenke ye these thingis,
29436	50	4	9	that also ye han lerud, and take, and heed, and seyn in me. Do ye these thingis, and God of pees schal be with you.
29437	50	4	10	But Y ioyede greetli in the Lord, that sum tyme aftirward ye floureden ayen to feele for me, as also ye feeliden. But ye weren ocupied, Y seie not as for nede,
29438	50	4	11	for Y haue lerud to be sufficient in whiche thingis Y am.
29439	50	4	12	And Y can also be lowid, Y can also haue plentee. Euery where and in alle thingis Y am tauyt to be fillid, and to hungur, and to abounde, and to suffre myseiste.
29440	50	4	13	Y may alle thingis in hym that coumfortith me.
29441	50	4	14	Netheles ye han doon wel, comynynge to my tribulacioun.
29442	50	4	15	For and ye, Filipensis, witen, that in the bigynnyng of the gospel, whanne Y wente forth fro Macedonye, no chirche comynede with me in resoun of thing youun and takun, but ye aloone.
29443	50	4	16	Whiche senten to Tessalonyk onys and twies also in to vss to me.
29444	50	4	17	Not for Y seke yifte, but Y requyre fruyt aboundinge in youre resoun.
29445	50	4	18	For Y haue alle thingis, and abounde; Y am fillid with tho thingis takun of Epafrodite, whiche ye senten in to the odour of swetnesse, a couenable sacrifice, plesynge to God.
29446	50	4	19	And my God fil alle youre desire, by hise richessis in glorie in Crist Jhesu.
29447	50	4	20	But to God and oure fadir be glorie in to worldis of worldis.
29448	50	4	21	Amen. Grete ye wel euery hooli man in Crist Jhesu.
29449	50	4	22	Tho britheren that ben with me, greten you wel. Alle hooli men greten you wel, moost sotheli thei that ben of the emperouris hous.
29450	50	4	23	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with youre spirit. Amen.
29451	51	1	1	Poul, apostle of `Crist Jhesu, bi the wille of God,
29452	51	1	2	and Tymothe, brother, to hem that ben at Colose, hooli and feithful britheren in Crist Jhesu,
29453	51	1	3	grace and pees to you of God oure fadir and of the Lord Jhesu Crist. We don thankyngis to God, and to the fader of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, euermore preiynge for you, herynge youre feith in Crist Jhesu,
29454	51	1	4	and the loue that ye han to alle hooli men,
29455	51	1	5	for the hope that is kept to you in heuenes. Which ye herden in the word of treuthe of the gospel,
29456	51	1	6	that cam to you, as also it is in al the world, and makith fruyt, and wexith, as in you, fro that dai in which ye herden and knewen the grace of God in treuthe.
29457	51	1	7	As ye lerneden of Epafras, oure felawe most dereworthe, which is a trewe mynystre of Jhesu Crist for you;
29458	51	1	8	which also schewide to vs youre louyng in spirit.
29459	51	1	9	Therfor we fro the dai in which we herden, ceessen not to preye for you, and to axe, that ye be fillid with the knowing of his wille in al wisdom and goostli vndurstondyng;
29460	51	1	10	that ye walke worthili to God plesynge bi alle thingis, and make fruyt in al good werk, and wexe in the science of God,
29461	51	1	11	and ben coumfortid in al vertu bi the miyt of his clerenesse, in al pacience and long abiding with ioye,
29462	51	1	12	that ye do thankyngis to God and to the fadir, which made you worthi in to the part of eritage of hooli men in liyt.
29463	51	1	13	Which delyueride vs fro the power of derknessis, and translatide in to the kyngdom of the sone of his louyng,
29464	51	1	14	in whom we han ayenbiyng and remyssioun of synnes.
29465	51	1	15	Which is the ymage of God vnuysible, the first bigetun of ech creature.
29466	51	1	16	For in hym alle thingis ben maad, in heuenes and in erthe, visible and vnuysible, ether trones, ether dominaciouns, ether princehodes, ethir poweris, alle thingis ben maad of nouyt bi hym, and in hym,
29467	51	1	17	and he is bifor alle, and alle thingis ben in hym.
29468	51	1	18	And he is heed of the bodi of the chirche; which is the bigynnyng and the firste bigetun of deede men, that he holde the firste dignyte in alle thingis.
29469	51	1	19	For in hym it pleside al plente to inhabite,
29470	51	1	20	and bi hym alle thingis to be recounselid in to hym, and made pees bi the blood of his cros, tho thingis that ben in erthis, ether that ben in heuenes.
29471	51	1	21	And whanne ye weren sumtyme aliened, and enemyes bi wit in yuele werkis,
29472	51	1	22	now he hath recounselid you in the bodi of his fleisch bi deth, to haue you hooli, and vnwemmyd, and with out repreef bifor hym.
29473	51	1	23	If netheles ye dwellen in the feith, foundid, and stable, and vnmouable fro the hope of the gospel that ye han herd, which is prechid in al creature that is vndur heuene. Of which Y Poul am maad mynystre,
29474	51	1	24	and now Y haue ioye in passioun for you, and Y fille tho thingis that failen of the passiouns of Crist in my fleisch, for his bodi, that is the chirche.
29475	51	1	25	Of which Y Poul am maad mynystre bi the dispensacioun of God, that is youun to me in you,
29476	51	1	26	that Y fille the word of God, the priuyte, that was hid fro worldis and generaciouns. But now it is schewid to his seyntis,
29477	51	1	27	to whiche God wold make knowun the richessis of the glorie of this sacrament in hethene men, which is Crist in you, the hope of glorie.
29478	51	1	28	Whom we schewen, repreuynge ech man, and techinge `ech man in al wisdom, that we offre ech man perfit in Crist Jhesu.
29479	51	1	29	In which thing also Y trauele in stryuynge bi the worching of hym, that he worchith in me in vertu.
29480	51	2	1	But Y wole that ye wite, what bisynesse Y haue for you, and for hem that ben at Laodice, and whiche euere saien not my face in fleisch,
29481	51	2	2	that her hertis ben coumfortid, and thei ben tauyt in charite, in to alle the richessis of the plente of the vndurstondyng, in to the knowyng of mysterie of God, the fadir of Jhesu Crist,
29482	51	2	3	in whom alle the tresouris of wisdom and of science ben hid.
29483	51	2	4	For this thing Y seie, that no man disseyue you in heiythe of wordis.
29484	51	2	5	For thouy Y be absent in bodi, bi spirit Y am with you, ioiynge and seynge youre ordre and the sadnesse of youre bileue that is in Crist.
29485	51	2	6	Therfor as ye han takun Jhesu Crist oure Lord,
29486	51	2	7	walke ye in hym, and be ye rootid and bieldid aboue in hym, and confermyd in the bileue, as ye han lerud, aboundinge in hym in doynge of thankyngis.
29487	51	2	8	Se ye that no man disseyue you bi filosofie and veyn fallace, aftir the tradicioun of men, aftir the elementis of the world, and not aftir Crist.
29488	51	2	9	For in hym dwellith bodilich al the fulnesse of the Godhed.
29489	51	2	10	And ye ben fillid in hym, that is heed of al principat and power.
29490	51	2	11	In whom also ye ben circumcidid in circumcisioun not maad with hoond, in dispoyling of the bodi of fleisch, but in circumcisioun of Crist;
29491	51	2	12	and ye ben biried togidere with hym in baptim, in whom also ye han rise ayen bi feith of the worching of God, that reiside hym fro deth.
29492	51	2	13	And whanne ye weren deed in giltis, and in the prepucie of youre fleisch, he quikenyde togidere you with hym;
29493	51	2	14	foryyuynge to you alle giltis, doynge awei that writing of decre that was ayens vs, that was contrarie to vs; and he took awei that fro the myddil, pitchinge it on the cros;
29494	51	2	15	and he spuylide principatis and poweris, and ledde out tristili, opynli ouercomynge hem in hym silf.
29495	51	2	16	Therfor no man iuge you in mete, or in drink, or in part of feeste dai, or of neomenye,
29496	51	2	17	or of sabatis, whiche ben schadewe of thingis to comynge; for the bodi is of Crist.
29497	51	2	18	No man disseyue you, willynge to teche in mekenesse, and religioun of aungelis, tho thingis whiche he hath not seyn, walkinge veynli, bolnyd with wit of his fleisch,
29498	51	2	19	and not holdynge the heed, of which al the bodi, bi boondis and ioynyngis togidere vndur mynystrid and maad, wexith in to encreessing of God.
29499	51	2	20	For if ye ben deed with Crist fro the elementis of this world, what yit as men lyuynge to the world demen ye?
29500	51	2	21	That ye touche not, nether taaste,
29501	51	2	22	nether trete with hoondis tho thingis, whiche alle ben in to deth bi the ilke vss, aftir the comaundementis and the techingis of men;
29502	51	2	23	whiche han a resoun of wisdom in veyn religioun and mekenesse, and not to spare the bodi, not in ony onour to the fulfillyng of the fleisch.
29503	51	3	1	Therfor if ye han risun togidere with Crist, seke ye tho thingis that ben aboue, where Crist is sittynge in the riythalf of God.
29504	51	3	2	Sauere ye tho thingis, that ben aboue, not tho that ben on the erthe.
29505	51	3	3	For ye ben deed, and youre lijf is hid with Crist in God.
29506	51	3	4	For whanne Crist schal appere, youre lijf, thanne also ye schulen appere with hym in glorie.
29507	51	3	5	Therfor sle ye youre membris, whiche ben on the erthe, fornycacioun, vnclennesse, letcherie, yuel coueitise, and aueryse, which is seruyse of mawmetis;
29508	51	3	6	for whiche thingis the wraththe of God cam on the sones of vnbileue;
29509	51	3	7	in whiche also ye walkiden sum tyme, whanne ye lyueden in hem.
29510	51	3	8	But now putte ye awei alle thingis, wraththe, indignacioun, malice, blasfemye and foule word of youre mouth.
29511	51	3	9	Nyle ye lie togidere; spuyle ye you fro the elde man with his dedes, and clothe ye the newe man,
29512	51	3	10	that is maad newe ayen in to the knowing of God, aftir the ymage of hym that made hym;
29513	51	3	11	where is not male and female, hethene man and Jew, circumcisioun and prepucie, barbarus and Scita, bonde man and fre man, but alle thingis and in alle thingis Crist.
29514	51	3	12	Therfor ye, as the chosun of God, hooli and louyd, clothe you with the entrailis of merci, benygnite, and mekenesse, temperaunce, pacience;
29515	51	3	13	and support ye echon other, and foryyue to you silf, if ony man ayens ony hath a querele; as the Lord foryaf to you, so also ye.
29516	51	3	14	And vpon alle these thingis haue ye charite, that is the boond of perfeccioun.
29517	51	3	15	And the pees of Crist enioye in youre hertis, in which ye ben clepid in o bodi, and be ye kynde.
29518	51	3	16	The word of Crist dwelle in you plenteuousli, in al wisdom; and teche and moneste you silf in salmes, and ympnes, and spiritual songis, in grace synginge in youre hertis to the Lord.
29519	51	3	17	Al thing, what euere thing ye don, in word or in dede, alle thingis in the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, doynge thankyngis to God and to the fadir bi hym.
29520	51	3	18	Wymmen, be ye sugetis to youre hosebondis, as it bihoueth in the Lord.
29521	51	3	19	Men, loue ye youre wyues, and nyle ye be bittere to hem.
29522	51	3	20	Sones, obeie ye to youre fadir and modir bi alle thingis; for this is wel plesinge in the Lord.
29523	51	3	21	Fadris, nyle ye terre youre sones to indignacioun, that thei be not maad feble hertid.
29524	51	3	22	Seruauntis, obeie ye bi alle thingis to fleischli lordis, not seruynge at iye, as plesynge to men, but in symplenesse of herte, dredinge the Lord.
29525	51	3	23	What euer ye doen, worche ye of wille, as to the Lord and not to men;
29526	51	3	24	witinge that of the Lord ye schulen take yelding of eritage. Serue ye to the Lord Crist.
29527	51	3	25	For he that doith iniurie, schal resseyue that that he dide yuele; and acceptacioun of persoones is not anentis God.
29528	51	4	1	Lordis, yyue ye to seruauntis that that is iust and euene, witinge that also ye han a Lord in heuene.
29529	51	4	2	Be ye bisi in preier, and wake in it, in doynge of thankyngis;
29530	51	4	3	and preie ech for othere, and for vs, that God opene to vs the dore of word, to speke the misterie of Crist;
29531	51	4	4	for which also Y am boundun, that Y schewe it, so as it bihoueth me to speke.
29532	51	4	5	Walke ye in wisdom to hem that ben with outen forth, ayenbiynge tyme.
29533	51	4	6	Youre word be sauered in salt eueremore in grace; that ye wite, hou it bihoueth you to answere to ech man.
29534	51	4	7	Titicus, most dere brother, and feithful mynyster, and my felowe in the Lord, schal make alle thingis knowun to you, that ben aboute me.
29535	51	4	8	Whom Y sente to you to this same thing, that he knowe what thingis ben aboute you, and coumforte youre hertis, with Onesyme,
29536	51	4	9	most dere and feithful brother, which is of you; whiche schulen make alle thingis that ben doon here, knowun to you.
29537	51	4	10	Aristark, prisoner with me, gretith you wel, and Mark, the cosyn of Barnabas, of whom ye han take maundementis; if he come to you, resseyue ye hym;
29538	51	4	11	and Jhesus, that is seid Just; whiche ben of circumcisioun; thei aloone ben myn helperis in the kingdom of God, that weren to me in solace.
29539	51	4	12	Epafras, that is of you, the seruaunt of Jhesu Crist, gretith you wel; euere bisi for you in preyeris, that ye stonde perfit and ful in al the wille of God.
29540	51	4	13	And Y bere witnessyng to hym, that he hath myche trauel for you, and for hem that ben at Loadice, and that ben at Ierapolim.
29541	51	4	14	Luk, the leche most dere, and Demas, greten you wel.
29542	51	4	15	Grete ye wel the britheren that ben at Loadice, and the womman Nynfam, and the chirche that is in hir hous.
29543	51	4	16	And whanne this pistle is red among you, do ye, that it be red in the chirche of Loadicensis; and rede ye that pistle that is of Loadicensis.
29544	51	4	17	And seie ye to Archippus, Se the mynysterie, that thou hast takun in the Lord, that thou fille it.
29545	51	4	18	My salutacioun, bi the hoond of Poul. Be ye myndeful of my boondis. The grace of the Lord Jhesu Crist be with you. Amen.
29546	52	1	1	Poul, and Siluan, and Tymothe, to the chirche of Tessalonicensis, in God the fadir,
29547	52	1	2	and in the Lord Jhesu Crist, grace and pees to you. We doon thankyngis to God euere more for alle you, and we maken mynde of you in oure preyeris withouten ceessyng;
29548	52	1	3	hauynge mynde of the werk of youre feith, and trauel, and charite, and abyding of the hope of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, bifor God and oure fadir.
29549	52	1	4	Ye louyde britheren of God, we witinge youre chesing;
29550	52	1	5	for oure gospel was not at you in word oneli, but also in vertu, and in the Hooli Goost, and in myche plente; as ye witen, whiche we weren among you for you;
29551	52	1	6	and ye ben maad foleweris of vs, and of the Lord, resseyuynge the word in myche tribulacioun, with ioye of the Hooli Goost;
29552	52	1	7	so that ye ben maad ensaumple to alle men that bileuen, in Macedonye and in Acaie.
29553	52	1	8	For of you the word of the Lord is pupplischid, not oneli in Macedonye and Acaie, but youre feith that is to God, in ech place is gon forth; so that it is not nede to vs to speke ony thing.
29554	52	1	9	For thei schewen of you, what maner entre we hadden to you, and hou ye ben conuertid to God fro maumettis, to serue to the lyuynge God and veri; and to abide his sone fro heuenes,
29555	52	1	10	whom he reiside fro deth, the Lord Jhesu, that delyuerede us fro wraththe to comynge.
29556	52	2	1	For, britheren, ye witen oure entre to you, for it was not veyn;
29557	52	2	2	but first we suffriden, and weren punyschid with wrongis, as ye witen in Filippis, and hadden trust in oure Lord, to speke to you the gospel of God in myche bisynesse.
29558	52	2	3	And oure exortacioun is not of errour, nether of vnclennesse, nether in gile,
29559	52	2	4	but as we ben preued of God, that the gospel of God schulde be takun to vs, so we speken; not as plesynge to men, but to God that preueth oure hertis.
29560	52	2	5	For nether we weren ony tyme in word of glosing, as ye witen, nether in occasioun of auerise; God is witnesse; nether sekinge glorie of men,
29561	52	2	6	nether of you,
29562	52	2	7	nether of othere, whanne we, as Cristis apostlis, miyten haue be in charge to you. But we weren maad litle in the myddil of you, as if a nursche fostre hir sones;
29563	52	2	8	so we desiringe you with greet loue, wolden haue bitake to you, not oneli the gospel of God, but also oure lyues, for ye ben maad most dereworthe to vs.
29564	52	2	9	For, britheren, ye ben myndeful of oure trauel and werynesse; we worchiden nyyt and day, that we schulden not greue ony of you, and prechiden to you the euangelie of God.
29565	52	2	10	God and ye ben witnessis, hou holili, and iustli, and with outen pleynt, we weren to you that bileueden.
29566	52	2	11	As ye witen, hou we preyeden you, and coumfortiden ech of you, as the fadir hise sones,
29567	52	2	12	and we han witnessid, that ye schulden go worthili to God, that clepide you in to his kingdom and glorie.
29568	52	2	13	Therfor we doon thankingis to God with outen ceessyng. For whanne ye hadden take of vs the word `of the heryng of God, ye token it not as the word of men, but as `it is verili, the word of God, that worchith in you that han bileued.
29569	52	2	14	For, britheren, ye ben maad foleweris of the chirchis of God, that ben in Jude, in Crist Jhesu, for ye han suffrid the same thingis of youre euene lynagis, as thei of the Jewis.
29570	52	2	15	Whiche slowen bothe the Lord Jhesu and the profetis, and pursueden vs, and thei plesen not to God, and thei ben aduersaries to alle men;
29571	52	2	16	forbedinge vs to speke to hethene men, that thei be maad saaf, that thei fille her synnes euere more; for the wraththe of God cam on hem in to the ende.
29572	52	2	17	And, britheren, we desolat fro you for a tyme, bi mouth and in biholding, but not in herte, han hiyed more plenteuousli to se youre face with greet desir.
29573	52	2	18	For we wolden come to you, yhe, Y Poul, onys and eftsoone, but Sathanas lettide vs.
29574	52	2	19	For whi what is oure hope, or ioye, or coroun of glorie? Whether ye ben not bifore oure Lord Jhesu Crist in his comyng?
29575	52	2	20	For ye ben oure glorie and ioye.
29576	52	3	1	For which thing we suffriden no lengere, and it pleside to vs to dwelle aloone at Atenys;
29577	52	3	2	and we senten Tymothe, oure brother, and mynystre of God in the euangelie of Crist, to you to be confermyd, and to be tauyt for youre feith,
29578	52	3	3	that no man be mouyd in these tribulaciouns. For ye silf witen, that in this this thing we ben set.
29579	52	3	4	For whanne we weren at you, we biforseiden to you, that we schulden suffre tribulaciouns; as it is don, and ye witen.
29580	52	3	5	Therfor Y Poul, no lenger abidinge, sente to knowe youre feith, lest perauenture he that temptith tempte you, and youre trauel be maad veyn.
29581	52	3	6	But now, whanne Tymothe schal come to vs fro you, and telle to vs youre feith and charite, and that ye han good mynde of vs, euere desyringe to se vs, as we also you;
29582	52	3	7	therfor, britheren, we ben coumfortid in you, in al oure nede and tribulacioun, bi youre feith.
29583	52	3	8	For now we lyuen, if ye stonden in the Lord.
29584	52	3	9	For what doyng of thankingis moun we yelde to God for you, in al ioye, in which we ioyen for you bifor oure Lord?
29585	52	3	10	nyyt and dai more plenteuousli preiynge, that we se youre face, and fulfille tho thingis that failen to youre feith.
29586	52	3	11	But God hym silf and oure fadir, and the Lord Jhesu Crist, dresse oure weye to you.
29587	52	3	12	And the Lord multiplie you, and make youre charite to be plenteuouse of ech to othere, and in to alle men, as also we in you;
29588	52	3	13	that youre hertis ben confermyd with outen pleynt in holynesse, bifor God and oure fadir, in the comyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist with alle hise seyntis. Amen.
29589	52	4	1	Therfor, britheren, fro hennus forward we preien you, and bisechen in the Lord Jhesu, that as ye han resseyued of vs, hou it bihoueth you to go and to plese God, so walke ye, that ye abounde the more.
29590	52	4	2	For ye witen what comaundementis Y haue youun to you bi the Lord Jhesu.
29591	52	4	3	For this is the wille of God, youre holynesse, that ye absteyne you fro fornycacioun.
29592	52	4	4	That ech of you kunne welde his vessel in holynesse, and onour;
29593	52	4	5	not in passioun of lust, as hethene men that knowen not God.
29594	52	4	6	And that no man ouergo, nethir disseyue his brothir in chaffaring. For the Lord is venger of alle these thingis, as we biforseiden to you, and han witnessid.
29595	52	4	7	For God clepide not vs in to vnclennesse, but in to holynesse.
29596	52	4	8	Therfor he that dispisith these thingis, dispisith not man, but God, that also yaf his holi spirit in vs.
29597	52	4	9	But of the charite of britherhed we hadden no nede to write to you; ye silf han lerud of God, that ye loue togidere;
29598	52	4	10	for ye don that in to alle britheren in al Macedonye. And, britheren, we preyen you, that ye abounde more; and taken kepe, that ye be quyet;
29599	52	4	11	and that ye do youre nede, and `ye worche with youre hoondis, as we han comaundid to you; and that ye wandre onestli to hem that ben with outforth, and that of no mannus ye desir ony thing.
29600	52	4	12	For, britheren, we wolen not, that ye vnknowe of men that dien, that ye be not soreuful, as othere that han not hope.
29601	52	4	13	For if we bileuen, that Jhesu was deed, and roos ayen, so God schal lede with hym hem that ben deed bi Jhesu.
29602	52	4	14	And we seien this thing to you in the word of the Lord, that we that lyuen, that ben left in the comyng of the Lord, schulen not come bifor hem that ben deed.
29603	52	4	15	For the Lord hym silf schal come doun fro heuene, in the comaundement, and in the vois of an archaungel, and in the trumpe of God; and the deed men that ben in Crist, schulen rise ayen first.
29604	52	4	16	Afterward we that lyuen, that ben left, schulen be rauyschid togidere with hem in cloudis, metinge Crist `in to the eir; and so euere more we schulen be with the Lord.
29605	52	4	17	Therfor be ye coumfortid togidere in these wordis.
29606	52	5	1	But, britheren, of tymes and momentis ye neden not that Y write to you.
29607	52	5	2	For ye silf witen diligentli, that the dai of the Lord schal come, as a theef in the niyt.
29608	52	5	3	For whanne thei schulen seie pees is, and sikirnesse, thanne sudeyn deth schal come on hem, as sorewe to a womman that is with child, and thei schulen not scape.
29609	52	5	4	But, britheren, ye ben not in derknessis, that the ilke dai as a theef catche you.
29610	52	5	5	For alle ye ben the sones of liyt, and sones of dai; we ben not of niyt, nether of derknessis.
29611	52	5	6	Therfor slepe we not as othere; but wake we, and be we sobre.
29612	52	5	7	For thei that slepen, slepen in the niyt, and thei that ben drunkun, ben drunkun in the niyt.
29613	52	5	8	But we that ben of the dai, ben sobre, clothid in the haburioun of feith and of charite, and in the helme of hope of heelthe.
29614	52	5	9	For God puttide not vs in to wraththe, but in to the purchasing of heelthe bi oure Lord Jhesu Crist, that was deed for vs;
29615	52	5	10	that whether we waken, whether we slepen, we lyue togidere with him.
29616	52	5	11	For which thing comforte ye togidere, and edefie ye ech other, as ye doon.
29617	52	5	12	And, britheren, we preien you, that ye knowen hem that trauelen among you, and ben souereyns to you in the Lord, and techen you,
29618	52	5	13	that ye han hem more aboundantli in charyte; and for the werk of hem, haue ye pees with hem.
29619	52	5	14	And, britheren, we preien you, repreue ye vnpesible men. Coumforte ye men of litil herte, resseyue ye sijke men, be ye pacient to alle men.
29620	52	5	15	Se ye, that no man yelde yuel for yuel to ony man; but euere more sue ye that that is good, ech to othere and to alle men.
29621	52	5	16	Euere more ioye ye; without ceessing preye ye;
29622	52	5	17	in alle thingis do ye thankyngis.
29623	52	5	18	For this is the wille of God in Crist Jhesu, in alle you.
29624	52	5	19	Nyle ye quenche the spirit;
29625	52	5	20	nyle ye dispise prophecies.
29626	52	5	21	But preue ye alle thingis, and holde ye that thing that is good.
29627	52	5	22	Absteyne you fro al yuel spice.
29628	52	5	23	And God hym silf of pees make you hooli bi alle thingis, that youre spirit be kept hool, and soule, and bodi, without pleynt, in the comyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29629	52	5	24	God is trewe, that clepide you, which also schal do.
29630	52	5	25	Britheren, preye ye for vs.
29631	52	5	26	Grete ye wel alle britheren in hooli cos.
29632	52	5	27	Y coniure you bi the Lord, that this pistle be red to alle hooli britheren.
29633	52	5	28	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with you. Amen.
29634	53	1	1	Poul, and Siluan, and Tymothe, to the chirche of Tessalonicensis, in God oure fadir,
29635	53	1	2	and in the Lord Jhesu Crist, grace to you and pees of God, oure fadir, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
29636	53	1	3	We owen to do thankyngis eueremore to God for you, britheren, so as it is worthi, for youre feith ouer wexith, and the charite of ech of you to othere aboundith.
29637	53	1	4	So that we silf glorien in you in the chirchis of God, for youre pacience and feith in alle youre persecuciouns and tribulaciouns.
29638	53	1	5	Whiche ye susteynen in to the ensaumple of the iust dom of God, that ye be had worthi in the kingdom of God, for which ye suffren.
29639	53	1	6	If netheles it is iust tofor God to quite tribulacioun to hem that troblen you,
29640	53	1	7	and to you that ben troblid, rest with vs in the schewing of the Lord Jhesu fro heuene, with aungelis of his vertu,
29641	53	1	8	in the flawme of fier, that schal yyue veniaunce to hem that knowen not God, and that obeien not to the euangelie of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29642	53	1	9	Whiche schulen suffre euere lastinge peynes, in perischinge fro the face of the Lord, and fro the glorie of his vertu,
29643	53	1	10	whanne he schal come to be glorified in hise seyntis, and to be maad wondurful in alle men that bileueden, for oure witnessing is bileuyd on you, in that dai.
29644	53	1	11	In which thing also we preien euere more for you, that oure God make you worthi to his cleping, and fille al the wille of his goodnesse, and the werk of feith in vertu;
29645	53	1	12	that the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be clarified in you, and ye in hym, bi the grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29646	53	2	1	But, britheren, we preien you bi the comyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and of oure congregacioun in to the same comyng,
29647	53	2	2	that ye be not mouyd soone fro youre witt, nether be aferd, nether bi spirit, nether bi word, nether bi epistle as sent bi vs, as if the dai of the Lord be nyy.
29648	53	2	3	No man disseyue you in ony manere. For but dissencioun come first, and the man of synne be schewid, the sonne of perdicioun,
29649	53	2	4	that is aduersarie, and is enhaunsid ouer `al thing that is seid God, or that is worschipid, so that he sitte in the temple of God, and schewe hym silf as if he were God.
29650	53	2	5	Whether ye holden not, that yit whanne Y was at you, Y seide these thingis to you?
29651	53	2	6	And now what withholdith, ye witen, that he be schewid in his tyme.
29652	53	2	7	For the priuete of wickidnesse worchith now; oneli that he that holdith now, holde, til he be do awei.
29653	53	2	8	And thanne thilke wickid man schal be schewid, whom the Lord Jhesu schal sle with the spirit of his mouth, and schal distrie with liytnyng of his comyng;
29654	53	2	9	hym, whos comyng is bi the worching of Sathanas, in al vertu, and signes,
29655	53	2	10	and grete wondris, false, and in al disseit of wickidnesse, to hem that perischen. For that thei resseyueden not the charite of treuthe, that thei schulden be maad saaf. And therfor God schal sende to hem a worching of errour, that thei bileue to leesing,
29656	53	2	11	that alle be demed, whiche bileueden not to treuthe, but consentiden to wickidnesse.
29657	53	2	12	But, britheren louyd of God, we owen to do thankyngis euermore to God for you, that God chees vs the firste fruytis in to heelthe, in halewing of spirit and in feith of treuthe;
29658	53	2	13	in which also he clepide you bi oure gospel, in to geting of the glorie of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
29659	53	2	14	Therfor, britheren, stonde ye, and holde ye the tradiciouns, that ye han lerud, ethir bi word, ethir bi oure pistle.
29660	53	2	15	And oure Lord Jhesu Crist him silf, and God oure fadir, which louyde vs, and yaf euerlastinge coumfort and good hope in grace, stire youre hertis,
29661	53	2	16	and conferme in al good werk and word.
29662	53	3	1	Britheren, fro hennus forward preye ye for vs, that the word of God renne, and be clarified, as it is anentis you;
29663	53	3	2	and that we be delyuered fro noyous and yuele men; for feith is not of alle men.
29664	53	3	3	But the Lord is trewe, that schal conferme you, and schal kepe fro yuel.
29665	53	3	4	And, britheren, we trusten of you in the Lord, for what euere thingis we comaunden to you, bothe ye don and schulen do.
29666	53	3	5	And the Lord dresse youre hertis, in the charite of God, and in the pacience of Crist.
29667	53	3	6	But, britheren, we denouncen to you in the name of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, that ye withdrawe you from ech brother that wandrith out of ordre, and not aftir the techyng, that thei resseyueden of vs.
29668	53	3	7	For `ye silf witen, hou it bihoueth to sue vs. For we weren not vnpesible among you,
29669	53	3	8	nethir with outen oure owne trauel we eeten breed of ony man, but in trauel and werynesse worchiden niyt and dai, that we greuyden noon of you.
29670	53	3	9	Not as we hadden not power, but that we schulden yyue vs silf ensaumple to you to sue vs.
29671	53	3	10	For also whanne we weren among you, we denounsiden this thing to you, that if ony man wole not worche, nethir ete he.
29672	53	3	11	For we han herd that summe among you goon in reste, and no thing worchen, but don curiousli.
29673	53	3	12	But we denouncen to hem that ben suche men, and bisechen in the Lord Jhesu Crist, that thei worchen with silence, and ete her owne breed.
29674	53	3	13	But nyle ye, britheren, faile wel doynge.
29675	53	3	14	That if ony man obeie not to oure word bi epistle, marke ye him, and comyne ye not with hym, that he be schamed;
29676	53	3	15	and nyle ye gesse hym as an enemye, but repreue ye hym as a brother. And God hym silf of pees yyue to you euerlastinge pees in al place.
29677	53	3	16	The Lord be with `you alle.
29678	53	3	17	My salutacioun bi the hoond of Poul; which signe in ech epistle Y write thus.
29679	53	3	18	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with `alle you. Amen.
29680	54	1	1	Poul, apostle `of Jhesu Crist, bi the comaundement of God oure sauyour, and of Jhesu Crist oure hope,
29681	54	1	2	to Tymothe, bilouyd sone in the feith, grace and merci and pees, of God the fadir, and of Jhesu Crist, oure Lord.
29682	54	1	3	As Y preyede thee, that thou schuldist dwelle at Effesi, whanne Y wente into Macedonye, that thou schuldist denounce to summe men, that thei schulden not teche othere weie,
29683	54	1	4	nether yyue tent to fablis and genologies that ben vncerteyn, whiche yyuen questiouns, more than edificacioun of God, that is in the feith.
29684	54	1	5	For the ende of comaundement is charite of clene herte, and good conscience, and of feith not feyned.
29685	54	1	6	Fro whiche thingis sum men han errid, and ben turned in to veyn speche;
29686	54	1	7	and willith to be techeris of the lawe, and vndurstonden not what thingis thei speken, nether of what thingis thei affermen.
29687	54	1	8	And we witen that the lawe is good, if ony man vse it lawefulli;
29688	54	1	9	and witinge this thing, that the lawe is not set to a iust man, but to vniust men and not suget, to wickid men and to synneris, to cursid men and defoulid, to sleeris of fadir, and sleeris of modir, to `men sleeris and lechouris,
29689	54	1	10	to hem that don letcherie with men, lesingmongeris and forsworun, and if ony othere thing is contrarie to the hoolsum teching,
29690	54	1	11	that is aftir the euangelie of the glorie of blessid God, which is bitakun to me.
29691	54	1	12	Y do thankingis to hym, that coumfortide me in Crist Jhesu oure Lord, for he gesside me feithful, and putte me in mynystrie,
29692	54	1	13	that first was a blasfeme, and a pursuere, and ful of wrongis. But Y haue getun the merci of God, for Y vnknowinge dide in vnbileue.
29693	54	1	14	But the grace of oure Lord ouer aboundide, with feith and loue that is in Crist Jhesu.
29694	54	1	15	A trewe word and worthi al resseyuyng, for Crist Jhesu cam in to this world to make synful men saaf, of whiche Y am the firste.
29695	54	1	16	But therfor Y haue getun merci, that Crist Jhesu schulde schewe in me first al pacience, to the enfourmyng of hem that schulen bileue to hym in to euerlastinge lijf.
29696	54	1	17	And to the king of worldis, vndeedli and vnvysible God aloone, be onour and glorie in to worldis of worldis. Amen.
29697	54	1	18	I bitake this comaundement to thee, thou sone Timothe, after the prophecies that han be hertofore in thee, that thou traueile in hem a good trauel,
29698	54	1	19	hauynge feith and good conscience, which summen casten awei, and perischiden aboute the feith.
29699	54	1	20	Of whiche is Ymeneus and Alisaundre, which Y bitook to Sathanas, that thei lerne `to not blasfeme.
29700	54	2	1	Therfor Y biseche first of alle thingis, that bisechingis, preieris, axyngis, doyngis of thankyngis, ben maad for alle men,
29701	54	2	2	for kingis and alle that ben set in hiynesse, that we leden a quyet and a pesible lijf, in al pite and chastite.
29702	54	2	3	For this thing is good and acceptid bifor God,
29703	54	2	4	oure sauyour, that wole that alle men ben maad saaf, and that thei come to the knowyng of treuthe.
29704	54	2	5	For o God and a mediatour is of God and of men, a man Crist Jhesus,
29705	54	2	6	that yaf him silf redempcioun for alle men. Whos witnessing is confermyd in his tymes;
29706	54	2	7	in which Y am set a prechour and an apostle. For Y seye treuthe, and Y lie not, that am a techere of hethene men in feith and in treuthe.
29707	54	2	8	Therfor Y wole, that men preye in al place, liftinge vp clene hondis with outen wraththe and strijf.
29708	54	2	9	Also wymmen in couenable abite, with schamefastnesse and sobrenesse araiynge hem silf, not in writhun heeris, ethir in gold, ethir peerlis, ethir preciouse cloth; but that that bicometh wymmen,
29709	54	2	10	biheetinge pite bi good werkis.
29710	54	2	11	A womman lerne in silence, with al subieccioun.
29711	54	2	12	But Y suffre not a womman to teche, nether to haue lordschip on the hosebonde, but to be in silence.
29712	54	2	13	For Adam was first formed, aftirward Eue;
29713	54	2	14	and Adam was not disseyued, but the womman was disseyued, in breking of the lawe.
29714	54	2	15	But sche schal be sauyd bi generacioun of children, if sche dwellith perfitli in feith, and loue, and hoolynesse, with sobrenesse.
29715	54	3	1	A feithful word. If ony man desirith a bishopriche, he desirith a good werk.
29716	54	3	2	Therfor it bihoueth a byschop to be with out repreef, the hosebonde of o wijf, sobre, prudent, chast, vertewous, holdinge hospitalite, a techere;
29717	54	3	3	not youun myche to wyn, not a smytere, but temperat, not ful of chiding, not coueitouse, wel reulinge his hous,
29718	54	3	4	and haue sones suget with al chastite;
29719	54	3	5	for if ony man kan not gouerne his house, hou schal he haue diligence of the chirche of God? not new conuertid to the feith,
29720	54	3	6	lest he be borun vp in to pride, and falle in to doom of the deuel.
29721	54	3	7	For it bihoueth hym to haue also good witnessing of hem that ben with outforth, that he falle not in to repreef, and in to the snare of the deuel.
29722	54	3	8	Also it bihoueth dekenes to be chast, not double tungid, not youun myche to wyn, not suynge foul wynnyng;
29723	54	3	9	that han the mysterie of feith in clene conscience.
29724	54	3	10	But be thei preued first, and mynystre so, hauynge no cryme.
29725	54	3	11	Also it bihoueth wymmen to be chast, not bacbitinge, sobre, feithful in alle thingis.
29726	54	3	12	Dekenes be hosebondis of o wijf; whiche gouerne wel her sones and her housis.
29727	54	3	13	For thei that mynystren wel, schulen gete a good degre to hem silf, and myche triste in the feith, that is in Crist Jhesu.
29728	54	3	14	Sone Timothe, Y write to thee these thingis, hopinge that Y schal come soon to thee;
29729	54	3	15	but if Y tarie, that thou wite, hou it bihoueth thee to lyue in the hous of God, that is the chirche of lyuynge God, a pilere and sadnesse of treuthe.
29730	54	3	16	And opynli it is a greet sacrament of pitee, that thing that was schewid in fleisch, it is iustified in spirit, it apperid to aungels, it is prechid to hethene men, it is bileuyd in the world, it is takun vp in glorie.
29731	54	4	1	But the spirit seith opynli, that in the laste tymes summen schulen departe fro the feith, yyuynge tent to spiritis of errour, and to techingis of deuelis; that speken leesing in ipocrisie,
29732	54	4	2	and haue her conscience corrupt,
29733	54	4	3	forbedinge to be weddid, to absteyne fro metis, whiche God made to take with doyng of thankingis, to feithful men, and hem that han knowe the treuthe.
29734	54	4	4	For ech creature of God is good, and no thing is to be cast awei, which is takun with doyng of thankyngis;
29735	54	4	5	for it is halewid bi the word of God, and bi preyer.
29736	54	4	6	Thou puttynge forth these thingis to britheren, schalt be a good mynystre of Crist Jhesu; nurschid with wordis of feith and of good doctryne, which thou hast gete.
29737	54	4	7	But eschewe thou vncouenable fablis, and elde wymmenus fablis; haunte thi silf to pitee.
29738	54	4	8	For bodili exercitation is profitable to litle thing; but pitee is profitable to alle thingis, that hath a biheest of lijf that now is, and that is to come.
29739	54	4	9	A trewe word, and worthi al acceptacioun.
29740	54	4	10	And in this thing we trauelen, and ben cursid, for we hopen in lyuyng God, that is sauyour of alle men, moost of feithful men.
29741	54	4	11	Comaunde thou this thing, and teche.
29742	54	4	12	No man dispise thi yongthe, but be thou ensaumple of feithful men in word, in lyuyng, in charite, in feith, in chastite.
29743	54	4	13	Tyl Y come, take tent to redyng, to exortacioun and teching.
29744	54	4	14	Nyle thou litil charge the grace which is in thee, that is youun to thee bi profecie, with putting on of the hondis of preesthod.
29745	54	4	15	Thenke thou these thingis, in these be thou, that thi profiting be schewid to alle men.
29746	54	4	16	Take tent to thi silf and to doctryn; be bisi in hem. For thou doynge these thingis, schalt `make bothe thi silf saaf, and hem that heren thee.
29747	54	4	1	Blame thou not an eldere man, but biseche as a fadir, yonge men as britheren; elde wymmen as modris,
29748	54	4	2	yonge wymmen as sistris, in al chastite.
29749	54	5	3	Honoure thou widewis, that ben very widewis.
29750	54	5	4	But if ony widewe hath children of sones, lerne sche first to gouerne her hous, and quyte to fadir and modir; for this thing is acceptid bifor God.
29751	54	5	5	And sche that is a widewe verili, and desolate, hope in to God, and be bisy in bisechingis and preieris niyt and dai.
29752	54	5	6	For sche that is lyuynge in delicis, is deed.
29753	54	5	7	And comaunde thou this thing, that thei be withouten repreef.
29754	54	5	8	For if ony man hath not cure of his owne, and most of hise household men, he hath denyed the feith, and is worse than an vnfeithful man.
29755	54	5	9	A widewe be chosun not lesse than sixti yeer, that was wijf of oon hosebonde,
29756	54	5	10	and hath witnessing in good werkis, if sche nurschede children, if sche resseyuede pore men to herbore, if sche hath waischun the feet of hooli men, if sche mynystride to men that suffriden tribulacioun, if sche folewide al good werk.
29757	54	5	11	But eschewe thou yongere widewis; for whanne thei han do letcherie, thei wolen be weddid in Crist,
29758	54	5	12	hauynge dampnacioun, for thei han maad voide the firste feith.
29759	54	5	13	Also thei idil lernen to go aboute housis, not oneli ydel, but ful of wordis and curiouse, spekynge thingis that bihoueth not.
29760	54	5	14	Therfor Y wole, that yongere widewis be weddid, and bringe forth children, and ben hosewyues, to yyue noon occasioun to the aduersarie, bi cause of cursid thing.
29761	54	5	15	For now summe ben turned abak aftir Sathanas.
29762	54	5	16	If ony feithful man hath widewis, mynystre he to hem, that the chirche be not greuyd, that it suffice to hem that ben very widewis.
29763	54	5	17	The prestis that ben wel gouernoures, be thei had worthi to double onour; moost thei that trauelen in word and teching.
29764	54	5	18	For scripture seith, Thou schalt not bridil the mouth of the oxe threischinge, and, A werk man is worthi his hire.
29765	54	5	19	Nyle thou resseyue accusyng ayens a preest, but vndur tweyne or thre witnessis.
29766	54	5	20	But reproue thou men that synnen bifor alle men, that also othere haue drede.
29767	54	5	21	Y preie bifor God, and Jhesu Crist, and hise chosun aungelis, that thou kepe these thingis with oute preiudice, and do no thing in bowynge `in to the othere side.
29768	54	5	22	Put thou hondis to no man, nether anoon comyne thou with othere mennus synnes. Kepe thi silf chast.
29769	54	5	23	Nyle thou yit drinke watir, but vse a litil wyn, for thi stomac, and `for thin ofte fallynge infirmytees.
29770	54	5	24	Sum mennus synnes ben opyn, bifor goynge to dom; but of summen thei comen aftir.
29771	54	5	25	And also goode dedis ben opyn, and tho that han hem in othere maner, moun not be hid.
29772	54	6	1	What euere seruauntis ben vndur yok, deme thei her lordis worthi al onour, lest the name of the Lord and the doctryn be blasfemyd.
29773	54	6	2	And thei that han feithful lordis, dispise hem not, for thei ben britheren; but more serue thei, for thei ben feithful and louyd, whiche ben parceneris of benefice. Teche thou these thingis, and moneste thou these thingis.
29774	54	6	3	If ony man techith othere wise, and acordith not to the hoolsum wordis of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, and to that teching that is bi pitee,
29775	54	6	4	he is proud, and kan no thing, but langwischith aboute questiouns and stryuyng of wordis, of the whiche ben brouyt forth enuyes, stryues, blasfemyes, yuele suspiciouns, fiytingis of men,
29776	54	6	5	that ben corrupt in soule, and that ben pryued fro treuthe, that demen wynnyng to be pitee.
29777	54	6	6	But a greet wynnyng is pitee, with sufficience.
29778	54	6	7	For we brouyten in no thing in to this world, and no doute, that we moun not bere `awey ony thing.
29779	54	6	8	But we hauynge foodis, and with what thingus we schulen be hilid, be we paied with these thingis.
29780	54	6	9	For thei that wolen be maad riche, fallen in to temptacioun, and `in to snare of the deuel, and in to many vnprofitable desiris and noyous, whiche drenchen men in to deth and perdicioun.
29781	54	6	10	For the rote of alle yuelis is coueytise, which summen coueitinge erriden fro the feith, and bisettiden hem with many sorewis.
29782	54	6	11	But, thou, man of God, fle these thingis; but sue thou riytwisnesse, pite, feith, charite, pacience, myldenesse.
29783	54	6	12	Stryue thou a good strijf of feith, catche euerlastinge lijf, in to which thou art clepid, and hast knoulechid a good knouleching bifor many witnessis.
29784	54	6	13	I comaunde to thee bifor God, that quikeneth alle thingis, and bifor Crist Jhesu, that yeldide a witnessing vnder Pilat of Pounce, a good confessioun,
29785	54	6	14	that thou kepe the comaundement with out wem, with out repreef, in to the comyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist;
29786	54	6	15	whom the blessid and aloone miyti king of kyngis and Lord of lordis schal schewe in his tymes.
29787	54	6	16	Which aloone hath vndeedlynesse, and dwellith in liyt, to which no man may come; whom no man say, nether may se; to whom glorie, and honour, and empire be with out ende.
29788	54	6	17	Amen. Comaunde thou to the riche men of this world, that thei vndurstonde not hiyli, nether that thei hope in vncerteynte of richessis, but in the lyuynge God, that yyueth to vs alle thingis plenteuously to vse;
29789	54	6	18	to do wel, to be maad riche in good werkis, liytli to yyue,
29790	54	6	19	to comyne, to tresoure to hem silf a good foundement in to tyme to comynge, that thei catche euerlastinge lijf.
29791	54	6	20	Thou Tymothe, kepe the thing bitakun to thee, eschewynge cursid noueltees of voicis, and opynyouns of fals name of kunnyng;
29792	54	6	21	which summen bihetinge, aboute the feith fellen doun. The grace of God be with thee. Amen.
29793	55	1	1	Poul, apostle of Jhesu Crist, bi the wille of God, bi the biheest of lijf that is in Crist Jhesu,
29794	55	1	2	to Tymothe, his moost dereworthe sone, grace, merci, and pees of God the fadir, and of Jhesu Crist, oure Lord.
29795	55	1	3	I do thankyngis to my God, to whom Y serue fro my progenytouris in clene conscience, that with outen ceessyng Y haue mynde of thee in my preyeris,
29796	55	1	4	niyt and dai, desirynge to se thee; hauynge mynde of thi teeris, that Y be fillid with ioye.
29797	55	1	5	And Y bithenke of that feith, that is in thee not feyned, which also dwellide firste in thin aunte Loide, and in thi modir Eunyce. And Y am certeyn, that also in thee.
29798	55	1	6	For which cause Y moneste thee, that thou reise ayen the grace of God, that is in thee bi the settyng on of myn hondis.
29799	55	1	7	For whi God yaf not to vs the spirit of drede, but of vertu, and of loue, and of sobrenesse.
29800	55	1	8	Therfor nyl thou schame the witnessyng of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, nether me, his prisoner; but trauele thou togidere in the gospel bi the vertu of God;
29801	55	1	9	that delyueride vs, and clepide with his hooli clepyng, not after oure werkis, but bi his purpos and grace, that is youun in Crist Jhesu bifore worldli tymes;
29802	55	1	10	but now it is opyn bi the liytnyng of oure sauyour Jhesu Crist, which destriede deth, and liytnede lijf and vncorrupcioun bi the gospel.
29803	55	1	11	In which Y am set a prechour and apostle, and maistir of hethene men.
29804	55	1	12	For which cause also Y suffre these thingis; but Y am not confoundid. For Y woot to whom Y haue bileuyd, and Y am certeyne that he is miyti for to kepe that is take to my keping in to that dai.
29805	55	1	13	Haue thou the fourme of hoolsum wordis, whiche thou herdist of me in feith and loue in Crist Jhesu.
29806	55	1	14	Kepe thou the good takun to thi kepyng bi the Hooli Goost, that dwellith in vs.
29807	55	1	15	Thou wost this, that alle that ben in Asie ben turnyd awey fro me, of whiche is Figelus and Ermogenes.
29808	55	1	16	The Lord yyue merci to the hous of Onesyforus, for ofte he refreischide me, and schamyde not my chayne.
29809	55	1	17	But whanne he cam to Rome, he souyte me bisili, and foond.
29810	55	1	18	The Lord yyue to hym to fynde merci of God in that dai. And hou grete thingis he mynystride to me at Effesi, thou knowist betere.
29811	55	2	1	Therfor thou, my sone, be coumfortid in grace that is in Crist Jhesu.
29812	55	2	2	And what thingis thou hast herd of me bi many witnessis, bitake thou these to feithful men, whiche schulen `be also able to teche othere men.
29813	55	2	3	Trauele thou as a good knyyt of Crist Jhesu.
29814	55	2	4	No man holdinge knyythod to God, wlappith hym silf with worldli nedis, that he plese to hym, to whom he hath preuyd hym silf.
29815	55	2	5	For he that fiytith in a batel, schal not be corowned, but he fiyte lawfuli.
29816	55	2	6	It bihoueth an erthetiliere to resseyue first of the fruytis.
29817	55	2	7	Vndurstonde thou what thingis Y seie. For the Lord schal yyue to thee vndurstonding in alle thingis.
29818	55	2	8	Be thou myndeful that the Lord Jhesu Crist of the seed of Dauid hath rise ayen fro deth,
29819	55	2	9	aftir my gospel, in which Y trauele `til to boondis, as worching yuele, but the word of God is not boundun.
29820	55	2	10	Therfor Y suffre alle thingis for the chosun, that also thei gete the heelthe, that is in Crist Jhesu, with heuenli glorie.
29821	55	2	11	A trewe word, that if we ben deed togidere, also we schulen liue togidere;
29822	55	2	12	if we suffren, we schulen regne togidere; if we denyen, he schal denye vs;
29823	55	2	13	if we bileuen not, he dwellith feithful, he mai not denye hym silf.
29824	55	2	14	Teche thou these thingis, witnessinge bifore God. Nyle thou stryue in wordis; for to no thing it is profitable, but to the subuerting of men that heren.
29825	55	2	15	Bisili kepe to yyue thi silf a preued preisable werkman to God, with oute schame, riytli tretinge the word of treuthe.
29826	55	2	16	But eschewe thou vnhooli and veyn spechis, for whi tho profiten myche to vnfeithfulnesse,
29827	55	2	17	and the word of hem crepith as a canker. Of whiche Filete is, and Ymeneus,
29828	55	2	18	whiche felden doun fro the treuthe, seiynge that the rising ayen is now doon, and thei subuertiden the feith of summen.
29829	55	2	19	But the sad foundement of God stondith, hauynge this marke, The Lord knowith whiche ben hise, and, Ech man that nameth the name of the Lord, departith fro wickidnesse.
29830	55	2	20	But in a greet hous ben not oneli vessels of gold and of siluer, but also of tree and of erthe; and so summen ben in to onour, and summe in to dispit.
29831	55	2	21	Therfor if ony man clensith hym silf fro these, he schal be a vessel halewid in to onour, and profitable to the Lord, redi to al good werk.
29832	55	2	22	And fle thou desiris of yongthe, but sue thou riytwisnesse, feith, charite, pees, with hem that inwardli clepen the Lord of a clene herte.
29833	55	2	23	And eschewe thou foltische questiouns, and without kunnyng, wytynge that tho gendren chidyngis.
29834	55	2	24	But it bihoueth the seruaunt of the Lord to chide not; but to be mylde to alle men, able to teche,
29835	55	2	25	paciente, with temperaunce repreuynge hem that ayenstonden the treuthe, that sum tyme God yyue to hem forthenkyng, that thei knowen the treuthe,
29836	55	2	26	and that thei rise ayen fro the snares of the deuel, of whom thei ben holdun prisoneris at his wille.
29837	55	3	1	But wite thou this thing, that in the laste daies perelouse tymes schulen neiye, and men schulen be louynge hem silf,
29838	55	3	2	coueitouse, hiy of bering, proude, blasfemeris, not obedient to fadir and modir, vnkynde,
29839	55	3	3	cursid, with outen affeccioun, with out pees, false blameris, vncontynent, vnmylde,
29840	55	3	4	with out benygnyte, traitouris, ouerthwert, bollun with proude thouytis, blynde, loueris of lustis more than of God,
29841	55	3	5	hauynge the licknesse of pitee, but denyynge the vertu of it. And eschewe thou these men.
29842	55	3	6	Of these thei ben that persen housis, and leden wymmen caitifs chargid with synnes, whiche ben led with dyuerse desiris, euere more lernynge,
29843	55	3	7	and neuere perfitli comynge to the science of treuthe.
29844	55	3	8	And as Jannes and Mambres ayenstoden Moises, so these ayenstonden treuthe, men corrupt in vndirstonding, repreuyd aboute the feith.
29845	55	3	9	But ferthere thei schulen not profite, for the vnwisdom of hem schal be knowun to alle men, as hern was.
29846	55	3	10	But thou hast getun my teching, ordinaunce, purposing, feith, long abiding, loue,
29847	55	3	11	pacience, persecuciouns, passiouns, whiche weren maad to me at Antioche, at Ycony, at Listris, what maner persecucyouns Y suffride, and the Lord hath delyuered me of alle.
29848	55	3	12	And alle men that wolen lyue feithfuli in Crist Jhesu, schulen suffre persecucioun.
29849	55	3	13	But yuele men and disseyueris schulen encreese in to worse, errynge, and sendinge in to errour.
29850	55	3	14	But dwelle thou in these thingis that thou hast lerud, and that ben bitakun to thee, witinge of whom thou hast lerud;
29851	55	3	15	for thou hast knowun hooli lettris fro thi youthe, whiche moun lerne thee to heelthe, bi feith that is in Crist Jhesu.
29852	55	3	16	For al scripture inspirid of God is profitable to teche, to repreue, to chastice, to lerne in riytwisnes, that the man of God be parfit, lerud to al good werk.
29853	55	4	1	I witnesse bifore God and Crist Jhesu, that schal deme the quike and the deed, and bi the comyng of hym, and the kyngdom of hym,
29854	55	4	2	preche the word, be thou bisi couenabli with outen rest, repreue thou, biseche thou, blame thou in al pacience and doctryn.
29855	55	4	3	For tyme schal be, whanne men schulen not suffre hoolsum teching, but at her desiris thei schulen gadere `togidere to hem silf maistris yitchinge to the eeris.
29856	55	4	4	And treuli thei schulen turne awei the heryng fro treuthe, but to fablis thei schulen turne.
29857	55	4	5	But wake thou, in alle thingis traueile thou, do the werk of an euangelist, fulfille thi seruyce, be thou sobre.
29858	55	4	6	For Y am sacrifisid now, and the tyme of my departyng is nyy.
29859	55	4	7	Y haue stryuun a good strijf, Y haue endid the cours, Y haue kept the feith.
29860	55	4	8	In `the tothir tyme a coroun of riytwisnesse is kept to me, which the Lord, a iust domesman, schal yelde to me in that dai; and not oneli to me, but also to these that louen his comyng.
29861	55	4	9	Hyye thou to come to me soone. For Demas, louynge this world, hath forsakun me, and wente to Tessalonyk,
29862	55	4	10	Crescens in to Galathi, Tite in to Dalmacie;
29863	55	4	11	Luk aloone is with me. Take thou Mark, and brynge with thee; for he is profitable to me in to seruyce.
29864	55	4	12	Forsothe Y sente Titicus to Effesi.
29865	55	4	13	The cloth which Y lefte at Troade at Carpe, whanne thou comest, bringe with thee, and the bookis, but moost parchemyne.
29866	55	4	14	Alisaundre, the tresorer, schewide to me myche yuele; `the Lord schal yelde to hym aftir his werkis.
29867	55	4	15	Whom also thou eschewe; for he ayenstood ful greetli oure wordis.
29868	55	4	16	In my firste defence no man helpide me, but alle forsoken me; be it not arettid to hem.
29869	55	4	17	But the Lord helpide me, and coumfortide me, that the preching be fillid bi me, and that alle folkis here, that Y am delyueride fro the mouth of the lioun.
29870	55	4	18	And the Lord delyueride me fro al yuel werk, and schal make me saaf in to his heuenly kingdom, to whom be glorie in to worldis of worldis.
29871	55	4	19	Amen. Grete wel Prisca, and Aquila, and the hous of Oneseforus.
29872	55	4	20	Erastus lefte at Corynthi, and Y lefte Trofymus sijk at Mylete.
29873	55	4	21	Hiye thou to come bifore wyntir. Eubolus, and Prudent, and Lynus, and Claudia, and alle britheren, greten thee wel.
29874	55	4	22	Oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with thi spirit. The grace of God be with you. Amen.
29875	56	1	1	Poul, the seruaunt of God, and apostle of Jhesu Crist, bi the feith of the chosun of God, and bi the knowing of the treuthe,
29876	56	1	2	whiche is aftir pitee, in to the hope of euerlastinge lijf, which lijf God that lieth not, bihiyte bifore tymes of the world;
29877	56	1	3	but he hath schewid in hise tymes his word in preching, that is bitakun to me bi the comaundement of `God oure sauyour,
29878	56	1	4	to Tite, most dereworthe sone bi the comyn feith, grace and pees of God the fadir, and of Crist Jhesu, oure sauyour.
29879	56	1	5	For cause of this thing Y lefte thee at Crete, that thou amende tho thingis that failen, and ordeyne preestis bi citees, as also Y disposide to thee.
29880	56	1	6	If ony man is withoute cryme, an hosebonde of o wijf, and hath feithful sones, not in accusacioun of letcherie, or not suget.
29881	56	1	7	For it bihoueth a bischop to be without cryme, a dispendour of God, not proud, not wrathful, not drunkelew, not smytere, not coueytouse of foul wynnyng;
29882	56	1	8	but holdinge hospitalite, benygne, prudent, sobre, iust,
29883	56	1	9	hooli, contynent, takinge that trewe word, that is aftir doctryn; that he be miyti to amoneste in hoolsum techyng, and to repreue hem that ayenseien.
29884	56	1	10	For ther ben many vnobedient, and veyn spekeris, and disseyueris, moost thei that ben of circumcisyoun,
29885	56	1	11	whiche it bihoueth to be repreued; whiche subuerten alle housis, techinge whiche thingis it bihoueth not, for the loue of foul wynnyng.
29886	56	1	12	And oon of hem, her propre profete, seide, Men of Crete ben euere more lyeris, yuele beestis, of slowe wombe.
29887	56	1	13	This witnessyng is trewe. For what cause blame hem sore, that thei be hool in feith,
29888	56	1	14	not yyuynge tent to fablis of Jewis, and to maundementis of men, that turnen awei hem fro treuthe.
29889	56	1	15	And alle thingis ben clene to clene men; but to vnclene men and to vnfeithful no thing is clene, for the soule and conscience of hem ben maad vnclene.
29890	56	1	16	Thei knoulechen that thei knowen God, but bi dedis thei denyen; whanne thei ben abhominable, and vnbileueful, and repreuable to al good werk.
29891	56	2	1	But speke thou tho thingis that bisemen hoolsum teching;
29892	56	2	2	that elde men be sobre, chast, prudent, hool in feith, in loue, and pacience;
29893	56	2	3	also olde wymmen in hooli abite, not sclaundereris, not seruynge myche to wyn, wel techynge, that thei teche prudence.
29894	56	2	4	Moneste thou yonge wymmen, that thei loue here hosebondis, that thei loue her children;
29895	56	2	5	and that thei be prudent, chast, sobre, hauynge cure of the hous, benygne, suget to her hosebondis, that the word of God be not blasfemyd.
29896	56	2	6	Also moneste thou yonge men, that thei be sobre.
29897	56	2	7	In alle thingis yyue thi silf ensaumple of good werkis, in teching, in hoolnesse, in sadnesse.
29898	56	2	8	An hoolsum word, and vnrepreuable; that he that is of the contrarie side, be aschamed, hauynge noon yuel thing to seie of you.
29899	56	2	9	Moneste thou seruauntis to be suget to her lordis; in alle thingis plesinge, not ayenseiynge, not defraudynge,
29900	56	2	10	but in alle thingis schewinge good feith, that thei onoure in alle thingis the doctryn of `God, oure sauyour.
29901	56	2	11	For the grace of `God, oure sauyour,
29902	56	2	12	hath apperid to alle men, and tauyte vs, that we forsake wickidnesse, and worldli desyris, lyue sobreli, and iustli, `and piteuousli in this world,
29903	56	2	13	abidinge the blessid hope and the comyng of the glorie of the greet God, and of oure sauyour Jhesu Crist;
29904	56	2	14	that yaf hym silf for vs, to ayenbie vs fro al wickidnesse, and make clene to hym silf a puple acceptable, and suere of good werkis.
29905	56	2	15	Speke thou these thingis, and moneste thou, and repreue thou with al comaundement; no man dispise thee.
29906	56	3	1	Amoneste hem to be sugetis to prynces, and to poweris; to obeische to that that is seid, and to be redi to al good werk;
29907	56	3	2	to blasfeme no man, to be not ful of chiding, but temperat, schewynge al myldenesse to alle men.
29908	56	3	3	For we weren sum tyme vnwise, vnbileueful, errynge, and seruynge to desiris, and to dyuerse lustis, doynge in malice and enuye, worthi to be hatid, hatinge ech othere.
29909	56	3	4	But whanne the benygnyte and the manhed of oure sauyour God aperide,
29910	56	3	5	not of werkis of riytwisnesse that we diden, but bi his merci he made vs saaf, bi waischyng of ayen bigetyng, and ayen newyng of the Hooli Goost,
29911	56	3	6	whom he schedde into vs plenteuousli bi Jhesu Crist,
29912	56	3	7	oure saueour, that we iustified bi his grace, ben eiris by hope of euerlastinge lijf.
29913	56	3	8	A trewe word is, and of these thingis Y wole that thou conferme othere, that thei that bileuen to God, be bisy to be aboue othere in good werkis. These thingis ben good, and profitable to men.
29914	56	3	9	And eschewe thou foltische questiouns, and genologies, and stryues, and fiytyngis of the lawe; for tho ben vnprofitable and veyn.
29915	56	3	10	Eschewe thou a man eretik, aftir oon and the secound correccioun;
29916	56	3	11	witinge that he that is siche a maner man is subuertid, and trespassith, and is dampned bi his owne dom.
29917	56	3	12	Whanne Y sende to thee Arteman, or Titicus, hiy thou to `come to me to Nycopolis; for Y haue purposid to dwelle in wyntir there.
29918	56	3	13	Bisili byfor sende Zenam, a wise man of lawe, and Apollo, that no thing faile to hem.
29919	56	3	14	Thei that ben of ouris, lerne to be gouernouris in good werkis, to necessarie vsis, that thei be not with out fruyt.
29920	56	3	15	Alle men that ben with me greeten thee wel. Grete thou wel hem, that louen vs in feith. The grace of God be with you alle. Amen.
29921	57	1	1	Poul, the boundun of Crist Jhesu, and Timothe, brother, to Filemon, bilouyd, and oure helpere, and to Appia,
29922	57	1	2	most dere sister, and to Archip, oure euene kniyt, and to the chirche that is in thin hous,
29923	57	1	3	grace be to you, and pees of God oure fader, and of the Lord Jhesu Crist.
29924	57	1	4	I do thankingis to my God, euere more makinge mynde of thee in my preieris,
29925	57	1	5	heringe thi charite and feith, that thou hast in the Lord Jhesu, and to alle hooli men,
29926	57	1	6	that the comynyng of thi feith be maad opyn, in knowing of al good thing in Crist Jhesu.
29927	57	1	7	And Y hadde greet ioye and coumfort in thi charite, for the entrailis of hooli men restiden bi thee, brother.
29928	57	1	8	For which thing Y hauynge myche trist in Crist Jhesu, to comaunde to thee that that perteyneth to profit;
29929	57	1	9	but Y biseche more for charite, sithen thou art siche as the elde Poul, and now the boundun of Jhesu Crist.
29930	57	1	10	Y biseche thee for my sone Onesyme, whom Y in boondis bigat,
29931	57	1	11	which sumtyme was vnprofitable to thee, but now profitable bothe to thee and to me; whom Y sente ayen to thee.
29932	57	1	12	And resseyue thou hym as myn entrailis;
29933	57	1	13	whom Y wolde withholde with me, that he schulde serue for thee to me in boondis of the gospel;
29934	57	1	14	but with out thi counseil Y wolde not do ony thing, that thi good schulde not be as of nede, but wilful.
29935	57	1	15	For perauenture therfor he departide fro thee for a tyme, that thou schuldist resseyue hym with outen ende;
29936	57	1	16	now not as a seruaunt, but for a seruaunt a most dere brother, most to me; and how myche more to thee, bothe in fleisch and in the Lord?
29937	57	1	17	Therfor if thou hast me a felowe, resseyue hym as me; for if he hath ony thing anoied thee,
29938	57	1	18	ethir owith, arette thou this thing to me.
29939	57	1	19	Y Poul wroot with myn hoond, Y schal yelde; that Y seie not to thee, that also thou owist to me thi silf.
29940	57	1	20	So, brothir, Y schal vse thee in the Lord; fille thou myn entrails in Crist.
29941	57	1	21	Y tristnynge of thin obedience wroot to thee, witynge that thou schalt do ouer that that Y seie.
29942	57	1	22	Also make thou redi to me an hous to dwelle in; for Y hope that bi youre preyeris Y schal be youun to you.
29943	57	1	23	Epafras, prisoner with me in Crist Jhesu,
29944	57	1	24	greetith thee wel, and Mark, Aristark, Demas, Lucas, myn helperis.
29945	57	1	25	The grace of oure Lord Jhesu Crist be with youre spirit. Amen.
29946	58	1	1	God, that spak sum tyme bi prophetis in many maneres to oure fadris, at the
29947	58	1	2	laste in these daies he hath spoke to vs bi the sone; whom he hath ordeyned eir of alle thingis, and bi whom he made the worldis.
