30539	62	2	8	Eftsoone Y write to you a newe maundement, that is trewe bothe in hym and in you; for derknessis ben passid, and veri liyt schyneth now.
30540	62	2	9	He that seith, that he is in liyt, and hatith his brother, is in derknesse yit.
30541	62	2	10	He that loueth his brothir, dwellith in liyt, and sclaundre is not in hym.
30542	62	2	11	But he that hatith his brother, is in derknessis, and wandrith in derknessis, and woot not whidir he goith; for derknessis han blindid hise iyen.
30543	62	2	12	Litle sones, Y write to you, that youre synnes ben foryouun to you for his name.
30544	62	2	13	Fadris, Y write to you, for ye han knowun hym, that is fro the bigynnyng. Yonge men, Y write to you, for ye han ouercomun the wickid.
30545	62	2	14	Y write to you, yonge children, for ye han knowe the fadir. Y write to you, britheren, for ye han knowen hym, that is fro the bigynnyng. Y write to you, yonge men, for ye ben stronge, and the word of God dwellith in you, and ye han ouercomun the wickid.
30546	62	2	15	Nyle ye loue the world, ne tho thingis that ben in the world. If ony man loueth the world, the charite of the fader is not in hym.
30547	62	2	16	For al thing that is in the world, is coueitise of fleisch, and coueitise of iyen, and pride of lijf, which is not of the fadir, but it is of the world.
30548	62	2	17	And the world schal passe, and the coueitise of it; but he that doith the wille of God, dwellith with outen ende.
30549	62	2	18	My litle sones, the laste our is; and as ye han herd, that antecrist cometh, now many antecristis ben maad; wherfor we witen, that it is the laste our.
30550	62	2	19	Thei wenten forth fro vs, but thei weren not of vs; for if thei hadden be of vs, thei hadden dwelte with vs; but that thei be knowun, that thei ben not of vs.
30551	62	2	20	But ye han anointyng of the Hooli Goost, and knowen alle thingis.
30552	62	2	21	Y wroot not to you, as to men that knowen not treuthe, but as to men that knowen it, and for ech leesing is not of treuthe.
30553	62	2	22	Who is a liere, but this that denyeth that Jhesu is not Crist? This is antecrist, that denyeth the fadir, and the sone.
30554	62	2	23	So ech that denyeth the sone, hath not the fadir; but he that knowlechith the sone, hath also the fadir.
30555	62	2	24	That thing that ye herden at the bigynnyng, dwelle it in you; for if that thing dwellith in you, which ye herden at the bigynnyng, ye schulen dwelle in the sone and in the fadir.
30556	62	2	25	And this is the biheeste, that he bihiyte to vs euerlastinge lijf.
30557	62	2	26	Y wroot these thingis to you, of hem that disseyuen you,
30558	62	2	27	and that the anoyntyng which ye resseyueden of hym, dwelle in you. And ye han not nede, that ony man teche you, but as his anoyntyng techith you of alle thingis, and it is trewe, and it is not leesyng; and as he tauyte you, dwelle ye in hym.
30559	62	2	28	And now, ye litle sones, dwelle ye in hym, that whanne he schal appere, we haue a trist, and be not confoundid of hym in his comyng.
30560	62	2	29	If ye witen that he is iust, wite ye that also ech that doith riytwisnesse, is borun of hym.
30561	62	3	1	Se ye what maner charite the fadir yaf to vs, that we be named the sones of God, and ben hise sones. For this thing the world knewe not vs, for it knew not hym.
30562	62	3	2	Moost dere britheren, now we ben the sones of God, and yit it apperide not, what we schulen be. We witen, that whanne he schal appere, we schulen be lijk hym, for we schulen se hym as he is.
30563	62	3	3	And ech man that hath this hope in hym, makith hym silf hooli, as he is hooli.
30564	62	3	4	Ech man that doith synne, doith also wickidnesse, and synne is wickidnesse.
30565	62	3	5	And ye witen, that he apperide to do awei synnes, and synne is not in hym.
30566	62	3	6	Ech man that dwellith in hym, synneth not; and ech that synneth, seeth not hym, nether knew hym.
30567	62	3	7	Litle sones, no man disseyue you; he that doith riytwysnesse, is iust, as also he is iust.
30568	62	3	8	He that doith synne, is of the deuel; for the deuel synneth fro the bigynnyng. In this thing the sone of God apperide, that he vndo the werkis of the deuel.
30569	62	3	9	Ech man that is borun of God, doith not synne; for the seed of God dwellith in hym, and he may not do synne, for he is borun of God.
30570	62	3	10	In this thing the sones of God ben knowun, and the sones of the feend. Ech man that is not iust, is not of God, and he that loueth not his brothir.
30571	62	3	11	For this is the tellyng, that ye herden at the bigynnyng, that ye loue ech othere;
30572	62	3	12	not as Caym, that was of the yuele, and slouy his brother. And for what thing slouy he him? for hise werkis weren yuele, and hise brotheris iust.
30573	62	3	13	Britheren, nyle ye wondre, if the world hatith you.
30574	62	3	14	We witen, that we ben translatid fro deeth to lijf, for we louen britheren. He that loueth not, dwellith in deth.
30575	62	3	15	Ech man that hatith his brother, is a man sleere; and ye witen, that ech mansleere hath not euerlastinge lijf dwellinge in hym.
30576	62	3	16	In this thing we han knowe the charite of God, for he puttide his lijf for vs, and we owen to putte oure lyues for oure britheren.
30577	62	3	17	He that hath the catel of this world, and seeth that his brothir hath nede, and closith his entrailis fro hym, hou dwellith the charite of God in hym?
30578	62	3	18	Mi litle sones, loue we not in word, nethir in tunge, but in werk and treuthe.
30579	62	3	19	In this thing we knowen, that we ben of treuthe, and in his siyt we monesten oure hertis.
30580	62	3	20	For if oure herte repreueth vs, God is more than oure hert, and knowith alle thingis.
30581	62	3	21	Moost dere britheren, if oure herte repreueth not vs, we han trust to God;
30582	62	3	22	and what euer we schulen axe, we schulen resseyue of hym, for we kepen hise comaundementis, and we don tho thingis that ben plesaunt bifor hym.
30583	62	3	23	And this is the comaundement of God, that we bileue in the name of his sone Jhesu Crist, and that we loue ech othere, as he yaf heeste to vs.
30584	62	3	24	And he that kepith hise comaundementis, dwellith in hym, and he in hym. And in this thing we witen, that he dwellith in vs, bi the spirit, whom he yaf to vs.
30585	62	4	1	Moost dere britheren, nyle ye bileue to ech spirit, but preue ye spiritis, if thei ben of God; for many false prophetis wenten out in to the world.
30586	62	4	2	In this thing the spirit of God is knowun; ech spirit that knowlechith that Jhesu Crist hath come in fleisch, is of God;
30587	62	4	3	and ech spirit that fordoith Jhesu, is not of God. And this is antecrist, of whom ye herden, that he cometh; and riyt now he is in the world.
30588	62	4	4	Ye, litle sones, ben of God, and ye han ouercome hym; for he that is in you is more, than he that is in the world.
30589	62	4	5	Thei ben of the world, therfor thei speken of the world, and the world herith hem.
30590	62	4	6	We ben of God; he that knowith God, herith vs; he that is not of God, herith not vs. In this thing we knowen the spirit of treuthe, and the spirit of errour.
30591	62	4	7	Moost dere britheren, loue we togidere, for charite is of God; and ech that loueth his brother, is borun of God, and knowith God.
30592	62	4	8	He that loueth not, knowith not God; for God is charite.
30593	62	4	9	In this thing the charite of God apperide in vs, for God sente hise oon bigetun sone in to the world, that we lyue bi hym.
30594	62	4	10	In this thing is charite, not as we hadden loued God, but for he firste louede vs, and sente hise sone foryyuenesse for oure synnes.
30595	62	4	11	Ye moost dere britheren, if God louede vs, we owen to loue ech other.
30596	62	4	12	No man say euer God; if we louen togidre, God dwellith in vs, and the charite of hym is perfit in vs.
30597	62	4	13	In this thing we knowen, that we dwellen in hym, and he in vs; for of his spirit he yaf to vs.
30598	62	4	14	And we sayen, and witnessen, that the fadir sente his sone sauyour of the world.
30599	62	4	15	Who euer knowlechith, that Jhesu is the sone of God, God dwellith in him, and he in God.
30600	62	4	16	And we han knowun, and bileuen to the charite, that God hath in vs. God is charite, and he that dwellith in charite, dwellith in God, and God in hym.
30601	62	4	17	In this thing is the perfit charite of God with vs, that we haue trist in the dai of dom; for as he is, also we ben in this world.
30602	62	4	18	Drede is not in charite, but perfit charite puttith out drede; for drede hath peyne. But he that dredith, is not perfit in charite.
30603	62	4	19	Therfor loue we God, for he louede vs bifore.
30604	62	4	20	If ony man seith, that `Y loue God, and hatith his brother, he is a liere. For he that loueth not his brothir, which he seeth, hou mai he loue God, whom he seeth not?
30605	62	4	21	And we han this comaundement of God, that he that loueth God, loue also his brothir.
30606	62	5	1	Ech man that bileueth that Jhesus is Crist, is borun of God; and ech man that loueth hym that gendride, loueth hym that is borun of hym.
30607	62	5	2	In this thing we knowen, that we louen the children of God, whanne we louen God, and don his maundementis.
30608	62	5	3	For this is the charite of God, that we kepe hise maundementis; and his maundementis ben not heuy.
30609	62	5	4	For al thing that is borun of God, ouercometh the world; and this is the victorie that ouercometh the world, oure feith.
30610	62	5	5	And who is he that ouercometh the world, but he that bileueth that Jhesus is the sone of God?
30611	62	5	6	This is Jhesus Crist, that cam bi watir and blood; not in water oonli, but in watir and blood. And the spirit is he that witnessith, that Crist is treuthe.
30612	62	5	7	For thre ben, that yyuen witnessing in heuene, the Fadir, the Sone, and the Hooli Goost; and these thre ben oon.
30613	62	5	8	`And thre ben, that yyuen witnessing in erthe, the spirit, water, and blood; and these thre ben oon.
30614	62	5	9	If we resseyuen the witnessing of men, the witnessing of God is more; for this is the witnessing of God, that is more, for he witnesside of his sone.
30615	62	5	10	He that bileueth in the sone of God, hath the witnessing of God in hym. He that bileueth not to the sone, makith hym a liere; for he bileueth not in the witnessing, that God witnesside of his sone.
30616	62	5	11	And this is the witnessyng, for God yaf to you euerlastinge lijf, and this lijf is in his sone.
30617	62	5	12	He that hath the sone of God, hath also lijf; he that hath not the sone of God, hath not lijf.
30618	62	5	13	I write to you these thingis, that ye wite, that ye han euerlastynge lijf, which bileuen in the name of Goddis sone.
30619	62	5	14	And this is the trist which we han to God, that what euer thing we axen aftir his wille, he schal here vs.
30620	62	5	15	And we witen, that he herith vs, what euer thing we axen; we witen, that we han the axyngis, which we axen of hym.
30621	62	5	16	He that woot that his brother synneth a synne not to deth, axe he, and lijf schal be youun to hym that synneth not to deth. Ther is a synne to deth; `not for it Y seie, that ony man preie.
30622	62	5	17	Ech wickidnesse is synne, and ther is synne to deth.
30623	62	5	18	We witen, that ech man that is borun of God, synneth not; but the generacioun of God kepith hym, and the wickid touchith hym not.
30624	62	5	19	We witen, that we ben of God, and al the world is set in yuel.
30625	62	5	20	And we witen, that the sone of God cam in fleisch, and yaf to vs wit, that we know veri God, and be in the veri sone of hym.
30626	62	5	21	This is veri God, and euerlastynge lijf. My litle sones, kepe ye you fro maumetis.
30627	63	1	1	The eldere man, to the chosun ladi, and to her children, whiche Y loue in treuthe; and not Y aloone, but also alle men that knowen treuthe;
30628	63	1	2	for the treuthe that dwellith in you, and with you schal be with outen ende.
30629	63	1	3	Grace be with you, merci, and pees of God the fadir, and of Jhesu Crist, the sone of the fadir, in treuthe and charite.
30630	63	1	4	I ioiede ful myche, for Y foond of thi sones goynge in treuthe, as we resseyueden maundement of the fadir.
30631	63	1	5	And now Y preye thee, ladi, not as writinge a newe maundement to thee, but that that we hadden fro the bigynnyng, that we loue ech other.
30632	63	1	6	And this is charite, that we walke after his maundementis. For this is the comaundement, that as ye herden at the bigynnyng, walke ye in hym.
30633	63	1	7	For many disseyueris wenten out in to the world, which knoulechen not that Jhesu Crist hath come in fleisch; this is a disseyuere and antecrist.
30634	63	1	8	Se ye you silf, lest ye lesen the thingis that ye han wrouyt, that ye resseyue ful mede;
30635	63	1	9	witynge that ech man that goith bifore, and dwellith not in the teching of Crist, hath not God. He that dwellith in the teching,  hath bothe the sone and the fadir.
30636	63	1	10	If ony man cometh to you, and bryngith not this teching, nyle ye resseyue hym in to hous, nether seie ye to hym, Heil.
30637	63	1	11	For he that seith to hym, Heil, comyneth with hise yuel werkis. Lo! Y biforseide to you, that ye be not confoundid in the dai of oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
30638	63	1	12	Y haue mo thingis to write to you, and Y wolde not bi parchemyn and enke; for Y hope that Y schal come to you, and speke mouth to mouth, that your ioye be ful.
30639	63	1	13	The sones of thi chosun sistir greten thee wel. The grace of God be with thee. Amen.
30640	64	1	1	The eldere man to Gayus, most dere brother, whom Y loue in treuthe.
30641	64	1	2	Most dere brothir, of alle thingis Y make preyer, that thou entre, and fare welefuly, as thi soule doith welefuli.
30642	64	1	3	Y ioyede greetli, for britheren camen, and baren witnessing to thi treuthe, `as thou walkist in treuthe.
30643	64	1	4	Y haue not more grace of these thingis, than that Y here that my sones walke in treuthe.
30644	64	1	5	Most dere brother, thou doist feithfuli, what euer thou worchist in britheren, and that in to pilgrymys,
30645	64	1	6	which yeldiden witnessing to thi charite, in the siyt of the chirche; which thou leddist forth, and doist wel worthili to God.
30646	64	1	7	For thei wenten forth for his name, and token no thing of hethene men.
30647	64	1	8	Therfor we owen to resseyue siche, that we be euen worcheris of treuthe.
30648	64	1	9	I hadde write perauenture to the chirche, but this Diotrepes, that loueth to bere primacie in hem, resseyueth not vs.
30649	64	1	10	For this thing, if Y schal come, Y schal moneste hise werkis, whiche he doith, chidinge ayens vs with yuel wordis. And as if these thingis suffisen not to hym, nether he resseyueth britheren,  and forbedith hem that resseyuen, and puttith out of the chirche.
30650	64	1	11	Moost dere brothir, nyle thou sue yuel thing, but that that is good thing. He that doith wel, is of God; he that doith yuel, seeth not God.
30651	64	1	12	Witnessing is yoldun to Demetrie of alle men, and of treuthe it silf; but also we beren witnessing, and thou knowist, that oure witnessing is trewe.
30652	64	1	13	Y hadde many thingis to wryte to thee, but Y wolde not write to thee bi enke and penne.
30653	64	1	14	For Y hope soone to se thee, and we schulen speke mouth to mouth. Pees be to thee. Frendis greten thee wel. Greete thou wel frendis bi name.
30654	65	1	1	Judas, the seruaunt of Jhesu Crist, and brother of James, to these that ben louyd, that ben in God the fadir, and to hem that ben clepid and kept of Jhesu Crist,
30655	65	1	2	mercy, and pees, and charite be fillid to you.
30656	65	1	3	Moost dere britheren, Y doynge al bisynesse to write to you of youre comyn helthe, hadde nede to write to you, and preye to striue strongli for the feith that is onys takun to seyntis.
30657	65	1	4	For summe vnfeithful men priueli entriden, that sum tyme weren bifore writun in to this dom, and ouerturnen the grace of oure God in to letcherie, and denyen hym that is oneli a Lord, oure Lord Jhesu Crist.
30658	65	1	5	But Y wole moneste you onys, that witen alle thingis, that Jhesus sauyde his puple fro the lond of Egipt, and the secunde tyme loste hem that bileueden not.
30659	65	1	6	And he reseruede vndur derknesse aungels, that kepten not her prinshod, but forsoken her hous, in to the dom of the greet God, in to euerlastynge bondis.
30660	65	1	7	As Sodom, and Gomorre, and the nyy coostid citees, that in lijk maner diden fornycacioun, and yeden  awei aftir othir fleisch, and ben maad ensaumple, suffrynge peyne of euerelastinge fier.
30661	65	1	8	In lijk maner also these that defoulen the fleisch, and dispisen lordschip, and blasfemen mageste.
30662	65	1	9	Whanne Myyhel, arkaungel, disputide with the deuel, and stroof of Moises bodi, he was not hardi to brynge in dom of blasfemye, but seide, The Lord comaunde to thee.
30663	65	1	10	But these men blasfemen, what euer thingis thei knowen not. For what euer thingis thei knowen kyndli as doumbe beestis, in these thei ben corupt.
30664	65	1	11	Wo to hem that wenten the weie of Caym, and that ben sched out bi errour of Balaam for mede, and perischiden in the ayenseiyng of Chore.
30665	65	1	12	These ben in her metis, feestynge togidere to filthe, with out drede fedinge hemsilf. These ben cloudis with out watir, that ben borun aboute of the wyndis; heruest trees with out fruyt, twies deed, drawun vp bi the roote;
30666	65	1	13	wawis of the woode see, fomynge out her confusiouns; errynge sterris, to whiche the tempest of derknessis is kept with outen ende.
30667	65	1	14	But Enoch, the seuenthe fro Adam, profeciede of these, and seide, Lo! the Lord cometh with hise hooli thousandis,
30668	65	1	15	to do dom ayens alle men, and to repreue alle vnfeithful men of alle the werkis of the wickidnesse of hem, bi whiche thei diden wickidli, and of alle the harde wordis, that wyckid synneris han spoke ayens God.
30669	65	1	16	These ben grutcheris ful of pleyntis, wandrynge aftir her desiris; and the mouth of hem spekith pride,  worschipinge persoones, bi cause of wynnyng.
30670	65	1	17	And ye, moost dere britheren, be myndeful of the wordis, whiche ben bifor seid of apostlis of oure Lord Jhesu Crist; whiche seiden to you,
30671	65	1	18	that in the laste tymes ther schulen come gilours, wandringe aftir her owne desiris, not in pitee.
30672	65	1	19	These ben, whiche departen hemsilf, beestli men, not hauynge spirit.
30673	65	1	20	But ye, moost dere britheren, aboue bilde you silf on youre moost hooli feith, and preye ye in the Hooli Goost,
30674	65	1	21	and kepe you silf in the loue of God, and abide ye the merci of oure Lord Jhesu Crist in to lijf euerlastynge.
30675	65	1	22	And repreue ye these men that ben demed,
30676	65	1	23	but saue ye hem, and take ye hem fro the fier. And do ye merci to othere men, in the drede of God, and hate ye also thilke defoulid coote, which is fleischli.
30677	65	1	24	But to him that is miyti to kepe you with out synne, and to ordeyne bifore the siyt of his glorie you vnwemmed in ful out ioye, in the comynge of oure Lord Jhesu Crist, to God aloone oure sauyour,
30678	65	1	25	bi Jhesu Crist oure Lord, be glorie, and magnefiyng, empire, and power, bifore alle worldis, `and now and in to alle worldis of worldis. Amen.
30679	66	1	1	Apocalips of Jhesu Crist, which God yaf to hym to make open to hise seruauntis, whiche thingis it bihoueth to be maad soone. And he signyfiede, sending bi his aungel to his seruaunt Joon,
30680	66	1	2	whiche bar witnessing to the word of God, and witnessing of Jhesu Crist, in these thingis, what euer thingis he say.
30681	66	1	3	Blessid is he that redith, and he that herith the wordis of this prophecie, and kepith tho thingis that ben writun in it; for the tyme is niy.
30682	66	1	4	Joon to seuene chirchis, that ben in Asie, grace and pees  to you, of him that is, and that was, and that is to comynge; and of the seuene spiritis, that ben in the siyt of his trone; and of Jhesu Crist,
30683	66	1	5	that is a feithful witnesse, the firste bigetun of deed men, and prince of kingis of the erthe; which louyde vs, and waischide vs fro oure synnes in his blood,
30684	66	1	6	and made vs a kyngdom, and preestis to God and to his fader; to hym be glorie and empire in to worldis of worldis.
30685	66	1	7	Amen. Lo! he cometh with clowdis, and ech iye schal se hym, and thei that prickiden hym; and alle the kynredis of the erthe schulen beweile hem silf on hym.
30686	66	1	8	Yhe, Amen! Y am alpha and oo, the bigynnyng and the ende, seith the Lord God, that is, and that was, and that is to comynge, almyyti.
30687	66	1	9	I, Joon, youre brothir, and partener in tribulacioun, and kingdom, and pacience in Crist Jhesu, was in an ile, that is clepid Pathmos, for the word of God, and for the witnessyng of Jhesu.
30688	66	1	10	Y was in spirit in the Lordis dai, and Y herde bihynde me a greet vois, as of a trumpe,
30689	66	1	11	seiynge to me, Write thou in a book that thing that thou seest, and sende to the seuene chirchis that ben in Asie; to Ephesus, to Smyrma, and to Pergamus, and to Tiatira, and to Sardis, and to Filadelfia, and to Loadicia.
30690	66	1	12	And Y turnede, that Y schulde se the vois that spak with me; and Y turnede, and Y say seuene candelstikis of gold,
30691	66	1	13	and in the myddil of the seuene goldun candelstikis oon lijk to the sone of man, clothid with a long garnement, and gird at the tetis with a goldun girdil.
30692	66	1	14	And the heed of hym and his heeris weren whijt, as whijt wolle, and as snow; and  the iyen of hym as flawme of fier,
30693	66	1	15	and hise feet lijk to latoun, as in a brennynge chymney; and the vois of hym as the vois of many watris.
30694	66	1	16	And he hadde in his riyt hoond seuene sterris, and a swerd scharp on euer ethir side wente out of his mouth; and his face as the sunne schyneth in his virtu.
30695	66	1	17	And whanne Y hadde seyn hym, Y felde doun at hise feet, as deed. And he puttide his riyt hond on me, and seide, Nyle thou drede; Y am the firste and the laste; and Y am alyue, and Y was deed;
30696	66	1	18	and lo! Y am lyuynge in to worldis of worldis, and Y haue the keyes of deth and of helle.
30697	66	1	19	Therfor write thou whiche thingis thou hast seyn, and whiche ben, and whiche it bihoueth to be don aftir these thingis.
30698	66	1	20	The sacrament of the seuene sterris, which thou seiyest in my riyt hond, and the seuene goldun candelstikis; the seuene sterris ben aungels of the seuene chirchis, and the seuene candelstikis ben seuene chirchis.
30699	66	2	1	And to the aungel of the chirche of Efesus write thou, These thingis seith he, that holdith the seuene sterris in his riyt hond, which walkith in the middil of the seuene goldun candilstikis.
30700	66	2	2	Y woot thi werkis, and trauel, and thi pacience, and that thou maist not suffre yuele men; and thou hast asaied hem that seien that thei ben apostlis, and ben not, and thou hast foundun hem lieris;
30701	66	2	3	and thou hast pacience, and thou hast suffrid for my name, and failidist not.
30702	66	2	4	But Y haue ayens thee a fewe thingis, that thou hast left thi firste charite.
30703	66	2	5	Therfor be thou myndeful fro  whennus thou hast falle, and do penaunce, and do the firste werkis; ether ellis, Y come soone to thee, and Y schal moue thi candilstike fro his place, but `thou do penaunce.
30704	66	2	6	But thou hast this good thing, that thou hatidist the dedis of Nycholaitis, the whiche also Y hate.
30705	66	2	7	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis. To hym that ouercometh Y schal yyue to ete of the tre of lijf, that is in the paradis of my God.
30706	66	2	8	And to the aungel of the chirche of Smyrma write thou, These thingis seith the firste and the laste, that was deed, and lyueth.
30707	66	2	9	Y woot thi tribulacioun, and thi pouert, but thou art riche; and thou art blasfemyd of hem, that seien, that thei ben Jewis, and ben not, but ben the synagoge of Sathanas.
30708	66	2	10	Drede thou no thing of these thingis, whiche thou schalt suffre. Lo! the deuel schal sende summe of you in to prisoun, that ye be temptid; and ye schulen haue tribulacioun ten daies. Be thou feithful to the deth, and Y schal yyue to thee a coroun of lijf.
30709	66	2	11	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis. He that ouercometh, schal not be hirt of the secounde deth.
30710	66	2	12	And to the aungel of the chirche of Pergamus write thou, These thingis seith he, that hath the swerd scharp on ech side.
30711	66	2	13	Y woot where thou dwellist, where the seete of Sathanas is; and thou holdist my name, and denyedist not my feith. And in tho daies was Antifas, my feithful witnesse, that was slayn at you, where Sathanas dwellith.
30712	66	2	14	But Y haue ayens thee a fewe thingis; for thou hast `there men holdinge the teching of Balaam,  which tauyte Balaac for to sende sclaundre bifor the sones of Israel, to ete of sacrificis of ydols, and to do fornicacioun;
30713	66	2	15	so also thou hast men holdinge the teching of Nycholaitis.
30714	66	2	16	Also do thou penaunce; `yif ony thing lesse, Y schal come soone to thee, and Y schal fiyte with hem with the swerd of my mouth.
30715	66	2	17	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirches. To him that ouercometh Y schal yyue aungel mete hid; and Y schal yyue to hym a whiit stoon, and in the stoon a newe name writun, which no man knowith, but he that takith.
30716	66	2	18	And to the aungel of the chirche of Tiatira write thou, These thingis seith the sone of God, that hath iyen as flawme of fier, and hise feet lijk latoun.
30717	66	2	19	Y knowe thi werkis, and feith, and charite, and thi seruyce, and thi pacience, and thi laste werkis mo than the formere.
30718	66	2	20	But Y haue ayens thee a fewe thingis; for thou suffrist the womman Jesabel, which seith that sche is a prophetesse, to teche and disseyue my seruauntis, to do letcherie, and to ete of thingis offrid to idols.
30719	66	2	21	And Y yaf to hir time, that sche schulde do penaunce, and sche wolde not do penaunce of hir fornycacioun.
30720	66	2	22	And lo! Y sende hir in to a bed, and thei that doen letcherie with hir schulen be in moost tribulacioun, but thei don penaunce of hir werkis.
30721	66	2	23	And Y schal slee hir sones in to deth, and alle chirchis schulen wite, that Y am serchinge reynes and hertis; and Y schal yyue to ech man of you after hise werkis.
30722	66	2	24	And Y seie to you, and to othere that ben at Tiatire, who euer han not this teching, and that knewen not the hiynesse of Sathanas, hou thei seien, Y  schal not sende on you another charge; netheles holde ye that that ye han,
30723	66	2	25	til Y come.
30724	66	2	26	And to hym that schal ouercome, and that schal kepe til in to the ende my werkis, Y schal yyue power on folkis,
30725	66	2	27	and he schal gouerne hem in an yrun yerde; and thei schulen be brokun to gidre,
30726	66	2	28	as a vessel of a pottere, as also Y resseyuede of my fadir; and Y schal yyue to hym a morewe sterre.
30727	66	2	29	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis.
30728	66	3	1	And to the aungel of the chirche of Sardis write thou, These thingis seith he, that hath the seuene spiritis of God, and the seuene sterris. Y woot thi werkis, for thou hast a name, that thou lyuest, and thou art deed.
30729	66	3	2	Be thou wakynge, and conferme thou othere thingis, that weren to diynge; for Y fynde not thi werkis fulle bifore my God.
30730	66	3	3	Therfor haue thou in mynde, hou thou resseyuedist, and herdist; and kepe, and do penaunce. Therfor if thou wake not, Y schal come as a nyyt theef to thee, and thou schalt not wite in what our Y schal come to thee.
30731	66	3	4	But thou hast a fewe names in Sardis, whiche han not defoulid her clothis; and thei schulen walke with me in whijt clothis, for thei ben worthi.
30732	66	3	5	He that ouercometh, schal be clothid thus with whijt clothis; and Y schal not do awei his name fro the book of lijf, and Y schal knoueleche his name bifore my fadir, and bifore hise aungels.
30733	66	3	6	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis.
30734	66	3	7	And to the aungel of the chirche of Filadelfie write thou, These thingis seith the hooli and trewe, that hath the keie of Dauid; which openeth, and no man closith, he  closith, and no man openith.
30735	66	3	8	I woot thi werkis, and lo! Y yaf bifore thee a dore opened, which no man may close; for thou hast a litil vertu, and hast kept my word, and denyest not my name.
30736	66	3	9	Lo! Y schal yyue to thee of the synagoge of Sathanas, whiche seien that thei ben Jewis, and ben not, but lyen. Lo! Y schal make hem, that thei come, and worschipe byfor thi feet; and thei schulen wite,
30737	66	3	10	that Y louyde thee, for thou keptist the word of my pacience. And Y schal kepe thee fro the our of temptacioun, that is to comynge in to al the world, to tempte men that dwellen in erthe.
30738	66	3	11	Lo! Y come soone; holde thou that that thou hast, that no man take thi coroun.
30739	66	3	12	And hym that schal ouercome, Y schal make a pilere in the temple of my God, and he schal no more go out; and Y schal write on hym the name of my God, and the name of the citee of my God, of the newe Jerusalem, that cometh doun fro heuene of my God, and my newe name.
30740	66	3	13	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis.
30741	66	3	14	And to the aungel of the chirche of Laodice write thou, These thingis seith Amen, the feithful witnesse and trewe, which is bigynnyng of Goddis creature.
30742	66	3	15	I woot thi werkis, for nether thou art cold, nether thou art hoot; Y wolde that thou were could, ethir hoot;
30743	66	3	16	but for thou art lew, and nether cold, nether hoot, Y schal bigynne to caste thee out of my mouth.
30744	66	3	17	For thou seist, That Y am riche, and ful of goodis, and Y haue nede of no thing; and thou wost not, that thou art a wretche, and wretcheful, `and pore, and blynde, and nakid.
30745	66	3	18	Y counsele thee to bie of me brent gold, and preued,  that thou be maad riche, and be clothid with whijt clothis, that the confusioun of thi nakidnesse be not seen; and anoynte thin iyen with a collerie, that thou se.
30746	66	3	19	Y repreue, and chastise whom Y loue; therfor sue thou goode men, and do penaunce.
30747	66	3	20	Lo! Y stonde at the dore, and knocke; if ony man herith my voys, and openith the yate to me, Y shal entre to hym, and soupe with hym, and he with me.
30748	66	3	21	And Y schal yyue to hym that schal ouercome, to sitte with me in my trone, as also Y ouercam, and sat with my fadir in his trone.
30749	66	3	22	He that hath eeris, here he, what the spirit seith to the chirchis.
30750	66	4	1	Aftir these thingis Y say, and lo! a dore was openyd in heuene. And the firste vois that Y herde, was as of a trumpe spekinge with me, and seide, Stye thou vp hidur, and Y shal schewe to thee whiche thingis it bihoueth to be don soone aftir these thingus.
30751	66	4	2	Anoon Y was in spirit, and lo! a seete was sett in heuene, and vpon the seete oon sittynge.
30752	66	4	3	And he that sat, was lijk the siyt of a stoon iaspis, and to sardyn; and a reynbowe was in cumpas of the seete, lijk the siyt of smaragdyn.
30753	66	4	4	And in the cumpas of the seete weren foure and twenti smale seetis; and aboue the troones foure and twenti eldre men sittinge, hilid aboute with whijt clothis, and in the heedis of hem goldun corouns.
30754	66	4	5	And leitis, and voices, and thundringis camen out of the trone; and seuene laumpis brennynge bifore the trone, whiche ben the seuene spiritis of God.
30755	66	4	6	And bifor  the seete as a see of glas, lijk a crystal, and in the myddil of the seete, and in the cumpas of the seete, foure beestis ful of iyen bifore and bihynde.
30756	66	4	7	And the firste beeste lijk a lyoun; and the secounde beeste lijk a calf; and the thridde beeste hauynge a face as of a man; and the fourthe beeste lijk an egle fleynge.
30757	66	4	8	And the foure beestis hadden euery of hem sixe wyngis; and al aboute and with ynne thei weren ful of iyen; and thei hadden not reste dai and nyyt, seiynge, Hooli, hooli, hooli, the Lord God almyyti, that was, and that is, and that is to comynge.
30758	66	4	9	And whanne tho foure beestis yauen glorie, and honour, and blessing to hym that sat on the trone, that lyueth in to worldis of worldis,
30759	66	4	10	the foure and twenti eldre men fellen doun bifor hym that sat on the trone, and worschipiden hym that lyueth in to worldis of worldis. And thei casten her corouns bifor the trone,
30760	66	4	11	and seiden, Thou, Lord `oure God, art worthi to take glorie, and onour, and vertu; for thou madist of nouyt alle thingis, and for thi wille tho weren, and ben maad of nouyt.
30761	66	5	1	And Y say in the riythond of the sittere on the trone, a book writun with ynne and with out, and seelid with seuene seelis.
30762	66	5	2	And Y say a strong aungel, prechynge with a greet vois, Who is worthi to opene the book, and to vndon the seelis of it?
30763	66	5	3	And noon in heuene, nether in erthe, nether vnder erthe, myyte opene the book, nether biholde it.
30764	66	5	4	And Y wepte myche, for noon was founde worthi to opene the book, nethir to se it.
30765	66	5	5	And oon of the eldre men seide to me, Wepe thou not; lo! a lioun of the lynage of Juda, the  roote of Dauid, hath ouercomun to opene the book, and to vndon the seuene seelis of it.
30766	66	5	6	And Y say, and lo! in the myddil of the trone, and of the foure beestis, and in the myddil of the eldre men, a lombe stondynge as slayn, that hadde seuene hornes, and seuene iyen, whiche ben seuene spiritis of God, sent in to al the erthe.
30767	66	5	7	And he cam, and took of the riythond of the sittere in the trone the book.
30768	66	5	8	And whanne he hadde opened the book, the foure beestis and the foure and twenti eldre men fellen doun bifore the lomb; and hadden ech of hem harpis, and goldun violis ful of odours, whiche ben the preyeris of seyntis.
30769	66	5	9	And thei sungun a newe song, and seiden, Lord oure God, thou art worthi to take the book, and to opene the seelis of it; for thou were slayn, and ayenbouytist vs to God in thi blood, of ech lynage, `and tunge, and puple, and nacioun;
30770	66	5	10	and madist vs a kyngdom, and prestis to oure God; and we schulen regne on erthe.
30771	66	5	11	And Y say, and herde the vois of many aungels al aboute the trone, and of the beestis, and of the eldre men. And the noumbre of hem was thousyndis of thousyndis, seiynge with a greet vois,
30772	66	5	12	The lomb that was slayn, is worthi to take vertu, and godhed, and wisdom, and strengthe, and onour, and glorie, and blessing.
30773	66	5	13	And ech creature that is in heuene, and that is on erthe, and vndur erthe, and the see, and whiche thingis ben in it, Y herde alle seiynge, To hym that sat in the trone, and to the lomb, blessyng, and onour, and glorie, and power, in to worldis of worldis.
30774	66	5	14	And the foure beestis seiden, Amen. And  the foure and twenti eldre men fellen doun on her faces, and worschipiden hym that lyueth in to worldis of worldis.
30775	66	6	1	And Y sai, that the lomb hadde openyd oon of the seuene seelis. And Y herde oon of the foure beestis seiynge, as a vois of thundur, Come, and se.
30776	66	6	2	And Y sai, and lo! a white hors; and he that sat on hym hadde a bouwe, and a coroun was youun to hym. And he wente out ouercomynge, that he schulde ouercome.
30777	66	6	3	And whanne he hadde openyd the secounde seel, I herde the secounde beest seiynge, Come `thou, and se.
30778	66	6	4	And another reed hors wente out; and it was youun to hym that sat on hym, that he schulde take pees fro the erthe, and that thei sle to gidere hem silf; and a greet swerd was youun to hym.
30779	66	6	5	And whanne he hadde openyd the thridde seel, Y herde the thridde beest seiynge, Come thou, and se. And lo! a blak hors; and he that sat on hym hadde a balaunce in his hond.
30780	66	6	6	And Y herde `as a vois in the myddil of the foure beestis, seiynge, A bilibre of wheete for a peny, and thre bilibris of barli for a peny; and hirte thou not wyn, ne oile.
30781	66	6	7	And whanne he hadde openyd the fourthe seel, Y herde a vois of the `foure beestis, seiynge, Come thou, and se.
30782	66	6	8	And lo! a pale hors; and the name was Deth to hym that sat on hym, and helle suede hym. And power was youun to hym on foure partis of the erthe, for to sle with swerd, and with hungur, and with deth, and with beestis of the erthe.
30783	66	6	9	And whanne he hadde opened the fyuethe seel, Y say vndur the auter the soulis of men slayn  for the word of God, and for the witnessing that thei hadden.
30784	66	6	10	And thei crieden with a geet vois, and seiden, Hou long thou, Lord, that art hooli and trewe, demest not, and vengest not oure blood of these that dwellen in the erthe?
30785	66	6	11	And white stoolis, for ech soule a stoole, weren youun to hem; and it was seide to hem, that thei schulden reste yit a litil tyme, til the noumbre of her felowis and of her britheren ben fulfillid, that ben to be slayn, as also thei.
30786	66	6	12	And Y say, whanne he hadde openyd the sixte seel, and lo! a greet erthe mouyng was maad; and the sunne was maad blak, as a sak of heire, and al the moone was maad as blood.
30787	66	6	13	And the sterris of heuene felden doun on the erthe, as a fige tre sendith his vnripe figis, whanne it is mouyd of a greet wynd.
30788	66	6	14	And heuene wente awei, as a book wlappid in; and alle munteyns and ilis weren mouyd fro her placis.
30789	66	6	15	And kingis of the erthe, and princis, and tribunes, and riche, and stronge, and ech bonde man, and freman, hidden hem in dennys and stoonys of hillis.
30790	66	6	16	And thei seien to hillis and to stoonys, Falle ye on vs, and hide ye vs fro the face of hym that sittith on the trone, and fro the wrath of the lomb;
30791	66	6	17	for the greet dai of her wraththe cometh, and who schal mowe stonde?
30792	66	7	1	Aftir these thingis Y sai foure aungels stondinge on the foure corneris of the erthe, holdinge foure wyndis of the erthe, that thei blewen not on the erthe, nether on the see, nether on ony tre.
30793	66	7	2	And Y sawy anothir aungel stiynge fro the risynge of the sunne, that hadde a signe of  the lyuynge God. And he criede with a greet vois to the foure aungels, to whiche it was youun to noye the erthe, and the see,
30794	66	7	3	and seide, Nyle ye noye the erthe, and see, nether trees, til we marken the seruauntis of oure God in the forhedis of hem.
30795	66	7	4	And I herde the noumbre of men that weren markid, an hundrid thousynde and foure and fourti thousynde markid, of euery lynage of the sones of Israel;
30796	66	7	5	of the lynage of Juda, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Ruben, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Gad, twelue thousynde markid;
30797	66	7	6	of the lynage of Aser, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Neptalym, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Manasse, twelue thousynde markid;
30798	66	7	7	of the lynage of Symeon, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Leuy, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Isachar, twelue thousynde markid;
30799	66	7	8	of the lynage of Zabulon, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Joseph, twelue thousynde markid; of the lynage of Beniamyn, twelue thousynde markid.
30800	66	7	9	Aftir these thingis Y sai a greet puple, whom no man myyte noumbre, of alle folkis, and lynagis, and puplis, and langagis, stondinge bifore the trone, in the siyt of the lomb; and thei weren clothid with white stoolis, and palmes weren in the hondis of hem.
30801	66	7	10	And thei crieden with greet vois, and seiden, Heelthe to oure God, that sittith on the troone, and to the lombe.
30802	66	7	11	And alle aungels `stoden al aboute the trone, and the eldre men, and the foure beestis. And thei fellen doun in the  siyt of the trone, on her faces, and worschipiden God, and seiden, Amen!
30803	66	7	12	blessyng, and clerenesse, and wisdom, and doynge of thankingis, and honour, and vertu, and strengthe to oure God, in to worldis of worldis.
30804	66	7	13	Amen. And oon of the senyours answerde, and seide to me, Who ben these, that ben clothid with white stoolis? and fro whennus came thei?
30805	66	7	14	And Y seide to hym, My lord, thou woost. And he seide to me, These ben thei, that camen fro greet tribulacioun, and waischiden her stoolis, and maden hem white in the blood of the lomb.
30806	66	7	15	Therfor thei ben bifor the trone of God, and seruen to hym dai and niyt, in his temple. And he that sittith in the trone, dwellith on hem.
30807	66	7	16	Thei schulen no more hungur, nether thirste, nether sunne schal falle on hem, ne ony heete.
30808	66	7	17	For the lomb, that is in the myddil of the trone, schal gouerne hem, and schal lede forth hem to the wellis of watris of lijf; and God schal wipe awei ech teer fro the iyen of hem.
30809	66	8	1	And whanne he hadde openyd the seuenthe seel, a silence was maad in heuene, as half an our.
30810	66	8	2	And Y say seuene aungels stondinge in the siyt of God, and seuene trumpis weren youun to hem.
30811	66	8	3	And another aungel cam, and stood bifor the auter, and hadde a goldun censer; and many encencis weren youun to hym, that he schulde yyue of the preiers of alle seyntis on the goldun auter, that is bifor the trone of God.
30812	66	8	4	And the smoke of encencis of the preiers of the hooli men stiede vp fro the aungels hoond bifor God.
30813	66	8	5	And the aungel took the censere, and fillide it of the fier of the auter, and  castide in to the erthe. And thundris, and voices, and leityngis weren maad, and a greet erthe mouyng.
30814	66	8	6	And the seuene aungels, that hadden seuene trumpis, maden hem redi, that thei schulden trumpe.
30815	66	8	7	And the firste aungel trumpide; and hail was maad, and fier meynd togidere in blood; and it was sent in to the erthe. And the thridde part of the erthe was brent, and the thridde part of trees was brent, and al the green gras was brent.
30816	66	8	8	And the secunde aungel trumpide; and as a greet hil brennynge with fier was cast in to the see;
30817	66	8	9	and the thridde part of the see was maad blood, and the thridde part of creature was deed, that hadde lyues in the see, and the thridde part of schippis perischide.
30818	66	8	10	And the thridde aungel trumpide; and a greet sterre brennynge as a litil brond, felle fro heuene; and it felle in to the thridde part of floodis, and in to the wellis of watris.
30819	66	8	11	And the name of the sterre is seid Wormod. And the thridde part of watris was maad in to wormod; and many men weren deed of the watris, for tho weren maad bittere.
30820	66	8	12	And the fourthe aungel trumpide; and the thridde part of the sunne was smytun, and the thridde part of the moone, and the thridde part of sterris, so that the thridde part of hem was derkid, and the thridde part of the dai schynede not, and also of the nyyt.
30821	66	8	13	And Y say, and herde the vois of an egle fleynge bi the myddil of heuene, and seiynge with a greet vois, Wo! wo! wo! to men that dwellen in erthe, of the othir voices of thre aungels, that schulen trumpe aftir.
30822	66	9	1	And the fyuethe aungel trumpide; and Y say, that a sterre hadde falle doun fro heuene in to erthe; and the keye of the pit of depnesse was youun to it.
30823	66	9	2	And it openede the pit of depnesse, and a smoke of the pit stiede vp, as the smoke of a greet furneis; and the sunne was derkid, and the eir, of the smoke of the pit.
30824	66	9	3	And locustis wenten out of the smoke of the pit in to erthe; and power was youun to hem, as scorpiouns of the erthe han power.
30825	66	9	4	And it was comaundid to hem, that thei schulden not hirte the gras of erthe, nether ony grene thing, nether ony tre, but oneli men, that han not the signe of God in her forhedis.
30826	66	9	5	And it was youun to hem, that thei schulden not sle hem, but that thei schulden `be turmentid fyue monethis; and the turmentyng of hem, as the turmentyng of a scorpioun, whanne he smytith a man.
30827	66	9	6	And in tho daies men schulen seke deth, and thei schulen not fynde it; and thei schulen desire to die, and deth schal fle fro hem.
30828	66	9	7	And the licnesse of locustis ben lijk horsis maad redi `in to batel; and on the heedis of hem as corouns lijk gold, and the facis of hem as the faces of men.
30829	66	9	8	And thei hadden heeris, as heeris of wymmen; and the teeth of hem weren as teeth of liouns.
30830	66	9	9	And thei hadden haburiouns, as yren haburiouns, and the vois of her wengis as the vois of charis of many horsis rennynge `in to batel.
30831	66	9	10	And thei hadden tailis lijk scorpiouns, and prickis weren in the tailis of hem; and the myyt of hem was to noye men fyue monethis.
30832	66	9	11	And thei hadden on hem a kyng, the aungel of depnesse, to whom the name bi Ebrew is Laabadon, but bi Greek Appollion, and bi Latyn `he hath a name `Extermynans, that is, a distriere.
30833	66	9	12	O wo is passid, and lo! yit comen twei woes.
30834	66	9	13	Aftir these thingis also the sixte aungel trumpide; and Y herde a vois fro foure corneris of the goldun auter, that is bifore the iyen of God,
30835	66	9	14	and seide to the sixte aungel that hadde a trumpe, Vnbynde thou foure aungels, that ben boundun in the greet flood Eufrates.
30836	66	9	15	And the foure aungels weren vnboundun, whiche weren redi in to our, and dai, and monethe, and yeer, to sle the thridde part of men.
30837	66	9	16	And the noumbre of the oost of horse men was twenti thousynde sithis ten thousynde. Y herde the noumbre of hem.
30838	66	9	17	And so Y say horsis in visioun; and thei that saten on hem hadden firy haburiouns, and of iacynt, and of brymstoon. And the heedis of the horsis weren as heedis of liouns; and fier, and smoke, and brymston, cometh forth of the mouth of hem.
30839	66	9	18	Of these thre plagis the thridde part of men was slayn, of the fier, and of the smoke, and of the brymston, that camen out of the mouth of hem.
30840	66	9	19	For the power of the horsis is in the mouth of hem, and in the tailis of hem; for the tailis of hem ben lyk to serpentis, hauynge heedis, and in hem thei noyen.
30841	66	9	20	And the tothir men, that weren not slayn in these plagis, nether dyden penaunce of the werkis of her hondis, that thei worschipeden not deuelis, and simylacris of gold,  and of siluer, and of bras, and of stoon, and of tre, whiche nethir mown se, nether heere, nether wandre;
30842	66	9	21	and diden not penaunce of her mansleyngis, nether of her witchecraftis, nethir of her fornicacioun, nethir of her theftis, weren slayn.
30843	66	10	1	And Y say another stronge aungel comynge doun fro heuene, clothid with a cloude, and the reynbowe on his heed; and the face of him was as the sunne, and the feet of hym as a piler of fier.
30844	66	10	2	And he hadde in his hoond a litil book openyd; and he sette his riyt foot on the see, and the left foot on the erthe.
30845	66	10	3	And he criede with a greet vois, as a lioun whanne he roreth; and whanne he hadde cried, the seuene thundris spaken her voicis.
30846	66	10	4	And whanne the seuene thundris hadden spoken her voicis, Y was to writynge. And Y herde a vois fro heuene, seiynge, Marke thou what thingis the seuene thundris spaken, and nyle thou write hem.
30847	66	10	5	And the aungel whom Y say stondinge aboue the see, and aboue the erthe, lifte vp his hond to heuene,
30848	66	10	6	and swoor bi hym that lyueth in to worldis of worldis, that maad of nouyt heuene, and tho thingis whiche ben in it, and the erthe, and tho thingis that ben in it, and the see, and tho thingis that ben in it, that time schal no more be.
30849	66	10	7	But in the daies of the vois of the seuenethe aungel, whanne he schal bigynne to trumpe, the mysterie of God schal be endid, as he prechide bi hise seruauntis prophetis.
30850	66	10	8	And Y herde a vois fro heuene eftsoone spekynge with me, and seiynge, Go thou, and take the book, that is openyd, fro the hoond of  the aungel, that stondith aboue the see, and on the lond.
30851	66	10	9	And Y wente to the aungel, and seide to hym, that he schulde yyue me the book. And he seide to me, Take the book, and deuoure it; and it schal make thi wombe to be bittir, but in thi mouth it schal be swete as hony.
30852	66	10	10	And Y took the book of the aungels hond, and deuouride it, and it was in my mouth as swete hony; and whanne Y hadde deuourid it, my wombe was bittere. And he seide to me, It bihoueth thee eftsoone to prophesie to hethene men, and to puplis, and langagis, and to many kingis.
30853	66	11	1	And a reed lijk a yerde was youun to me, and it was seid to me, Rise thou, and meete the temple of God, and the auter, and men that worschipen in it.
30854	66	11	2	But caste thou out the foryerd, that is with out the temple, and mete not it; for it is youun to hethene men, and thei schulen defoule the hooli citee bi fourti monethis and tweyne.
30855	66	11	3	And Y schal yyue `to my twey witnessis, and thei schulen prophesie a thousynde daies two hundrid and sixti, and schulen be clothid with sackis.
30856	66	11	4	These ben tweyne olyues, and twei candilstikis, and thei stonden in the siyt of the Lord of the erthe.
30857	66	11	5	And if ony man wole anoye hem, fier schal go out of the mouth of hem, and schal deuoure her enemyes. And if ony wole hirte hem, thus it bihoueth hym to be slayn.
30858	66	11	6	These han power to close heuene, that it reyne not in the daies of her prophesie; and thei han power on watris, to turne hem in to blood; and to smyte the erthe with euery plage, and as ofte as thei wolen.
30859	66	11	7	And whanne thei schulen  ende her witnessing, the beeste that stieth vp fro depnesse, schal make batel ayens hem, and schal ouercome hem, and schal sle hem.
30860	66	11	8	And the bodies of hem schulen ligge in the stretis of the greet citee, that is clepid goostli Sodom, and Egipt, where the Lord of hem was crucified.
30861	66	11	9	And summe of lynagis, and of puplis, and of langagis, and of hethene men, schulen se the bodies of hem bi thre daies and an half; and thei schulen not suffre the bodies of hem to be put in biriels.
30862	66	11	10	And men enhabitynge the erthe schulen haue ioye on hem; and thei schulen make myrie, and schulen sende yiftis togidere, for these twei prophetis turmentiden hem that dwellen on the erthe.
30863	66	11	11	And aftir thre daies and an half, the spirit of lijf of God entride in to hem; and thei stoden on her feet, and greet dreed felle on hem that sayn hem.
30864	66	11	12	And thei herden a greet vois fro heuene, seiynge to hem, Come vp hidir. And thei stieden in to heuene in a cloude, and the enemyes of hem sayn hem.
30865	66	11	13	And in that our a greet erthe mouyng was maad, and the tenthe part of the citee felle doun; and the names of men seuene thousynde weren slayn in the erthe mouyng; and the tother weren sent in to drede, and yauen glorie to God of heuene.
30866	66	11	14	The secounde wo is gon, and lo! the thridde wo schal come soone.
30867	66	11	15	And the seuenthe aungel trumpide, and grete voicis weren maad in heuene, and seiden, The rewme of this world is maad `oure Lordis, and of Crist, his sone; and he schal regne in to worldis of worldis.
30868	66	11	16	Amen. And the foure and twenti eldre  men, that saten in her seetis in the siyt of the Lord, fellen on her faces, and worschipiden God,
30869	66	11	17	and seiden, We don thankyngis to thee, Lord God almyyti, which art, and which were, and which art to comynge; which hast takun thi greet vertu, and hast regned.
30870	66	11	18	And folkis ben wrooth, and thi wraththe cam, and tyme of dede men to be demyd, and to yelde mede to thi seruauntis, and prophetis, and halewis, and dredynge thi name, to smale and to grete, and to distrie hem that corrumpiden the erthe.
30871	66	12	19	And the temple of God in heuene was openyd, and the arke of his testament was seyn in his temple; and leityngis weren maad, and voices, and thondris, and `erthe mouyng, and greet hail.
30872	66	12	1	And a greet signe apperide in heuene; a womman clothid with the sunne, and the moone vndur hir feet, and in the heed of hir a coroun of twelue sterris.
30873	66	12	2	And sche hadde in wombe, and sche crieth, trauelynge of child, and is turmentid, that sche bere child.
30874	66	12	3	And another signe was seyn in heuene; and lo! a greet reede dragoun, that hadde seuene heedis, and ten hornes, and in the heedis of hym seuene diademes.
30875	66	12	4	And the tail of hym drow the thridde part of sterris of heuene, and sente hem in to the erthe. And the dragoun stood bifore the womman, that was to berynge child, that whanne sche hadde borun child, he schulde deuoure hir sone.
30876	66	12	5	And sche bar a knaue child, that was to reulinge alle folkis in an yrun yerde; and hir sone was rauyschid to God, and  to his trone.
30877	66	12	6	And the womman flei in to wildirnesse, where sche hath a place maad redi of God, that he fede hir there a thousynde daies two hundrid and sixti.
30878	66	12	7	And a greet batel was maad in heuene, and Myyhel and hise aungels fouyten with the dragoun. And the dragoun fauyt, and hise aungels;
30879	66	12	8	and thei hadden not myyt, nether the place of hem was foundun more in heuene.
30880	66	12	9	And thilke dragoun was cast doun, the greet elde serpent, that is clepid the Deuel, and Sathanas, that disseyueth al the world; he was cast doun in to the erthe, and hise aungels weren sent with hym.
30881	66	12	10	And Y herde a greet vois in heuene, seiynge, Now is maad helthe, and vertu, and kyngdom of oure God, and the power of his Crist; for the accuser of oure britheren is cast doun, which accuside hem bifor the siyte of oure God dai and nyyt.
30882	66	12	11	And thei ouercamen hym for the blood of the lomb, and for the word of his witnessing; and thei louyden not her lyues til to deth.
30883	66	12	12	Therfor, ye heuenes, be ye glad, and ye that dwellen in hem. Wo to the erthe, and to the see; for the fend is come doun to you, and hath greet wraththe, witynge that he hath litil tyme.
30884	66	12	13	And after that the dragoun sai, that he was cast doun to the erthe, he pursuede the womman, that bare the knaue child.
30885	66	12	14	And twei wengis of a greet egle weren youun to the womman, that sche schulde flee in to deseert, in to hir place, where sche is fed by tyme, and tymes, and half a tyme, fro the face of the serpent.
30886	66	12	15	And the serpent sente out of his mouth aftir the womman watir as a flood, that he schulde make hir to be drawun of the flood.
30887	66	12	16	And the erthe  helpide the womman, and the erthe openyde his mouth, and soop up the flood, that the dragoun sente of his mouth.
30888	66	12	17	And the dragoun was wrooth ayens the womman, and he wente to make batel with othere of hir seed, that kepen the maundementis of God, and han the witnessing of Jhesu Crist.
30889	66	12	18	And he stood on the grauel of the see.
30890	66	13	1	And Y sai a beeste stiynge vp of the see, hauynge seuene heedis, and ten hornes; and on hise hornes ten diademes, and on hise heedis the names of blasfemye.
30891	66	13	2	And the beeste, whom Y sai, was lijk a pard, and hise feet as the feet of a beere, and his mouth as the mouth of a lioun; and the dragoun yaf his vertu and greet power to hym.
30892	66	13	3	And Y sai oon of hise heedis, as slayn in to deth; and the wounde of his deth was curid. And al erthe wondride after the beeste.
30893	66	13	4	And thei worschipiden the dragoun, that yaf power to the beeste; and thei worschipeden the beeste, and seiden, Who is lijk the beeste, and who schal mowe fiyte with it?
30894	66	13	5	And a mouth spekynge grete thingis, and blasfemyes, was youun `to it; and power was youun to it, to do two and fourti monethis.
30895	66	13	6	And it openyde his mouth in to blasfemyes to God, to blasfeme his name, and his tabernacle, and hem that dwellen in heuene.
30896	66	13	7	And it was youun to hym to make batel with seyntis, and to ouercome hem; and power was youun to hym in to ech lynage, and puple, and langage, and folk.
30897	66	13	8	And alle men worschipiden it, that dwellen in erthe, whos names ben not writun in the book of lijf of the  lomb, that was slayn fro the bigynnyng of the world.
30898	66	13	9	If ony man hath eeris, here he.
30899	66	13	10	He that ledith in to caitifte, schal go in to caitifte; he that sleeth with swerd, it bihoueth hym to be slayn with swerd. This is the pacience and the feith of seyntis.
30900	66	13	11	And Y sai another beeste stiynge vp fro the erthe, and it hadde two hornes, lijk the lomb; and it spak as the dragoun,
30901	66	13	12	and dide al the power of the formere beeste, in his siyt. And it made the erthe, and men dwellinge in it, to worschipe the firste beeste, whos wounde of deth was curid.
30902	66	13	13	And it dide grete signes, that also it made fier to come doun fro heuene in to the erthe, in the siyt of alle men.
30903	66	13	14	And it disseyueth men, that dwellen in erthe, for signes whiche ben youun `to it to do in the siyt of the beeste; seiynge to men dwellinge in erthe, that thei make an ymage of the beeste, that hath the wounde of swerd, and lyuede.
30904	66	13	15	And it was youun to hym, that he schulde yyue spirit to the ymage of the beeste, and that the ymage of the beeste speke. And he schal make, that who euere honouren not the ymage of the beeste, be slayn.
30905	66	13	16	And he schal make alle, smale and grete, and riche and pore, and fre men and bonde men, to haue a carecter in her riythoond, ethir in her forheedis; that no man may bie,
30906	66	13	17	ethir sille, but thei han the caracter, ether the name of the beeste, ethir the noumbre of his name.
30907	66	13	18	Here is wisdom; he that hath vndurstonding, acounte the noumbre of the beeste; for it is the noumbre of man, and his noumbre is sixe hundrid sixti and sixe.
30908	66	14	1	And Y sai, and lo! lomb stood on the mount of Sion, and with hym an hundrid thousynde and foure and fourti thousynde, hauynge his name, and the name of his fadir writun in her forhedis.
30909	66	14	2	And Y herde a vois fro heuene, as the vois of many watris, and as the vois of a greet thundur; and the vois which is herd, was as of many harperis harpinge in her harpis.
30910	66	14	3	And thei sungun as a newe song bifor the seete of God, and bifore the foure beestis, and senyouris. And no man miyte seie the song, but thei an hundrid thousynde and foure and fourti thousynde, that ben bouyt fro the erthe.
30911	66	14	4	These it ben, that ben not defoulid with wymmen; for thei ben virgyns. These suen the lomb, whidir euer he schal go; these ben bouyt of alle men, the firste fruytis to God, and to the lomb;
30912	66	14	5	and in the mouth of hem lesyng is not foundun; for thei ben with out wem bifor the trone of God.
30913	66	14	6	And Y say another aungel, fliynge bi the myddil of heuene, hauynge an euerlastinge gospel, that he schulde preche to men sittynge on erthe, and on ech folk, and lynage, and langage, and puple;
30914	66	14	7	and seide with a greet vois, Drede ye the Lord, and yyue ye to hym onour, for the our of his dom cometh; and worschipe ye hym, that made heuene and erthe, the see, and alle thingis that ben in hem, and the wellis of watris.
30915	66	14	8	And anothir aungel suede, seiynge, Thilke greet Babiloyne fel doun, fel doun, which yaf drinke to alle folkis of the wyn of wraththe of her fornycacioun.
30916	66	14	9	And the thridde aungel suede hem, and seide with  a greet vois, If ony man worschipe the beeste, and the ymage of it, and takith the carecter in his forheed, ether in his hoond,
30917	66	14	10	this schal drynke of the wyn of Goddis wraththe, that is meynd with clere wyn in the cuppe of his wraththe, and schal be turmentid with fier and brymston, in the siyt of hooli aungels, and bifore the siyt of the lomb.
30918	66	14	11	And the smoke of her turmentis schal stie vp in to the worldis of worldis; nether thei han reste dai and niyt, whiche worschipiden the beeste and his ymage, and yf ony man take the carect of his name.
30919	66	14	12	Here is the pacience of seyntis, whiche kepen the maundementis of God, and the feith of Jhesu.
30920	66	14	13	And Y herde a vois fro heuene, seiynge to me, Write thou, Blessid ben deed men, that dien in the Lord; fro hennus forth now the spirit seith, that thei reste of her traueilis; for the werkis of hem suen hem.
30921	66	14	14	And Y say, and lo! a white cloude, and aboue the cloude a sittere, lijk the sone of man, hauynge in his heed a goldun coroun, and in his hond a scharp sikil.
30922	66	14	15	And another aungel wente out of the temple, and criede with greet vois to hym that sat on the cloude, Sende thi sikil, and repe, for the our cometh, that it be ropun; for the corn of the erthe is ripe.
30923	66	14	16	And he that sat on the cloude, sente his sikil in to the erthe, and rap the erthe.
30924	66	14	17	And another aungel wente out of the temple, that is in heuene, and he also hadde a scharp sikile.
30925	66	14	18	And another aungel wente out fro the auter, that hadde power on fier and water; and he criede with a greet vois to hym that hadde the scharp sikil, and seide, Sende thi scharp  sikil, and kitte awei the clustris of the vynyerd of the erthe, for the grapis of it ben ripe.
30926	66	14	19	And the aungel sente his sikil in to the erthe, and gaderide grapis of the vynyerd of the erthe, and sente into the greet lake of Goddis wraththe.
30927	66	14	20	And the lake was troddun without the citee, and the blood wente out of the lake til to the `bridels of horsis, bi furlongis a thousynd and six hundrid.
30928	66	15	1	And Y say another signe in heuene, greet and wondurful; seuene aungels hauynge `seuene the laste veniauncis, for the wraththe of God is endid in hem.
30929	66	15	2	And Y say as a glasun see meynd with fier, and hem that ouercamen the beeste, and his ymage, and the noumbre of his name, stondynge aboue the glasun see, hauynge the harpis of God;
30930	66	15	3	and syngynge the song of Moises, the seruaunt of God, and the song of the lomb, and seiden, Grete and wondurful ben thi werkis, Lord God almyyti; thi weies ben iust and trewe, Lord, kyng of worldis.
30931	66	15	4	Lord, who schal not drede thee, and magnyfie thi name? for thou aloone art merciful; for alle folkis schulen come, and worschipe in thi siyt, for thi domes ben open.
30932	66	15	5	And aftir these thingis Y say, and lo! the temple of the tabernacle of witnessyng was opened in heuene;
30933	66	15	6	and seuene aungels hauynge seuene plagis, wenten out of the temple, and weren clothid with a stoon clene and white, and weren bifor gird with goldun girdlis about the brestis.
30934	66	15	7	And oon of the foure beestis yaf to the seuene aungels seuene goldun viols, ful of the wraththe of God, that lyueth in to  worldis of worldis.
30935	66	15	8	And the temple was fillid with smooke of the majestee of God, and of the vertu of hym; and no man myyte entre in to the temple, til the seuene plagis of seuene angels weren endid.
30936	66	16	1	And Y herde a greet vois fro heuene, seiynge to the seuene aungels, Go ye, and schede out the seuene viols of Goddis wraththe in to erthe.
30937	66	16	2	And the firste aungel wente, and schedde out his viol in to the erthe; and a wounde fers and werst was maad on alle that hadden the carect of the beeste, and on hem that worschipiden the beeste, and his ymage.
30938	66	16	3	And the secounde aungel schedde out his viol in to the see, and the blood was maad, as of a deed thing; and ech man lyuynge was deed in the see.
30939	66	16	4	And the thridde aungel schedde out his viol on the floodis, and on the wellis of watris, and seide,
30940	66	16	5	Just art thou, Lord, that art, and that were hooli, that demest these thingis;
30941	66	16	6	for thei schedden out the blood of halewis and prophetis, and thou hast youun to hem blood to drinke; for thei ben worthi.
30942	66	16	7	And I herde anothir seiynge, Yhe! Lord God almiyti, trewe and iust ben thi domes.
30943	66	16	8	And the fourthe aungel schedde out his viol in to the sunne, and it was youun to hym to turmente men with heete and fier.
30944	66	16	9	And men swaliden with greet heete, and blasfemyden the name of God hauynge power on these plagis, nether thei diden penaunce, that thei schulden yyue glorie to hym.
30945	66	16	10	And the fifte aungel schedde out his viol on the seete of the beeste, and his kyngdom was maad derk; and thei eten togidere her tungis for sorewe,
30946	66	16	11	and thei  blasfemyden God of heuene, for sorewis of her woundis; and thei diden not penaunce of her werkis.
30947	66	16	12	And the sixte aungel schedde out his viol in `that ilke greet flood Eufratis, and driede the watir of it, that weie were maad redi to kingis fro the sunne rysyng.
30948	66	16	13	And Y say thre vnclene spiritis bi the manner of froggis go out of the mouth of the dragoun, and of the mouth of the beeste, and of the mouth of the fals prophete.
30949	66	16	14	For thei ben spiritis of deuels, makynge signes, and thei gon forth to kingis of al erthe, to gadere hem in to batel, to the greet dai of almiyti God.
30950	66	16	15	Lo! Y come, as a niyt theefe. Blessid is he that wakith, and kepith hise clothis, that he wandre not nakid, and that thei se not the filthhed of hym.
30951	66	16	16	And he schal gadre hem in to a place, that is clepid in Ebreu Hermagedon.
30952	66	16	17	And the seuenthe aungel schedde out his viol in to the eyr, and a greet vois wente out of heuene fro the trone, and seide, It is don.
30953	66	16	18	And leityngis weren maad, and voices, and thundris; and a greet erthe mouyng was maad, which manere neuere was, sithen men weren on erthe, siche `erthe mouyng so greet.
30954	66	16	19	And the greet citee was maad in to thre parties, and the citees of hethene men felden doun; and greet Babiloyne cam in to mynde byfor God, to yyue to it the cuppe of wyn of the indignacyoun of his wraththe.
30955	66	16	20	And ech ile flei awei, and hillis ben not foundun.
30956	66	16	21	And greet hail as a talent cam doun fro heuene in to men; and men blasfemyden God, for the plage of hail, for it was maad ful greet.
30957	66	17	1	And oon of the seuene aungels cam, that hadde seuene viols, and spak with me, and seide, Come thou, Y schal schewe to thee the dampnacioun of the greet hoore, that sittith on many watris, with which kyngis of erthe diden fornicacioun;
30958	66	17	2	and thei that dwellen in the erthe ben maad drunkun of the wyn of her letcherie.
30959	66	17	3	And he took me in to desert in spirit. And Y say a womman sittynge on a reed beeste, ful of names of blasfemye, hauynge seuene heedis, and ten hornes.
30960	66	17	4	And the womman was enuyround with purpur, and reed, and ouergild with gold, and preciouse stoon, and peerls, hauynge a goldun cuppe in hir hoond, ful of abhomynaciouns and vnclennesse of her fornycacioun.
30961	66	17	5	And a name writun in the forheed of hir, Mysterie, Babiloyn the greet, modir of fornycaciouns, and of abhomynaciouns of erthe.
30962	66	17	6	And Y say a womman drunkun of the blood of seyntis, and of the blood of martris of Jhesu. And whanne Y say hir, Y wondride with greet wondryng.
30963	66	17	7	And the aungel seide to me, Whi wondrist thou? I schal seie to thee the sacrament yf the womman, and of the beeste that berith hir, that hath seuene heedis and ten hornes.
30964	66	17	8	The beeste which thou seist, was, and is not; and sche schal stie fro depnesse, and sche schal go `in to perisching. And men dwellinge in erthe schulen wondre, whos names ben not writun in the book of lijf fro the makinge of the world, seynge the beeste, that was, and is not.
30965	66	17	9	And this is the witt, who that hath wisdom. The seuene heedis ben seuene hillis, on  whiche the womman sittith, and kyngis seuene ben.
30966	66	17	10	Fyue han feld doun, oon is, and anothir cometh not yit. And whanne he schal come, it bihoueth hym to dwelle a schort tyme.
30967	66	17	11	And the beeste that was, and is not, and sche is the eiytthe, and is of the seuene, and schal go in to perischyng.
30968	66	17	12	And the ten hornes whiche thou hast seyn, ben ten kyngis, that yit han not take kyngdom; but thei schulen take power as kingis, oon our after the beeste.
30969	66	17	13	These han a counsel, and schulen bitake her vertu and power to the beeste.
30970	66	17	14	These schulen fiyte with the lomb, and the lomb schal ouercome hem; for he is Lord of lordis, and kyng of kyngis; and thei that ben with hym, ben clepid, chosun, and feithful.
30971	66	17	15	And he seide to me, The watris whiche thou hast seyn, where the hoore sittith, ben puplis, and folkis, and langagis.
30972	66	17	16	And the ten hornes that thou hast seyn in the beeste, these schulen make hir desolat and nakid, and schulen ete the fleischis of hir, and schulen brenne togidere hir with fier.
30973	66	17	17	For God yaf in to the hertis of hem, that thei do that that is pleasaunt to hym, that thei yyue her kyngdom to the beeste, til the wordis of God ben endid.
30974	66	17	18	And the womman whom thou hast seyn, is the greet citee, that hath kingdom on kyngis of the erthe.
30975	66	18	1	And aftir these thingis Y siy another aungel comynge doun fro heuene, hauynge greet power; and the erthe was liytned of his glorie.
30976	66	18	2	`And he criede with strong vois, `and seide, Greet Babiloyn felde doun, felde doun, and is maad the habitacioun of deuelis, and the keping of ech vnclene spirit, and `the  keping of ech vnclene foul, and hateful.
30977	66	18	3	For alle folkis drunkun of the wraththe of fornycacioun of hir, and kingis of the erthe, and marchauntis of the erthe, diden fornycacioun with hir; and thei ben maad riche of the vertu of delices of hir.
30978	66	18	4	And Y herde another vois of heuene, seiynge, My puple, go ye out of it, and be ye not parceneris of the trespassis of it, and ye schulen not resseyue of the woundis of it.
30979	66	18	5	For the synnes of it camen `til to heuene, and the Lord hadde mynde of the wickidnesse of it.
30980	66	18	6	Yelde ye to it, as sche yeldide to you; and double ye double thingis, aftir her werkis; in the drynke that she meddlid to you, mynge ye double to hir.
30981	66	18	7	As myche as sche glorifiede hir silf, and was in delicis, so myche turment yyue to hir, and weilyng; for in hir herte sche seith, Y sitte a queen, and Y am not a widewe, and Y schal not se weiling.
30982	66	18	8	And therfor in o day hir woundis schulen come, deth, and mornyng, and hungur; and sche schal be brent in fier, for God is strong, that schal deme hir.
30983	66	18	9	And the kingis of the erthe schulen biwepe, and biweile hem silf on hir, whiche diden fornicacioun with hir, and lyueden in delicis, whanne thei schulen se the smoke of the brennyng of it;
30984	66	18	10	stondynge fer, for drede of the turmentis of it, and seiynge, Wo! wo! wo! thilke greet citee Babiloyn, and thilke stronge citee; for in oon our thi dom cometh.
30985	66	18	11	And marchauntis of the erthe schulen wepe on it, and morne, for no man schal bie more the marchaundise of hem;
30986	66	18	12	the marchaundies of gold, and of siluer, and of preciouse stoon, and of peerl, and of  bies, and of purpur, and of silk, and coctyn, and ech tre tymus, and alle vessels of yuer, and alle vessels of preciouse stoon, and of bras, and of yrun, and of marbil,
30987	66	18	13	and canel, and amonye, and of swete smellinge thingis, and oynementis, and encense, and of wyn, and of oyle, and of flour, and of whete, and of werk beestis, and of scheep, and of horsis, and of cartis, and of seruauntis, and other lyues of men.
30988	66	18	14	And thin applis of the desire of thi lijf wenten awei fro thee, and alle fatte thingis, and ful clere perischiden fro thee.
30989	66	18	15	And marchaundis of these thingis schulen no more fynde tho thingis. Thei that ben maad riche of it, schulen stonde fer, for drede of turmentis of it, wepynge, and mornynge, and seiynge, Wo!
30990	66	18	16	wo! thilke greet citee, that was clothid with bijs, and purpur, and reed scarlet, and was ouergild with gold, and preciouse stoon, and margaritis,
30991	66	18	17	for in oon our so many richessis ben destitute. And ech gouernour, and alle that saylen bi schip in to place, and maryneris, and that worchen in the see, stoden fer,
30992	66	18	18	and crieden, seynge the place of the brennyng of it, seiynge, What is lijk this greet citee?
30993	66	18	19	And thei casten poudre on her heedis, and crieden, wepynge, and mornynge, and seiynge, Wo! wo! thilke greet citee, in which alle that han schippis in the see ben maad riche of pricis of it; for in oon our it is desolat.
30994	66	18	20	Heuene, and hooli apostlis, and prophetis, make ye ful out ioye on it, for God hath demed youre dom of it.
30995	66	18	21	And o stronge aungel took vp a stoon, as a greet mylne stoon, and keste in to the  see, and seide, In this bire thilke greet citee Babiloyn schal be sent, and now it schal no more be foundun.
30996	66	18	22	And the vois of harpis, and of men of musik, and syngynge with pipe and trumpe, schal no more be herd in it. And ech crafti man, and ech craft, schal no more be foundun in it. And the vois of mylne stoon schal no more be herde in thee,
30997	66	18	23	and the liyt of lanterne schal no more schyne to thee, and the vois of the hosebonde and of the wijf schal no more yit be herd in thee; for thi marchauntis weren princis of the erthe. For in thi witchecraftis alle folkis erriden.
30998	66	18	24	And the blood of prophetis and seyntis is foundun in it, and of alle men that ben slayn in erthe.
30999	66	19	1	Aftir these thingis Y herde as a greet vois of many trumpis in heuene, seiynge, Alleluya; heriynge, and glorie, and vertu is to oure God;
31000	66	19	2	for trewe and iust ben the domes of hym, whiche demede of the greet hoore, that defoulide the erthe in her letcherye, and vengide the blood of hise seruauntis, of the hondis of hir.
31001	66	19	3	And eft thei seiden, Alleluya. And the smoke of it stieth vp, in to worldis of worldis.
31002	66	19	4	And the foure and twenti senyouris and foure beestis felden doun, and worschipiden God sittynge on the trone, and seiden, Amen, Alleluya.
31003	66	19	5	And a vois wente out of the trone, and seide, Alle the seruauntis of oure God, seie ye heriyngus to oure God, and ye that dreden God, smale and grete.
31004	66	19	6	And Y herde a vois of a grete trumpe, as the vois of many watris, and as the vois of grete thundris, seiynge, Alleluya; for  oure Lord God almyyti hath regned.
31005	66	19	7	Ioye we, and make we myrthe, and yyue glorie to hym; for the weddingis of the lomb camen, and the wijf of hym made redy hir silf.
31006	66	19	8	And it is youun to hir, that sche kyuere hir with white bissyn schynynge; for whi bissyn is iustifiyngis of seyntis.
31007	66	19	9	And he seide to me, Write thou, Blessid ben thei that ben clepid to the soper of weddyngis of the lomb. And he seide to me, These wordis of God ben trewe.
31008	66	19	10	And Y felde doun bifore hise feet, to worschipe hym. And he seide to me, Se thou, that thou do not; Y am a seruaunt with thee, and of thi britheren, hauynge the witnessyng of Jhesu; worschipe thou God. For the witnessing of Jhesu is spirit of profesie.
31009	66	19	11	And Y say heuene openyd, and lo! a whit hors, and he that sat on hym was clepid Feithful and sothefast; and with riytwisnesse he demeth, and fiytith.
31010	66	19	12	And `the iyen of hym weren as flawme of fier, and in his heed many diademys; and he hadde a name writun, which no man knew, but he.
31011	66	19	13	And he was clothid in a cloth spreynt with blood; and the name of hym was clepid The sone of God.
31012	66	19	14	And the oostis that ben in heuene, sueden hym on white horsis, clothid with bissyn, white and clene.
31013	66	19	15	And a swerd scharp on ech side cam forth of his mouth, that with it he smyte folkis; and he shal reule hem with an yren yerde. And he tredith the pressour of wyn of stronge veniaunce of the wraththe of almyyti God.
31014	66	19	16	And he hath writun in his cloth, and in the hemme, Kyng of kyngis and Lord of lordis.
31015	66	19	17	And Y say an aungel, stondynge in the sunne; and he criede with  greet vois, and seide to alle briddis that flowen bi the myddil of heuene, Come ye, and be ye gaderid to the greet soper of God,
31016	66	19	18	that ye ete the fleisch of kingis, and fleisch of tribunes, and fleisch of stronge men, and fleisch of horsis, and of tho that sitten on hem, and the fleisch of alle fre men and bonde men, and of smale and of grete.
31017	66	19	19	And Y sai the beeste, and the kyngis of the erthe, and the oostis of hem gaderid, to make batel with hym, that sat on the hors, and with his oost.
31018	66	19	20	And the beeste was cauyt, and with hir the false prophete, that made signes bifor hir; in whiche he disseyuede hem that token the carect of the beeste, and that worschipiden the ymage of it. These tweyne weren sent quyke in to the pool of fier, brennynge with brymstoon.
31019	66	19	21	And the othere weren slayn of swerd of hym that sat on the hors, that cometh forth of the mouth of hym; and alle briddis weren fillid with the fleisch of hem.
31020	66	20	1	And Y say an aungel comynge doun fro heuene, hauynge the keie of depnesse, and a greet chayne in his hoond.
31021	66	20	2	And he cauyte the dragoun, the elde serpent, that is the deuel and Sathanas; and he boonde hym bi a thousynde yeeris.
31022	66	20	3	And he sente hym `in to depnesse, and closide on hym, that he disseyue no more the folkis, til a thousynde yeeris be fillid. Aftir these thingis it bihoueth hym to be vnboundun a litil tyme.
31023	66	20	4	And Y say seetis, and thei saten on hem, and doom was youun to hem. And the soulis of men biheedid for the witnessyng of Jhesu,  and for the word of God, and hem that worschipiden not the beeste, nether the ymage of it, nethir token the carect of it in her forheedis, nethir in her hoondis. And thei lyueden, and regneden with Crist a thousynde yeeris.
31024	66	20	5	Othere of deed men lyueden not, til a thousynde yeeris ben endid. This is the first ayen risynge.
31025	66	20	6	Blessid and hooli is he, that hath part in the firste ayenrysyng. In these men the secunde deth hath not power; but thei schulen be prestis of God, and of Crist, and thei schulen regne with hym a thousynde yeeris.
31026	66	20	7	And whanne a thousynde yeeris schulen be endid, Sathanas schal be vnboundun of his prisoun; and he schal go out, and schal disseyue folkis, that ben on foure corners of the erthe, Gog and Magog. And he schal gadere hem in to batel, whos noumbre is as the grauel of the see.
31027	66	20	8	And thei stieden vp on the broodnesse of erthe, and enuyrounede the castels of seyntis, and the louyd citee.
31028	66	20	9	And fier cam doun `of God fro heuene, and deuourede hem. And the deuel, that disseyuede hem, was sent in to the pool of fier and of brymston,
31029	66	20	10	where bothe the beeste and fals prophetis schulen be turmentid dai and niyt, in to worldis of worldis.
31030	66	20	11	Amen. And Y say a greet white trone, and oon sittynge on it, fro whos siyt erthe fled and heuene; and the place is not foundun `of hem.
31031	66	20	12	And Y sai deed men, grete and smale, stondynge in the siyt of the trone; and bookis weren opened, and deed men weren demed of these thingis that weren writun in the bookis, aftir the werkis of hem.
31032	66	20	13	And the see yaf his deed men, that weren in it; and deth and helle  yauen her deed men, that weren in hem. And it was demed of ech, aftir the werkis of hem.
31033	66	20	14	And helle and deth weren sent in to a poole of fier. `This is the secunde deth.
31034	66	20	15	And he that was not foundun writun in the book of lijf, was sent in to the pool of fier.
31035	66	21	1	And Y sai newe heuene and newe erthe; for the firste heuene and the firste erthe wenten awei, and the see is not now.
31036	66	21	2	And Y Joon say the hooli citee Jerusalem, newe, comynge doun fro heuene, maad redi of God, as a wijf ourned to hir hosebonde.
